Cauchy-Schwarz we have the pointwise estimate</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_%7Bj%3D1%7D%5En+%5Chat+f_j%28%5Cxi%29%7C+%5Cleq+A_2%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%28%5Csum_%7Bj%3D1%7D%5En+%7C%5Chat+f_j%28%5Cxi%29%7C%5E2%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  |\\sum_{j=1}^n \\hat f_j(\\xi)| \\leq A_2^{1/2} (\\sum_{j=1}^n |\\hat f_j(\\xi)|^2)^{1/2} \" title=\"\\displaystyle  |\\sum_{j=1}^n \\hat f_j(\\xi)| \\leq A_2^{1/2} (\\sum_{j=1}^n |\\hat f_j(\\xi)|^2)^{1/2} \" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p>and hence by Fubini’s theorem</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5C%7C+%5Csum_%7Bj%3D1%7D%5En+f_j+%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5Ed%29%7D+%5Cleq+A_2%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%28%5Csum_%7Bj%3D1%7D%5En+%5C%7C%5Chat+f_j+%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5Ed%29%7D%5E2%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\| \\sum_{j=1}^n f_j \\|_{L^2({\\bf R}^d)} \\leq A_2^{1/2} (\\sum_{j=1}^n \\|\\hat f_j \\|_{L^2({\\bf R}^d)}^2)^{1/2}.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\| \\sum_{j=1}^n f_j \\|_{L^2({\\bf R}^d)} \\leq A_2^{1/2} (\\sum_{j=1}^n \\|\\hat f_j \\|_{L^2({\\bf R}^d)}^2)^{1/2}.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p>The claim then follows by a further application of Plancherel’s theorem and Fubini’s theorem. For (ii), we observe that</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle+%5C%7C+%5Csum_%7Bj%3D1%7D%5En+f_j+%5C%7C_%7BL%5E4%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5Ed%29%7D%5E2+%3D+%5C%7C+%5Csum_%7Bi%3D1%7D%5En+%5Csum_%7Bj%3D1%7D%5En+f_i+f_j+%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle \\| \\sum_{j=1}^n f_j \\|_{L^4({\\bf R}^d)}^2 = \\| \\sum_{i=1}^n \\sum_{j=1}^n f_i f_j \\|_{L^2({\\bf R}^2)}\" title=\"\\displaystyle \\| \\sum_{j=1}^n f_j \\|_{L^4({\\bf R}^d)}^2 = \\| \\sum_{i=1}^n \\sum_{j=1}^n f_i f_j \\|_{L^2({\\bf R}^2)}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p>and</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle+%5C%7C+%28%5Csum_%7Bj%3D1%7D%5En+%7Cf_j%7C%5E2%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5C%7C_%7BL%5E4%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5Ed%29%7D%5E2+%3D+%5C%7C+%28%5Csum_%7Bi%3D1%7D%5En+%5Csum_%7Bj%3D1%7D%5En+%7Cf_i+f_j%7C%5E2%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%29%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle \\| (\\sum_{j=1}^n |f_j|^2)^{1/2} \\|_{L^4({\\bf R}^d)}^2 = \\| (\\sum_{i=1}^n \\sum_{j=1}^n |f_i f_j|^2)^{1/2} \\|_{L^2({\\bf R}^2)}.\" title=\"\\displaystyle \\| (\\sum_{j=1}^n |f_j|^2)^{1/2} \\|_{L^4({\\bf R}^d)}^2 = \\| (\\sum_{i=1}^n \\sum_{j=1}^n |f_i f_j|^2)^{1/2} \\|_{L^2({\\bf R}^2)}.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p>Since <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf_i+f_j%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{f_i f_j}\" title=\"{f_i f_j}\" class=\"latex\" /> has Fourier support in <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5COmega_i+%2B+%5COmega_j%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\Omega_i + \\Omega_j}\" title=\"{\\Omega_i + \\Omega_j}\" class=\"latex\" />, the claim (ii) now follows from (i). <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5CBox&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\Box\" title=\"\\Box\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<blockquote>\n <p><b>Remark 7</b> By using <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf_i+%5Coverline%7Bf_j%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{f_i \\overline{f_j}}\" title=\"{f_i \\overline{f_j}}\" class=\"latex\" /> in place of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf_i+f_j%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{f_i f_j}\" title=\"{f_i f_j}\" class=\"latex\" />, one can also establish a variant of Lemma <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#bio\">6</a>(ii) in which the sum set <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5COmega_i+%2B+%5COmega_j%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\Omega_i + \\Omega_j}\" title=\"{\\Omega_i + \\Omega_j}\" class=\"latex\" /> is replaced by the difference set <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5COmega_i+-+%5COmega_j+%3A%3D+%5C%7B+%5Cxi_i+-+%5Cxi_j%3A+%5Cxi_i+%5Cin+%5COmega_i%2C+%5Cxi_j+%5Cin+%5COmega_j+%5C%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\Omega_i - \\Omega_j := \\{ \\xi_i - \\xi_j: \\xi_i \\in \\Omega_i, \\xi_j \\in \\Omega_j \\}}\" title=\"{\\Omega_i - \\Omega_j := \\{ \\xi_i - \\xi_j: \\xi_i \\in \\Omega_i, \\xi_j \\in \\Omega_j \\}}\" class=\"latex\" />. It is also clear how to extend the lemma to other even exponent Lebesgue spaces such as <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BL%5E6%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{L^6}\" title=\"{L^6}\" class=\"latex\" />; see for instance <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1906.05877\">this recent paper of Gressman, Guo, Pierce, Roos, and Yung</a>. However, we will not use these variants here.</p>\n</blockquote> \n<p>We can use this lemma to establish the following <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BL%5E4%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{L^4}\" title=\"{L^4}\" class=\"latex\" /> reverse square function estimate for the circle:</p> \n<blockquote>\n <p><b>Exercise 8 (Square function estimate for circle and parabola)</b> <a name=\"circ-para\"></a> Let <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B0+%3C+%5Cdelta+%5Cleq+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{0 < \\delta \\leq 1}\" title=\"{0 < \\delta \\leq 1}\" class=\"latex\" />, let <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5COmega%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\Omega}\" title=\"{\\Omega}\" class=\"latex\" /> be a <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cgtrsim+%5Cdelta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\gtrsim \\delta}\" title=\"{\\gtrsim \\delta}\" class=\"latex\" />-separated subset of the unit circle <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BS%5E1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{S^1}\" title=\"{S^1}\" class=\"latex\" />, and for each <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Comega+%5Cin+%5COmega%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\omega \\in \\Omega}\" title=\"{\\omega \\in \\Omega}\" class=\"latex\" />, let <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf_%5Comega+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{f_\\omega \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R}^2)}\" title=\"{f_\\omega \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R}^2)}\" class=\"latex\" /> have Fourier support in the rectangle</p> \n <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++R_%5Comega+%3A%3D+%5C%7B+%5Cxi+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%3A+%7C%5Cxi+%5Ccdot+%5Comega+-+1%7C+%3C+%5Cdelta%5E2%3B+%7C%5Cxi+-+%28%5Cxi+%5Ccdot+%5Comega%29+%5Comega%7C+%3C+%5Cdelta+%5C%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  R_\\omega := \\{ \\xi \\in {\\bf R}^2: |\\xi \\cdot \\omega - 1| < \\delta^2; |\\xi - (\\xi \\cdot \\omega) \\omega| < \\delta \\}.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  R_\\omega := \\{ \\xi \\in {\\bf R}^2: |\\xi \\cdot \\omega - 1| < \\delta^2; |\\xi - (\\xi \\cdot \\omega) \\omega| < \\delta \\}.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n <ul> \n  <li>(i) Use Lemma <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#bio\">6</a>(ii) to establish the reverse square function estimate <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5C%7C%5Csum_%7B%5Comega+%5Cin+%5COmega%7D+f_%5Comega+%5C%7C_%7BL%5E4%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%29%7D+%5Clesssim+%5C%7C+%28%5Csum_%7B%5Comega+%5Cin+%5COmega%7D+%7Cf_%5Comega%7C%5E2%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5C%7C_%7BL%5E4%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%29%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\|\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\Omega} f_\\omega \\|_{L^4({\\bf R}^2)} \\lesssim \\| (\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\Omega} |f_\\omega|^2)^{1/2} \\|_{L^4({\\bf R}^2)}.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\|\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\Omega} f_\\omega \\|_{L^4({\\bf R}^2)} \\lesssim \\| (\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\Omega} |f_\\omega|^2)^{1/2} \\|_{L^4({\\bf R}^2)}.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> </li> \n  <li>(ii) If the elements of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5COmega%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\Omega}\" title=\"{\\Omega}\" class=\"latex\" /> are <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BC%5Cdelta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{C\\delta}\" title=\"{C\\delta}\" class=\"latex\" />-separated for a sufficiently large absolute constant <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BC%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{C}\" title=\"{C}\" class=\"latex\" />, establish the matching square function estimate <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5C%7C%5Csum_%7B%5Comega+%5Cin+%5COmega%7D+f_%5Comega+%5C%7C_%7BL%5E4%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%29%7D+%5Cgtrsim+%5C%7C+%28%5Csum_%7B%5Comega+%5Cin+%5COmega%7D+%7Cf_%5Comega%7C%5E2%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5C%7C_%7BL%5E4%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%29%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\|\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\Omega} f_\\omega \\|_{L^4({\\bf R}^2)} \\gtrsim \\| (\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\Omega} |f_\\omega|^2)^{1/2} \\|_{L^4({\\bf R}^2)}.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\|\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\Omega} f_\\omega \\|_{L^4({\\bf R}^2)} \\gtrsim \\| (\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\Omega} |f_\\omega|^2)^{1/2} \\|_{L^4({\\bf R}^2)}.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> </li> \n  <li>(iii) Obtain analogous claims to (i), (ii) in which <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5COmega+%3D+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\Omega = \\phi(\\Sigma)}\" title=\"{\\Omega = \\phi(\\Sigma)}\" class=\"latex\" /> for some <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cdelta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\delta}\" title=\"{\\delta}\" class=\"latex\" />-separated subset <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5CSigma%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\Sigma}\" title=\"{\\Sigma}\" class=\"latex\" /> of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5B-1%2C1%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{[-1,1]}\" title=\"{[-1,1]}\" class=\"latex\" />, where <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cphi%3A+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Crightarrow+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\phi: {\\bf R} \\rightarrow {\\bf R}^2}\" title=\"{\\phi: {\\bf R} \\rightarrow {\\bf R}^2}\" class=\"latex\" /> is the graphing function <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cphi%28%5Cxi%29+%3A%3D%28%5Cxi%2C%5Cxi%5E2%29%3A+%5Cxi+%3D+O%281%29+%5C%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\phi(\\xi) :=(\\xi,\\xi^2): \\xi = O(1) \\}}\" title=\"{\\phi(\\xi) :=(\\xi,\\xi^2): \\xi = O(1) \\}}\" class=\"latex\" />, and to each <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Comega+%3D+%28%5Comega_1%2C%5Comega_1%5E2%29+%5Cin+%5COmega%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\omega = (\\omega_1,\\omega_1^2) \\in \\Omega}\" title=\"{\\omega = (\\omega_1,\\omega_1^2) \\in \\Omega}\" class=\"latex\" /> one uses the parallelogram <a name=\"trom\"> <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Ctilde+R_%5Comega+%3A%3D+%5C%7B+%28%5Cxi_1%2C%5Cxi_2%29+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%3A+%7C%5Cxi_1+-+%5Comega_1%7C+%3C+%5Cdelta%3B+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%285%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\tilde R_\\omega := \\{ (\\xi_1,\\xi_2) \\in {\\bf R}^2: |\\xi_1 - \\omega_1| < \\delta; \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (5)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\tilde R_\\omega := \\{ (\\xi_1,\\xi_2) \\in {\\bf R}^2: |\\xi_1 - \\omega_1| < \\delta; \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (5)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> <p></p></a> <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Cxi_2+-+%5Comega_1%5E2+-+2%5Comega_1%28%5Cxi_1-%5Comega_1%29%7C+%3C+%5Cdelta%5E2+%5C%7D+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  |\\xi_2 - \\omega_1^2 - 2\\omega_1(\\xi_1-\\omega_1)| < \\delta^2 \\} \" title=\"\\displaystyle  |\\xi_2 - \\omega_1^2 - 2\\omega_1(\\xi_1-\\omega_1)| < \\delta^2 \\} \" class=\"latex\" /></p> <p>in place of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BR_%5Comega%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{R_\\omega}\" title=\"{R_\\omega}\" class=\"latex\" />. </p></li> \n  <li>(iv) (Optional, as it was added after this exercise was first assigned as homework) Show that in (i) one cannot replace the <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BL%5E4%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{L^4}\" title=\"{L^4}\" class=\"latex\" /> norms on both sides by <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BL%5Ep%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{L^p}\" title=\"{L^p}\" class=\"latex\" /> for any given <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B4+%3C+p+%3C+%5Cinfty%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{4 < p < \\infty}\" title=\"{4 < p < \\infty}\" class=\"latex\" />. (<em>Hint:</em> use a Knapp type example for each <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf_%5Comega%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{f_\\omega}\" title=\"{f_\\omega}\" class=\"latex\" /> and ensure that there is enough constructive interference in <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Csum_%7B%5Comega+%5Cin+%5COmega%7D+f_%5Comega%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\Omega} f_\\omega}\" title=\"{\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\Omega} f_\\omega}\" class=\"latex\" /> near the origin.) On the other hand, using Exercise <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#lipi\">4</a> show that the <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BL%5E4%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{L^4}\" title=\"{L^4}\" class=\"latex\" /> norm in (ii) can be replaced by an <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BL%5Ep%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{L^p}\" title=\"{L^p}\" class=\"latex\" /> norm for any <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B2+%5Cleq+p+%5Cleq+%5Cinfty%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{2 \\leq p \\leq \\infty}\" title=\"{2 \\leq p \\leq \\infty}\" class=\"latex\" />.</li> \n </ul> \n</blockquote> \n<p>For a more sophisticated estimate along these lines, using sectors of the plane rather than rectangles near the unit circle, see <a href=\"https://mathscinet.ams.org/mathscinet-getitem?mr=688026\">this paper of Cordóba</a>. An analogous reverse square function estimate is also conjectured in higher dimensions (with <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BL%5E4%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{L^4}\" title=\"{L^4}\" class=\"latex\" /> replaced by the endpoint restriction exponent <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BL%5E%7B2d%2F%28d-1%29%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{L^{2d/(d-1)}}\" title=\"{L^{2d/(d-1)}}\" class=\"latex\" />), but this remains open, and in fact is at least as hard as the restriction and Kakeya conjectures; see <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1507.02515\">this paper of Carbery</a>.</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><b> — 2. Decoupling estimates — </b></p> \n<p>We now turn to decoupling estimates. We begin with a general definition.</p> \n<blockquote>\n <p><b>Definition 9 (Decoupling constant)</b> Let <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+U%7D+%3D+%5C%7BU_1%2C%5Cdots%2CU_n%5C%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal U} = \\{U_1,\\dots,U_n\\}}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal U} = \\{U_1,\\dots,U_n\\}}\" class=\"latex\" /> be a finite collection of non-empty open subsets of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5Ed%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf R}^d}\" title=\"{{\\bf R}^d}\" class=\"latex\" /> for some <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn+%5Cgeq+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{n \\geq 1}\" title=\"{n \\geq 1}\" class=\"latex\" /> (we permit repetitions, so <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+U%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal U}}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal U}}\" class=\"latex\" /> may be a multi-set rather than a set), and let <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B1+%5Cleq+p+%5Cleq+%5Cinfty%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{1 \\leq p \\leq \\infty}\" title=\"{1 \\leq p \\leq \\infty}\" class=\"latex\" />. We define the <em>decoupling constant</em> <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cmathrm%7BDec%7D_p%28%7B%5Cmathcal+U%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\mathrm{Dec}_p({\\mathcal U})}\" title=\"{\\mathrm{Dec}_p({\\mathcal U})}\" class=\"latex\" /> to be the smallest constant for which one has the inequality <a name=\"fnjp\"></a></p> \n <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5C%7C+%5Csum_%7Bj%3D1%7D%5En+f_j+%5C%7C_%7BL%5Ep%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5Ed%29%7D+%5Cleq+%5Cmathrm%7BDec%7D_p%28%7B%5Cmathcal+U%7D%29+%28%5Csum_%7Bj%3D1%7D%5En+%5C%7Cf_j%5C%7C_%7BL%5Ep%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5Ed%29%7D%5E2%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%286%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\| \\sum_{j=1}^n f_j \\|_{L^p({\\bf R}^d)} \\leq \\mathrm{Dec}_p({\\mathcal U}) (\\sum_{j=1}^n \\|f_j\\|_{L^p({\\bf R}^d)}^2)^{1/2} \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (6)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\| \\sum_{j=1}^n f_j \\|_{L^p({\\bf R}^d)} \\leq \\mathrm{Dec}_p({\\mathcal U}) (\\sum_{j=1}^n \\|f_j\\|_{L^p({\\bf R}^d)}^2)^{1/2} \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (6)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n <p> whenever <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf_j+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5Ed%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{f_j \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R}^d)}\" title=\"{f_j \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R}^d)}\" class=\"latex\" /> has Fourier support in <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BU_j%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{U_j}\" title=\"{U_j}\" class=\"latex\" /> for <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bj%3D1%2C%5Cdots%2Cn%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{j=1,\\dots,n}\" title=\"{j=1,\\dots,n}\" class=\"latex\" />.</p>\n</blockquote> \n<p>We have the trivial upper and lower bounds <a name=\"don\"></a></p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++1+%5Cleq+%5Cmathrm%7BDec%7D_p%28%7B%5Cmathcal+U%7D%29+%5Cleq+n%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%2C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%287%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  1 \\leq \\mathrm{Dec}_p({\\mathcal U}) \\leq n^{1/2}, \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (7)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  1 \\leq \\mathrm{Dec}_p({\\mathcal U}) \\leq n^{1/2}, \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (7)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p> with the lower bound arising from restricting to the case when all but one of the <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf_j%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{f_j}\" title=\"{f_j}\" class=\"latex\" /> vanish, and the upper bound following from the triangle inequality and Cauchy-Schwarz. In the literature, decoupling inequalities are also considered with the <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cell%5E2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\ell^2}\" title=\"{\\ell^2}\" class=\"latex\" /> summation of the <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5C%7Cf_j%5C%7C_%7BL%5Ep%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5Ed%29%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\|f_j\\|_{L^p({\\bf R}^d)}}\" title=\"{\\|f_j\\|_{L^p({\\bf R}^d)}}\" class=\"latex\" /> norms replaced by other summations (for instance, the original decoupling inequality <a href=\"https://mathscinet.ams.org/mathscinet-getitem?mr=1800068\">of Wolff</a> used <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cell%5Ep%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\ell^p}\" title=\"{\\ell^p}\" class=\"latex\" /> norms) but we will focus only on <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cell%5E2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\ell^2}\" title=\"{\\ell^2}\" class=\"latex\" /> decoupling estimates in this post. In the literature it is common to restrict attention to the case when the sets <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BU_1%2C%5Cdots%2CU_n%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{U_1,\\dots,U_n}\" title=\"{U_1,\\dots,U_n}\" class=\"latex\" /> are disjoint, but for minor technical reasons we will not impose this extra condition in our definition.</p> \n<blockquote>\n <p><b>Exercise 10 (Elementary properties of decoupling constants)</b> <a name=\"elem\"></a> Let <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B1+%5Cleq+p+%5Cleq+%5Cinfty%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{1 \\leq p \\leq \\infty}\" title=\"{1 \\leq p \\leq \\infty}\" class=\"latex\" /> and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bd+%5Cgeq+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{d \\geq 1}\" title=\"{d \\geq 1}\" class=\"latex\" />.</p> \n <ul> \n  <li>(i) (Monotonicity) Show that <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cmathrm%7BDec%7D_p%28+%5C%7B+U_1%2C%5Cdots%2CU_n%5C%7D%29+%5Cleq+%5Cmathrm%7BDec%7D_p%28+%5C%7B+U%27_1%2C%5Cdots%2CU%27_n%5C%7D%29+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Dec}_p( \\{ U_1,\\dots,U_n\\}) \\leq \\mathrm{Dec}_p( \\{ U'_1,\\dots,U'_n\\}) \" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Dec}_p( \\{ U_1,\\dots,U_n\\}) \\leq \\mathrm{Dec}_p( \\{ U'_1,\\dots,U'_n\\}) \" class=\"latex\" /></p> <p>whenever <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BU_j%2CU%27_j%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{U_j,U'_j}\" title=\"{U_j,U'_j}\" class=\"latex\" /> are non-empty open subsets of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5Ed%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf R}^d}\" title=\"{{\\bf R}^d}\" class=\"latex\" /> with <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BU_j+%5Csubset+U%27_j%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{U_j \\subset U'_j}\" title=\"{U_j \\subset U'_j}\" class=\"latex\" /> for <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bj%3D1%2C%5Cdots%2Cn%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{j=1,\\dots,n}\" title=\"{j=1,\\dots,n}\" class=\"latex\" />. </p></li> \n  <li>(ii) (Triangle inequality) Show that <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cmathrm%7BDec%7D_p%28+%7B%5Cmathcal+U%7D+%29%2C+%5Cmathrm%7BDec%7D_p%28+%7B%5Cmathcal+U%7D%27+%29+%5Cleq+%5Cmathrm%7BDec%7D_p%28+%7B%5Cmathcal+U%7D+%5Ccup+%7B%5Cmathcal+U%7D%27+%29+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Dec}_p( {\\mathcal U} ), \\mathrm{Dec}_p( {\\mathcal U}' ) \\leq \\mathrm{Dec}_p( {\\mathcal U} \\cup {\\mathcal U}' ) \" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Dec}_p( {\\mathcal U} ), \\mathrm{Dec}_p( {\\mathcal U}' ) \\leq \\mathrm{Dec}_p( {\\mathcal U} \\cup {\\mathcal U}' ) \" class=\"latex\" /></p> <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle+%5Cleq+%28%5Cmathrm%7BDec%7D_p%28+%7B%5Cmathcal+U%7D+%29%5E2+%2B+%5Cmathrm%7BDec%7D_p%28+%7B%5Cmathcal+U%7D%27+%29%5E2%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle \\leq (\\mathrm{Dec}_p( {\\mathcal U} )^2 + \\mathrm{Dec}_p( {\\mathcal U}' )^2)^{1/2}\" title=\"\\displaystyle \\leq (\\mathrm{Dec}_p( {\\mathcal U} )^2 + \\mathrm{Dec}_p( {\\mathcal U}' )^2)^{1/2}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> <p>for any finite non-empty collections <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+U%7D%2C+%7B%5Cmathcal+U%7D%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal U}, {\\mathcal U}'}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal U}, {\\mathcal U}'}\" class=\"latex\" /> of open non-empty subsets of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5Ed%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf R}^d}\" title=\"{{\\bf R}^d}\" class=\"latex\" />. </p></li> \n  <li>(iii) (Affine invariance) Show that <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cmathrm%7BDec%7D_p%28+%5C%7B+LU_1%2C%5Cdots%2CLU_n%5C%7D%29+%3D+%5Cmathrm%7BDec%7D_p%28+%5C%7B+U_1%2C%5Cdots%2CU_n%5C%7D%29+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Dec}_p( \\{ LU_1,\\dots,LU_n\\}) = \\mathrm{Dec}_p( \\{ U_1,\\dots,U_n\\}) \" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Dec}_p( \\{ LU_1,\\dots,LU_n\\}) = \\mathrm{Dec}_p( \\{ U_1,\\dots,U_n\\}) \" class=\"latex\" /></p> <p>whenever <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BU_1%2C%5Cdots%2CU_n+%5Csubset+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5Ed%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{U_1,\\dots,U_n \\subset {\\bf R}^d}\" title=\"{U_1,\\dots,U_n \\subset {\\bf R}^d}\" class=\"latex\" /> are open non-empty and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BL%3A+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5Ed+%5Crightarrow+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5Ed%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{L: {\\bf R}^d \\rightarrow {\\bf R}^d}\" title=\"{L: {\\bf R}^d \\rightarrow {\\bf R}^d}\" class=\"latex\" /> is an invertible affine transformation. </p></li> \n  <li>(iv) (Interpolation) Suppose that <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7Bp%7D+%3D+%5Cfrac%7B1-%5Ctheta%7D%7Bp_0%7D+%2B+%5Cfrac%7B%5Ctheta%7D%7Bp_1%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\frac{1}{p} = \\frac{1-\\theta}{p_0} + \\frac{\\theta}{p_1}}\" title=\"{\\frac{1}{p} = \\frac{1-\\theta}{p_0} + \\frac{\\theta}{p_1}}\" class=\"latex\" /> for some <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B1+%5Cleq+p_0+%5Cleq+p+%5Cleq+p_1+%5Cleq+%5Cinfty%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{1 \\leq p_0 \\leq p \\leq p_1 \\leq \\infty}\" title=\"{1 \\leq p_0 \\leq p \\leq p_1 \\leq \\infty}\" class=\"latex\" /> and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B0+%5Cleq+%5Ctheta+%5Cleq+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{0 \\leq \\theta \\leq 1}\" title=\"{0 \\leq \\theta \\leq 1}\" class=\"latex\" />, and suppose also that <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+U%7D+%3D+%5C%7BU_1%2C%5Cdots%2CU_n%5C%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal U} = \\{U_1,\\dots,U_n\\}}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal U} = \\{U_1,\\dots,U_n\\}}\" class=\"latex\" /> is a non-empty collection of open non-empty subsets of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5Ed%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf R}^d}\" title=\"{{\\bf R}^d}\" class=\"latex\" /> for which one has the projection bounds <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5C%7C+P_%7BU_j%7D+f+%5C%7C_%7BL%5E%7Bp_i%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5Ed%29%7D+%5Clesssim_%7Bp_i%2Cd%7D+%5C%7Cf%5C%7C_%7BL%5E%7Bp_i%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5Ed%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\| P_{U_j} f \\|_{L^{p_i}({\\bf R}^d)} \\lesssim_{p_i,d} \\|f\\|_{L^{p_i}({\\bf R}^d)}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\| P_{U_j} f \\|_{L^{p_i}({\\bf R}^d)} \\lesssim_{p_i,d} \\|f\\|_{L^{p_i}({\\bf R}^d)}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> <p>for all <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5Ed%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{f \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R}^d)}\" title=\"{f \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R}^d)}\" class=\"latex\" />, <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bi%3D0%2C1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{i=0,1}\" title=\"{i=0,1}\" class=\"latex\" />, and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bj%3D1%2C%5Cdots%2Cn%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{j=1,\\dots,n}\" title=\"{j=1,\\dots,n}\" class=\"latex\" />, where the Fourier multiplier <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP_%7BU_j%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P_{U_j}}\" title=\"{P_{U_j}}\" class=\"latex\" /> is defined by</p> <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cwidehat%7BP_%7BU_j%7D+f%7D%28%5Cxi%29+%3D+1_%7BU_j%7D%28%5Cxi%29+%5Chat+f%28%5Cxi%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\widehat{P_{U_j} f}(\\xi) = 1_{U_j}(\\xi) \\hat f(\\xi).\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\widehat{P_{U_j} f}(\\xi) = 1_{U_j}(\\xi) \\hat f(\\xi).\" class=\"latex\" /></p> <p>Show that</p> <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cmathrm%7BDec%7D_p%28%7B%5Cmathcal+U%7D%29+%5Clesssim_%7Bp_0%2Cp_1%2Cd%2C%5Ctheta%7D+%5Cmathrm%7BDec%7D_%7Bp_0%7D%28%7B%5Cmathcal+U%7D%29%5E%7B1-%5Ctheta%7D+%5Cmathrm%7BDec%7D_%7Bp_1%7D%28%7B%5Cmathcal+U%7D%29%5E%7B%5Ctheta%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Dec}_p({\\mathcal U}) \\lesssim_{p_0,p_1,d,\\theta} \\mathrm{Dec}_{p_0}({\\mathcal U})^{1-\\theta} \\mathrm{Dec}_{p_1}({\\mathcal U})^{\\theta}.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Dec}_p({\\mathcal U}) \\lesssim_{p_0,p_1,d,\\theta} \\mathrm{Dec}_{p_0}({\\mathcal U})^{1-\\theta} \\mathrm{Dec}_{p_1}({\\mathcal U})^{\\theta}.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> </li> \n  <li>(v) (Multiplicativity) Suppose that <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+U%7D+%3D+%5C%7B+U_1%2C%5Cdots%2CU_n%5C%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal U} = \\{ U_1,\\dots,U_n\\}}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal U} = \\{ U_1,\\dots,U_n\\}}\" class=\"latex\" /> is a family of open non-empty subsets of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5Ed%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf R}^d}\" title=\"{{\\bf R}^d}\" class=\"latex\" />, with each <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BU_j%2C+j%3D1%2C%5Cdots%2Cn%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{U_j, j=1,\\dots,n}\" title=\"{U_j, j=1,\\dots,n}\" class=\"latex\" /> containing further open non-empty subsets <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BU_%7Bj%2Ci%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{U_{j,i}}\" title=\"{U_{j,i}}\" class=\"latex\" /> for <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bi%3D1%2C%5Cdots%2Cm%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{i=1,\\dots,m}\" title=\"{i=1,\\dots,m}\" class=\"latex\" />. Show that <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cmathrm%7BDec%7D_p%28+%5C%7B+U_%7Bj%2Ci%7D%3A+1+%5Cleq+j+%5Cleq+n%2C+1+%5Cleq+i+%5Cleq+m+%5C%7D+%29+%5Cleq+%5Cmathrm%7BDec%7D_p%28%7B%5Cmathcal+U%7D%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Dec}_p( \\{ U_{j,i}: 1 \\leq j \\leq n, 1 \\leq i \\leq m \\} ) \\leq \\mathrm{Dec}_p({\\mathcal U})\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Dec}_p( \\{ U_{j,i}: 1 \\leq j \\leq n, 1 \\leq i \\leq m \\} ) \\leq \\mathrm{Dec}_p({\\mathcal U})\" class=\"latex\" /></p> <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Ctimes+%5Csup_%7B1+%5Cleq+j+%5Cleq+n%7D+%5Cmathrm%7BDec%7D_p%28+%5C%7B+U_%7Bj%2C1%7D%2C%5Cdots%2CU_%7Bj%2Cm%7D%5C%7D%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\times \\sup_{1 \\leq j \\leq n} \\mathrm{Dec}_p( \\{ U_{j,1},\\dots,U_{j,m}\\}).\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\times \\sup_{1 \\leq j \\leq n} \\mathrm{Dec}_p( \\{ U_{j,1},\\dots,U_{j,m}\\}).\" class=\"latex\" /></p> </li> \n  <li>(vi) (Adding dimensions) Suppose that <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5C%7B+U_1%2C%5Cdots%2CU_n%5C%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\{ U_1,\\dots,U_n\\}}\" title=\"{\\{ U_1,\\dots,U_n\\}}\" class=\"latex\" /> is a family of disjoint open non-empty subsets of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5Ed%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf R}^d}\" title=\"{{\\bf R}^d}\" class=\"latex\" /> and that <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bp+%5Cgeq+2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{p \\geq 2}\" title=\"{p \\geq 2}\" class=\"latex\" />. Show that for any <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bd%27+%5Cgeq+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{d' \\geq 1}\" title=\"{d' \\geq 1}\" class=\"latex\" />, one has <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cmathrm%7BDec%7D_p%28+%5C%7B+U_1%2C%5Cdots%2CU_n%5C%7D+%29+%3D+%5Cmathrm%7BDec%7D_p%28+%5C%7B+U_1+%5Ctimes+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E%7Bd%27%7D%2C%5Cdots%2CU_n+%5Ctimes+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E%7Bd%27%7D%5C%7D+%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Dec}_p( \\{ U_1,\\dots,U_n\\} ) = \\mathrm{Dec}_p( \\{ U_1 \\times {\\bf R}^{d'},\\dots,U_n \\times {\\bf R}^{d'}\\} )\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Dec}_p( \\{ U_1,\\dots,U_n\\} ) = \\mathrm{Dec}_p( \\{ U_1 \\times {\\bf R}^{d'},\\dots,U_n \\times {\\bf R}^{d'}\\} )\" class=\"latex\" /></p> <p>where the right-hand side is a decoupling constant in <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5Ed+%5Ctimes+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E%7Bd%27%7D+%3D+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E%7Bd%2Bd%27%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf R}^d \\times {\\bf R}^{d'} = {\\bf R}^{d+d'}}\" title=\"{{\\bf R}^d \\times {\\bf R}^{d'} = {\\bf R}^{d+d'}}\" class=\"latex\" />.</p></li> \n </ul> \n</blockquote> \n<p>The most useful decoupling inequalites in practice turn out to be those where the decoupling constant <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cmathrm%7BDec%7D_p%28%7B%5Cmathcal+U%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\mathrm{Dec}_p({\\mathcal U})}\" title=\"{\\mathrm{Dec}_p({\\mathcal U})}\" class=\"latex\" /> is close to the lower bound of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{1}\" title=\"{1}\" class=\"latex\" />, for instance if one has the sub-polynomial bounds</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cmathrm%7BDec%7D_p%28%7B%5Cmathcal+U%7D%29+%5Clesssim_%7Bp%2Cd%2C%5Cvarepsilon%7D+n%5E%5Cvarepsilon&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Dec}_p({\\mathcal U}) \\lesssim_{p,d,\\varepsilon} n^\\varepsilon\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Dec}_p({\\mathcal U}) \\lesssim_{p,d,\\varepsilon} n^\\varepsilon\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p>for every <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cvarepsilon%3E0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\varepsilon>0}\" title=\"{\\varepsilon>0}\" class=\"latex\" />. We informally say that the collection <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+U%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal U}}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal U}}\" class=\"latex\" /> of sets <em>exhibits decoupling in <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BL%5Ep%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{L^p}\" title=\"{L^p}\" class=\"latex\" /></em> when this is the case.<br /> For <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bp%3D2%2C4%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{p=2,4}\" title=\"{p=2,4}\" class=\"latex\" />, Lemma <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#bio\">6</a> (and <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#rop\">(3)</a>) already gives some decoupling estimates: one has <a name=\"a2\"></a></p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cmathrm%7BDec%7D_2%28%7B%5Cmathcal+U%7D%29+%5Cleq+A_2%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%288%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Dec}_2({\\mathcal U}) \\leq A_2^{1/2} \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (8)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Dec}_2({\\mathcal U}) \\leq A_2^{1/2} \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (8)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p> if the sets <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BU_1%2C%5Cdots%2CU_n%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{U_1,\\dots,U_n}\" title=\"{U_1,\\dots,U_n}\" class=\"latex\" /> have an overlap of at most <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BA_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{A_2}\" title=\"{A_2}\" class=\"latex\" />, and similarly</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cmathrm%7BDec%7D_4%28%7B%5Cmathcal+U%7D%29+%5Cleq+A_4%5E%7B1%2F4%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Dec}_4({\\mathcal U}) \\leq A_4^{1/4}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Dec}_4({\\mathcal U}) \\leq A_4^{1/4}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p>when the sets <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BU_i%2BU_j%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{U_i+U_j}\" title=\"{U_i+U_j}\" class=\"latex\" />, <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B1+%5Cleq+i%2Cj+%5Cleq+n%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{1 \\leq i,j \\leq n}\" title=\"{1 \\leq i,j \\leq n}\" class=\"latex\" /> have an overlap of at most <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BA_4%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{A_4}\" title=\"{A_4}\" class=\"latex\" />.<br /> For <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bp%3C2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{p<2}\" title=\"{p<2}\" class=\"latex\" />, it is not possible to exhibit decoupling in the limit <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn+%5Crightarrow+%5Cinfty%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{n \\rightarrow \\infty}\" title=\"{n \\rightarrow \\infty}\" class=\"latex\" />:</p> \n<blockquote>\n <p><b>Exercise 11</b> If <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+U%7D+%3D+%5C%7BU_1%2C%5Cdots%2CU_n%5C%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal U} = \\{U_1,\\dots,U_n\\}}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal U} = \\{U_1,\\dots,U_n\\}}\" class=\"latex\" /> is a collection of non-empty open subsets of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5Ed%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf R}^d}\" title=\"{{\\bf R}^d}\" class=\"latex\" />, show that</p> \n <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cmathrm%7BDec%7D_p%28%7B%5Cmathcal+U%7D%29+%5Cgtrsim_%7Bp%2Cd%7D+n%5E%7B%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7Bp%7D-%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B2%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Dec}_p({\\mathcal U}) \\gtrsim_{p,d} n^{\\frac{1}{p}-\\frac{1}{2}}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Dec}_p({\\mathcal U}) \\gtrsim_{p,d} n^{\\frac{1}{p}-\\frac{1}{2}}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n <p>for any <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B1+%5Cleq+p+%5Cleq+2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{1 \\leq p \\leq 2}\" title=\"{1 \\leq p \\leq 2}\" class=\"latex\" />. (<em>Hint:</em> select the <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf_1%2C%5Cdots%2Cf_n%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{f_1,\\dots,f_n}\" title=\"{f_1,\\dots,f_n}\" class=\"latex\" /> to be concentrated in widely separated large balls.)</p>\n</blockquote> \n<p>Henceforth we now focus on the regime <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bp+%5Cgeq+2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{p \\geq 2}\" title=\"{p \\geq 2}\" class=\"latex\" />. By <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#a2\">(8)</a>, <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BL%5E2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{L^2}\" title=\"{L^2}\" class=\"latex\" /> decoupling is easily obtained if the regions <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BU_j%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{U_j}\" title=\"{U_j}\" class=\"latex\" /> are of bounded overlap. For <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bp%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{p}\" title=\"{p}\" class=\"latex\" /> larger than <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{2}\" title=\"{2}\" class=\"latex\" />, bounded overlap is insufficient by itself; the arrangement of the regions <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BU_j%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{U_j}\" title=\"{U_j}\" class=\"latex\" /> must also exhibit some “curvature”, as the following example shows.</p> \n<blockquote>\n <p><b>Exercise 12</b> If <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+U%7D+%3D+%5C%7B+%28i%2Ci%2B1%29%3A+0+%5Cleq+i+%3C+n+%5C%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal U} = \\{ (i,i+1): 0 \\leq i < n \\}}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal U} = \\{ (i,i+1): 0 \\leq i < n \\}}\" class=\"latex\" />, and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B2+%5Cleq+p+%5Cleq+%5Cinfty%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{2 \\leq p \\leq \\infty}\" title=\"{2 \\leq p \\leq \\infty}\" class=\"latex\" />, show that</p> \n <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cmathrm%7BDec%7D_p%28%7B%5Cmathcal+U%7D%29+%5Csim_p+n%5E%7B%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B2%7D+-+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7Bp%7D%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Dec}_p({\\mathcal U}) \\sim_p n^{\\frac{1}{2} - \\frac{1}{p}}.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Dec}_p({\\mathcal U}) \\sim_p n^{\\frac{1}{2} - \\frac{1}{p}}.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n <p>(<em>Hint:</em> for the upper bound, use a variant of Exercise 24(ii) from <a href=\"https://terrytao.wordpress.com/2020/03/29/247b-notes-1-restriction-theory/\">Notes 1</a>, or adapt the interpolation arguemnt used to establish that exercise.)</p>\n</blockquote> \n<p>Now we establish a significantly more non-trivial decoupling theorem:</p> \n<blockquote>\n <p><b>Theorem 13 (Decoupling for the parabola)</b> <a name=\"parabb\"></a> Let <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B0+%3C+%5Cdelta+%5Cleq+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{0 < \\delta \\leq 1}\" title=\"{0 < \\delta \\leq 1}\" class=\"latex\" />, let <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5COmega+%3D+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\Omega = \\phi(\\Sigma)}\" title=\"{\\Omega = \\phi(\\Sigma)}\" class=\"latex\" /> for some <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cdelta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\delta}\" title=\"{\\delta}\" class=\"latex\" />-separated subset <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5CSigma%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\Sigma}\" title=\"{\\Sigma}\" class=\"latex\" /> of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5B-1%2C1%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{[-1,1]}\" title=\"{[-1,1]}\" class=\"latex\" />, where <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cphi%28%5Cxi%29+%3A%3D+%28%5Cxi%2C%5Cxi%5E2%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\phi(\\xi) := (\\xi,\\xi^2)}\" title=\"{\\phi(\\xi) := (\\xi,\\xi^2)}\" class=\"latex\" />, and to each <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Comega+%5Cin+%5COmega%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\omega \\in \\Omega}\" title=\"{\\omega \\in \\Omega}\" class=\"latex\" /> let <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Ctilde+R_%7B%5Comega%2C%5Cdelta%7D+%3D+%5Ctilde+R_%7B%5Comega%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\tilde R_{\\omega,\\delta} = \\tilde R_{\\omega}}\" title=\"{\\tilde R_{\\omega,\\delta} = \\tilde R_{\\omega}}\" class=\"latex\" /> be the parallelogram <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#trom\">(5)</a>. Then</p> \n <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cmathrm%7BDec%7D_6%28+%5C%7B+%5Ctilde+R_%7B%5Comega%2C%5Cdelta%7D%3A+%5Comega+%5Cin+%5COmega+%5C%7D+%29+%5Clesssim_%5Cvarepsilon+%5Cdelta%5E%7B-%5Cvarepsilon%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Dec}_6( \\{ \\tilde R_{\\omega,\\delta}: \\omega \\in \\Omega \\} ) \\lesssim_\\varepsilon \\delta^{-\\varepsilon}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Dec}_6( \\{ \\tilde R_{\\omega,\\delta}: \\omega \\in \\Omega \\} ) \\lesssim_\\varepsilon \\delta^{-\\varepsilon}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n <p>for any <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cvarepsilon%3E0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\varepsilon>0}\" title=\"{\\varepsilon>0}\" class=\"latex\" />.</p>\n</blockquote> \n<p>This result was first established <a href=\"https://mathscinet.ams.org/mathscinet-getitem?mr=3374964\">by Bourgain and Demeter</a>; our arguments here will loosely follow an argument <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1805.10551\">of Li</a>, that is based in turn on the efficient congruencing methods <a href=\"https://mathscinet.ams.org/mathscinet-getitem?mr=3938716\">of Wooley</a>, as recounted for instance in this exposition <a href=\"https://mathscinet.ams.org/mathscinet-getitem?mr=3939285\">of Pierce</a>.<br /> We first explain the significance of the exponent <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B6%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{6}\" title=\"{6}\" class=\"latex\" /> in Theorem <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#parabb\">13</a>. Let <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5CSigma%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\Sigma}\" title=\"{\\Sigma}\" class=\"latex\" /> be a maximal <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cdelta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\delta}\" title=\"{\\delta}\" class=\"latex\" />-separated subset <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5B-1%2C1%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{[-1,1]}\" title=\"{[-1,1]}\" class=\"latex\" /> for some small <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B0+%3C+%5Cdelta+%3C+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{0 < \\delta < 1}\" title=\"{0 < \\delta < 1}\" class=\"latex\" />, so that <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5CSigma%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\Sigma}\" title=\"{\\Sigma}\" class=\"latex\" /> has cardinality <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Csim+%5Cdelta%5E%7B-1%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\sim \\delta^{-1}}\" title=\"{\\sim \\delta^{-1}}\" class=\"latex\" />. For each <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Comega+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma)}\" title=\"{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma)}\" class=\"latex\" />, choose <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf_%5Comega%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{f_\\omega}\" title=\"{f_\\omega}\" class=\"latex\" /> so that <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Chat+f_%5Comega%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\hat f_\\omega}\" title=\"{\\hat f_\\omega}\" class=\"latex\" /> is a non-negative bump function (not identically zero) adapted to the parallelogram <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Ctilde+R_%7B%5Comega%2C%5Cdelta%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\tilde R_{\\omega,\\delta}}\" title=\"{\\tilde R_{\\omega,\\delta}}\" class=\"latex\" />, which is comparable to a <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cdelta+%5Ctimes+%5Cdelta%5E2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\delta \\times \\delta^2}\" title=\"{\\delta \\times \\delta^2}\" class=\"latex\" /> rectangle. From the Fourier inversion formula, <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf_%5Comega%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{f_\\omega}\" title=\"{f_\\omega}\" class=\"latex\" /> will then have magnitude <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BO%28%5Cdelta%5E3%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{O(\\delta^3)}\" title=\"{O(\\delta^3)}\" class=\"latex\" /> on a dual rectangle of dimensions comparable to <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B1%2F%5Cdelta+%5Ctimes+1%2F%5Cdelta%5E2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{1/\\delta \\times 1/\\delta^2}\" title=\"{1/\\delta \\times 1/\\delta^2}\" class=\"latex\" />, and is rapidly decreasing away from that rectangle, so we have</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5C%7Cf_%5Comega%5C%7C_%7BL%5Ep%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%29%7D+%5Clesssim_p+%5Cdelta%5E3+%5Cdelta%5E%7B-3%2Fp%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\|f_\\omega\\|_{L^p({\\bf R}^2)} \\lesssim_p \\delta^3 \\delta^{-3/p}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\|f_\\omega\\|_{L^p({\\bf R}^2)} \\lesssim_p \\delta^3 \\delta^{-3/p}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p>for all <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B1+%5Cleq+p+%5Cleq+%5Cinfty%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{1 \\leq p \\leq \\infty}\" title=\"{1 \\leq p \\leq \\infty}\" class=\"latex\" /> and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Comega+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma)}\" title=\"{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma)}\" class=\"latex\" />. In particular</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%28+%5Csum_%7B%5Comega+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma%29%7D+%5C%7Cf_%5Comega%5C%7C_%7BL%5Ep%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%29%7D%5E2%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5Csim_p+%5Cdelta%5E%7B%5Cfrac%7B5%7D%7B2%7D+-+%5Cfrac%7B3%7D%7Bp%7D%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  ( \\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma)} \\|f_\\omega\\|_{L^p({\\bf R}^2)}^2)^{1/2} \\sim_p \\delta^{\\frac{5}{2} - \\frac{3}{p}}.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  ( \\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma)} \\|f_\\omega\\|_{L^p({\\bf R}^2)}^2)^{1/2} \\sim_p \\delta^{\\frac{5}{2} - \\frac{3}{p}}.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p>On the other hand, we have <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cmathrm%7BRe%7D+f_%5Comega%28x%29+%5Cgtrsim+%5Cdelta%5E3%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\mathrm{Re} f_\\omega(x) \\gtrsim \\delta^3}\" title=\"{\\mathrm{Re} f_\\omega(x) \\gtrsim \\delta^3}\" class=\"latex\" /> for <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7Cx%7C+%5Cleq+c%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{|x| \\leq c}\" title=\"{|x| \\leq c}\" class=\"latex\" /> if <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bc%3E0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{c>0}\" title=\"{c>0}\" class=\"latex\" /> is a sufficiently small absolute constant, hence</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle+%5C%7C%5Csum_%7B%5Comega+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma%29%7D+f_%5Comega%5C%7C_%7BL%5Ep%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%29%7D+%5Cgtrsim_p+%5Cdelta%5E2.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle \\|\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma)} f_\\omega\\|_{L^p({\\bf R}^2)} \\gtrsim_p \\delta^2.\" title=\"\\displaystyle \\|\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma)} f_\\omega\\|_{L^p({\\bf R}^2)} \\gtrsim_p \\delta^2.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p>Comparing this with <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#fnjp\">(6)</a>, we conclude that</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cmathrm%7BDec%7D_p%28+%5C%7B+%5Ctilde+R_%5Comega%3A+%5Comega+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma%29+%5C%7D+%29+%5Cgtrsim_p+%5Cdelta%5E%7B%5Cfrac%7B3%7D%7Bp%7D+-+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B2%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Dec}_p( \\{ \\tilde R_\\omega: \\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma) \\} ) \\gtrsim_p \\delta^{\\frac{3}{p} - \\frac{1}{2}}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Dec}_p( \\{ \\tilde R_\\omega: \\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma) \\} ) \\gtrsim_p \\delta^{\\frac{3}{p} - \\frac{1}{2}}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p>so Theorem <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#parabb\">13</a> cannot hold if the exponent <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B6%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{6}\" title=\"{6}\" class=\"latex\" /> is replaced by any larger exponent. On the other direction, by using Exercise <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#elem\">10</a>(iv) and the trivial <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bp%3D2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{p=2}\" title=\"{p=2}\" class=\"latex\" /> decoupling from <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#a2\">(8)</a>, we see that we also have decoupling in <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BL%5Ep%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{L^p}\" title=\"{L^p}\" class=\"latex\" /> for any <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B2+%5Cleq+p+%5Cleq+6%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{2 \\leq p \\leq 6}\" title=\"{2 \\leq p \\leq 6}\" class=\"latex\" />. (Note from the boundedness of the Hilbert transform that a Fourier projection to any polygon of boundedly many sides will be bounded in <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BL%5Ep%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{L^p}\" title=\"{L^p}\" class=\"latex\" /> for any <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B1+%3C+p+%3C+%5Cinfty%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{1 < p < \\infty}\" title=\"{1 < p < \\infty}\" class=\"latex\" /> with norm <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BO_p%281%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{O_p(1)}\" title=\"{O_p(1)}\" class=\"latex\" />.) Note that reverse square function estimates in Exercise <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#circ-para\">8</a> only give decoupling in the smaller range <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B2+%5Cleq+p+%5Cleq+4%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{2 \\leq p \\leq 4}\" title=\"{2 \\leq p \\leq 4}\" class=\"latex\" />; the <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BL%5E6%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{L^6}\" title=\"{L^6}\" class=\"latex\" /> version of Lemma <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#bio\">6</a> is not strong enough to extend the decoupling estimates to larger ranges because the triple sums <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Ctilde+R_%7B%5Comega_1%7D+%2B+%5Ctilde+R_%7B%5Comega_2%7D+%2B+%5Ctilde+R_%7B%5Comega_3%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\tilde R_{\\omega_1} + \\tilde R_{\\omega_2} + \\tilde R_{\\omega_3}}\" title=\"{\\tilde R_{\\omega_1} + \\tilde R_{\\omega_2} + \\tilde R_{\\omega_3}}\" class=\"latex\" /> have too much overlap.<br /> For any <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B0+%3C+%5Cdelta+%5Cleq+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{0 < \\delta \\leq 1}\" title=\"{0 < \\delta \\leq 1}\" class=\"latex\" />, let <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BD%28%5Cdelta%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{D(\\delta)}\" title=\"{D(\\delta)}\" class=\"latex\" /> denote the supremum of the decoupling constants <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cmathrm%7BDec%7D_6%28+%5C%7B+%5Ctilde+R_%7B%5Comega%2C%5Cdelta%7D%3A+%5Comega+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma%29+%5C%7D+%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\mathrm{Dec}_6( \\{ \\tilde R_{\\omega,\\delta}: \\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma) \\} )}\" title=\"{\\mathrm{Dec}_6( \\{ \\tilde R_{\\omega,\\delta}: \\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma) \\} )}\" class=\"latex\" /> over all <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cdelta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\delta}\" title=\"{\\delta}\" class=\"latex\" />-separated subsets <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5CSigma%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\Sigma}\" title=\"{\\Sigma}\" class=\"latex\" /> of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5B-1%2C1%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{[-1,1]}\" title=\"{[-1,1]}\" class=\"latex\" />. From <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#don\">(7)</a> we have the trivial bound</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++1+%5Cleq+D%28%5Cdelta%29+%5Clesssim+%5Cdelta%5E%7B-1%2F2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  1 \\leq D(\\delta) \\lesssim \\delta^{-1/2}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  1 \\leq D(\\delta) \\lesssim \\delta^{-1/2}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p>and our task is to show that <a name=\"deps\"></a></p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++D%28%5Cdelta%29+%5Clesssim_%5Cvarepsilon+%5Cdelta%5E%7B-%5Cvarepsilon%7D+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%289%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  D(\\delta) \\lesssim_\\varepsilon \\delta^{-\\varepsilon} \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (9)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  D(\\delta) \\lesssim_\\varepsilon \\delta^{-\\varepsilon} \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (9)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p> for any <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cvarepsilon%3E0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\varepsilon>0}\" title=\"{\\varepsilon>0}\" class=\"latex\" />.<br /> We first make a minor observation on the stability of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BD%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{D}\" title=\"{D}\" class=\"latex\" /> that is not absolutely essential for the arguments, but is convenient for cleaning up the notation slightly (otherwise we would have to replace various scales <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cdelta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\delta}\" title=\"{\\delta}\" class=\"latex\" /> that appear in later arguments by comparable scales <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cdelta%27+%5Csim+%5Cdelta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\delta' \\sim \\delta}\" title=\"{\\delta' \\sim \\delta}\" class=\"latex\" />).</p> \n<blockquote>\n <p><b>Lemma 14 (Stability of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BD%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{D}\" title=\"{D}\" class=\"latex\" />)</b> <a name=\"d-stable\"></a> If <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B0+%3C+%5Cdelta%2C%5Cdelta%27+%5Cleq+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{0 < \\delta,\\delta' \\leq 1}\" title=\"{0 < \\delta,\\delta' \\leq 1}\" class=\"latex\" /> are such that <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cdelta+%5Csim+%5Cdelta%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\delta \\sim \\delta'}\" title=\"{\\delta \\sim \\delta'}\" class=\"latex\" /> then <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BD%28%5Cdelta%29+%5Csim+D%28%5Cdelta%27%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{D(\\delta) \\sim D(\\delta')}\" title=\"{D(\\delta) \\sim D(\\delta')}\" class=\"latex\" />.</p>\n</blockquote> \n<p><em>Proof:</em> Without loss of generality we may assume that <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cdelta%27+%5Cgeq+%5Cdelta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\delta' \\geq \\delta}\" title=\"{\\delta' \\geq \\delta}\" class=\"latex\" />. We first show that <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BD%28%5Cdelta%29+%5Clesssim+D%28%5Cdelta%27%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{D(\\delta) \\lesssim D(\\delta')}\" title=\"{D(\\delta) \\lesssim D(\\delta')}\" class=\"latex\" />. We need to show that</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cmathrm%7BDec%7D_6%28+%5C%7B+%5Ctilde+R_%7B%5Comega%2C%5Cdelta%7D%3A+%5Comega+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma%29%5C%7D+%29+%5Clesssim+D%28%5Cdelta%27%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Dec}_6( \\{ \\tilde R_{\\omega,\\delta}: \\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma)\\} ) \\lesssim D(\\delta')\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Dec}_6( \\{ \\tilde R_{\\omega,\\delta}: \\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma)\\} ) \\lesssim D(\\delta')\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p>whenever <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5CSigma%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\Sigma}\" title=\"{\\Sigma}\" class=\"latex\" /> is a <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cdelta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\delta}\" title=\"{\\delta}\" class=\"latex\" />-separated subset of the <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5B-1%2C1%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{[-1,1]}\" title=\"{[-1,1]}\" class=\"latex\" />. By partitioning <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5CSigma%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\Sigma}\" title=\"{\\Sigma}\" class=\"latex\" /> into <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BO%281%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{O(1)}\" title=\"{O(1)}\" class=\"latex\" /> pieces and using Exercise <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#elem\">10</a>(ii) we may assume without loss of generality that <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5CSigma%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\Sigma}\" title=\"{\\Sigma}\" class=\"latex\" /> is in fact <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cdelta%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\delta'}\" title=\"{\\delta'}\" class=\"latex\" />-separated. In particular</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cmathrm%7BDec%7D_6%28+%5C%7B+%5Ctilde+R_%7B%5Comega%2C%5Cdelta%27%7D%3A+%5Comega+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma%29+%5C%7D+%29+%5Cleq+D%28%5Cdelta%27%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Dec}_6( \\{ \\tilde R_{\\omega,\\delta'}: \\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma) \\} ) \\leq D(\\delta').\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Dec}_6( \\{ \\tilde R_{\\omega,\\delta'}: \\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma) \\} ) \\leq D(\\delta').\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p>The claim now follows from Exercise <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#elem\">10</a>(i) and the inclusion</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle+%5Ctilde+R_%7B%5Comega%2C%5Cdelta%7D+%5Csubset+%5Ctilde+R_%7B%5Comega%2C%5Cdelta%27%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle \\tilde R_{\\omega,\\delta} \\subset \\tilde R_{\\omega,\\delta'}.\" title=\"\\displaystyle \\tilde R_{\\omega,\\delta} \\subset \\tilde R_{\\omega,\\delta'}.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p>Conversely, we need to show that</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cmathrm%7BDec%7D_6%28+%5C%7B+%5Ctilde+R_%7B%5Comega%27%2C%5Cdelta%27%7D%3A+%5Comega%27+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma%27%29+%5C%7D+%29+%5Clesssim+D%28%5Cdelta%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Dec}_6( \\{ \\tilde R_{\\omega',\\delta'}: \\omega' \\in \\phi(\\Sigma') \\} ) \\lesssim D(\\delta)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Dec}_6( \\{ \\tilde R_{\\omega',\\delta'}: \\omega' \\in \\phi(\\Sigma') \\} ) \\lesssim D(\\delta)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p>whenever <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5CSigma%27+%5Csubset+%5B-1%2C1%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\Sigma' \\subset [-1,1]}\" title=\"{\\Sigma' \\subset [-1,1]}\" class=\"latex\" /> is <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cdelta%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\delta'}\" title=\"{\\delta'}\" class=\"latex\" />-separated, or equivalently that</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5C%7C+%5Csum_%7B%5Comega%27+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma%27%29%7D+f_%7B%5Comega%27%7D+%5C%7C_%7BL%5E6%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%29%7D+%5Clesssim+D%28%5Cdelta%29+%28%5Csum_%7B%5Comega%27+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma%27%29%7D+%5C%7Cf_%7B%5Comega%27%7D%5C%7C_%7BL%5E6%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%29%7D%5E2%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\| \\sum_{\\omega' \\in \\phi(\\Sigma')} f_{\\omega'} \\|_{L^6({\\bf R}^2)} \\lesssim D(\\delta) (\\sum_{\\omega' \\in \\phi(\\Sigma')} \\|f_{\\omega'}\\|_{L^6({\\bf R}^2)}^2)^{1/2}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\| \\sum_{\\omega' \\in \\phi(\\Sigma')} f_{\\omega'} \\|_{L^6({\\bf R}^2)} \\lesssim D(\\delta) (\\sum_{\\omega' \\in \\phi(\\Sigma')} \\|f_{\\omega'}\\|_{L^6({\\bf R}^2)}^2)^{1/2}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p>when <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf_%7B%5Comega%27%7D+%5Cin+L%5E6%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{f_{\\omega'} \\in L^6({\\bf R}^2)}\" title=\"{f_{\\omega'} \\in L^6({\\bf R}^2)}\" class=\"latex\" /> (we can extend from <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal S}({\\bf R}^2)}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal S}({\\bf R}^2)}\" class=\"latex\" /> to all of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BL%5E6%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{L^6({\\bf R}^2)}\" title=\"{L^6({\\bf R}^2)}\" class=\"latex\" /> by a limiting argument). From elementary geometry we see that for each <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cxi%27+%5Cin+%5CSigma%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\xi' \\in \\Sigma'}\" title=\"{\\xi' \\in \\Sigma'}\" class=\"latex\" /> we can find a subset <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5CSigma_%7B%5Cxi%27%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\Sigma_{\\xi'}}\" title=\"{\\Sigma_{\\xi'}}\" class=\"latex\" /> of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5B%5Cxi%27-%5Cdelta%27%2C%5Cxi%27%2B%5Cdelta%27%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{[\\xi'-\\delta',\\xi'+\\delta']}\" title=\"{[\\xi'-\\delta',\\xi'+\\delta']}\" class=\"latex\" /> of cardinality <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BO%281%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{O(1)}\" title=\"{O(1)}\" class=\"latex\" />, such that the parallelograms <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Ctilde+R_%7B%5Cphi%28%5Cxi%29%2C%5Cdelta%7D+%2B+%280%2C+jc%5Cdelta%5E2%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\tilde R_{\\phi(\\xi),\\delta} + (0, jc\\delta^2)}\" title=\"{\\tilde R_{\\phi(\\xi),\\delta} + (0, jc\\delta^2)}\" class=\"latex\" /> with <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bj%3DO%281%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{j=O(1)}\" title=\"{j=O(1)}\" class=\"latex\" /> an integer, <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cxi+%5Cin+%5CSigma_%7B%5Cxi%27%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\xi \\in \\Sigma_{\\xi'}}\" title=\"{\\xi \\in \\Sigma_{\\xi'}}\" class=\"latex\" />, and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bc%3E0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{c>0}\" title=\"{c>0}\" class=\"latex\" /> a sufficiently small absolute constant, cover <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BR_%7B%5Cphi%28%5Cxi%27%29%2C%5Cdelta%27%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{R_{\\phi(\\xi'),\\delta'}}\" title=\"{R_{\\phi(\\xi'),\\delta'}}\" class=\"latex\" />. In particular, using Fourier projections to polygons with <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BO%281%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{O(1)}\" title=\"{O(1)}\" class=\"latex\" /> sides, one can split <a name=\"fom\"></a></p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++f_%7B%5Cphi%28%5Cxi%27%29%7D+%3D+%5Csum_%7B%5Cxi+%5Cin+%5CSigma_%7B%5Cxi%27%7D%7D+%5Csum_%7Bj%3DO%281%29%7D+g_%7B%5Cphi%28%5Cxi%29%2Cj%7D%2C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2810%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  f_{\\phi(\\xi')} = \\sum_{\\xi \\in \\Sigma_{\\xi'}} \\sum_{j=O(1)} g_{\\phi(\\xi),j}, \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (10)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  f_{\\phi(\\xi')} = \\sum_{\\xi \\in \\Sigma_{\\xi'}} \\sum_{j=O(1)} g_{\\phi(\\xi),j}, \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (10)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p> where each <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bg_%7B%5Cphi%28%5Cxi%29%2Cj%7D+%5Cin+L%5E6%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{g_{\\phi(\\xi),j} \\in L^6({\\bf R}^2)}\" title=\"{g_{\\phi(\\xi),j} \\in L^6({\\bf R}^2)}\" class=\"latex\" /> has Fourier support in <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Ctilde+R_%7B%5Cphi%28%5Cxi%29%2C%5Cdelta%7D+%2B+%280%2Cjc%5Cdelta%5E2%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\tilde R_{\\phi(\\xi),\\delta} + (0,jc\\delta^2)}\" title=\"{\\tilde R_{\\phi(\\xi),\\delta} + (0,jc\\delta^2)}\" class=\"latex\" /> and <a name=\"gom\"></a></p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5C%7Cg_%7B%5Cphi%28%5Cxi%29%2Cj%7D+%5C%7C_%7BL%5E6%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%29%7D+%5Clesssim+%5C%7Cf_%7B%5Cphi%28%5Cxi%27%29%7D+%5C%7C_%7BL%5E6%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%29%7D.+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2811%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\|g_{\\phi(\\xi),j} \\|_{L^6({\\bf R}^2)} \\lesssim \\|f_{\\phi(\\xi')} \\|_{L^6({\\bf R}^2)}. \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (11)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\|g_{\\phi(\\xi),j} \\|_{L^6({\\bf R}^2)} \\lesssim \\|f_{\\phi(\\xi')} \\|_{L^6({\\bf R}^2)}. \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (11)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p> Now the collection <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cbigcup_%7B%5Cxi%27+%5Cin+%5CSigma%27%7D+%5CSigma_%7B%5Cxi%27%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\bigcup_{\\xi' \\in \\Sigma'} \\Sigma_{\\xi'}}\" title=\"{\\bigcup_{\\xi' \\in \\Sigma'} \\Sigma_{\\xi'}}\" class=\"latex\" /> can be partitioned into <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BO%281%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{O(1)}\" title=\"{O(1)}\" class=\"latex\" /> subcollections, each of which is <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cdelta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\delta}\" title=\"{\\delta}\" class=\"latex\" />-separated. From this and Exercise <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#elem\">10</a>(ii), (iii) we see that</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cmathrm%7BDec%7D_6%28+%5C%7B+%5Ctilde+R_%7B%5Cphi%28%5Cxi%29%2C%5Cdelta%7D+%2B+%280%2C+jc%5Cdelta%5E2%29%3A+%5Cxi+%5Cin+%5Cbigcup_%7B%5Cxi%27+%5Cin+%5CSigma%27%7D+%5CSigma_%7B%5Cxi%27%7D%3B+j+%3D+O%281%29+%5C%7D+%29+%5Clesssim+D%28%5Cdelta%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Dec}_6( \\{ \\tilde R_{\\phi(\\xi),\\delta} + (0, jc\\delta^2): \\xi \\in \\bigcup_{\\xi' \\in \\Sigma'} \\Sigma_{\\xi'}; j = O(1) \\} ) \\lesssim D(\\delta)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Dec}_6( \\{ \\tilde R_{\\phi(\\xi),\\delta} + (0, jc\\delta^2): \\xi \\in \\bigcup_{\\xi' \\in \\Sigma'} \\Sigma_{\\xi'}; j = O(1) \\} ) \\lesssim D(\\delta)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p>and thus</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5C%7C+%5Csum_%7B%5Cxi%27+%5Cin%5CSigma%27%7D+%5Csum_%7B%5Cxi+%5Cin+%5CSigma_%7B%5Cxi%27%7D%7D+%5Csum_%7Bj+%3D+O%281%29%7D+g_%7B%5Cphi%28%5Cxi%29%2Cj%7D+%5C%7C_%7BL%5E6%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%29%7D+%5Clesssim+D%28%5Cdelta%29+%28%5Csum_%7B%5Cxi%27+%5Cin+%5CSigma%27%7D+%5Csum_%7B%5Cxi+%5Cin+%5CSigma_%7B%5Cxi%27%7D%7D+%5Csum_%7Bj%3DO%281%29%7D+%5C%7Cg_%7B%5Cphi%28%5Cxi%29%2Cj%7D%5C%7C_%7BL%5E6%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%29%7D%5E2%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\| \\sum_{\\xi' \\in\\Sigma'} \\sum_{\\xi \\in \\Sigma_{\\xi'}} \\sum_{j = O(1)} g_{\\phi(\\xi),j} \\|_{L^6({\\bf R}^2)} \\lesssim D(\\delta) (\\sum_{\\xi' \\in \\Sigma'} \\sum_{\\xi \\in \\Sigma_{\\xi'}} \\sum_{j=O(1)} \\|g_{\\phi(\\xi),j}\\|_{L^6({\\bf R}^2)}^2)^{1/2}.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\| \\sum_{\\xi' \\in\\Sigma'} \\sum_{\\xi \\in \\Sigma_{\\xi'}} \\sum_{j = O(1)} g_{\\phi(\\xi),j} \\|_{L^6({\\bf R}^2)} \\lesssim D(\\delta) (\\sum_{\\xi' \\in \\Sigma'} \\sum_{\\xi \\in \\Sigma_{\\xi'}} \\sum_{j=O(1)} \\|g_{\\phi(\\xi),j}\\|_{L^6({\\bf R}^2)}^2)^{1/2}.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p>Applying <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#fom\">(10)</a>, <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#gom\">(11)</a> we obtain the claim. <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5CBox&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\Box\" title=\"\\Box\" class=\"latex\" /><br /> More importantly, we can use the symmetries of the parabola to control decoupling constants for parallelograms <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BR_%7B%5Comega%2C%5Cdelta%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{R_{\\omega,\\delta}}\" title=\"{R_{\\omega,\\delta}}\" class=\"latex\" /> in a set of diameter <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BO%28%5Cdelta_0%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{O(\\delta_0)}\" title=\"{O(\\delta_0)}\" class=\"latex\" /> in terms of a coarser scale decoupling constant <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BD%28%5Cdelta%2F%5Cdelta_0%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{D(\\delta/\\delta_0)}\" title=\"{D(\\delta/\\delta_0)}\" class=\"latex\" />:</p> \n<blockquote>\n <p><b>Proposition 15 (Parabolic rescaling)</b> <a name=\"parab-resc\"></a> Let <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B0+%3C+%5Cdelta+%5Cleq+%5Cdelta_0+%5Cleq+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{0 < \\delta \\leq \\delta_0 \\leq 1}\" title=\"{0 < \\delta \\leq \\delta_0 \\leq 1}\" class=\"latex\" />, and let <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5CSigma%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\Sigma}\" title=\"{\\Sigma}\" class=\"latex\" /> be a <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cdelta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\delta}\" title=\"{\\delta}\" class=\"latex\" />-separated subset of an interval <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI+%5Csubset+%5B-1%2C1%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{I \\subset [-1,1]}\" title=\"{I \\subset [-1,1]}\" class=\"latex\" /> of length <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B2%5Cdelta_0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{2\\delta_0}\" title=\"{2\\delta_0}\" class=\"latex\" />. Then <a name=\"d6\"></a></p> \n <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cmathrm%7BDec%7D_6%28+%5C%7B+%5Ctilde+R_%7B%5Comega%2C%5Cdelta%7D%3A+%5Comega+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma%29+%5C%7D+%29+%5Clesssim+D%28%5Cdelta%2F%5Cdelta_0%29.+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2812%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Dec}_6( \\{ \\tilde R_{\\omega,\\delta}: \\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma) \\} ) \\lesssim D(\\delta/\\delta_0). \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (12)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Dec}_6( \\{ \\tilde R_{\\omega,\\delta}: \\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma) \\} ) \\lesssim D(\\delta/\\delta_0). \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (12)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n <p></p>\n</blockquote> \n<p><em>Proof:</em> We can assume that <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cdelta_0%3Cc%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\delta_0<c}\" title=\"{\\delta_0<c}\" class=\"latex\" /> for a small absolute constant <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bc%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{c}\" title=\"{c}\" class=\"latex\" />, since when <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bc+%5Cleq+%5Cdelta_0+%5Cleq+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{c \\leq \\delta_0 \\leq 1}\" title=\"{c \\leq \\delta_0 \\leq 1}\" class=\"latex\" /> the claim follows from Lemma <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#d-stable\">14</a>. Write <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI+%3D+%5B%5Cxi_0-%5Cdelta_0%2C%5Cxi_0%2B%5Cdelta_0%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{I = [\\xi_0-\\delta_0,\\xi_0+\\delta_0]}\" title=\"{I = [\\xi_0-\\delta_0,\\xi_0+\\delta_0]}\" class=\"latex\" />. Applying the Galilean transform</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++G%3A+%28%5Cxi_1%2C+%5Cxi_2%29+%5Cmapsto+%28%5Cxi_1+-+%5Cxi_%7B0%7D%2C+%5Cxi_2+-+2+%5Cxi_%7B0%7D+%5Cxi_1+%2B+%5Cxi_%7B0%7D%5E2%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  G: (\\xi_1, \\xi_2) \\mapsto (\\xi_1 - \\xi_{0}, \\xi_2 - 2 \\xi_{0} \\xi_1 + \\xi_{0}^2)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  G: (\\xi_1, \\xi_2) \\mapsto (\\xi_1 - \\xi_{0}, \\xi_2 - 2 \\xi_{0} \\xi_1 + \\xi_{0}^2)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p>(which preserves the parabola, and maps parallelograms <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Ctilde+R_%7B%5Comega%2C%5Cdelta%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\tilde R_{\\omega,\\delta}}\" title=\"{\\tilde R_{\\omega,\\delta}}\" class=\"latex\" /> to <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Ctilde+R_%7BG%28%5Comega%29%2C%5Cdelta%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\tilde R_{G(\\omega),\\delta}}\" title=\"{\\tilde R_{G(\\omega),\\delta}}\" class=\"latex\" />) and Exercise <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#elem\">10</a>(iii), we may normalise <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cxi_0%3D0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\xi_0=0}\" title=\"{\\xi_0=0}\" class=\"latex\" />, so <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5CSigma+%5Csubset+%5B-%5Cdelta_0%2C%5Cdelta_0%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\Sigma \\subset [-\\delta_0,\\delta_0]}\" title=\"{\\Sigma \\subset [-\\delta_0,\\delta_0]}\" class=\"latex\" />.<br /> Now let <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BT%3A+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2+%5Crightarrow+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{T: {\\bf R}^2 \\rightarrow {\\bf R}^2}\" title=\"{T: {\\bf R}^2 \\rightarrow {\\bf R}^2}\" class=\"latex\" /> be the parabolic rescaling map</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++T%3A+%28%5Cxi_1%2C%5Cxi_2%29+%5Cmapsto+%28%5Cxi_1%2F%5Cdelta_0%2C+%5Cxi_2%2F%5Cdelta%5E2_0%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  T: (\\xi_1,\\xi_2) \\mapsto (\\xi_1/\\delta_0, \\xi_2/\\delta^2_0).\" title=\"\\displaystyle  T: (\\xi_1,\\xi_2) \\mapsto (\\xi_1/\\delta_0, \\xi_2/\\delta^2_0).\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p>Observe that <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BT%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{T}\" title=\"{T}\" class=\"latex\" /> maps <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Ctilde+R_%7B%5Cphi%28%5Cxi%29%2C%5Cdelta%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\tilde R_{\\phi(\\xi),\\delta}}\" title=\"{\\tilde R_{\\phi(\\xi),\\delta}}\" class=\"latex\" /> to <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Ctilde+R_%7B%5Cphi%28%5Cxi%2F%5Cdelta_0%29%2C%5Cdelta%2F%5Cdelta_0%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\tilde R_{\\phi(\\xi/\\delta_0),\\delta/\\delta_0}}\" title=\"{\\tilde R_{\\phi(\\xi/\\delta_0),\\delta/\\delta_0}}\" class=\"latex\" /> for any <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cxi%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\xi}\" title=\"{\\xi}\" class=\"latex\" />. From Exercise <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#elem\">10</a>(iii) again, we can write the left-hand side of <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#d6\">(12)</a> as</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cmathrm%7BDec%7D_6%28+%5C%7B+%5Ctilde+R_%7B%5Comega%2C%5Cdelta%2F%5Cdelta%7D%3A+%5Comega+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma%2F%5Cdelta_0%29%5C%7D+%29%3B&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Dec}_6( \\{ \\tilde R_{\\omega,\\delta/\\delta}: \\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma/\\delta_0)\\} );\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Dec}_6( \\{ \\tilde R_{\\omega,\\delta/\\delta}: \\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma/\\delta_0)\\} );\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p>since <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5CSigma%2F%5Cdelta_0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\Sigma/\\delta_0}\" title=\"{\\Sigma/\\delta_0}\" class=\"latex\" /> is <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cdelta_0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\delta_0}\" title=\"{\\delta_0}\" class=\"latex\" />-separated, the claim then follows. <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5CBox&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\Box\" title=\"\\Box\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<blockquote>\n <p><b>Exercise 16 (Multiplicativity)</b> <a name=\"mult\"></a> Show that <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BD%28%5Cdelta_1+%5Cdelta_2%29+%5Clesssim+D%28%5Cdelta_1%29+D%28%5Cdelta_2%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{D(\\delta_1 \\delta_2) \\lesssim D(\\delta_1) D(\\delta_2)}\" title=\"{D(\\delta_1 \\delta_2) \\lesssim D(\\delta_1) D(\\delta_2)}\" class=\"latex\" /> for all <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B0+%3C+%5Cdelta_1%2C%5Cdelta_2+%5Cleq+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{0 < \\delta_1,\\delta_2 \\leq 1}\" title=\"{0 < \\delta_1,\\delta_2 \\leq 1}\" class=\"latex\" />.</p>\n</blockquote> \n<p>The multiplicativity property in Exercise <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#mult\">16</a> suggests that an induction on scales
