approach could be fruitful to establish <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#deps\">(9)</a>. Interestingly, it does not seem possible to induct directly on <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BD%28%5Cdelta%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{D(\\delta)}\" title=\"{D(\\delta)}\" class=\"latex\" />; all the known proofs of this decoupling estimate proceed by introducing some auxiliary variant of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BD%28%5Cdelta%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{D(\\delta)}\" title=\"{D(\\delta)}\" class=\"latex\" /> that looks more complicated (in particular, involving additional scale parameters than just the base scale <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cdelta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\delta}\" title=\"{\\delta}\" class=\"latex\" />), but which obey some inequalities somewhat reminiscent of the one in Exercise <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#mult\">16</a> for which an induction on scale argument can be profitably executed. It is yet not well understood exactly what choices of auxiliary quantity work best, but we will use the following choice <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1805.10551\">of Li</a> of a certain “asymmetric bilinear” variant of the decoupling constant:</p> \n<blockquote>\n <p><b>Definition 17 (Bilinear decoupling constant)</b> Let <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B0+%5Cleq+%5Cdelta+%5Cleq+%5Crho_1%2C%5Crho_2+%5Cleq+%5Cnu+%5Cleq+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{0 \\leq \\delta \\leq \\rho_1,\\rho_2 \\leq \\nu \\leq 1}\" title=\"{0 \\leq \\delta \\leq \\rho_1,\\rho_2 \\leq \\nu \\leq 1}\" class=\"latex\" />. Define <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BM_%7B2%2C4%7D%28%5Cdelta%2C%5Cnu%2C+%5Crho_1%2C%5Crho_2%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu, \\rho_1,\\rho_2)}\" title=\"{M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu, \\rho_1,\\rho_2)}\" class=\"latex\" /> to be the best constant for which one has the estimate <a name=\"moo\"></a></p> \n <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cint_%7B%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%7D+%7C%5Csum_%7B%5Comega_1+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma_1%29%7D+f_%7B%5Comega_1%7D%7C%5E2+%7C%5Csum_%7B%5Comega_2+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma_2%29%7D+g_%7B%5Comega_2%7D%7C%5E4+%5Cleq+M_%7B2%2C4%7D%28%5Cdelta%2C%5Cnu%2C%5Crho_1%2C%5Crho_2%29%5E6+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2813%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\int_{{\\bf R}^2} |\\sum_{\\omega_1 \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_1)} f_{\\omega_1}|^2 |\\sum_{\\omega_2 \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_2)} g_{\\omega_2}|^4 \\leq M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\rho_1,\\rho_2)^6 \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (13)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\int_{{\\bf R}^2} |\\sum_{\\omega_1 \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_1)} f_{\\omega_1}|^2 |\\sum_{\\omega_2 \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_2)} g_{\\omega_2}|^4 \\leq M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\rho_1,\\rho_2)^6 \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (13)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n <p></p> \n <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Ctimes+%28%5Csum_%7B%5Comega_1+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma_1%29%7D+%5C%7Cf_%7B%5Comega_1%7D%5C%7C_%7BL%5E6%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%29%7D%5E2%29+%28%5Csum_%7B%5Comega_2+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma_2%29%7D+%5C%7Cg_%7B%5Comega_2%7D%5C%7C_%7BL%5E6%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%29%7D%5E2%29%5E2+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\times (\\sum_{\\omega_1 \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_1)} \\|f_{\\omega_1}\\|_{L^6({\\bf R}^2)}^2) (\\sum_{\\omega_2 \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_2)} \\|g_{\\omega_2}\\|_{L^6({\\bf R}^2)}^2)^2 \" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\times (\\sum_{\\omega_1 \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_1)} \\|f_{\\omega_1}\\|_{L^6({\\bf R}^2)}^2) (\\sum_{\\omega_2 \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_2)} \\|g_{\\omega_2}\\|_{L^6({\\bf R}^2)}^2)^2 \" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n <p>whenever <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5CSigma_1%2C%5CSigma_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\Sigma_1,\\Sigma_2}\" title=\"{\\Sigma_1,\\Sigma_2}\" class=\"latex\" /> are <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cdelta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\delta}\" title=\"{\\delta}\" class=\"latex\" />-separated subsets of intervals <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI_1%2C+I_2+%5Csubset+%5B0%2C1%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{I_1, I_2 \\subset [0,1]}\" title=\"{I_1, I_2 \\subset [0,1]}\" class=\"latex\" /> of length <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Crho_1%2C+%5Crho_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\rho_1, \\rho_2}\" title=\"{\\rho_1, \\rho_2}\" class=\"latex\" /> respectively with <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cmathrm%7Bdist%7D%28I_1%2CI_2%29+%5Cgeq+%5Cnu%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\mathrm{dist}(I_1,I_2) \\geq \\nu}\" title=\"{\\mathrm{dist}(I_1,I_2) \\geq \\nu}\" class=\"latex\" />, and for each <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Comega_1+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5COmega_1%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\omega_1 \\in \\phi(\\Omega_1)}\" title=\"{\\omega_1 \\in \\phi(\\Omega_1)}\" class=\"latex\" />, <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf_%7B%5Comega_1%7D+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{f_{\\omega_1} \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R})}\" title=\"{f_{\\omega_1} \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R})}\" class=\"latex\" /> has Fourier support in <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Ctilde+R_%7B%5Comega_1%2C%5Cdelta%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\tilde R_{\\omega_1,\\delta}}\" title=\"{\\tilde R_{\\omega_1,\\delta}}\" class=\"latex\" />, and similarly for each <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Comega_2+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5COmega_2%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\omega_2 \\in \\phi(\\Omega_2)}\" title=\"{\\omega_2 \\in \\phi(\\Omega_2)}\" class=\"latex\" />, <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bg_%7B%5Comega_2%7D+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{g_{\\omega_2} \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R})}\" title=\"{g_{\\omega_2} \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R})}\" class=\"latex\" /> has Fourier support in <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Ctilde+R_%7B%5Comega_2%2C%5Cdelta%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\tilde R_{\\omega_2,\\delta}}\" title=\"{\\tilde R_{\\omega_2,\\delta}}\" class=\"latex\" />.</p>\n</blockquote> \n<p>The scale <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cnu%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\nu}\" title=\"{\\nu}\" class=\"latex\" /> is present for technical reasons and the reader may wish to think of it as essentially being comparable to <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{1}\" title=\"{1}\" class=\"latex\" />. Rather than inducting in <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cdelta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\delta}\" title=\"{\\delta}\" class=\"latex\" />, we shall mostly keep <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cdelta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\delta}\" title=\"{\\delta}\" class=\"latex\" /> fixed and primarily induct instead on <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Crho_1%2C%5Crho_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\rho_1,\\rho_2}\" title=\"{\\rho_1,\\rho_2}\" class=\"latex\" />. As we shall see later, the asymmetric splitting of the sixth power exponent as <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B6%3D2%2B4%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{6=2+4}\" title=\"{6=2+4}\" class=\"latex\" /> is in order to exploit <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BL%5E2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{L^2}\" title=\"{L^2}\" class=\"latex\" /> orthogonality in the first factor.<br /> From Hölder’s inequality, the left-hand side of <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#moo\">(13)</a> is bounded by</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5C%7C+%5Csum_%7B%5Comega_1+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma_1%29%7D+f_%7B%5Comega_1%7D%5C%7C_%7BL%5E6%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%29%7D%5E2+%5C%7C+%5Csum_%7B%5Comega_1+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma_1%29%7D+g_%7B%5Comega_1%7D%5C%7C_%7BL%5E6%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%29%7D%5E4&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\| \\sum_{\\omega_1 \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_1)} f_{\\omega_1}\\|_{L^6({\\bf R}^2)}^2 \\| \\sum_{\\omega_1 \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_1)} g_{\\omega_1}\\|_{L^6({\\bf R}^2)}^4\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\| \\sum_{\\omega_1 \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_1)} f_{\\omega_1}\\|_{L^6({\\bf R}^2)}^2 \\| \\sum_{\\omega_1 \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_1)} g_{\\omega_1}\\|_{L^6({\\bf R}^2)}^4\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p>from which we conclude the bound <a name=\"mad\"></a></p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++M_%7B2%2C4%7D%28%5Cdelta%2C%5Cnu%2C%5Crho_1%2C%5Crho_2%29+%5Cleq+D%28%5Cdelta%29.+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2814%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\rho_1,\\rho_2) \\leq D(\\delta). \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (14)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\rho_1,\\rho_2) \\leq D(\\delta). \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (14)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p><br /> When <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Crho_1%2C%5Crho_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\rho_1,\\rho_2}\" title=\"{\\rho_1,\\rho_2}\" class=\"latex\" /> are at their maximal size <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Crho_1%3D%5Crho_2%3D%5Cnu%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\rho_1=\\rho_2=\\nu}\" title=\"{\\rho_1=\\rho_2=\\nu}\" class=\"latex\" /> we can use these bilinear decoupling constants <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BM_%7B2%2C4%7D%28%5Cdelta%2C%5Cnu%2C%5Crho_1%2C%5Crho_2%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\rho_1,\\rho_2)}\" title=\"{M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\rho_1,\\rho_2)}\" class=\"latex\" /> to recover control on the decoupling constants <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BD%28%5Cdelta%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{D(\\delta)}\" title=\"{D(\\delta)}\" class=\"latex\" />, thanks to parabolic rescaling:</p> \n<blockquote>\n <p><b>Proposition 18 (Bilinear reduction)</b> <a name=\"bile\"></a> If <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B0+%5Cleq+%5Cdelta+%5Cleq+%5Cnu+%5Cleq+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{0 \\leq \\delta \\leq \\nu \\leq 1}\" title=\"{0 \\leq \\delta \\leq \\nu \\leq 1}\" class=\"latex\" />, then</p> \n <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++D%28%5Cdelta%29+%5Clesssim+%5Cnu%5E%7B-O%281%29%7D+M_%7B2%2C4%7D%28%5Cdelta%2C+%5Cnu%2C+%5Cnu%2C+%5Cnu%29+%2B+D%28%5Cdelta%2F%5Cnu%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  D(\\delta) \\lesssim \\nu^{-O(1)} M_{2,4}(\\delta, \\nu, \\nu, \\nu) + D(\\delta/\\nu).\" title=\"\\displaystyle  D(\\delta) \\lesssim \\nu^{-O(1)} M_{2,4}(\\delta, \\nu, \\nu, \\nu) + D(\\delta/\\nu).\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n</blockquote> \n<p><em>Proof:</em> Let <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5CSigma%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\Sigma}\" title=\"{\\Sigma}\" class=\"latex\" /> be a <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cdelta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\delta}\" title=\"{\\delta}\" class=\"latex\" />-separated subset of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5B-1%2C1%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{[-1,1]}\" title=\"{[-1,1]}\" class=\"latex\" />, and for each <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Comega+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma)}\" title=\"{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma)}\" class=\"latex\" /> let <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf_%5Comega+%5Cin+L%5E6%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{f_\\omega \\in L^6({\\bf R}^2)}\" title=\"{f_\\omega \\in L^6({\\bf R}^2)}\" class=\"latex\" /> be Fourier supported in <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Ctilde+R_%7B%5Comega%2C%5Cdelta%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\tilde R_{\\omega,\\delta}}\" title=\"{\\tilde R_{\\omega,\\delta}}\" class=\"latex\" />. We may normalise <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Csum_%7B%5Comega+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma%29%7D+%5C%7C+f_%5Comega%5C%7C_%7BL%5E6%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%29%7D%5E2+%3D+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma)} \\| f_\\omega\\|_{L^6({\\bf R}^2)}^2 = 1}\" title=\"{\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma)} \\| f_\\omega\\|_{L^6({\\bf R}^2)}^2 = 1}\" class=\"latex\" />. It will then suffice to show that <a name=\"super\"></a></p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cint_%7B%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%7D+%7C%5Csum_%7B%5Comega+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma%29%7D+f_%5Comega%7C%5E6+%5Clesssim+%5Cnu%5E%7B-O%281%29%7D+M_%7B2%2C4%7D%28%5Cdelta%2C+%5Cnu%2C+%5Cnu%2C+%5Cnu%29%5E6+%2B+D%28%5Cdelta%2F%5Cnu%29%5E6.+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2815%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\int_{{\\bf R}^2} |\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma)} f_\\omega|^6 \\lesssim \\nu^{-O(1)} M_{2,4}(\\delta, \\nu, \\nu, \\nu)^6 + D(\\delta/\\nu)^6. \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (15)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\int_{{\\bf R}^2} |\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma)} f_\\omega|^6 \\lesssim \\nu^{-O(1)} M_{2,4}(\\delta, \\nu, \\nu, \\nu)^6 + D(\\delta/\\nu)^6. \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (15)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p> We partition <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5CSigma%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\Sigma}\" title=\"{\\Sigma}\" class=\"latex\" /> into disjoint components <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5CSigma_I%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\Sigma_I}\" title=\"{\\Sigma_I}\" class=\"latex\" />, each of which is supported in a subinterval <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{I}\" title=\"{I}\" class=\"latex\" /> of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5B-1%2C1%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{[-1,1]}\" title=\"{[-1,1]}\" class=\"latex\" /> of length <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cnu%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\nu}\" title=\"{\\nu}\" class=\"latex\" />, with the family <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+I%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal I}}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal I}}\" class=\"latex\" /> of intervals <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{I}\" title=\"{I}\" class=\"latex\" /> having bounded overlap, so in particular <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+I%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal I}}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal I}}\" class=\"latex\" /> has cardinality <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BO%28%5Cnu%5E%7B-1%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{O(\\nu^{-1})}\" title=\"{O(\\nu^{-1})}\" class=\"latex\" />. Then for any <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bx+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{x \\in {\\bf R}^2}\" title=\"{x \\in {\\bf R}^2}\" class=\"latex\" />, we of course have</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_%7B%5Comega+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma%29%7D+f_%5Comega%28x%29%7C+%5Cleq+%5Csum_%7BI+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+I%7D%7D+%7C%5Csum_%7B%5Comega+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma_I%29%7D+f_%5Comega%28x%29%7C.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  |\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma)} f_\\omega(x)| \\leq \\sum_{I \\in {\\mathcal I}} |\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_I)} f_\\omega(x)|.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  |\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma)} f_\\omega(x)| \\leq \\sum_{I \\in {\\mathcal I}} |\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_I)} f_\\omega(x)|.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p>From the pigeonhole principle, this implies at least one of the following statements needs to hold for each given <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bx%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{x}\" title=\"{x}\" class=\"latex\" />:</p> \n<ul> \n <li>(i) (Narrow case) There exists <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+I%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{I \\in {\\mathcal I}}\" title=\"{I \\in {\\mathcal I}}\" class=\"latex\" /> such that <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_%7B%5Comega+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma%29%7D+f_%5Comega%28x%29%7C+%5Clesssim+%7C%5Csum_%7B%5Comega+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma_I%29%7D+f_%5Comega%28x%29%7C.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  |\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma)} f_\\omega(x)| \\lesssim |\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_I)} f_\\omega(x)|.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  |\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma)} f_\\omega(x)| \\lesssim |\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_I)} f_\\omega(x)|.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> </li> \n <li>(ii) (Broad case) There exist distinct intervals <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI%2CJ+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+I%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{I,J \\in {\\mathcal I}}\" title=\"{I,J \\in {\\mathcal I}}\" class=\"latex\" /> with <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cmathrm%7Bdist%7D%28I%2CJ%29+%5Cgeq+%5Cnu%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\mathrm{dist}(I,J) \\geq \\nu}\" title=\"{\\mathrm{dist}(I,J) \\geq \\nu}\" class=\"latex\" /> such that <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_%7B%5Comega+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma%29%7D+f_%5Comega%28x%29%7C+%5Clesssim+%5Cnu%5E%7B-O%281%29%7D+%7C%5Csum_%7B%5Comega+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma_I%29%7D+f_%5Comega%28x%29%7C%2C+%5Cnu%5E%7B-O%281%29%7D+%7C%5Csum_%7B%5Comega+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma_J%29%7D+f_%5Comega%28x%29%7C.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  |\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma)} f_\\omega(x)| \\lesssim \\nu^{-O(1)} |\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_I)} f_\\omega(x)|, \\nu^{-O(1)} |\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_J)} f_\\omega(x)|.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  |\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma)} f_\\omega(x)| \\lesssim \\nu^{-O(1)} |\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_I)} f_\\omega(x)|, \\nu^{-O(1)} |\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_J)} f_\\omega(x)|.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> </li> \n</ul> \n<p>(The reason for this is as follows. Write <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BA+%3A%3D+%7C%5Csum_%7B%5Comega+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma%29%7D+f_%5Comega%28x%29%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{A := |\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma)} f_\\omega(x)|}\" title=\"{A := |\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma)} f_\\omega(x)|}\" class=\"latex\" /> and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BA_I+%3A%3D+%7C%5Csum_%7B%5Comega+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma_I%29%7D+f_%5Comega%28x%29%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{A_I := |\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_I)} f_\\omega(x)|}\" title=\"{A_I := |\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_I)} f_\\omega(x)|}\" class=\"latex\" />, then <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BA+%5Cleq+%5Csum_I+A_I%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{A \\leq \\sum_I A_I}\" title=\"{A \\leq \\sum_I A_I}\" class=\"latex\" />. Let <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN+%3D+O%28%5Cnu%5E%7B-1%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{N = O(\\nu^{-1})}\" title=\"{N = O(\\nu^{-1})}\" class=\"latex\" /> be the number of intervals <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{I}\" title=\"{I}\" class=\"latex\" />, then <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Csum_%7BI%3A+A_I+%5Cleq+A%2F2N%7D+A_I+%5Cleq+A%2F2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\sum_{I: A_I \\leq A/2N} A_I \\leq A/2}\" title=\"{\\sum_{I: A_I \\leq A/2N} A_I \\leq A/2}\" class=\"latex\" />, hence <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Csum_%7BI%3A+A_I+%3E+A%2F2N%7D+A_I+%3E+A%2F2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\sum_{I: A_I > A/2N} A_I > A/2}\" title=\"{\\sum_{I: A_I > A/2N} A_I > A/2}\" class=\"latex\" />. If there are only <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BO%281%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{O(1)}\" title=\"{O(1)}\" class=\"latex\" /> intervals <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{I}\" title=\"{I}\" class=\"latex\" /> for which <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BA_I+%3E+A%2F2N%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{A_I > A/2N}\" title=\"{A_I > A/2N}\" class=\"latex\" />, then by the pigeonhole principle we have <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BA_I+%5Cgtrsim+A%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{A_I \\gtrsim A}\" title=\"{A_I \\gtrsim A}\" class=\"latex\" /> for one of these <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{I}\" title=\"{I}\" class=\"latex\" /> and we are in the narrow case (i); otherwise, if there are sufficiently many <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{I}\" title=\"{I}\" class=\"latex\" /> for which <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BA_I+%3E+A%2F2N%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{A_I > A/2N}\" title=\"{A_I > A/2N}\" class=\"latex\" />, one can find two such <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI%2CJ%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{I,J}\" title=\"{I,J}\" class=\"latex\" /> with <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cmathrm%7Bdist%7D%28I%2CJ%29+%5Cgeq+%5Cnu%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\mathrm{dist}(I,J) \\geq \\nu}\" title=\"{\\mathrm{dist}(I,J) \\geq \\nu}\" class=\"latex\" />, and we are in the broad case (ii).) This implies the pointwise bound</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_%7B%5Comega+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma%29%7D+f_%5Comega%7C%5E6+%5Clesssim+%5Cnu%5E%7B-O%281%29%7D+%5Csum_%7BI%2CJ+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+I%7D%3A+%5Cmathrm%7Bdist%7D%28I%2CJ%29+%5Cgeq+%5Cnu%7D+%7C%5Csum_%7B%5Comega+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma_I%29%7D+f_%5Comega%7C%5E2+%7C%5Csum_%7B%5Comega+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma_J%29%7D+f_%5Comega%7C%5E4+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  |\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma)} f_\\omega|^6 \\lesssim \\nu^{-O(1)} \\sum_{I,J \\in {\\mathcal I}: \\mathrm{dist}(I,J) \\geq \\nu} |\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_I)} f_\\omega|^2 |\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_J)} f_\\omega|^4 \" title=\"\\displaystyle  |\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma)} f_\\omega|^6 \\lesssim \\nu^{-O(1)} \\sum_{I,J \\in {\\mathcal I}: \\mathrm{dist}(I,J) \\geq \\nu} |\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_I)} f_\\omega|^2 |\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_J)} f_\\omega|^4 \" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle+%2B+%5Csum_%7BI+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+I%7D%7D+%7C%5Csum_%7B%5Comega+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma_I%29%7D+f_%5Comega%7C%5E6.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle + \\sum_{I \\in {\\mathcal I}} |\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_I)} f_\\omega|^6.\" title=\"\\displaystyle + \\sum_{I \\in {\\mathcal I}} |\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_I)} f_\\omega|^6.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p>(We remark that more advanced versions of this “narrow-broad decomposition” in higher dimensions, taking into account more of the geometry of the various frequencies <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Comega%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\omega}\" title=\"{\\omega}\" class=\"latex\" /> that arise in such sums, are useful in both restriction and decoupling theory; see this <a href=\"https://mathscinet.ams.org/mathscinet-getitem?mr=3877019\">paper of Guth</a> for more discussion.) From <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#moo\">(13)</a> we have</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cint_%7B%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%7D+%7C%5Csum_%7B%5Comega+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma_I%29%7D+f_%5Comega%7C%5E2+%7C%5Csum_%7B%5Comega+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma_J%29%7D+f_%5Comega%7C%5E4+%5Clesssim+M_%7B2%2C4%7D%28%5Cdelta%2C%5Cnu%2C%5Cnu%2C%5Cnu%29%5E6&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\int_{{\\bf R}^2} |\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_I)} f_\\omega|^2 |\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_J)} f_\\omega|^4 \\lesssim M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\nu,\\nu)^6\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\int_{{\\bf R}^2} |\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_I)} f_\\omega|^2 |\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_J)} f_\\omega|^4 \\lesssim M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\nu,\\nu)^6\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p>while from Proposition <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#parab-resc\">15</a> we have</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cint_%7B%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%7D+%7C%5Csum_%7B%5Comega+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma_I%29%7D+f_%5Comega%7C%5E6+%5Clesssim+D%28%5Cdelta%2F%5Cnu%29%5E6+%28%5Csum_%7B%5Comega+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma_I%29%7D+%5C%7C+f_%5Comega%5C%7C_%7BL%5E6%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%29%7D%5E2%29%5E3+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\int_{{\\bf R}^2} |\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_I)} f_\\omega|^6 \\lesssim D(\\delta/\\nu)^6 (\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_I)} \\| f_\\omega\\|_{L^6({\\bf R}^2)}^2)^3 \" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\int_{{\\bf R}^2} |\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_I)} f_\\omega|^6 \\lesssim D(\\delta/\\nu)^6 (\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_I)} \\| f_\\omega\\|_{L^6({\\bf R}^2)}^2)^3 \" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p>and hence</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7BI+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+I%7D%7D+%5Cint_%7B%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%7D+%7C%5Csum_%7B%5Comega+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma_I%29%7D+f_%5Comega%7C%5E6+%5Clesssim+D%28%5Cdelta%2F%5Cnu%29%5E6+%28%5Csum_%7B%5Comega+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma%29%7D+%5C%7C+f_%5Comega%5C%7C_%7BL%5E6%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%29%7D%5E2%29%5E3+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{I \\in {\\mathcal I}} \\int_{{\\bf R}^2} |\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_I)} f_\\omega|^6 \\lesssim D(\\delta/\\nu)^6 (\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma)} \\| f_\\omega\\|_{L^6({\\bf R}^2)}^2)^3 \" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{I \\in {\\mathcal I}} \\int_{{\\bf R}^2} |\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_I)} f_\\omega|^6 \\lesssim D(\\delta/\\nu)^6 (\\sum_{\\omega \\in \\phi(\\Sigma)} \\| f_\\omega\\|_{L^6({\\bf R}^2)}^2)^3 \" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%3D+D%28%5Cdelta%2F%5Cnu%29%5E6.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  = D(\\delta/\\nu)^6.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  = D(\\delta/\\nu)^6.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p>Combining all these estimates, we obtain the claim. <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5CBox&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\Box\" title=\"\\Box\" class=\"latex\" /><br /> In practice the <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BD%28%5Cdelta%2F%5Cnu%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{D(\\delta/\\nu)}\" title=\"{D(\\delta/\\nu)}\" class=\"latex\" /> term here will be negligible as long as <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cnu%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\nu}\" title=\"{\\nu}\" class=\"latex\" /> is just slightly smaller than <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{1}\" title=\"{1}\" class=\"latex\" /> (e.g. <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cnu+%3D+%5Cdelta%5E%5Cvarepsilon%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\nu = \\delta^\\varepsilon}\" title=\"{\\nu = \\delta^\\varepsilon}\" class=\"latex\" /> for some small <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cvarepsilon%3E0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\varepsilon>0}\" title=\"{\\varepsilon>0}\" class=\"latex\" />). Thus, the above bilinear reduction is asserting that up to powers of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cnu%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\nu}\" title=\"{\\nu}\" class=\"latex\" /> (which will be an acceptable loss in practice), the quantity <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BD%28%5Cdelta%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{D(\\delta)}\" title=\"{D(\\delta)}\" class=\"latex\" /> is basically comparable to <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BM_%7B2%2C4%7D%28%5Cdelta%2C%5Cnu%2C%5Cnu%2C%5Cnu%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\nu,\\nu)}\" title=\"{M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\nu,\\nu)}\" class=\"latex\" />.<br /> If we immediately apply insert <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#mad\">(14)</a> into the above lemma, we obtain a useless inequality due to the loss of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cnu%5E%7B-O%281%29%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\nu^{-O(1)})}\" title=\"{\\nu^{-O(1)})}\" class=\"latex\" /> in the main term on the right-hand side. To get an improved estimate, we will need a recursive inequality that allows one to slowly gain additional powers of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cnu%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\nu}\" title=\"{\\nu}\" class=\"latex\" /> at the cost of decreasing the size of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Crho_1%2C%5Crho_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\rho_1,\\rho_2}\" title=\"{\\rho_1,\\rho_2}\" class=\"latex\" /> factors (but as long as <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cnu%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\nu}\" title=\"{\\nu}\" class=\"latex\" /> is much larger than <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cdelta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\delta}\" title=\"{\\delta}\" class=\"latex\" />, we will have enough “room” to iterate this inequality repeatedly). The key tool for doing this (and the main reason why we make the rather odd choice of splitting the exponents as <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B6%3D2%2B4%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{6=2+4}\" title=\"{6=2+4}\" class=\"latex\" />) is</p> \n<blockquote>\n <p><b>Proposition 19 (Key estimate)</b> <a name=\"key\"></a> If <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B0+%5Cleq+%5Cdelta+%5Cleq+%5Crho%27_1%2C%5Crho_1%2C%5Crho_2+%5Cleq+%5Cnu+%5Cleq+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{0 \\leq \\delta \\leq \\rho'_1,\\rho_1,\\rho_2 \\leq \\nu \\leq 1}\" title=\"{0 \\leq \\delta \\leq \\rho'_1,\\rho_1,\\rho_2 \\leq \\nu \\leq 1}\" class=\"latex\" /> with <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Crho_2%5E2+%5Cleq+%5Crho%27_1+%5Cleq+%5Crho_1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\rho_2^2 \\leq \\rho'_1 \\leq \\rho_1}\" title=\"{\\rho_2^2 \\leq \\rho'_1 \\leq \\rho_1}\" class=\"latex\" /> then</p> \n <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++M_%7B2%2C4%7D%28%5Cdelta%2C%5Cnu%2C%5Crho_1%2C%5Crho_2%29+%5Clesssim+%5Cnu%5E%7B-O%281%29%7D+M_%7B2%2C4%7D%28%5Cdelta%2C%5Cnu%2C%5Crho%27_1%2C%5Crho_2%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\rho_1,\\rho_2) \\lesssim \\nu^{-O(1)} M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\rho'_1,\\rho_2).\" title=\"\\displaystyle  M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\rho_1,\\rho_2) \\lesssim \\nu^{-O(1)} M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\rho'_1,\\rho_2).\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n</blockquote> \n<p><em>Proof:</em> It will suffice to show that <a name=\"lh\"></a></p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cint_%7B%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%7D+%7C%5Csum_%7B%5Comega_1+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma_1%29%7D+f_%7B%5Comega_1%7D%7C%5E2+%7C%5Csum_%7B%5Comega_2+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma_2%29%7D+g_%7B%5Comega_2%7D%7C%5E4+%5Clesssim+%5Cnu%5E%7B-O%281%29%7D+M_%7B2%2C4%7D%28%5Cdelta%2C%5Cnu%2C%5Crho%27_1%2C%5Crho_2%29%5E6+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2816%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\int_{{\\bf R}^2} |\\sum_{\\omega_1 \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_1)} f_{\\omega_1}|^2 |\\sum_{\\omega_2 \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_2)} g_{\\omega_2}|^4 \\lesssim \\nu^{-O(1)} M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\rho'_1,\\rho_2)^6 \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (16)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\int_{{\\bf R}^2} |\\sum_{\\omega_1 \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_1)} f_{\\omega_1}|^2 |\\sum_{\\omega_2 \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_2)} g_{\\omega_2}|^4 \\lesssim \\nu^{-O(1)} M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\rho'_1,\\rho_2)^6 \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (16)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p> whenever <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5CSigma_1%2C+%5CSigma_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\Sigma_1, \\Sigma_2}\" title=\"{\\Sigma_1, \\Sigma_2}\" class=\"latex\" /> are <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cdelta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\delta}\" title=\"{\\delta}\" class=\"latex\" />-separated subsets of intervals <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI%2C+J+%5Csubset+%5B-1%2C1%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{I, J \\subset [-1,1]}\" title=\"{I, J \\subset [-1,1]}\" class=\"latex\" /> of length <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Crho_1%2C+%5Crho_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\rho_1, \\rho_2}\" title=\"{\\rho_1, \\rho_2}\" class=\"latex\" /> respectively with <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cmathrm%7Bdist%7D%28I%2CJ%29+%5Cgeq+%5Cnu%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\mathrm{dist}(I,J) \\geq \\nu}\" title=\"{\\mathrm{dist}(I,J) \\geq \\nu}\" class=\"latex\" />, and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf_%7B%5Comega_1%7D%2C+g_%7B%5Comega_2%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{f_{\\omega_1}, g_{\\omega_2}}\" title=\"{f_{\\omega_1}, g_{\\omega_2}}\" class=\"latex\" /> have Fourier support on <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Ctilde+R_%7B%5Comega_1%2C%5Cdelta%7D%2C+%5Ctilde+R_%7B%5Comega_2%2C%5Cdelta%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\tilde R_{\\omega_1,\\delta}, \\tilde R_{\\omega_2,\\delta}}\" title=\"{\\tilde R_{\\omega_1,\\delta}, \\tilde R_{\\omega_2,\\delta}}\" class=\"latex\" /> respectvely for <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Comega_1+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma_1%29%2C+%5Comega_2+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma_2%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\omega_1 \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_1), \\omega_2 \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_2)}\" title=\"{\\omega_1 \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_1), \\omega_2 \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_2)}\" class=\"latex\" />, and we have the normalisation</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7B%5Comega_1+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma_1%29%7D+%5C%7Cf_%7B%5Comega_1%7D%5C%7C_%7BL%5E6%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%29%7D%5E2+%3D+%5Csum_%7B%5Comega_2+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma_2%29%7D+%5C%7Cg_%7B%5Comega_2%7D%5C%7C_%7BL%5E6%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%29%7D%5E2+%3D+1.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{\\omega_1 \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_1)} \\|f_{\\omega_1}\\|_{L^6({\\bf R}^2)}^2 = \\sum_{\\omega_2 \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_2)} \\|g_{\\omega_2}\\|_{L^6({\\bf R}^2)}^2 = 1.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{\\omega_1 \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_1)} \\|f_{\\omega_1}\\|_{L^6({\\bf R}^2)}^2 = \\sum_{\\omega_2 \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_2)} \\|g_{\\omega_2}\\|_{L^6({\\bf R}^2)}^2 = 1.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p>We can partition <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5CSigma_1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\Sigma_1}\" title=\"{\\Sigma_1}\" class=\"latex\" /> as <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5CSigma_1+%3D+%5Cbiguplus_%7BI%27+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+I%7D%27%7D+%5CSigma_%7B1%2CI%27%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\Sigma_1 = \\biguplus_{I' \\in {\\mathcal I}'} \\Sigma_{1,I'}}\" title=\"{\\Sigma_1 = \\biguplus_{I' \\in {\\mathcal I}'} \\Sigma_{1,I'}}\" class=\"latex\" />, where <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+I%7D%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal I}'}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal I}'}\" class=\"latex\" /> is a collection of intervals <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI%27+%5Csubset+I%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{I' \\subset I}\" title=\"{I' \\subset I}\" class=\"latex\" /> of length <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Crho%27_1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\rho'_1}\" title=\"{\\rho'_1}\" class=\"latex\" /> that have bounded overlap, and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5CSigma_%7B1%2CI%27%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\Sigma_{1,I'}}\" title=\"{\\Sigma_{1,I'}}\" class=\"latex\" /> is a <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cdelta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\delta}\" title=\"{\\delta}\" class=\"latex\" />-separated subset of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{I'}\" title=\"{I'}\" class=\"latex\" />. We can then rewrite the left-hand side of <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#lh\">(16)</a> as</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5C%7C+%5Csum_%7BI%27+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+I%7D%27%7D+F_%7BI%27%7D+G%5E2+%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%29%7D%5E2&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\| \\sum_{I' \\in {\\mathcal I}'} F_{I'} G^2 \\|_{L^2({\\bf R}^2)}^2\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\| \\sum_{I' \\in {\\mathcal I}'} F_{I'} G^2 \\|_{L^2({\\bf R}^2)}^2\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p>where</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++F_%7BI%27%7D+%3A%3D+%5Csum_%7B%5Comega_1+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma_%7B1%2CI%27%7D%29%7D+f_%7B%5Comega_1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  F_{I'} := \\sum_{\\omega_1 \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_{1,I'})} f_{\\omega_1}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  F_{I'} := \\sum_{\\omega_1 \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_{1,I'})} f_{\\omega_1}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p>and</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++G+%3A%3D+%5Csum_%7B%5Comega_2+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma_2%29%7D+g_%7B%5Comega_2%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  G := \\sum_{\\omega_2 \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_2)} g_{\\omega_2}.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  G := \\sum_{\\omega_2 \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_2)} g_{\\omega_2}.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p>From <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#moo\">(13)</a> we have</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5C%7C+F_%7BI%27%7D+G%5E2+%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%29%7D%5E2+%5Cleq+M_%7B2%2C4%7D%28%5Cdelta%2C%5Cnu%2C%5Crho%27_1%2C%5Crho_2%29%5E6+%5Csum_%7B%5Comega_1+%5Cin+%5Cphi%28%5CSigma_%7B1%2CI%27%7D%29%7D+%5C%7Cf_%7B%5Comega_1%7D%5C%7C_%7BL%5E6%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%29%7D%5E2&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\| F_{I'} G^2 \\|_{L^2({\\bf R}^2)}^2 \\leq M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\rho'_1,\\rho_2)^6 \\sum_{\\omega_1 \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_{1,I'})} \\|f_{\\omega_1}\\|_{L^6({\\bf R}^2)}^2\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\| F_{I'} G^2 \\|_{L^2({\\bf R}^2)}^2 \\leq M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\rho'_1,\\rho_2)^6 \\sum_{\\omega_1 \\in \\phi(\\Sigma_{1,I'})} \\|f_{\\omega_1}\\|_{L^6({\\bf R}^2)}^2\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p>so it will suffice to prove the almost orthogonality estimate</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5C%7C+%5Csum_%7BI%27+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+I%7D%27%7D+F_%7BI%27%7D+G%5E2+%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%29%7D%5E2+%5Clesssim+%5Cnu%5E%7B-O%281%29%7D+%5Csum_%7BI%27+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+I%7D%27%7D+%5C%7C+F_%7BI%27%7D+G%5E2+%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%29%7D%5E2.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\| \\sum_{I' \\in {\\mathcal I}'} F_{I'} G^2 \\|_{L^2({\\bf R}^2)}^2 \\lesssim \\nu^{-O(1)} \\sum_{I' \\in {\\mathcal I}'} \\| F_{I'} G^2 \\|_{L^2({\\bf R}^2)}^2.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\| \\sum_{I' \\in {\\mathcal I}'} F_{I'} G^2 \\|_{L^2({\\bf R}^2)}^2 \\lesssim \\nu^{-O(1)} \\sum_{I' \\in {\\mathcal I}'} \\| F_{I'} G^2 \\|_{L^2({\\bf R}^2)}^2.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p>By Lemma <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#bio\">6</a>(i), it suffices to show that the Fourier supports of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BF_%7BI%27%7D+G%5E2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{F_{I'} G^2}\" title=\"{F_{I'} G^2}\" class=\"latex\" /> have overlap <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BO%28%5Cnu%5E%7B-O%281%29%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{O(\\nu^{-O(1)})}\" title=\"{O(\\nu^{-O(1)})}\" class=\"latex\" />.<br /> Applying a Galilean transformation, we may normalise the interval <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BJ%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{J}\" title=\"{J}\" class=\"latex\" /> to be centered at the origin, thus <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BJ+%3D+%5B-%5Crho_2%2F2%2C%5Crho_2%2F2%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{J = [-\\rho_2/2,\\rho_2/2]}\" title=\"{J = [-\\rho_2/2,\\rho_2/2]}\" class=\"latex\" />, and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{I}\" title=\"{I}\" class=\"latex\" /> is now at a distance <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cgtrsim+%5Cnu%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\gtrsim \\nu}\" title=\"{\\gtrsim \\nu}\" class=\"latex\" /> from the origin. (Strictly speaking this may push <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI%2C+I%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{I, I'}\" title=\"{I, I'}\" class=\"latex\" /> out to now lie in <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5B-2%2C2%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{[-2,2]}\" title=\"{[-2,2]}\" class=\"latex\" /> rather than <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5B-1%2C1%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{[-1,1]}\" title=\"{[-1,1]}\" class=\"latex\" />, but this will not make a significant impact to the arguments.) In particular, all the rectangles <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Ctilde+R_%7B%5Comega_2%2C%5Cdelta%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\tilde R_{\\omega_2,\\delta}}\" title=\"{\\tilde R_{\\omega_2,\\delta}}\" class=\"latex\" />, <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Comega_2+%5Cin+%5CSigma_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\omega_2 \\in \\Sigma_2}\" title=\"{\\omega_2 \\in \\Sigma_2}\" class=\"latex\" />, now lie in a rectangle of the form <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5C%7B+%28%5Cxi_1%2C%5Cxi_2%29%3A+%5Cxi_1+%3D+O%28%5Crho_2%29%2C+%5Cxi_2+%3D+O%28%5Crho_2%5E2+%2B+%5Cdelta%29+%5C%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\{ (\\xi_1,\\xi_2): \\xi_1 = O(\\rho_2), \\xi_2 = O(\\rho_2^2 + \\delta) \\}}\" title=\"{\\{ (\\xi_1,\\xi_2): \\xi_1 = O(\\rho_2), \\xi_2 = O(\\rho_2^2 + \\delta) \\}}\" class=\"latex\" />, and hence <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BG%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{G}\" title=\"{G}\" class=\"latex\" /> and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BG%5E2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{G^2}\" title=\"{G^2}\" class=\"latex\" /> have Fourier support in such a rectangle also (after enlarging the implied constants in the <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BO%28%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{O()}\" title=\"{O()}\" class=\"latex\" /> notation appropriately). Meanwhile, if <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI%27+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+I%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{I' \\in {\\mathcal I}}\" title=\"{I' \\in {\\mathcal I}}\" class=\"latex\" /> is centered at <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cxi_%7BI%27%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\xi_{I'}}\" title=\"{\\xi_{I'}}\" class=\"latex\" />, then (since the map <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cxi+%5Cmapsto+%5Cxi%5E2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\xi \\mapsto \\xi^2}\" title=\"{\\xi \\mapsto \\xi^2}\" class=\"latex\" /> has Lipschitz constant <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BO%281%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{O(1)}\" title=\"{O(1)}\" class=\"latex\" /> when <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cxi+%5Cin+%5B-2%2C2%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\xi \\in [-2,2]}\" title=\"{\\xi \\in [-2,2]}\" class=\"latex\" /> and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cdelta+%5Cleq+%5Crho%27_1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\delta \\leq \\rho'_1}\" title=\"{\\delta \\leq \\rho'_1}\" class=\"latex\" />) the parallelogram <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Ctilde+R_%7B%5Comega_1%2C%5Cdelta%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\tilde R_{\\omega_1,\\delta}}\" title=\"{\\tilde R_{\\omega_1,\\delta}}\" class=\"latex\" /> is supported in the strip <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5C%7B+%28%5Cxi_1%2C%5Cxi_2%29%3A+%5Cxi_2+%3D+%5Cxi_%7BI%27%7D%5E2+%2B+O%28+%5Crho%27_1+%29+%5C%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\{ (\\xi_1,\\xi_2): \\xi_2 = \\xi_{I'}^2 + O( \\rho'_1 ) \\}}\" title=\"{\\{ (\\xi_1,\\xi_2): \\xi_2 = \\xi_{I'}^2 + O( \\rho'_1 ) \\}}\" class=\"latex\" /> for any <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Comega_1+%5Cin+%5CSigma_%7B1%2CI%27%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\omega_1 \\in \\Sigma_{1,I'}}\" title=\"{\\omega_1 \\in \\Sigma_{1,I'}}\" class=\"latex\" />, hence <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BF_%7BI%27%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{F_{I'}}\" title=\"{F_{I'}}\" class=\"latex\" /> will also be supported in such a strip. Since <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Crho%27_1+%5Cgeq+%5Crho_2%5E2%2C+%5Cdelta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\rho'_1 \\geq \\rho_2^2, \\delta}\" title=\"{\\rho'_1 \\geq \\rho_2^2, \\delta}\" class=\"latex\" />, <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BF_%7BI%27%7D+G%5E2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{F_{I'} G^2}\" title=\"{F_{I'} G^2}\" class=\"latex\" /> is supported in a similar strip (with slightly different implied constants in the <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BO%28%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{O()}\" title=\"{O()}\" class=\"latex\" /> notation). Thus, if <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BF_%7BI%27%7D+G%5E2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{F_{I'} G^2}\" title=\"{F_{I'} G^2}\" class=\"latex\" /> and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BF_%7BJ%27%7D+G%5E2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{F_{J'} G^2}\" title=\"{F_{J'} G^2}\" class=\"latex\" /> have overlapping Fourier supports for <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI%27%2CJ%27+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+I%7D%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{I',J' \\in {\\mathcal I}'}\" title=\"{I',J' \\in {\\mathcal I}'}\" class=\"latex\" />, then <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cxi_%7BI%27%7D%5E2+%3D+%5Cxi_%7BJ%27%7D%5E2+%2B+O%28%5Crho%27_1%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\xi_{I'}^2 = \\xi_{J'}^2 + O(\\rho'_1)}\" title=\"{\\xi_{I'}^2 = \\xi_{J'}^2 + O(\\rho'_1)}\" class=\"latex\" />, hence (since <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7C%5Cxi_%7BI%27%7D%7C+%5Cgtrsim+%5Cnu%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{|\\xi_{I'}| \\gtrsim \\nu}\" title=\"{|\\xi_{I'}| \\gtrsim \\nu}\" class=\"latex\" />) <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cxi_%7BI%27%7D+%3D+%5Cpm+%5Cxi_%7BJ%27%7D+%2B+O%28%5Cnu%5E%7B-O%281%29%7D+%5Crho%27_1%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\xi_{I'} = \\pm \\xi_{J'} + O(\\nu^{-O(1)} \\rho'_1)}\" title=\"{\\xi_{I'} = \\pm \\xi_{J'} + O(\\nu^{-O(1)} \\rho'_1)}\" class=\"latex\" />. Since the intervals <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BJ%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{J'}\" title=\"{J'}\" class=\"latex\" /> have length <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Crho%27_1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\rho'_1}\" title=\"{\\rho'_1}\" class=\"latex\" /> and bounded overlap, we thus see that each <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{I'}\" title=\"{I'}\" class=\"latex\" /> has at most <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BO%28%5Cnu%5E%7B-O%281%29%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{O(\\nu^{-O(1)})}\" title=\"{O(\\nu^{-O(1)})}\" class=\"latex\" /> intervals <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BJ%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{J'}\" title=\"{J'}\" class=\"latex\" /> for which <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BF_%7BI%27%7D+G%5E2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{F_{I'} G^2}\" title=\"{F_{I'} G^2}\" class=\"latex\" /> and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BF_%7BJ%27%7D+G%5E2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{F_{J'} G^2}\" title=\"{F_{J'} G^2}\" class=\"latex\" /> have overlapping Fourier supports, and the claim follows. <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5CBox&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\Box\" title=\"\\Box\" class=\"latex\" /><br /> The final ingredient needed is a simple application of Hölder’s inequality to allow one to (partially) swap <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Crho_1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\rho_1}\" title=\"{\\rho_1}\" class=\"latex\" /> and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Crho_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\rho_2}\" title=\"{\\rho_2}\" class=\"latex\" />:</p> \n<blockquote>\n <p><b>Exercise 20</b> <a name=\"ook\"></a> For any <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B0+%5Cleq+%5Cdelta+%5Cleq+%5Crho_1+%5Cleq+%5Crho_2+%5Cleq+%5Cnu+%5Cleq+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{0 \\leq \\delta \\leq \\rho_1 \\leq \\rho_2 \\leq \\nu \\leq 1}\" title=\"{0 \\leq \\delta \\leq \\rho_1 \\leq \\rho_2 \\leq \\nu \\leq 1}\" class=\"latex\" />, establish the inequality</p> \n <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++M_%7B2%2C4%7D%28%5Cdelta%2C%5Cnu%2C%5Crho_1%2C%5Crho_2%29+%5Clesssim+M_%7B2%2C4%7D%28%5Cdelta%2C%5Cnu%2C%5Crho_2%2C%5Crho_1%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+D%28%5Cdelta%2F%5Crho_2%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\rho_1,\\rho_2) \\lesssim M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\rho_2,\\rho_1)^{1/2} D(\\delta/\\rho_2)^{1/2}.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\rho_1,\\rho_2) \\lesssim M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\rho_2,\\rho_1)^{1/2} D(\\delta/\\rho_2)^{1/2}.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n</blockquote> \n<p>Now we have enough inequalities to establish the claim <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#deps\">(9)</a>. Let <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Calpha%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\alpha}\" title=\"{\\alpha}\" class=\"latex\" /> be the least exponent for which we have the bound</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++D%28%5Cdelta%29+%5Clesssim_%5Cvarepsilon+%5Cdelta%5E%7B-%5Calpha-%5Cvarepsilon%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  D(\\delta) \\lesssim_\\varepsilon \\delta^{-\\alpha-\\varepsilon}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  D(\\delta) \\lesssim_\\varepsilon \\delta^{-\\alpha-\\varepsilon}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p>for all <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B0+%3C+%5Cdelta+%5Cleq+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{0 < \\delta \\leq 1}\" title=\"{0 < \\delta \\leq 1}\" class=\"latex\" /> and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cvarepsilon%3E0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\varepsilon>0}\" title=\"{\\varepsilon>0}\" class=\"latex\" />; equivalently, we have</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Calpha+%3D+%5Climsup_%7B%5Cdelta+%5Crightarrow+0%7D+%5Cfrac%7B%5Clog+D%28%5Cdelta%29%7D%7B%5Clog+1%2F%5Cdelta%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\alpha = \\limsup_{\\delta \\rightarrow 0} \\frac{\\log D(\\delta)}{\\log 1/\\delta}.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\alpha = \\limsup_{\\delta \\rightarrow 0} \\frac{\\log D(\\delta)}{\\log 1/\\delta}.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p>Another equivalent formulation is that <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Calpha%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\alpha}\" title=\"{\\alpha}\" class=\"latex\" /> is the least exponent for which we have the bound <a name=\"dad\"></a></p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++D%28%5Cdelta%29+%5Cleq+%5Cdelta%5E%7B-%5Calpha-o%281%29%7D+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2817%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  D(\\delta) \\leq \\delta^{-\\alpha-o(1)} \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (17)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  D(\\delta) \\leq \\delta^{-\\alpha-o(1)} \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (17)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p> as <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cdelta+%5Crightarrow+0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\delta \\rightarrow 0}\" title=\"{\\delta \\rightarrow 0}\" class=\"latex\" /> where <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bo%281%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{o(1)}\" title=\"{o(1)}\" class=\"latex\" /> denotes a quantity that goes to zero as <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cdelta+%5Crightarrow+0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\delta \\rightarrow 0}\" title=\"{\\delta \\rightarrow 0}\" class=\"latex\" />. Clearly <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Calpha+%5Cgeq+0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\alpha \\geq 0}\" title=\"{\\alpha \\geq 0}\" class=\"latex\" />; our task is to show that <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Calpha%3D0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\alpha=0}\" title=\"{\\alpha=0}\" class=\"latex\" />.<br /> Suppose for contradiction that <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Calpha+%3E+0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\alpha > 0}\" title=\"{\\alpha > 0}\" class=\"latex\" />. We will establish the bound <a name=\"dodo\"></a></p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++D%28%5Cdelta%29+%5Cleq+%5Cdelta%5E%7B-%5Calpha%27-o%281%29%7D+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2818%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  D(\\delta) \\leq \\delta^{-\\alpha'-o(1)} \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (18)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  D(\\delta) \\leq \\delta^{-\\alpha'-o(1)} \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (18)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p> as <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cdelta+%5Crightarrow+0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\delta \\rightarrow 0}\" title=\"{\\delta \\rightarrow 0}\" class=\"latex\" /> for some <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Calpha%27+%3C+%5Calpha%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\alpha' < \\alpha}\" title=\"{\\alpha' < \\alpha}\" class=\"latex\" />, which will give the desired contradiction.<br /> Let <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cnu+%3D+%5Cdelta%5E%5Cvarepsilon%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\nu = \\delta^\\varepsilon}\" title=\"{\\nu = \\delta^\\varepsilon}\" class=\"latex\" /> for some small exponent <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cvarepsilon%3E0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\varepsilon>0}\" title=\"{\\varepsilon>0}\" class=\"latex\" /> (independent of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cdelta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\delta}\" title=\"{\\delta}\" class=\"latex\" />, but depending on <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Calpha%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\alpha}\" title=\"{\\alpha}\" class=\"latex\" />) to be chosen later. From Proposition <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#bile\">18</a> and <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#dad\">(17)</a> we have <a name=\"dd\"></a></p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++D%28%5Cdelta%29+%5Clesssim+%5Cdelta%5E%7B-O%28%5Cvarepsilon%29%7D+M_%7B2%2C4%7D%28%5Cdelta%2C%5Cnu%2C%5Cnu%2C%5Cnu%29+%2B+%5Cdelta%5E%7B-%281-%5Cvarepsilon%29%5Calpha-o%281%29%7D.+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2819%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  D(\\delta) \\lesssim \\delta^{-O(\\varepsilon)} M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\nu,\\nu) + \\delta^{-(1-\\varepsilon)\\alpha-o(1)}. \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (19)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  D(\\delta) \\lesssim \\delta^{-O(\\varepsilon)} M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\nu,\\nu) + \\delta^{-(1-\\varepsilon)\\alpha-o(1)}. \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (19)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p> Since <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Calpha%3E0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\alpha>0}\" title=\"{\\alpha>0}\" class=\"latex\" />, the second term on the right-hand side is already of the desired form; it remains to get a sufficiently good bound on the first term. Note that a direct application of <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#mad\">(14)</a>, <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#dad\">(17)</a> bounds this term by <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cdelta%5E%7B%5Calpha+%2B+O%28%5Cvarepsilon%29+%2B+o%281%29%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\delta^{\\alpha + O(\\varepsilon) + o(1)}}\" title=\"{\\delta^{\\alpha + O(\\varepsilon) + o(1)}}\" class=\"latex\" />; we need to improve this bound by a large multiple of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cvarepsilon%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\varepsilon}\" title=\"{\\varepsilon}\" class=\"latex\" /> to conclude. To obtain this improvement we will repeatedly use Proposition <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#key\">19</a> and Exercise <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#ook\">20</a>. Firstly, from Proposition <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#key\">19</a> we have <a name=\"nunu\"></a></p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++M_%7B2%2C4%7D%28%5Cdelta%2C%5Cnu%2C%5Cnu%2C%5Cnu%29+%5Clesssim+%5Cnu%5E%7B-O%281%29%7D+M_%7B2%2C4%7D%28%5Cdelta%2C%5Cnu%2C%5Cnu%5E2%2C%5Cnu%29+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2820%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\nu,\\nu) \\lesssim \\nu^{-O(1)} M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\nu^2,\\nu) \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (20)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\nu,\\nu) \\lesssim \\nu^{-O(1)} M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\nu^2,\\nu) \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (20)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p> if <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cvarepsilon%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\varepsilon}\" title=\"{\\varepsilon}\" class=\"latex\" /> is small enough. To control the right-hand side, we more generally consider expressions of the form</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++M_%7B2%2C4%7D%28%5Cdelta%2C%5Cnu%2C%5Cnu%5E%7B2a%7D%2C%5Cnu%5E%7Ba%7D%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\nu^{2a},\\nu^{a})\" title=\"\\displaystyle  M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\nu^{2a},\\nu^{a})\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p>for various <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba+%5Cgeq+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a \\geq 1}\" title=\"{a \\geq 1}\" class=\"latex\" />; this quantity is well-defined if <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cvarepsilon%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\varepsilon}\" title=\"{\\varepsilon}\" class=\"latex\" /> is small enough depending on <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a}\" title=\"{a}\" class=\"latex\" />. From Exercise <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#ook\">20</a> and <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#dad\">(17)</a> we have</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++M_%7B2%2C4%7D%28%5Cdelta%2C%5Cnu%2C%5Cnu%5E%7B2a%7D%2C%5Cnu%5Ea%29+%5Clesssim+M_%7B2%2C4%7D%28%5Cdelta%2C%5Cnu%2C%5Cnu%5E%7Ba%7D%2C%5Cnu%5E%7B2a%7D%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5Cdelta%5E%7B-%5Calpha%2F2-o%281%29%7D+%5Cdelta%5E%7B%5Calpha+a+%5Cvarepsilon%2F2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\nu^{2a},\\nu^a) \\lesssim M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\nu^{a},\\nu^{2a})^{1/2} \\delta^{-\\alpha/2-o(1)} \\delta^{\\alpha a \\varepsilon/2}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\nu^{2a},\\nu^a) \\lesssim M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\nu^{a},\\nu^{2a})^{1/2} \\delta^{-\\alpha/2-o(1)} \\delta^{\\alpha a \\varepsilon/2}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p>and then by Proposition <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#key\">19</a> <a name=\"manu\"></a></p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++M_%7B2%2C4%7D%28%5Cdelta%2C%5Cnu%2C%5Cnu%5E%7B2a%7D%2C%5Cnu%5Ea%29+%5Clesssim+%5Cnu%5E%7B-O%281%29%7D+M_%7B2%2C4%7D%28%5Cdelta%2C%5Cnu%2C%5Cnu%5E%7B4a%7D%2C%5Cnu%5E%7B2a%7D%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5Cdelta%5E%7B-%5Calpha%2F2-o%281%29%7D+%5Cdelta%5E%7B%5Calpha+a+%5Cvarepsilon%2F2%7D+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2821%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\nu^{2a},\\nu^a) \\lesssim \\nu^{-O(1)} M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\nu^{4a},\\nu^{2a})^{1/2} \\delta^{-\\alpha/2-o(1)} \\delta^{\\alpha a \\varepsilon/2} \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (21)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\nu^{2a},\\nu^a) \\lesssim \\nu^{-O(1)} M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\nu^{4a},\\nu^{2a})^{1/2} \\delta^{-\\alpha/2-o(1)} \\delta^{\\alpha a \\varepsilon/2} \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (21)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p> if <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cvarepsilon%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\varepsilon}\" title=\"{\\varepsilon}\" class=\"latex\" /> is small enough depending on <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a}\" title=\"{a}\" class=\"latex\" />. We rearrange this as</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%28%5Cdelta%5E%7B%5Calpha%7D+M_%7B2%2C4%7D%28%5Cdelta%2C%5Cnu%2C%5Cnu%5E%7B2a%7D%2C%5Cnu%5Ea%29%29%5E%7B1%2Fa%7D+%5Clesssim+%28%5Cdelta%5E%7B%5Calpha%7D+M_%7B2%2C4%7D%28%5Cdelta%2C%5Cnu%2C%5Cnu%5E%7B4a%7D%2C%5Cnu%5E%7B2a%7D%29%29%5E%7B1%2F2a%7D+%5Cdelta%5E%7B%5Calpha+%5Cvarepsilon%2F2+-+O%28%5Cvarepsilon%2Fa%29+-+o%281%29%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  (\\delta^{\\alpha} M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\nu^{2a},\\nu^a))^{1/a} \\lesssim (\\delta^{\\alpha} M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\nu^{4a},\\nu^{2a}))^{1/2a} \\delta^{\\alpha \\varepsilon/2 - O(\\varepsilon/a) - o(1)}.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  (\\delta^{\\alpha} M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\nu^{2a},\\nu^a))^{1/a} \\lesssim (\\delta^{\\alpha} M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\nu^{4a},\\nu^{2a}))^{1/2a} \\delta^{\\alpha \\varepsilon/2 - O(\\varepsilon/a) - o(1)}.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p>The crucial fact here is that we gain a small power of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cdelta%5E%5Cvarepsilon%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\delta^\\varepsilon}\" title=\"{\\delta^\\varepsilon}\" class=\"latex\" /> on the right-hand side when <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a}\" title=\"{a}\" class=\"latex\" /> is large. Iterating this inequality <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bk%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{k}\" title=\"{k}\" class=\"latex\" /> times, we see that</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cdelta%5E%7B%5Calpha%7D+M_%7B2%2C4%7D%28%5Cdelta%2C%5Cnu%2C%5Cnu%5E%7B2%7D%2C%5Cnu%29+%5Clesssim_k+%28%5Cdelta%5E%7B%5Calpha%7D+M_%7B2%2C4%7D%28%5Cdelta%2C%5Cnu%2C%5Cnu%5E%7B2%5E%7Bk%2B1%7D%7D%2C%5Cnu%5E%7B2%5Ek%7D%29%29%5E%7B1%2F2%5Ek%7D+%5Cdelta%5E%7Bk%5Calpha+%5Cvarepsilon%2F2-O%28%5Cvarepsilon%29+-+o_k%281%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\delta^{\\alpha} M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\nu^{2},\\nu) \\lesssim_k (\\delta^{\\alpha} M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\nu^{2^{k+1}},\\nu^{2^k}))^{1/2^k} \\delta^{k\\alpha \\varepsilon/2-O(\\varepsilon) - o_k(1)}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\delta^{\\alpha} M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\nu^{2},\\nu) \\lesssim_k (\\delta^{\\alpha} M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\nu^{2^{k+1}},\\nu^{2^k}))^{1/2^k} \\delta^{k\\alpha \\varepsilon/2-O(\\varepsilon) - o_k(1)}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p>for any given <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bk%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{k}\" title=\"{k}\" class=\"latex\" />, if <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cvarepsilon%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\varepsilon}\" title=\"{\\varepsilon}\" class=\"latex\" /> is small enough depending on <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bk%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{k}\" title=\"{k}\" class=\"latex\" />, and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bo_k%281%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{o_k(1)}\" title=\"{o_k(1)}\" class=\"latex\" /> denotes a quantity that goes to zero in the limit <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cdelta+%5Crightarrow+0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\delta \\rightarrow 0}\" title=\"{\\delta \\rightarrow 0}\" class=\"latex\" /> holding <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bk%2C%5Cvarepsilon%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{k,\\varepsilon}\" title=\"{k,\\varepsilon}\" class=\"latex\" /> fixed. Now we can afford to apply <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#mad\">(14)</a>, <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#dad\">(17)</a> and conclude that</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cdelta%5E%7B%5Calpha%7D+M_%7B2%2C4%7D%28%5Cdelta%2C%5Cnu%2C%5Cnu%5E%7B2%7D%2C%5Cnu%29+%5Clesssim+%5Cdelta%5E%7Bk%5Calpha+%5Cvarepsilon%2F2-O%28%5Cvarepsilon%29+-+o%281%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\delta^{\\alpha} M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\nu^{2},\\nu) \\lesssim \\delta^{k\\alpha \\varepsilon/2-O(\\varepsilon) - o(1)}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\delta^{\\alpha} M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\nu^{2},\\nu) \\lesssim \\delta^{k\\alpha \\varepsilon/2-O(\\varepsilon) - o(1)}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p>which when inserted back into <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#nunu\">(20)</a>, <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#dd\">(19)</a> gives</p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++D%28%5Cdelta%29+%5Clesssim+%5Cdelta%5E%7B-%5Calpha+%2B+k%5Calpha+%5Cvarepsilon%2F2+-+O%28%5Cvarepsilon%29+%2B+o%281%29%7D+%2B+%5Cdelta%5E%7B-%5Calpha+%2B+%5Cvarepsilon+%5Calpha+%2B+o%281%29%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  D(\\delta) \\lesssim \\delta^{-\\alpha + k\\alpha \\varepsilon/2 - O(\\varepsilon) + o(1)} + \\delta^{-\\alpha + \\varepsilon \\alpha + o(1)}.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  D(\\delta) \\lesssim \\delta^{-\\alpha + k\\alpha \\varepsilon/2 - O(\\varepsilon) + o(1)} + \\delta^{-\\alpha + \\varepsilon \\alpha + o(1)}.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p>If we then choose <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bk%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{k}\" title=\"{k}\" class=\"latex\" /> large enough depending on <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Calpha%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\alpha}\" title=\"{\\alpha}\" class=\"latex\" />, and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cvarepsilon%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\varepsilon}\" title=\"{\\varepsilon}\" class=\"latex\" /> small enough depending on <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bk%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{k}\" title=\"{k}\" class=\"latex\" />, we obtain the desired improved bound <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#dodo\">(18)</a>.</p> \n<blockquote>\n <p><b>Remark 21</b> An alternate arrangement of the above argument is as follows. For any exponent <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Ctheta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\theta}\" title=\"{\\theta}\" class=\"latex\" />, let <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%28%5Ctheta%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P(\\theta)}\" title=\"{P(\\theta)}\" class=\"latex\" /> denote the claim that <a name=\"m24\"></a></p> \n <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++M_%7B2%2C4%7D%28%5Cdelta%2C%5Cnu%2C%5Cnu%5E%7B2a%7D%2C%5Cnu%5E%7Ba%7D%29+%5Clesssim_%5Ctheta+%5Cdelta%5E%7B-%5Calpha+%2B+o%281%29%7D+%5Cnu%5E%7Ba%5Ctheta+%2B+O_%5Ctheta%281%29%7D+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2822%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\nu^{2a},\\nu^{a}) \\lesssim_\\theta \\delta^{-\\alpha + o(1)} \\nu^{a\\theta + O_\\theta(1)} \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (22)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  M_{2,4}(\\delta,\\nu,\\nu^{2a},\\nu^{a}) \\lesssim_\\theta \\delta^{-\\alpha + o(1)} \\nu^{a\\theta + O_\\theta(1)} \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (22)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n <p> whenever <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba+%5Cgeq+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a \\geq 1}\" title=\"{a \\geq 1}\" class=\"latex\" />, <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cnu+%3D+%5Cdelta%5E%5Cvarepsilon%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\nu = \\delta^\\varepsilon}\" title=\"{\\nu = \\delta^\\varepsilon}\" class=\"latex\" /> with <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cvarepsilon%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\varepsilon}\" title=\"{\\varepsilon}\" class=\"latex\" /> sufficiently small depending on <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a}\" title=\"{a}\" class=\"latex\" />, and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cdelta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\delta}\" title=\"{\\delta}\" class=\"latex\" /> is sent to zero holding <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%2C%5Cvarepsilon%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a,\\varepsilon}\" title=\"{a,\\varepsilon}\" class=\"latex\" /> fixed. The bounds <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#mad\">(14)</a>, <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#dad\">(17)</a> give the claim <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%280%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P(0)}\" title=\"{P(0)}\" class=\"latex\" />. On the other hand, the bound <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#manu\">(21)</a> shows that <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%28%5Ctheta%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P(\\theta)}\" title=\"{P(\\theta)}\" class=\"latex\" /> implies <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%28%5Ctheta%2B%5Calpha%2F2%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P(\\theta+\\alpha/2)}\" title=\"{P(\\theta+\\alpha/2)}\" class=\"latex\" /> for any given <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Ctheta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\theta}\" title=\"{\\theta}\" class=\"latex\" />. Thus if <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Calpha%3E0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\alpha>0}\" title=\"{\\alpha>0}\" class=\"latex\" />, we can establish <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%28%5Ctheta%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P(\\theta)}\" title=\"{P(\\theta)}\" class=\"latex\" /> for arbitrarily large <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Ctheta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\theta}\" title=\"{\\theta}\" class=\"latex\" />, and for <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Ctheta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\theta}\" title=\"{\\theta}\" class=\"latex\" /> large enough we can insert the bound <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#m24\">(22)</a> (with <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a}\" title=\"{a}\" class=\"latex\" /> sufficiently large depending on <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Ctheta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\theta}\" title=\"{\\theta}\" class=\"latex\" />) into <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#dd\">(19)</a>, <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#nunu\">(20)</a> to obtain the required claim <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#dodo\">(18)</a>. See <a href=\"https://terrytao.wordpress.com/2019/06/14/abstracting-induction-on-scales-arguments/\">this blog post</a> for a further elaboration of this approach, which allows one to systematically determine the optimal exponents one can conclude from a system of inequalities of the type one sees in Proposition <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#key\">19</a> or Exercise <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#ook\">20</a> (it boils down to computing the Perron-Frobenius eigenvalue of certain matrices).</p>\n</blockquote> \n<blockquote>\n <p><b>Exercise 22</b> By carefully unpacking the above iterative arguments, establish a bound of the form</p> \n <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++D%28%5Cdelta%29+%5Clesssim+%5Cexp%28+O%28+%5Cfrac%7B%5Clog+1%2F%5Cdelta%7D%7B%5Clog%5Clog+1%2F%5Cdelta%7D+%29+%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  D(\\delta) \\lesssim \\exp( O( \\frac{\\log 1/\\delta}{\\log\\log 1/\\delta} ) )\" title=\"\\displaystyle  D(\\delta) \\lesssim \\exp( O( \\frac{\\log 1/\\delta}{\\log\\log 1/\\delta} ) )\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n <p>for all sufficiently small <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cdelta%3E0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\delta>0}\" title=\"{\\delta>0}\" class=\"latex\" />. (This bound was first established <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1805.10551\">by Li</a>.)</p>\n</blockquote> \n<blockquote>\n <p><b>Exercise 23 (Localised decoupling)</b> Let <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B0+%3C+%5Cdelta+%3C+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{0 < \\delta < 1}\" title=\"{0 < \\delta < 1}\" class=\"latex\" />, and let <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+I%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal I}}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal I}}\" class=\"latex\" /> be a family of boundedly overlapping intervals <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{I}\" title=\"{I}\" class=\"latex\" /> in <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5B-1%2C1%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{[-1,1]}\" title=\"{[-1,1]}\" class=\"latex\" /> of length <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cdelta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\delta}\" title=\"{\\delta}\" class=\"latex\" />. For each <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+I%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{I \\in {\\mathcal I}}\" title=\"{I \\in {\\mathcal I}}\" class=\"latex\" />, let <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bg_I+%5Cin+L%5E1%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{g_I \\in L^1({\\bf R})}\" title=\"{g_I \\in L^1({\\bf R})}\" class=\"latex\" /> be an integrable function supported on <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{I}\" title=\"{I}\" class=\"latex\" />, and let <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+E%7D+g_I%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal E} g_I}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal E} g_I}\" class=\"latex\" /> denote the extension operator</p> \n <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7B%5Cmathcal+E%7D+g_I%28x_1%2Cx_2%29+%3A%3D+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+g_I%28%5Cxi%29+e%5E%7B2%5Cpi+i+%28%5Cxi+x_1+%2B+%5Cxi%5E2+x_2%29%7D%5C+d%5Cxi.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathcal E} g_I(x_1,x_2) := \\int_{\\bf R} g_I(\\xi) e^{2\\pi i (\\xi x_1 + \\xi^2 x_2)}\\ d\\xi.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathcal E} g_I(x_1,x_2) := \\int_{\\bf R} g_I(\\xi) e^{2\\pi i (\\xi x_1 + \\xi^2 x_2)}\\ d\\xi.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n <p>For any ball <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BB+%3D+B%28x_0%2C+%5Cdelta%5E%7B-2%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{B = B(x_0, \\delta^{-2})}\" title=\"{B = B(x_0, \\delta^{-2})}\" class=\"latex\" /> of radius <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cdelta%5E%7B-2%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\delta^{-2}}\" title=\"{\\delta^{-2}}\" class=\"latex\" />, use Theorem <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11649#parabb\">13</a> to establish the local decoupling inequality</p> \n <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5C%7C+%5Csum_%7BI+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+I%7D%7D+%7B%5Cmathcal+E%7D+g_I+%5C%7C_%7BL%5E6%28B%29%7D+%5Clesssim_%5Cvarepsilon+%5Cdelta%5E%7B-%5Cvarepsilon%7D+%28%5Csum_%7BI+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+I%7D%7D+%5C%7C%7B%5Cmathcal+E%7D+g_I%5C%7C_%7BL%5E6%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%5E2%2C+w_B%5C+dx%29%7D%5E2%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\| \\sum_{I \\in {\\mathcal I}} {\\mathcal E} g_I \\|_{L^6(B)} \\lesssim_\\varepsilon \\delta^{-\\varepsilon} (\\sum_{I \\in {\\mathcal I}} \\|{\\mathcal E} g_I\\|_{L^6({\\bf R}^2, w_B\\ dx)}^2)^{1/2}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\| \\sum_{I \\in {\\mathcal I}} {\\mathcal E} g_I \\|_{L^6(B)} \\lesssim_\\varepsilon \\delta^{-\\varepsilon} (\\sum_{I \\in {\\mathcal I}} \\|{\\mathcal E} g_I\\|_{L^6({\\bf R}^2, w_B\\ dx)}^2)^{1/2}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n <p>for any <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cvarepsilon%3E0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\varepsilon>0}\" title=\"{\\varepsilon>0}\" class=\"latex\" />, where <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bw_B%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{w_B}\" title=\"{w_B}\" class=\"latex\" /> is the weight function</p> \n <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++w_B%28x%29+%3A%3D+%5Clangle+%5Cfrac%7Bx-x_0%7D%7B%5Cdelta%5E%7B-2%7D%7D+%5Crangle%5E%7B-100%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  w_B(x) := \\langle \\frac{x-x_0}{\\delta^{-2}} \\rangle^{-100}.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  w_B(x) := \\langle \\frac{x-x_0}{\\delta^{-2}} \\rangle^{-100}.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n</blockquote> \n<p>The decoupling theorem for the parabola has been extended in a number of directions. <a href=\"https://mathscinet.ams.org/mathscinet-getitem?mr=3374964\">Bourgain and Demeter obtained</a> the analogous decoupling theorem for the paraboloid:</p> \n<blockquote>\n <p><b>Theorem 24 (Decoupling for the paraboloid)</b> <a name=\"decoupp\"></a> Let <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bd+%5Cgeq+2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{d \\geq 2}\" title=\"{d \\geq 2}\" class=\"latex\" />, let <img
