src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++a%28X%2CD%29+b%28X%2CD%29+f%28x%29+%3D+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+a%28x%2C%5Ceta%29+b%28y%2C%5Cxi%29+%5Chat+f%28%5Cxi%29+e%5E%7B2%5Cpi+i+%28y+%5Cxi-y%5Ceta+%2B+x+%5Ceta%29%7D%5C+d%5Cxi+dy+d%5Ceta&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  a(X,D) b(X,D) f(x) = \\int_{\\bf R} \\int_{\\bf R} \\int_{\\bf R} a(x,\\eta) b(y,\\xi) \\hat f(\\xi) e^{2\\pi i (y \\xi-y\\eta + x \\eta)}\\ d\\xi dy d\\eta\" title=\"\\displaystyle  a(X,D) b(X,D) f(x) = \\int_{\\bf R} \\int_{\\bf R} \\int_{\\bf R} a(x,\\eta) b(y,\\xi) \\hat f(\\xi) e^{2\\pi i (y \\xi-y\\eta + x \\eta)}\\ d\\xi dy d\\eta\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p> and hence by Fubini’s theorem (and the compact support of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%2Cb%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a,b}\" title=\"{a,b}\" class=\"latex\" /> and the Schwartz nature of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{f}\" title=\"{f}\" class=\"latex\" />) we have <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%28X%2CD%29+b%28X%2CD%29+%3D+%28a+%5Cast+b%29%28X%2CD%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a(X,D) b(X,D) = (a \\ast b)(X,D)}\" title=\"{a(X,D) b(X,D) = (a \\ast b)(X,D)}\" class=\"latex\" />, where <a name=\"ast-def\"></a></p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%28a+%5Cast+b%29%28x%2C%5Cxi%29+%3A%3D+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+a%28x%2C%5Ceta%29+b%28y%2C%5Cxi%29+e%5E%7B2%5Cpi+i+%28y-x%29%28%5Cxi-%5Ceta%29%7D%5C+dy+d%5Ceta.+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2824%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  (a \\ast b)(x,\\xi) := \\int_{\\bf R} \\int_{\\bf R} a(x,\\eta) b(y,\\xi) e^{2\\pi i (y-x)(\\xi-\\eta)}\\ dy d\\eta. \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (24)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  (a \\ast b)(x,\\xi) := \\int_{\\bf R} \\int_{\\bf R} a(x,\\eta) b(y,\\xi) e^{2\\pi i (y-x)(\\xi-\\eta)}\\ dy d\\eta. \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (24)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p> Our task is now to show that <a name=\"xl\"></a></p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cfrac%7B%5Cpartial%5Ej%7D%7B%5Cpartial+x%5Ej%7D+%5Cfrac%7B%5Cpartial%5El%7D%7B%5Cpartial+%5Cxi%5El%7D+%28a+%5Cast+b%29%28x%2C%5Cxi%29+%5Clesssim_%7Ba%2Cb%2C%5Calpha%2C%5Cbeta%2Cj%2Cl%7D+%5Clangle+%5Cxi+%5Crangle%5E%7B%5Calpha%2B%5Cbeta-l%7D%2C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2825%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\frac{\\partial^j}{\\partial x^j} \\frac{\\partial^l}{\\partial \\xi^l} (a \\ast b)(x,\\xi) \\lesssim_{a,b,\\alpha,\\beta,j,l} \\langle \\xi \\rangle^{\\alpha+\\beta-l}, \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (25)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\frac{\\partial^j}{\\partial x^j} \\frac{\\partial^l}{\\partial \\xi^l} (a \\ast b)(x,\\xi) \\lesssim_{a,b,\\alpha,\\beta,j,l} \\langle \\xi \\rangle^{\\alpha+\\beta-l}, \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (25)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p> for all <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bj%2Cl+%5Cgeq+0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{j,l \\geq 0}\" title=\"{j,l \\geq 0}\" class=\"latex\" /> and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bx%2C%5Cxi+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{x,\\xi \\in {\\bf R}}\" title=\"{x,\\xi \\in {\\bf R}}\" class=\"latex\" />, where the understanding is that the dependence of constants on <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%2Cb%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a,b}\" title=\"{a,b}\" class=\"latex\" /> is only through the symbol bounds <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11722#class-symb\">(8)</a> for these symbols.</p> \n<p> From differentiation under the integral sign and integration by parts we obtain the Leibniz identities </p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cfrac%7B%5Cpartial%7D%7B%5Cpartial+x%7D+%28a+%5Cast+b%29+%3D+%28%5Cfrac%7B%5Cpartial%7D%7B%5Cpartial+x%7D+a%29+%5Cast+b+%2B+a+%5Cast+%28%5Cfrac%7B%5Cpartial%7D%7B%5Cpartial+x%7D+b%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\frac{\\partial}{\\partial x} (a \\ast b) = (\\frac{\\partial}{\\partial x} a) \\ast b + a \\ast (\\frac{\\partial}{\\partial x} b)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\frac{\\partial}{\\partial x} (a \\ast b) = (\\frac{\\partial}{\\partial x} a) \\ast b + a \\ast (\\frac{\\partial}{\\partial x} b)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p> and </p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cfrac%7B%5Cpartial%7D%7B%5Cpartial+%5Cxi%7D+%28a+%5Cast+b%29+%3D+%28%5Cfrac%7B%5Cpartial%7D%7B%5Cpartial+%5Cxi%7D+a%29+%5Cast+b+%2B+a+%5Cast+%28%5Cfrac%7B%5Cpartial%7D%7B%5Cpartial+%5Cxi%7D+b%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\frac{\\partial}{\\partial \\xi} (a \\ast b) = (\\frac{\\partial}{\\partial \\xi} a) \\ast b + a \\ast (\\frac{\\partial}{\\partial \\xi} b).\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\frac{\\partial}{\\partial \\xi} (a \\ast b) = (\\frac{\\partial}{\\partial \\xi} a) \\ast b + a \\ast (\\frac{\\partial}{\\partial \\xi} b).\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p> From this and an induction on <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bj%2Bl%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{j+l}\" title=\"{j+l}\" class=\"latex\" /> (varying <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Calpha%2C%5Cbeta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\alpha,\\beta}\" title=\"{\\alpha,\\beta}\" class=\"latex\" /> as necessary, noting that if <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cfrac%7B%5Cpartial%7D%7B%5Cpartial+x%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\frac{\\partial}{\\partial x}}\" title=\"{\\frac{\\partial}{\\partial x}}\" class=\"latex\" /> maps <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%5E%5Calpha%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal S}^\\alpha}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal S}^\\alpha}\" class=\"latex\" /> to <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%5E%5Calpha%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal S}^\\alpha}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal S}^\\alpha}\" class=\"latex\" /> and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cfrac%7B%5Cpartial%7D%7B%5Cpartial+%5Cxi%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\frac{\\partial}{\\partial \\xi}}\" title=\"{\\frac{\\partial}{\\partial \\xi}}\" class=\"latex\" /> maps <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%5E%5Cbeta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal S}^\\beta}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal S}^\\beta}\" class=\"latex\" /> to <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%5E%7B%5Cbeta-1%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal S}^{\\beta-1}}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal S}^{\\beta-1}}\" class=\"latex\" />) we see that to prove <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11722#xl\">(25)</a> it suffices to do so in the <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bj%3Dl%3D0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{j=l=0}\" title=\"{j=l=0}\" class=\"latex\" /> case, thus we now only need to show that <a name=\"yo\"></a></p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+a%28x%2C%5Ceta%29+b%28y%2C%5Cxi%29+e%5E%7B2%5Cpi+i+%28y-x%29%28%5Cxi-%5Ceta%29%7D%5C+dy+d%5Ceta+%5Clesssim_%7Ba%2Cb%2C%5Calpha%2C%5Cbeta%7D+%5Clangle+%5Cxi+%5Crangle%5E%7B%5Calpha%2B%5Cbeta%7D+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2826%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\int_{\\bf R} \\int_{\\bf R} a(x,\\eta) b(y,\\xi) e^{2\\pi i (y-x)(\\xi-\\eta)}\\ dy d\\eta \\lesssim_{a,b,\\alpha,\\beta} \\langle \\xi \\rangle^{\\alpha+\\beta} \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (26)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\int_{\\bf R} \\int_{\\bf R} a(x,\\eta) b(y,\\xi) e^{2\\pi i (y-x)(\\xi-\\eta)}\\ dy d\\eta \\lesssim_{a,b,\\alpha,\\beta} \\langle \\xi \\rangle^{\\alpha+\\beta} \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (26)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p> for a given <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bx%2C%5Cxi%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{x,\\xi}\" title=\"{x,\\xi}\" class=\"latex\" />.</p> \n<p> Applying a smooth partition of unity in the <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Ceta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\eta}\" title=\"{\\eta}\" class=\"latex\" /> variable to <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a}\" title=\"{a}\" class=\"latex\" />, it suffices to verify the claim in one of two cases: </p> \n<ul> \n <li> <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%28x%2C%5Ceta%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a(x,\\eta)}\" title=\"{a(x,\\eta)}\" class=\"latex\" /> is supported in the region <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5C%7B+%28x%2C%5Ceta%29%3A+%7C%5Ceta+-+%5Cxi%7C+%5Cleq+%5Clangle+%5Cxi+%5Crangle%2F2+%5C%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\{ (x,\\eta): |\\eta - \\xi| \\leq \\langle \\xi \\rangle/2 \\}}\" title=\"{\\{ (x,\\eta): |\\eta - \\xi| \\leq \\langle \\xi \\rangle/2 \\}}\" class=\"latex\" /> (so in particular <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Clangle+%5Ceta+%5Crangle+%5Csim+%5Clangle+%5Cxi+%5Crangle%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\langle \\eta \\rangle \\sim \\langle \\xi \\rangle}\" title=\"{\\langle \\eta \\rangle \\sim \\langle \\xi \\rangle}\" class=\"latex\" />). </li> \n <li> <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%28x%2C%5Ceta%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a(x,\\eta)}\" title=\"{a(x,\\eta)}\" class=\"latex\" /> is supported in the region <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5C%7B+%28x%2C%5Ceta%29%3A+%7C%5Ceta+-+%5Cxi%7C+%5Cgeq+%5Clangle+%5Cxi+%5Crangle%2F4+%5C%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\{ (x,\\eta): |\\eta - \\xi| \\geq \\langle \\xi \\rangle/4 \\}}\" title=\"{\\{ (x,\\eta): |\\eta - \\xi| \\geq \\langle \\xi \\rangle/4 \\}}\" class=\"latex\" />. </li> \n</ul> \n<p> (One can verify that applying the required cutoffs to <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a}\" title=\"{a}\" class=\"latex\" /> do not significantly worsen the symbol estimates <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11722#class-symb\">(8)</a>.) In the former case we write the left-hand side as </p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+K_x%28x-y%29+b%28y%2C%5Cxi%29+e%5E%7B2%5Cpi+i+%28y-x%29%5Cxi%7D%5C+dy&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\int_{\\bf R} K_x(x-y) b(y,\\xi) e^{2\\pi i (y-x)\\xi}\\ dy\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\int_{\\bf R} K_x(x-y) b(y,\\xi) e^{2\\pi i (y-x)\\xi}\\ dy\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p> where </p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++K_x%28z%29+%3A%3D+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+a%28x%2C%5Ceta%29+e%5E%7B2%5Cpi+i+z+%5Ceta%7D%5C+d%5Ceta.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  K_x(z) := \\int_{\\bf R} a(x,\\eta) e^{2\\pi i z \\eta}\\ d\\eta.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  K_x(z) := \\int_{\\bf R} a(x,\\eta) e^{2\\pi i z \\eta}\\ d\\eta.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p> By repeating the proof of <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11722#k1\">(14)</a> we have </p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++K_x%28z%29+%5Clesssim_%7Ba%2C%5Calpha%7D+%5Clangle+%5Cxi+%5Crangle%5E%7B%5Calpha%2B1%7D+%5Clangle+%5Clangle+%5Cxi+%5Crangle+z+%5Crangle%5E%7B-2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  K_x(z) \\lesssim_{a,\\alpha} \\langle \\xi \\rangle^{\\alpha+1} \\langle \\langle \\xi \\rangle z \\rangle^{-2}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  K_x(z) \\lesssim_{a,\\alpha} \\langle \\xi \\rangle^{\\alpha+1} \\langle \\langle \\xi \\rangle z \\rangle^{-2}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p> so from this and the symbol bound <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bb%28y%2C%5Cxi%29+%5Clesssim_b+%5Clangle+%5Cxi%5Crangle%5E%5Cbeta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{b(y,\\xi) \\lesssim_b \\langle \\xi\\rangle^\\beta}\" title=\"{b(y,\\xi) \\lesssim_b \\langle \\xi\\rangle^\\beta}\" class=\"latex\" /> we obtain the claim in this case.</p> \n<p> It remains to handle the latter case. Here we integrate by parts repeatedly in the <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7By%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{y}\" title=\"{y}\" class=\"latex\" /> variable to write the left-hand side of <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11722#yo\">(26)</a> as </p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Cfrac%7Ba%28x%2C%5Ceta%29%7D%7B%282%5Cpi+i%28%5Ceta-%5Cxi%29%29%5Em%7D+%5Cfrac%7B%5Cpartial%5Em%7D%7B%5Cpartial+y%5Em%7D+b%28y%2C%5Cxi%29+e%5E%7B2%5Cpi+i+%28y-x%29%28%5Cxi-%5Ceta%29%7D%5C+dy+d%5Ceta&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\int_{\\bf R} \\int_{\\bf R} \\frac{a(x,\\eta)}{(2\\pi i(\\eta-\\xi))^m} \\frac{\\partial^m}{\\partial y^m} b(y,\\xi) e^{2\\pi i (y-x)(\\xi-\\eta)}\\ dy d\\eta\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\int_{\\bf R} \\int_{\\bf R} \\frac{a(x,\\eta)}{(2\\pi i(\\eta-\\xi))^m} \\frac{\\partial^m}{\\partial y^m} b(y,\\xi) e^{2\\pi i (y-x)(\\xi-\\eta)}\\ dy d\\eta\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p> for any <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bm%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{m}\" title=\"{m}\" class=\"latex\" />. Then as before we can rewrite this as </p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+K_%7Bx%2Cm%7D%28x-y%29+%5Cfrac%7B%5Cpartial%5Em%7D%7B%5Cpartial+y%5Em%7D+b%28y%2C%5Cxi%29+e%5E%7B2%5Cpi+i+%28y-x%29%5Cxi%7D%5C+dy&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\int_{\\bf R} K_{x,m}(x-y) \\frac{\\partial^m}{\\partial y^m} b(y,\\xi) e^{2\\pi i (y-x)\\xi}\\ dy\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\int_{\\bf R} K_{x,m}(x-y) \\frac{\\partial^m}{\\partial y^m} b(y,\\xi) e^{2\\pi i (y-x)\\xi}\\ dy\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p> where </p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++K_%7Bx%2Cm%7D%28z%29+%3A%3D+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Cfrac%7Ba%28x%2C%5Ceta%29%7D%7B%282%5Cpi+i%28%5Ceta-%5Cxi%29%29%5Em%7D+e%5E%7B2%5Cpi+i+z+%5Ceta%7D%5C+d%5Ceta.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  K_{x,m}(z) := \\int_{\\bf R} \\frac{a(x,\\eta)}{(2\\pi i(\\eta-\\xi))^m} e^{2\\pi i z \\eta}\\ d\\eta.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  K_{x,m}(z) := \\int_{\\bf R} \\frac{a(x,\\eta)}{(2\\pi i(\\eta-\\xi))^m} e^{2\\pi i z \\eta}\\ d\\eta.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p> By taking <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bm%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{m}\" title=\"{m}\" class=\"latex\" /> large enough we will eventually recover the bound </p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++K_%7Bx%2Cm%7D%28z%29+%5Clesssim_%7Ba%2C%5Calpha%7D+%5Clangle+%5Cxi+%5Crangle%5E%7B%5Calpha%2B1%7D+%5Clangle+%5Clangle+%5Cxi+%5Crangle+z+%5Crangle%5E%7B-2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  K_{x,m}(z) \\lesssim_{a,\\alpha} \\langle \\xi \\rangle^{\\alpha+1} \\langle \\langle \\xi \\rangle z \\rangle^{-2}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  K_{x,m}(z) \\lesssim_{a,\\alpha} \\langle \\xi \\rangle^{\\alpha+1} \\langle \\langle \\xi \\rangle z \\rangle^{-2}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p> (in fact one can gain arbitrary powers of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Clangle+%5Cxi+%5Crangle%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\langle \\xi \\rangle}\" title=\"{\\langle \\xi \\rangle}\" class=\"latex\" /> if desired), and so by repeating the previous arguments we also obtain the claim in this case. <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5CBox&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\Box\" title=\"\\Box\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p> The above proposition shows that if <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%5E%5Calpha%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a \\in {\\mathcal S}^\\alpha}\" title=\"{a \\in {\\mathcal S}^\\alpha}\" class=\"latex\" /> and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bb+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%5E%5Cbeta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{b \\in {\\mathcal S}^\\beta}\" title=\"{b \\in {\\mathcal S}^\\beta}\" class=\"latex\" /> then <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba+%5Cast+b+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%5E%7B%5Calpha%2B%5Cbeta%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a \\ast b \\in {\\mathcal S}^{\\alpha+\\beta}}\" title=\"{a \\ast b \\in {\\mathcal S}^{\\alpha+\\beta}}\" class=\"latex\" />. The following exercise gives some refinements to this fact: </p> \n<blockquote>\n <p><b>Exercise 9 (Composition of pseudodifferential operators)</b> <a name=\"comp-p\"></a> Let <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%5E%5Calpha%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a \\in {\\mathcal S}^\\alpha}\" title=\"{a \\in {\\mathcal S}^\\alpha}\" class=\"latex\" /> and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bb+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%5E%5Cbeta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{b \\in {\\mathcal S}^\\beta}\" title=\"{b \\in {\\mathcal S}^\\beta}\" class=\"latex\" /> for some <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Calpha%2C%5Cbeta+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\alpha,\\beta \\in {\\bf R}}\" title=\"{\\alpha,\\beta \\in {\\bf R}}\" class=\"latex\" />. </p> \n <ul> \n  <li>(i) Show that <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba+%5Cast+b+-+ab+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%5E%7B%5Calpha%2B%5Cbeta-1%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a \\ast b - ab \\in {\\mathcal S}^{\\alpha+\\beta-1}}\" title=\"{a \\ast b - ab \\in {\\mathcal S}^{\\alpha+\\beta-1}}\" class=\"latex\" />. (<em>Hint:</em> reduce as before to the case where <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%2Cb%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a,b}\" title=\"{a,b}\" class=\"latex\" /> are compactly supported, and use the fundamental theorem of calculus to write <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%28x%2C%5Ceta%29+%3D+a%28x%2C%5Cxi%29+%2B+%28%5Ceta-%5Cxi%29+%5Cint_0%5E1+a_%5Cxi%28x%2C+%5Cxi+%2B+t%28%5Ceta-%5Cxi%29%29%5C+dt%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a(x,\\eta) = a(x,\\xi) + (\\eta-\\xi) \\int_0^1 a_\\xi(x, \\xi + t(\\eta-\\xi))\\ dt}\" title=\"{a(x,\\eta) = a(x,\\xi) + (\\eta-\\xi) \\int_0^1 a_\\xi(x, \\xi + t(\\eta-\\xi))\\ dt}\" class=\"latex\" />, where <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba_%5Cxi%28x%2C%5Cxi%29+%3A%3D+%5Cfrac%7B%5Cpartial+a%7D%7B%5Cpartial+%5Cxi%7D%28x%2C%5Cxi%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a_\\xi(x,\\xi) := \\frac{\\partial a}{\\partial \\xi}(x,\\xi)}\" title=\"{a_\\xi(x,\\xi) := \\frac{\\partial a}{\\partial \\xi}(x,\\xi)}\" class=\"latex\" />. Then use the Fourier inversion formula, integration by parts, and arguments similar to those used to prove Theorem <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11722#precomp\">8</a>. </li> \n  <li>(ii) Show that <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba+%5Cast+b+-+ab+-+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B2%5Cpi+i%7D+a_%5Cxi+b_x+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%5E%7B%5Calpha%2B%5Cbeta-2%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a \\ast b - ab - \\frac{1}{2\\pi i} a_\\xi b_x \\in {\\mathcal S}^{\\alpha+\\beta-2}}\" title=\"{a \\ast b - ab - \\frac{1}{2\\pi i} a_\\xi b_x \\in {\\mathcal S}^{\\alpha+\\beta-2}}\" class=\"latex\" />, where <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba_%5Cxi%28x%2C%5Cxi%29+%3A%3D+%5Cfrac%7B%5Cpartial+a%7D%7B%5Cpartial+%5Cxi%7D%28x%2C%5Cxi%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a_\\xi(x,\\xi) := \\frac{\\partial a}{\\partial \\xi}(x,\\xi)}\" title=\"{a_\\xi(x,\\xi) := \\frac{\\partial a}{\\partial \\xi}(x,\\xi)}\" class=\"latex\" /> and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bb_x%28x%2C%5Cxi%29+%3A%3D+%5Cfrac%7B%5Cpartial+b%7D%7B%5Cpartial+x%7D%28x%2C%5Cxi%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{b_x(x,\\xi) := \\frac{\\partial b}{\\partial x}(x,\\xi)}\" title=\"{b_x(x,\\xi) := \\frac{\\partial b}{\\partial x}(x,\\xi)}\" class=\"latex\" />. (Hint: now apply the fundamental theorem of calculus once more to expand <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba_%5Cxi%28x%2C%5Cxi%2Bt%28%5Ceta-%5Cxi%29%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a_\\xi(x,\\xi+t(\\eta-\\xi))}\" title=\"{a_\\xi(x,\\xi+t(\\eta-\\xi))}\" class=\"latex\" />.) </li> \n  <li>(iii) Check (i) and (ii) directly in the classical case when <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%28x%2C%5Cxi%29+%3D+A%28x%29+%5Cxi%5El%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a(x,\\xi) = A(x) \\xi^l}\" title=\"{a(x,\\xi) = A(x) \\xi^l}\" class=\"latex\" /> and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bb%28x%2C%5Cxi%29+%3D+B%28x%29+%5Cxi%5Em%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{b(x,\\xi) = B(x) \\xi^m}\" title=\"{b(x,\\xi) = B(x) \\xi^m}\" class=\"latex\" /> for some smooth <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BA%2CB%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{A,B}\" title=\"{A,B}\" class=\"latex\" /> obeying the bounds <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11722#cb\">(9)</a> and for <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bl%2Cm+%5Cgeq+0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{l,m \\geq 0}\" title=\"{l,m \\geq 0}\" class=\"latex\" />. Based on this, for any integer <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Br+%5Cgeq+0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{r \\geq 0}\" title=\"{r \\geq 0}\" class=\"latex\" />, make a prediction for an approximation to <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba+%5Cast+b%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a \\ast b}\" title=\"{a \\ast b}\" class=\"latex\" /> as a polynomial combination of the symbols arbitrary <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%5E%5Calpha%2C+b+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%5E%5Cbeta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a \\in {\\mathcal S}^\\alpha, b \\in {\\mathcal S}^\\beta}\" title=\"{a \\in {\\mathcal S}^\\alpha, b \\in {\\mathcal S}^\\beta}\" class=\"latex\" /> and finitely many of their derivatives which is accurate up to an error in <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%5E%7B%5Calpha%2B%5Cbeta-r%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal S}^{\\alpha+\\beta-r}}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal S}^{\\alpha+\\beta-r}}\" class=\"latex\" />. Then verify this prediction. </li> \n </ul> \n</blockquote>  \n<blockquote>\n <p><b>Remark 10</b> <a name=\"ph\"></a> From Exercise <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11722#comp-p\">9</a> we see that if <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%28X%2CD%29%2C+b%28X%2CD%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a(X,D), b(X,D)}\" title=\"{a(X,D), b(X,D)}\" class=\"latex\" /> are pseudodifferential operators of order <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Calpha%2C%5Cbeta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\alpha,\\beta}\" title=\"{\\alpha,\\beta}\" class=\"latex\" /> respectively, then the commutator <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Ba%28X%2CD%29%2Cb%28X%2CD%29%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{[a(X,D),b(X,D)]}\" title=\"{[a(X,D),b(X,D)]}\" class=\"latex\" /> differs from <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B2%5Cpi+i%7D+%5C%7Ba%2Cb%5C%7D%28X%2CD%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\frac{1}{2\\pi i} \\{a,b\\}(X,D)}\" title=\"{\\frac{1}{2\\pi i} \\{a,b\\}(X,D)}\" class=\"latex\" /> by a pseudodifferential operator of order <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Calpha%2B%5Cbeta-2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\alpha+\\beta-2}\" title=\"{\\alpha+\\beta-2}\" class=\"latex\" />, where <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5C%7Ba%2Cb%5C%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\{a,b\\}}\" title=\"{\\{a,b\\}}\" class=\"latex\" /> is the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Poisson_bracket\">Poisson bracket</a> </p> \n <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5C%7Ba%2Cb%5C%7D%28x%2C%5Cxi%29+%3A%3D+%5Cfrac%7B%5Cpartial+a%7D%7B%5Cpartial+%5Cxi%7D%28x%2C%5Cxi%29+%5Cfrac%7B%5Cpartial+b%7D%7B%5Cpartial+x%7D%28x%2C%5Cxi%29+-+%5Cfrac%7B%5Cpartial+a%7D%7B%5Cpartial+x%7D%28x%2C%5Cxi%29+%5Cfrac%7B%5Cpartial+b%7D%7B%5Cpartial+%5Cxi%7D%28x%2C%5Cxi%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\{a,b\\}(x,\\xi) := \\frac{\\partial a}{\\partial \\xi}(x,\\xi) \\frac{\\partial b}{\\partial x}(x,\\xi) - \\frac{\\partial a}{\\partial x}(x,\\xi) \\frac{\\partial b}{\\partial \\xi}(x,\\xi).\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\{a,b\\}(x,\\xi) := \\frac{\\partial a}{\\partial \\xi}(x,\\xi) \\frac{\\partial b}{\\partial x}(x,\\xi) - \\frac{\\partial a}{\\partial x}(x,\\xi) \\frac{\\partial b}{\\partial \\xi}(x,\\xi).\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n <p> This approximate correspondence between the Lie bracket <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5B%2C%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{[,]}\" title=\"{[,]}\" class=\"latex\" /> (which plays a fundamental role in the dynamics of quantum mechanics) and the Poisson bracket <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5C%7B%2C%5C%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\{,\\}}\" title=\"{\\{,\\}}\" class=\"latex\" /> (which plays a fundamental role in the dynamics of classical mechanics) is one of the mathematical foundations of the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Correspondence_principle\">correspondence principle</a> relating quantum and classical mechanics, but we will not discuss this topic further here. </p>\n</blockquote>  \n<p> There is also a companion result regarding adjoints of pseudodifferential operators: </p> \n<blockquote>\n <p><b>Exercise 11 (Adjoint of pseudodifferential operator)</b> <a name=\"adj-p\"></a> Let <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%5E%5Calpha%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a \\in {\\mathcal S}^\\alpha}\" title=\"{a \\in {\\mathcal S}^\\alpha}\" class=\"latex\" />. </p> \n <ul> \n  <li>(i) If <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a}\" title=\"{a}\" class=\"latex\" /> is compactly supported, show that the function <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Ctilde+a%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\tilde a}\" title=\"{\\tilde a}\" class=\"latex\" /> defined by <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Ctilde+a%28x%2C%5Cxi%29+%3A%3D+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Coverline%7Ba%7D%28y%2C%5Ceta%29+e%5E%7B2%5Cpi+i+%28x-y%29%28%5Ceta-%5Cxi%29%7D%5C+dy+d%5Ceta&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\tilde a(x,\\xi) := \\int_{\\bf R} \\int_{\\bf R} \\overline{a}(y,\\eta) e^{2\\pi i (x-y)(\\eta-\\xi)}\\ dy d\\eta\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\tilde a(x,\\xi) := \\int_{\\bf R} \\int_{\\bf R} \\overline{a}(y,\\eta) e^{2\\pi i (x-y)(\\eta-\\xi)}\\ dy d\\eta\" class=\"latex\" /></p> <p> is also a symbol of order <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Calpha%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\alpha}\" title=\"{\\alpha}\" class=\"latex\" />, and that <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Ctilde+a%28X%2CD%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\tilde a(X,D)}\" title=\"{\\tilde a(X,D)}\" class=\"latex\" /> is the adjoint of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%28X%2CD%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a(X,D)}\" title=\"{a(X,D)}\" class=\"latex\" /> in the sense that </p> <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clangle+a%28X%2CD%29+f%2C+g+%5Crangle+%3D+%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Ctilde+a%28X%2CD%29+g+%5Crangle&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\langle a(X,D) f, g \\rangle = \\langle f, \\tilde a(X,D) g \\rangle\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\langle a(X,D) f, g \\rangle = \\langle f, \\tilde a(X,D) g \\rangle\" class=\"latex\" /></p> <p> for all <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%2Cg+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{f,g \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R})}\" title=\"{f,g \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R})}\" class=\"latex\" />. </p></li> \n  <li>(ii) Show that even if <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a}\" title=\"{a}\" class=\"latex\" /> is not compactly supported, there is a unique pseudodifferential operator <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%28X%2CD%29%5E%2A%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a(X,D)^*}\" title=\"{a(X,D)^*}\" class=\"latex\" /> of order <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Calpha%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\alpha}\" title=\"{\\alpha}\" class=\"latex\" /> which is the adjoint of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%28X%2CD%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a(X,D)}\" title=\"{a(X,D)}\" class=\"latex\" /> in the sense that <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clangle+a%28X%2CD%29+f%2C+g+%5Crangle+%3D+%5Clangle+f%2C+a%28X%2CD%29%5E%2A+g+%5Crangle&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\langle a(X,D) f, g \\rangle = \\langle f, a(X,D)^* g \\rangle\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\langle a(X,D) f, g \\rangle = \\langle f, a(X,D)^* g \\rangle\" class=\"latex\" /></p> <p> for all <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%2Cg+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{f,g \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R})}\" title=\"{f,g \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R})}\" class=\"latex\" />. </p></li> \n  <li>(iii) Show that <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%28X%2CD%29%5E%2A+-+%5Coverline%7Ba%7D%28X%2CD%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a(X,D)^* - \\overline{a}(X,D)}\" title=\"{a(X,D)^* - \\overline{a}(X,D)}\" class=\"latex\" /> is a pseudodifferential operator of order <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Calpha-1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\alpha-1}\" title=\"{\\alpha-1}\" class=\"latex\" />. </li> \n </ul> \n</blockquote>  \n<p> Now we give some applications of the above pseudodifferential calculus. </p> \n<blockquote>\n <p><b>Exercise 12 (Pseudodifferential operators and Sobolev spaces)</b> <a name=\"sob\"></a> For any <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B1+%3C+p+%3C+%5Cinfty%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{1 < p < \\infty}\" title=\"{1 < p < \\infty}\" class=\"latex\" /> and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bs+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{s \\in {\\bf R}}\" title=\"{s \\in {\\bf R}}\" class=\"latex\" />, define the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sobolev_space\">Sobolev space</a> <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BW%5E%7Bs%2Cp%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{W^{s,p}({\\bf R})}\" title=\"{W^{s,p}({\\bf R})}\" class=\"latex\" /> to be the completion of the Schwartz functions <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal S}({\\bf R})}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal S}({\\bf R})}\" class=\"latex\" /> with respect to the norm </p> \n <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5C%7Cf%5C%7C_%7BW%5E%7Bs%2Cp%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D+%3A%3D+%5C%7C+%5Clangle+D+%5Crangle%5Es+f+%5C%7C_%7BL%5Ep%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\|f\\|_{W^{s,p}({\\bf R})} := \\| \\langle D \\rangle^s f \\|_{L^p({\\bf R})}.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\|f\\|_{W^{s,p}({\\bf R})} := \\| \\langle D \\rangle^s f \\|_{L^p({\\bf R})}.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n <ul> \n  <li>(i) If <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bs%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{s}\" title=\"{s}\" class=\"latex\" /> is a non-negative integer, show that <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5C%7Cf%5C%7C_%7BW%5E%7Bs%2Cp%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D+%5Csim_%7Bs%2Cp%7D+%5Csum_%7Bj%3D0%7D%5Es+%5C%7C+%5Cfrac%7Bd%5Ej%7D%7Bdx%5Ej%7D+f%5C%7C_%7BL%5Ep%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\|f\\|_{W^{s,p}({\\bf R})} \\sim_{s,p} \\sum_{j=0}^s \\| \\frac{d^j}{dx^j} f\\|_{L^p({\\bf R})}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\|f\\|_{W^{s,p}({\\bf R})} \\sim_{s,p} \\sum_{j=0}^s \\| \\frac{d^j}{dx^j} f\\|_{L^p({\\bf R})}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> <p> for any <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{f \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R})}\" title=\"{f \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R})}\" class=\"latex\" />, thus in this case the Sobolev spaces agree (up to constants) with the classical Sobolev spaces (as discussed for instance in <a href=\"https://terrytao.wordpress.com/2009/04/30/245c-notes-4-sobolev-spaces/\">this set of notes</a>). </p></li> \n  <li>(ii) If <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%28X%2CD%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a(X,D)}\" title=\"{a(X,D)}\" class=\"latex\" /> is a pseudodifferential operator of some order <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Calpha+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\alpha \\in {\\bf R}}\" title=\"{\\alpha \\in {\\bf R}}\" class=\"latex\" />, show that <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5C%7Ca%28X%2CD%29+f%5C%7C_%7BW%5E%7Bs-%5Calpha%2Cp%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D+%5Clesssim_%7Ba%2C%5Calpha%2Cs%2Cp%7D+%5C%7Cf%5C%7C_%7BW%5E%7Bs%2Cp%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\|a(X,D) f\\|_{W^{s-\\alpha,p}({\\bf R})} \\lesssim_{a,\\alpha,s,p} \\|f\\|_{W^{s,p}({\\bf R})}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\|a(X,D) f\\|_{W^{s-\\alpha,p}({\\bf R})} \\lesssim_{a,\\alpha,s,p} \\|f\\|_{W^{s,p}({\\bf R})}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> <p> for any <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{f \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R})}\" title=\"{f \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R})}\" class=\"latex\" />, thus <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%28X%2CD%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a(X,D)}\" title=\"{a(X,D)}\" class=\"latex\" /> extends to a bounded linear map from <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BW%5E%7Bs%2Cp%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{W^{s,p}({\\bf R})}\" title=\"{W^{s,p}({\\bf R})}\" class=\"latex\" /> to <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BW%5E%7Bs-%5Calpha%2Cp%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{W^{s-\\alpha,p}({\\bf R})}\" title=\"{W^{s-\\alpha,p}({\\bf R})}\" class=\"latex\" />. (<em>Hint:</em> use Theorem <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11722#cv\">4</a> and Theorem <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11722#precomp\">8</a>). </p></li> \n  <li>(iii) Let <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%28X%2CD%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a(X,D)}\" title=\"{a(X,D)}\" class=\"latex\" /> be a pseudodifferential operator of some order <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Calpha+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\alpha \\in {\\bf R}}\" title=\"{\\alpha \\in {\\bf R}}\" class=\"latex\" /> that obeys the strong ellipticity condition <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cmathrm%7BRe%7D+a%28x%2C%5Cxi%29+%5Csim_a+%5Clangle+%5Cxi+%5Crangle%5E%5Calpha&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Re} a(x,\\xi) \\sim_a \\langle \\xi \\rangle^\\alpha\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Re} a(x,\\xi) \\sim_a \\langle \\xi \\rangle^\\alpha\" class=\"latex\" /></p> <p> for all <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bx%2C%5Cxi+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{x,\\xi \\in {\\bf R}}\" title=\"{x,\\xi \\in {\\bf R}}\" class=\"latex\" />. Establish the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/G%C3%A5rding%27s_inequality\">Garding inequality</a> </p> <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cmathrm%7BRe%7D+%5Clangle+a%28X%2CD%29+f%2C+f+%5Crangle+%5Cgeq+c+%5C%7C+f%5C%7C_%7BW%5E%7B%5Calpha%2F2%2C+2%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D%5E2+-+C+%5C%7C+f+%5C%7C_%7BW%5E%7B%28%5Calpha-1%29%2F2%2C2%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D%5E2+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Re} \\langle a(X,D) f, f \\rangle \\geq c \\| f\\|_{W^{\\alpha/2, 2}({\\bf R})}^2 - C \\| f \\|_{W^{(\\alpha-1)/2,2}({\\bf R})}^2 \" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Re} \\langle a(X,D) f, f \\rangle \\geq c \\| f\\|_{W^{\\alpha/2, 2}({\\bf R})}^2 - C \\| f \\|_{W^{(\\alpha-1)/2,2}({\\bf R})}^2 \" class=\"latex\" /></p> <p> for all <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{f \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R})}\" title=\"{f \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R})}\" class=\"latex\" /> and some <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bc%2CC%3E0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{c,C>0}\" title=\"{c,C>0}\" class=\"latex\" /> depending only on <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%2C%5Calpha%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a,\\alpha}\" title=\"{a,\\alpha}\" class=\"latex\" />. (<em>Hint:</em> use Exercises <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11722#comp-p\">9</a>, <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11722#adj-p\">11</a> to express <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B2%7D+%28a%28X%2CD%29+%2B+a%28X%2CD%29%5E%2A%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\frac{1}{2} (a(X,D) + a(X,D)^*)}\" title=\"{\\frac{1}{2} (a(X,D) + a(X,D)^*)}\" class=\"latex\" /> as <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bb%28X%2CD%29+b%28X%2CD%29%5E%2A+%2B+e%28X%2CD%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{b(X,D) b(X,D)^* + e(X,D)}\" title=\"{b(X,D) b(X,D)^* + e(X,D)}\" class=\"latex\" /> for some pseudodifferential operators <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bb%2Ce%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{b,e}\" title=\"{b,e}\" class=\"latex\" /> of orders <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Calpha%2F2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\alpha/2}\" title=\"{\\alpha/2}\" class=\"latex\" /> and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Calpha-1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\alpha-1}\" title=\"{\\alpha-1}\" class=\"latex\" /> respectively.) If <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Calpha+%5Cgeq+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\alpha \\geq 1}\" title=\"{\\alpha \\geq 1}\" class=\"latex\" />, deduce also the variant inequality </p> <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cmathrm%7BRe%7D+%5Clangle+a%28X%2CD%29+f%2C+f+%5Crangle+%5Cgeq+c+%5C%7C+f%5C%7C_%7BW%5E%7B%5Calpha%2F2%2C+2%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D%5E2+-+C+%5C%7C+f+%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D%5E2+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Re} \\langle a(X,D) f, f \\rangle \\geq c \\| f\\|_{W^{\\alpha/2, 2}({\\bf R})}^2 - C \\| f \\|_{L^2({\\bf R})}^2 \" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Re} \\langle a(X,D) f, f \\rangle \\geq c \\| f\\|_{W^{\\alpha/2, 2}({\\bf R})}^2 - C \\| f \\|_{L^2({\\bf R})}^2 \" class=\"latex\" /></p> <p> (possibly with slightly different choices of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bc%2CC%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{c,C}\" title=\"{c,C}\" class=\"latex\" />). </p></li> \n </ul> \n</blockquote>  \n<p> The behaviour of pseudodifferential operators may be clarified by using a type of phase space transform, which we will call a <em>Gabor-type transform</em>. </p> \n<blockquote>\n <p><b>Exercise 13 (Gabor-type transforms and pseudodifferential operators)</b> <a name=\"gabor\"></a> Given any function <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cphi+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\phi \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R})}\" title=\"{\\phi \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R})}\" class=\"latex\" /> with the <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BL%5E2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{L^2}\" title=\"{L^2}\" class=\"latex\" /> normalisation <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5C%7C%5Cphi%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D%3D1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\|\\phi\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})}=1}\" title=\"{\\|\\phi\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})}=1}\" class=\"latex\" />, and any <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{f \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R})}\" title=\"{f \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R})}\" class=\"latex\" />, define the <em>Gabor-type transform</em> <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BT_%5Cphi+f%3A+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Ctimes+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Crightarrow+%7B%5Cbf+C%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{T_\\phi f: {\\bf R} \\times {\\bf R} \\rightarrow {\\bf C}}\" title=\"{T_\\phi f: {\\bf R} \\times {\\bf R} \\rightarrow {\\bf C}}\" class=\"latex\" /> by the formula </p> \n <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++T_%5Cphi+f%28x%2C%5Cxi%29+%3A%3D+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+f%28y%29+%5Coverline%7B%5Cphi%7D%28y-x%29+e%5E%7B-2%5Cpi+i+y+%5Cxi%7D%5C+dy%2C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  T_\\phi f(x,\\xi) := \\int_{\\bf R} f(y) \\overline{\\phi}(y-x) e^{-2\\pi i y \\xi}\\ dy,\" title=\"\\displaystyle  T_\\phi f(x,\\xi) := \\int_{\\bf R} f(y) \\overline{\\phi}(y-x) e^{-2\\pi i y \\xi}\\ dy,\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n <p> thus <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BT_%5Cphi+f%28x%2C%5Cxi%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{T_\\phi f(x,\\xi)}\" title=\"{T_\\phi f(x,\\xi)}\" class=\"latex\" /> is the inner product of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{f}\" title=\"{f}\" class=\"latex\" /> with the function <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7By+%5Cmapsto+%5Cphi%28y-x%29+e%5E%7B2%5Cpi+i+y+%5Cxi%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{y \\mapsto \\phi(y-x) e^{2\\pi i y \\xi}}\" title=\"{y \\mapsto \\phi(y-x) e^{2\\pi i y \\xi}}\" class=\"latex\" />, which is the “wave packet” formed from function <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cphi%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\phi}\" title=\"{\\phi}\" class=\"latex\" /> by translating by <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bx%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{x}\" title=\"{x}\" class=\"latex\" /> and then modulating by <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cxi%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\xi}\" title=\"{\\xi}\" class=\"latex\" />. (Intuitively, <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BT_%5Cphi+f%28x%2C%5Cxi%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{T_\\phi f(x,\\xi)}\" title=\"{T_\\phi f(x,\\xi)}\" class=\"latex\" /> measures the extent to which <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{f}\" title=\"{f}\" class=\"latex\" /> lives at spatial location <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bx%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{x}\" title=\"{x}\" class=\"latex\" /> and frequency location <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cxi%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\xi}\" title=\"{\\xi}\" class=\"latex\" />.) We also define the adjoint map <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BT_%5Cphi%5E%2A+F%3A+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Crightarrow+%7B%5Cbf+C%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{T_\\phi^* F: {\\bf R} \\rightarrow {\\bf C}}\" title=\"{T_\\phi^* F: {\\bf R} \\rightarrow {\\bf C}}\" class=\"latex\" /> for <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BF+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Ctimes+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{F \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R} \\times {\\bf R})}\" title=\"{F \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R} \\times {\\bf R})}\" class=\"latex\" /> by the formula </p> \n <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++T_%5Cphi%5E%2A+F%28y%29+%3A%3D+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+F%28x%2C%5Cxi%29+%5Cphi%28y-x%29+e%5E%7B2%5Cpi+i+y+%5Cxi%7D%5C+dx+d%5Cxi.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  T_\\phi^* F(y) := \\int_{\\bf R} \\int_{\\bf R} F(x,\\xi) \\phi(y-x) e^{2\\pi i y \\xi}\\ dx d\\xi.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  T_\\phi^* F(y) := \\int_{\\bf R} \\int_{\\bf R} F(x,\\xi) \\phi(y-x) e^{2\\pi i y \\xi}\\ dx d\\xi.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n <ul> \n  <li>(i) Show that for any <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{f \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R})}\" title=\"{f \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R})}\" class=\"latex\" />, <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BT_%5Cphi+f%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{T_\\phi f}\" title=\"{T_\\phi f}\" class=\"latex\" /> is a Schwartz function on <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Ctimes+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf R} \\times {\\bf R}}\" title=\"{{\\bf R} \\times {\\bf R}}\" class=\"latex\" />, thus <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BT_%5Cphi%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{T_\\phi}\" title=\"{T_\\phi}\" class=\"latex\" /> is a linear map from <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal S}({\\bf R})}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal S}({\\bf R})}\" class=\"latex\" /> to <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Ctimes+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal S}({\\bf R} \\times {\\bf R})}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal S}({\\bf R} \\times {\\bf R})}\" class=\"latex\" />. Similarly, show that for <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BF+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Ctimes+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{F \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R} \\times {\\bf R})}\" title=\"{F \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R} \\times {\\bf R})}\" class=\"latex\" />, <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BT_%5Cphi%5E%2A+F%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{T_\\phi^* F}\" title=\"{T_\\phi^* F}\" class=\"latex\" /> is a Schwartz function on <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf R}}\" title=\"{{\\bf R}}\" class=\"latex\" />, thus <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BT_%5Cphi%5E%2A%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{T_\\phi^*}\" title=\"{T_\\phi^*}\" class=\"latex\" /> is a linear map from <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Ctimes+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal S}({\\bf R} \\times {\\bf R})}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal S}({\\bf R} \\times {\\bf R})}\" class=\"latex\" /> to <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal S}({\\bf R})}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal S}({\\bf R})}\" class=\"latex\" />. </li> \n  <li>(ii) Establish the identity <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BT_%5Cphi%5E%2A+T_%5Cphi+f+%3D+f%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{T_\\phi^* T_\\phi f = f}\" title=\"{T_\\phi^* T_\\phi f = f}\" class=\"latex\" /> for any <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{f \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R})}\" title=\"{f \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R})}\" class=\"latex\" />, and conclude inparticular that <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5C%7C+T_%5Cphi+f+%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Ctimes+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D+%3D+%5C%7Cf%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\| T_\\phi f \\|_{L^2({\\bf R} \\times {\\bf R})} = \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})} \" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\| T_\\phi f \\|_{L^2({\\bf R} \\times {\\bf R})} = \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})} \" class=\"latex\" /></p> <p> for any <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{f \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R})}\" title=\"{f \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R})}\" class=\"latex\" />, thus <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BT_%5Cphi%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{T_\\phi}\" title=\"{T_\\phi}\" class=\"latex\" /> extends to a linear isometry from <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{L^2({\\bf R})}\" title=\"{L^2({\\bf R})}\" class=\"latex\" /> into <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Ctimes+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{L^2({\\bf R} \\times {\\bf R})}\" title=\"{L^2({\\bf R} \\times {\\bf R})}\" class=\"latex\" />. </p></li> \n  <li>(iii) For any smooth compactly supported <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba+%5Cin+C%5E%5Cinfty_c%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a \\in C^\\infty_c({\\bf R})}\" title=\"{a \\in C^\\infty_c({\\bf R})}\" class=\"latex\" /> and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{f \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R})}\" title=\"{f \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R})}\" class=\"latex\" />, establish the identity <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++T_%5Cphi%5E%2A+%28a+T_%5Cphi+f%29+%3D+%28a%2AW_%5Cphi%29%28X%2CD%29+f%2C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  T_\\phi^* (a T_\\phi f) = (a*W_\\phi)(X,D) f,\" title=\"\\displaystyle  T_\\phi^* (a T_\\phi f) = (a*W_\\phi)(X,D) f,\" class=\"latex\" /></p> <p> where <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BW_%5Cphi%3A+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Ctimes+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Crightarrow+%7B%5Cbf+C%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{W_\\phi: {\\bf R} \\times {\\bf R} \\rightarrow {\\bf C}}\" title=\"{W_\\phi: {\\bf R} \\times {\\bf R} \\rightarrow {\\bf C}}\" class=\"latex\" /> is the (Kohn-Nirenberg) <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wigner_quasiprobability_distribution\">Wigner distribution</a> of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cphi%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\phi}\" title=\"{\\phi}\" class=\"latex\" />, defined by the formula </p> <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++W_%5Cphi%28x%2C%5Cxi%29+%3D+%5Cphi%28x%29+%5Coverline%7B%5Chat+%5Cphi%7D%28%5Cxi%29+e%5E%7B-2%5Cpi+i+x+%5Cxi%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  W_\\phi(x,\\xi) = \\phi(x) \\overline{\\hat \\phi}(\\xi) e^{-2\\pi i x \\xi}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  W_\\phi(x,\\xi) = \\phi(x) \\overline{\\hat \\phi}(\\xi) e^{-2\\pi i x \\xi}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> <p> and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%2AW_%5Cphi%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a*W_\\phi}\" title=\"{a*W_\\phi}\" class=\"latex\" /> is the phase space convolution </p> <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++a%2AW_%5Cphi%28x%2C%5Cxi%29+%3A%3D+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+a%28y%2C%5Ceta%29+W_%5Cphi%28x-y%2C+%5Cxi-%5Ceta%29%5C+dy+d%5Ceta.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  a*W_\\phi(x,\\xi) := \\int_{\\bf R} \\int_{\\bf R} a(y,\\eta) W_\\phi(x-y, \\xi-\\eta)\\ dy d\\eta.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  a*W_\\phi(x,\\xi) := \\int_{\\bf R} \\int_{\\bf R} a(y,\\eta) W_\\phi(x-y, \\xi-\\eta)\\ dy d\\eta.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> </li> \n </ul> \n</blockquote>  \n<blockquote>\n <p><b>Remark 14</b> When <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cphi%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\phi}\" title=\"{\\phi}\" class=\"latex\" /> is a Gaussian, the transform <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BT_%5Cphi%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{T_\\phi}\" title=\"{T_\\phi}\" class=\"latex\" /> is essentially the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gabor_transform\">Gabor transform</a> (in signal processing) or the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fourier%E2%80%93Bros%E2%80%93Iagolnitzer_transform\">FBI transform</a> (in microlocal analysis), and is also closely related to the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Segal%E2%80%93Bargmann_space#The_Segal%E2%80%93Bargmann_transform\">Bargmann transform</a> in complex analysis. There are some technical advantages with working with Gaussian choices of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cphi%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\phi}\" title=\"{\\phi}\" class=\"latex\" />, particularly with regards to the treatment of certain lower order terms in the pseudodifferential calculus; see for instance <a href=\"https://math.berkeley.edu/~tataru/papers/phasespace.pdf\">these notes of Tataru</a>. </p>\n</blockquote>  \n<p> Note that <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BW_%5Cphi%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{W_\\phi}\" title=\"{W_\\phi}\" class=\"latex\" /> is a Schwartz function on <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Ctimes+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf R} \\times {\\bf R}}\" title=\"{{\\bf R} \\times {\\bf R}}\" class=\"latex\" />, and by the Fourier inversion formula it has unit mass: <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+W_%5Cphi%28x%2C%5Cxi%29%5C+dx+d%5Cxi+%3D+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\int_{\\bf R} \\int_{\\bf R} W_\\phi(x,\\xi)\\ dx d\\xi = 1}\" title=\"{\\int_{\\bf R} \\int_{\\bf R} W_\\phi(x,\\xi)\\ dx d\\xi = 1}\" class=\"latex\" />. (One also has the marginal distributions <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+W_%5Cphi%28x%2C%5Cxi%29%5C+d%5Cxi+%3D+%7C%5Cphi%28x%29%7C%5E2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\int_{\\bf R} W_\\phi(x,\\xi)\\ d\\xi = |\\phi(x)|^2}\" title=\"{\\int_{\\bf R} W_\\phi(x,\\xi)\\ d\\xi = |\\phi(x)|^2}\" class=\"latex\" /> and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+W_%5Cphi%28x%2C%5Cxi%29%5C+dx+%3D+%7C%5Chat+%5Cphi%28%5Cxi%29%7C%5E2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\int_{\\bf R} W_\\phi(x,\\xi)\\ dx = |\\hat \\phi(\\xi)|^2}\" title=\"{\\int_{\\bf R} W_\\phi(x,\\xi)\\ dx = |\\hat \\phi(\\xi)|^2}\" class=\"latex\" />, so <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BW_%5Cphi%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{W_\\phi}\" title=\"{W_\\phi}\" class=\"latex\" /> would be a strong candidate for a “phase space probability distribution” for <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cphi%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\phi}\" title=\"{\\phi}\" class=\"latex\" />, save for the unfortunate fact that <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BW_%5Cphi%28x%2C%5Cxi%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{W_\\phi(x,\\xi)}\" title=\"{W_\\phi(x,\\xi)}\" class=\"latex\" /> has no reason to be non-negative. But even with oscillation, <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BW_%5Cphi%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{W_\\phi}\" title=\"{W_\\phi}\" class=\"latex\" /> still behaves like an approximation to the identity, so for <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a}\" title=\"{a}\" class=\"latex\" /> slowly varying <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%2AW_%5Cphi%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a*W_\\phi}\" title=\"{a*W_\\phi}\" class=\"latex\" /> can be viewed as an approximation to <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a}\" title=\"{a}\" class=\"latex\" />. Thus, Exercise <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11722#gabor\">13</a>(iii) can be intuitively viewed as saying that <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%28X%2CD%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a(X,D)}\" title=\"{a(X,D)}\" class=\"latex\" /> behaves approximately like a multiplier in phase space: </p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++a%28X%2CD%29+%5Capprox+T_%5Cphi%5E%2A+a+T_%5Cphi.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  a(X,D) \\approx T_\\phi^* a T_\\phi.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  a(X,D) \\approx T_\\phi^* a T_\\phi.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p> Another informal way of viewing this assertion is that (for suitable choices of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cphi%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\phi}\" title=\"{\\phi}\" class=\"latex\" />) the translated and modulated functions <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7By+%5Cmapsto+%5Cphi%28y-x%29+e%5E%7B2%5Cpi+i+y+%5Cxi%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{y \\mapsto \\phi(y-x) e^{2\\pi i y \\xi}}\" title=\"{y \\mapsto \\phi(y-x) e^{2\\pi i y \\xi}}\" class=\"latex\" /> can be viewed as approximate eigenfunctions of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%28X%2CD%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a(X,D)}\" title=\"{a(X,D)}\" class=\"latex\" /> with eigenvalue <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Capprox+a%28x%2C%5Cxi%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\approx a(x,\\xi)}\" title=\"{\\approx a(x,\\xi)}\" class=\"latex\" />. This is for instance consistent with the approximate functional calculus <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%28X%2CD%29+b%28X%2CD%29+%5Capprox+%28ab%29%28X%2CD%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a(X,D) b(X,D) \\approx (ab)(X,D)}\" title=\"{a(X,D) b(X,D) \\approx (ab)(X,D)}\" class=\"latex\" /> and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%28X%2CD%29%5E%2A+%5Capprox+%5Coverline%7Ba%7D%28X%2CD%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a(X,D)^* \\approx \\overline{a}(X,D)}\" title=\"{a(X,D)^* \\approx \\overline{a}(X,D)}\" class=\"latex\" /> that one saw in Exercises <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11722#comp-p\">9</a>, <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11722#adj-p\">11</a>. The exercise below gives another way to view this approximation:</p> \n<blockquote>\n <p><b>Exercise 15 (<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BS%5E0_%7B0%2C0%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{S^0_{0,0}}\" title=\"{S^0_{0,0}}\" class=\"latex\" /> <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BL%5E2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{L^2}\" title=\"{L^2}\" class=\"latex\" /> bound)</b> Let <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%3A+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Ctimes+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Crightarrow+%7B%5Cbf+C%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a: {\\bf R} \\times {\\bf R} \\rightarrow {\\bf C}}\" title=\"{a: {\\bf R} \\times {\\bf R} \\rightarrow {\\bf C}}\" class=\"latex\" /> be a smooth function obeying the “<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BS%5E0_%7B0%2C0%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{S^0_{0,0}}\" title=\"{S^0_{0,0}}\" class=\"latex\" /> bound” </p> \n <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle+%5Cfrac%7B%5Cpartial%5Ej%7D%7B%5Cpartial+x%5Ej%7D+%5Cfrac%7B%5Cpartial%5El%7D%7B%5Cpartial+%5Cxi%5El%7D+a%28x%2C%5Cxi%29+%5Clesssim_%7Ba%2Cj%2Cl%7D+1&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle \\frac{\\partial^j}{\\partial x^j} \\frac{\\partial^l}{\\partial \\xi^l} a(x,\\xi) \\lesssim_{a,j,l} 1\" title=\"\\displaystyle \\frac{\\partial^j}{\\partial x^j} \\frac{\\partial^l}{\\partial \\xi^l} a(x,\\xi) \\lesssim_{a,j,l} 1\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n <p> for all <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bj%2Cl+%5Cgeq+0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{j,l \\geq 0}\" title=\"{j,l \\geq 0}\" class=\"latex\" /> and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%28x%2C%5Cxi%29+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Ctimes+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{(x,\\xi) \\in {\\bf R} \\times {\\bf R}}\" title=\"{(x,\\xi) \\in {\\bf R} \\times {\\bf R}}\" class=\"latex\" />. Let <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cphi%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\phi}\" title=\"{\\phi}\" class=\"latex\" /> and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BT_%5Cphi%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{T_\\phi}\" title=\"{T_\\phi}\" class=\"latex\" /> be as in Exercise <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11722#gabor\">13</a>. Show that there is a smooth kernel <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BK%3A+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Ctimes+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Ctimes+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Ctimes+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Crightarrow+%7B%5Cbf+C%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{K: {\\bf R} \\times {\\bf R} \\times {\\bf R} \\times {\\bf R} \\rightarrow {\\bf C}}\" title=\"{K: {\\bf R} \\times {\\bf R} \\times {\\bf R} \\times {\\bf R} \\rightarrow {\\bf C}}\" class=\"latex\" /> obeying the bounds </p> \n <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++K%28+x%2C%5Cxi%2C+y%2C%5Ceta+%29+%5Clesssim_%7Ba%2Cm%7D+%5Clangle+%28x%2C%5Cxi%29+-+%28y%2C%5Ceta%29+%5Crangle%5E%7B-m%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  K( x,\\xi, y,\\eta ) \\lesssim_{a,m} \\langle (x,\\xi) - (y,\\eta) \\rangle^{-m}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  K( x,\\xi, y,\\eta ) \\lesssim_{a,m} \\langle (x,\\xi) - (y,\\eta) \\rangle^{-m}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n <p> for any <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bm+%5Cgeq+0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{m \\geq 0}\" title=\"{m \\geq 0}\" class=\"latex\" />, such that </p> \n <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++T_%5Cphi+a%28X%2CD%29+T_%5Cphi%5E%2A+F%28x%2C%5Cxi%29+%3D+%5Cint_%7B%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Ctimes+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%7D+K%28x%2C%5Cxi%2Cy%2C%5Ceta%29+F%28y%2C%5Ceta%29%5C+dy+d%5Ceta&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  T_\\phi a(X,D) T_\\phi^* F(x,\\xi) = \\int_{{\\bf R} \\times {\\bf R}} K(x,\\xi,y,\\eta) F(y,\\eta)\\ dy d\\eta\" title=\"\\displaystyle  T_\\phi a(X,D) T_\\phi^* F(x,\\xi) = \\int_{{\\bf R} \\times {\\bf R}} K(x,\\xi,y,\\eta) F(y,\\eta)\\ dy d\\eta\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n <p> for any <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BF+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Ctimes+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{F \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R} \\times {\\bf R})}\" title=\"{F \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R} \\times {\\bf R})}\" class=\"latex\" />. (<em>Hint:</em> work first in the case when <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a}\" title=\"{a}\" class=\"latex\" /> is compactly supported, where one can use Fubini’s theorem to derive an explicit integral expression for <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BK%28x%2C%5Cxi%2Cy%2C%5Ceta%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{K(x,\\xi,y,\\eta)}\" title=\"{K(x,\\xi,y,\\eta)}\" class=\"latex\" />, which one can then control by various integrations by parts.) Use this to establish the <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BL%5E2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{L^2}\" title=\"{L^2}\" class=\"latex\" /> bound </p> \n <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5C%7Ca%28X%2CD%29+f+%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D+%5Clesssim_a+%5C%7Cf%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\|a(X,D) f \\|_{L^2({\\bf R})} \\lesssim_a \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\|a(X,D) f \\|_{L^2({\\bf R})} \\lesssim_a \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n <p> for any <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{f \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R})}\" title=\"{f \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R})}\" class=\"latex\" />; note that this gives an alternate proof of <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11722#p2\">(18)</a>. (See also <a href=\"https://math.berkeley.edu/~tataru/papers/phasespace.pdf\">these notes of Tataru</a> for further elaboration of this approach to pseudodifferential operators.) </p>\n</blockquote>  \n<p> As a sample application of the Gabor transform formalism we give a variant of the Garding inequality from Exercise <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11722#sob\">12</a>(iii). </p> \n<blockquote>\n <p><b>Theorem 16 (Sharp Garding inequality)</b> Let <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%28X%2CD%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a(X,D)}\" title=\"{a(X,D)}\" class=\"latex\" /> be a pseudodifferential operator of order <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Calpha%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\alpha}\" title=\"{\\alpha}\" class=\"latex\" /> such that <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cmathrm%7BRe%7D+a%28x%2C%5Cxi%29+%5Cgeq+0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\mathrm{Re} a(x,\\xi) \\geq 0}\" title=\"{\\mathrm{Re} a(x,\\xi) \\geq 0}\" class=\"latex\" /> for all <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bx%2C%5Cxi%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{x,\\xi}\" title=\"{x,\\xi}\" class=\"latex\" />. Then one has </p> \n <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cmathrm%7BRe%7D+%5Clangle+a%28X%2CD%29+f%2C+f+%5Crangle+%5Cgeq+-C+%5C%7Cf%5C%7C_%7BW%5E%7B%5Calpha-%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B2%7D%2C2%7D%7D%5E2&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Re} \\langle a(X,D) f, f \\rangle \\geq -C \\|f\\|_{W^{\\alpha-\\frac{1}{2},2}}^2\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Re} \\langle a(X,D) f, f \\rangle \\geq -C \\|f\\|_{W^{\\alpha-\\frac{1}{2},2}}^2\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n <p> for all <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{f \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R})}\" title=\"{f \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R})}\" class=\"latex\" />, where <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BC%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{C}\" title=\"{C}\" class=\"latex\" /> depends only on <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%2C%5Calpha%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a,\\alpha}\" title=\"{a,\\alpha}\" class=\"latex\" />. </p>\n</blockquote>  \n<p> <em>Proof:</em> From Exercise <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11722#adj-p\">11</a> we see that <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%28i+%5Cmathrm%7BIm%7D+a%29%28X%2CD%29+%2B+%28i+%5Cmathrm%7BIm%7D+a%29%28X%2CD%29%5E%2A%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{(i \\mathrm{Im} a)(X,D) + (i \\mathrm{Im} a)(X,D)^*}\" title=\"{(i \\mathrm{Im} a)(X,D) + (i \\mathrm{Im} a)(X,D)^*}\" class=\"latex\" /> is a pseudodifferential operator of order <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Calpha-1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\alpha-1}\" title=\"{\\alpha-1}\" class=\"latex\" />, hence by Exercise <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11722#sob\">12</a>(ii) we have </p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cmathrm%7BRe%7D+%5Clangle+%28i+%5Cmathrm%7BIm%7D+a%29%28X%2CD%29+f%2C+f+%5Crangle+%5Clesssim_a+%5C%7Cf%5C%7C_%7BW%5E%7B%5Calpha-%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B2%7D%2C2%7D%7D%5E2.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Re} \\langle (i \\mathrm{Im} a)(X,D) f, f \\rangle \\lesssim_a \\|f\\|_{W^{\\alpha-\\frac{1}{2},2}}^2.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Re} \\langle (i \\mathrm{Im} a)(X,D) f, f \\rangle \\lesssim_a \\|f\\|_{W^{\\alpha-\\frac{1}{2},2}}^2.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p> Thus we may remove the imaginary part from <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a}\" title=\"{a}\" class=\"latex\" /> and assume that <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a}\" title=\"{a}\" class=\"latex\" /> is real and non-negative. Applying a smooth partition of unity of Littlewood-Paley type, we can write <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba+%3D+%5Csum_%7Bk%3D0%7D%5E%5Cinfty+a_k%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a = \\sum_{k=0}^\\infty a_k}\" title=\"{a = \\sum_{k=0}^\\infty a_k}\" class=\"latex\" />, where each <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba_k%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a_k}\" title=\"{a_k}\" class=\"latex\" /> is also non-negative, supported on the region <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5C%7B+%28x%2C%5Cxi%29%3A+%5Clangle+%5Cxi+%5Crangle+%5Csim+2%5Ek+%5C%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\{ (x,\\xi): \\langle \\xi \\rangle \\sim 2^k \\}}\" title=\"{\\{ (x,\\xi): \\langle \\xi \\rangle \\sim 2^k \\}}\" class=\"latex\" />, and obeys essentially the same symbol estimates as <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a}\" title=\"{a}\" class=\"latex\" /> uniformly in <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bk%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{k}\" title=\"{k}\" class=\"latex\" />. It then suffices to show that </p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cmathrm%7BRe%7D+%5Clangle+%5Csum_%7Bk%3D0%7D%5EK+a_k%28X%2CD%29+f%2C+f+%5Crangle+%5Cgeq+-C+%5C%7Cf%5C%7C_%7BW%5E%7B%5Calpha-%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B2%7D%2C2%7D%7D%5E2&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Re} \\langle \\sum_{k=0}^K a_k(X,D) f, f \\rangle \\geq -C \\|f\\|_{W^{\\alpha-\\frac{1}{2},2}}^2\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Re} \\langle \\sum_{k=0}^K a_k(X,D) f, f \\rangle \\geq -C \\|f\\|_{W^{\\alpha-\\frac{1}{2},2}}^2\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p> uniformly in <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BK%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{K}\" title=\"{K}\" class=\"latex\" />. </p> \n<p> We now use the Gabor-type transforms <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BT_%5Cphi%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{T_\\phi}\" title=\"{T_\\phi}\" class=\"latex\" /> from Exercise <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11722#gabor\">13</a>, except that we make <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cphi%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\phi}\" title=\"{\\phi}\" class=\"latex\" /> dependent on <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bk%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{k}\" title=\"{k}\" class=\"latex\" />. Specifically we pick a single real even <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cphi_0+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\phi_0 \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R})}\" title=\"{\\phi_0 \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R})}\" class=\"latex\" /> with <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BL%5E2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{L^2}\" title=\"{L^2}\" class=\"latex\" /> norm <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{1}\" title=\"{1}\" class=\"latex\" />, then define <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cphi_k%28x%29+%3A%3D+2%5E%7Bk%2F4%7D+%5Cphi%282%5E%7Bk%2F2%7D+x%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\phi_k(x) := 2^{k/4} \\phi(2^{k/2} x)}\" title=\"{\\phi_k(x) := 2^{k/4} \\phi(2^{k/2} x)}\" class=\"latex\" /> for all <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bk%3E0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{k>0}\" title=\"{k>0}\" class=\"latex\" />. We will approximate <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba_k%28X%2CD%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a_k(X,D)}\" title=\"{a_k(X,D)}\" class=\"latex\" /> by </p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%28a_k+%2A+W_%7B%5Cphi_k%7D%29%28X%2CD%29+%3D+T_%7B%5Cphi_k%7D%5E%2A+a_k+T_%7B%5Cphi_k%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  (a_k * W_{\\phi_k})(X,D) = T_{\\phi_k}^* a_k T_{\\phi_k}.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  (a_k * W_{\\phi_k})(X,D) = T_{\\phi_k}^* a_k T_{\\phi_k}.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p> Observe that </p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clangle+T_%7B%5Cphi_k%7D%5E%2A+a_k+T_%7B%5Cphi_k%7D+f%2C+f+%5Crangle+%3D+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+a_k%28x%2C%5Cxi%29+%7CT_%7B%5Cphi_k%7Df%28x%2C%5Cxi%29%7C%5E2%5C+dx+d%5Cxi+%5Cgeq+0&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\langle T_{\\phi_k}^* a_k T_{\\phi_k} f, f \\rangle = \\int_{\\bf R} \\int_{\\bf R} a_k(x,\\xi) |T_{\\phi_k}f(x,\\xi)|^2\\ dx d\\xi \\geq 0\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\langle T_{\\phi_k}^* a_k T_{\\phi_k} f, f \\rangle = \\int_{\\bf R} \\int_{\\bf R} a_k(x,\\xi) |T_{\\phi_k}f(x,\\xi)|^2\\ dx d\\xi \\geq 0\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p> so by the triangle inequality it will suffice to establish the bound </p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clangle+%5Csum_%7Bk%3D0%7D%5EK+%28a_k+-+a_k+%2A+W_%7B%5Cphi_k%7D%29%28X%2CD%29+f%2C+f+%5Crangle+%5Clesssim_a+%5C%7Cf%5C%7C_%7BW%5E%7B%5Calpha-%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B2%7D%2C2%7D%7D%5E2.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\langle \\sum_{k=0}^K (a_k - a_k * W_{\\phi_k})(X,D) f, f \\rangle \\lesssim_a \\|f\\|_{W^{\\alpha-\\frac{1}{2},2}}^2.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\langle \\sum_{k=0}^K (a_k - a_k * W_{\\phi_k})(X,D) f, f \\rangle \\lesssim_a \\|f\\|_{W^{\\alpha-\\frac{1}{2},2}}^2.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p> However, it is not difficult (see exercise below) to show that <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Csum_%7Bk%3D0%7D%5EK+a_k+-+a_k+%2A+W_%7B%5Cphi_k%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\sum_{k=0}^K a_k - a_k * W_{\\phi_k}}\" title=\"{\\sum_{k=0}^K a_k - a_k * W_{\\phi_k}}\" class=\"latex\" /> is a symbol of order <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Calpha-1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\alpha-1}\" title=\"{\\alpha-1}\" class=\"latex\" /> uniformly in <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BK%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{K}\" title=\"{K}\" class=\"latex\" />, and the claim now follows from Exercise <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11722#sob\">12</a>(ii). <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5CBox&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\Box\" title=\"\\Box\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<blockquote>\n <p><b>Exercise 17</b> Verify the claim that <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Csum_%7Bk%3D0%7D%5EK+a_k+-+a_k+%2A+W_%7B%5Cphi_k%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\sum_{k=0}^K a_k - a_k * W_{\\phi_k}}\" title=\"{\\sum_{k=0}^K a_k - a_k * W_{\\phi_k}}\" class=\"latex\" /> is a symbol of order <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Calpha-1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\alpha-1}\" title=\"{\\alpha-1}\" class=\"latex\" /> uniformly in <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BK%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{K}\" title=\"{K}\" class=\"latex\" />. (Here one will need the fact that <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BW_%7B%5Cphi_k%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{W_{\\phi_k}}\" title=\"{W_{\\phi_k}}\" class=\"latex\" /> is a rescaling by a scaling factor <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B2%5E%7Bk%2F2%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{2^{k/2}}\" title=\"{2^{k/2}}\" class=\"latex\" /> of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BW_%5Cphi%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{W_\\phi}\" title=\"{W_\\phi}\" class=\"latex\" />, which is an even Schwartz function of mean <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{1}\" title=\"{1}\" class=\"latex\" />. The even nature of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BW_%5Cphi%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{W_\\phi}\" title=\"{W_\\phi}\" class=\"latex\" /> is needed to cancel some linear terms which would otherwise only allow one to obtain symbol bounds of order <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Calpha-1%2F2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\alpha-1/2}\" title=\"{\\alpha-1/2}\" class=\"latex\" /> rather than <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Calpha-1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\alpha-1}\" title=\"{\\alpha-1}\" class=\"latex\" />.) </p>\n</blockquote>  \n<blockquote>\n <p><b>Remark 18</b> It is possible to improve the error term in the sharp Garding inequality, particularly if one uses the Weyl quantization rather than the Kohn-Nirenberg one (see Remark <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11722#weyl\">19</a> below); also the non-negativity hypothesis on <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{a}\" title=\"{a}\" class=\"latex\" /> can be relaxed in a manner consistent with the uncertainty principle;
