src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cfrac%7B5%7D%7B%5Clog%28R%5Cdelta%29%7D+%3C+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B2%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\frac{5}{\\log(R\\delta)} < \\frac{1}{2}}\" title=\"{\\frac{5}{\\log(R\\delta)} < \\frac{1}{2}}\" class=\"latex\" />, hence \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7B%5Cmathbb+E%7D+%7C%7B%5Cbf+A%7D%27+%5Cbackslash+%7B%5Cbf+V%7D%7C+%3C+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7Br%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb E} |{\\bf A}' \\backslash {\\bf V}| < \\frac{1}{r}.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb E} |{\\bf A}' \\backslash {\\bf V}| < \\frac{1}{r}.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> In particular with probability at least \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B1+-+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7Br%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{1 - \\frac{1}{r}}\" title=\"{1 - \\frac{1}{r}}\" class=\"latex\" />, there must exist \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BA_i%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{A_i}\" title=\"{A_i}\" class=\"latex\" /> such that \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7CA_i+%5Cbackslash+%7B%5Cbf+V%7D%7C+%3D+0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{|A_i \\backslash {\\bf V}| = 0}\" title=\"{|A_i \\backslash {\\bf V}| = 0}\" class=\"latex\" />, giving the proposition. \n<p> It remains to establish Proposition <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11852#Refinement\">6</a>. This is the difficult step, and requires a clever way to find the variant <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+A%7D%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf A}'}\" title=\"{{\\bf A}'}\" class=\"latex\" /> of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+A%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf A}}\" title=\"{{\\bf A}}\" class=\"latex\" /> that has better containment properties in <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+V%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf V}}\" title=\"{{\\bf V}}\" class=\"latex\" /> than <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+A%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf A}}\" title=\"{{\\bf A}}\" class=\"latex\" /> does. The main trick is to make a conditional copy <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%28%7B%5Cbf+A%7D%27%2C+%7B%5Cbf+V%7D%27%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{({\\bf A}', {\\bf V}')}\" title=\"{({\\bf A}', {\\bf V}')}\" class=\"latex\" /> of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%28%7B%5Cbf+A%7D%2C+%7B%5Cbf+V%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{({\\bf A}, {\\bf V})}\" title=\"{({\\bf A}, {\\bf V})}\" class=\"latex\" /> that is conditionally independent of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%28%7B%5Cbf+A%7D%2C+%7B%5Cbf+V%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{({\\bf A}, {\\bf V})}\" title=\"{({\\bf A}, {\\bf V})}\" class=\"latex\" /> subject to the constraint <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+A%7D+%5Ccup+%7B%5Cbf+V%7D+%3D+%7B%5Cbf+A%7D%27+%5Ccup+%7B%5Cbf+V%7D%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf A} \\cup {\\bf V} = {\\bf A}' \\cup {\\bf V}'}\" title=\"{{\\bf A} \\cup {\\bf V} = {\\bf A}' \\cup {\\bf V}'}\" class=\"latex\" />. The point here is that this constrant implies the inclusions <a name=\"av1\"><p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7B%5Cbf+A%7D%27+%5Cbackslash+%7B%5Cbf+V%7D+%5Csubset+%7B%5Cbf+A%7D+%5Ccap+%7B%5Cbf+A%7D%27+%5Csubset+%5Csubset+%7B%5Cbf+A%7D+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%284%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  {\\bf A}' \\backslash {\\bf V} \\subset {\\bf A} \\cap {\\bf A}' \\subset \\subset {\\bf A} \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (4)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  {\\bf A}' \\backslash {\\bf V} \\subset {\\bf A} \\cap {\\bf A}' \\subset \\subset {\\bf A} \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (4)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> </a> and <a name=\"av2\"><p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7B%5Cbf+A%7D%27+%5Cbackslash+%7B%5Cbf+A%7D+%5Csubset+%7B%5Cbf+V%7D.+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%285%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  {\\bf A}' \\backslash {\\bf A} \\subset {\\bf V}. \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (5)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  {\\bf A}' \\backslash {\\bf A} \\subset {\\bf V}. \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (5)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> </a> Because of the <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BR%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{R}\" title=\"{R}\" class=\"latex\" />-spread hypothesis, it is hard for <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+A%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf A}}\" title=\"{{\\bf A}}\" class=\"latex\" /> to contain any fixed large set. If we could apply this observation in the contrapositive to <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+A%7D+%5Ccap+%7B%5Cbf+A%7D%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf A} \\cap {\\bf A}'}\" title=\"{{\\bf A} \\cap {\\bf A}'}\" class=\"latex\" /> we could hope to get a good upper bound on the size of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+A%7D+%5Ccap+%7B%5Cbf+A%7D%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf A} \\cap {\\bf A}'}\" title=\"{{\\bf A} \\cap {\\bf A}'}\" class=\"latex\" /> and hence on <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+A%7D+%5Cbackslash+%7B%5Cbf+V%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf A} \\backslash {\\bf V}}\" title=\"{{\\bf A} \\backslash {\\bf V}}\" class=\"latex\" /> thanks to <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11852#av1\">(4)</a>. One can also hope to improve such an upper bound by also employing <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11852#av2\">(5)</a>, since it is also hard for the random set <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+V%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf V}}\" title=\"{{\\bf V}}\" class=\"latex\" /> to contain a fixed large set. There are however difficulties with implementing this approach due to the fact that the random sets <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+A%7D+%5Ccap+%7B%5Cbf+A%7D%27%2C+%7B%5Cbf+A%7D%27+%5Cbackslash+%7B%5Cbf+A%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf A} \\cap {\\bf A}', {\\bf A}' \\backslash {\\bf A}}\" title=\"{{\\bf A} \\cap {\\bf A}', {\\bf A}' \\backslash {\\bf A}}\" class=\"latex\" /> are coupled with <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+A%7D%2C+%7B%5Cbf+V%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf A}, {\\bf V}}\" title=\"{{\\bf A}, {\\bf V}}\" class=\"latex\" /> in a moderately complicated fashion. In Rao’s argument a somewhat complicated encoding scheme was created to give information-theoretic control on these random variables; below thefold we accomplish a similar effect by using Shannon entropy inequalities in place of explicit encoding. A certain amount of information-theoretic sleight of hand is required to decouple certain random variables to the extent that the Shannon inequalities can be effectively applied. The argument bears some resemblance to the “entropy compression method” discussed in <a href=\"https://terrytao.wordpress.com/2009/08/05/mosers-entropy-compression-argument/\">this previous blog post</a>; there may be a way to more explicitly express the argument below in terms of that method. (There is also some kinship with the <a href=\"http://math.mit.edu/~fox/paper-dependent-random-choice.pdf\">method of dependent random choice</a>, which is used for instance to establish the Balog-Szemerédi-Gowers lemma, and was also translated into information theoretic language in <a href=\"http://www.math.ucla.edu/~tao/preprints/Expository/chapter_entropy.dvi\">these unpublished notes of Van Vu and myself</a>.) </p>\n<p> <span id=\"more-11852\"></span> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p align=\"center\"><b> — 1. Shannon entropy — </b></p> \n<p> In this section we lay out all the tools from the theory of Shannon entropy that we will need. </p>\n<p> Define an <em>empirical sequence</em> for a random variable <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf X}}\" title=\"{{\\bf X}}\" class=\"latex\" /> taking values in a discrete set <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BS%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{S}\" title=\"{S}\" class=\"latex\" /> to be a sequence <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BX_1%2CX_2%2C%5Cdots%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{X_1,X_2,\\dots}\" title=\"{X_1,X_2,\\dots}\" class=\"latex\" /> in <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BS%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{S}\" title=\"{S}\" class=\"latex\" /> such that the empirical samples of this sequence converge in distribution to <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf X}}\" title=\"{{\\bf X}}\" class=\"latex\" /> in the sense that <a name=\"lim\"><p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7B%5Cmathbb+P%7D%28+X_%7B%5Cbf+n%7D+%3D+X+%29+%3D+%7B%5Cmathbb+P%7D%28+%7B%5Cbf+X%7D+%3D+X+%29+%2B+o%281%29+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%286%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb P}( X_{\\bf n} = X ) = {\\mathbb P}( {\\bf X} = X ) + o(1) \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (6)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb P}( X_{\\bf n} = X ) = {\\mathbb P}( {\\bf X} = X ) + o(1) \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (6)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> </a> as <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN+%5Crightarrow+%5Cinfty%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{N \\rightarrow \\infty}\" title=\"{N \\rightarrow \\infty}\" class=\"latex\" />, where <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+n%7D+%3D+%7B%5Cbf+n%7D_N%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf n} = {\\bf n}_N}\" title=\"{{\\bf n} = {\\bf n}_N}\" class=\"latex\" /> is a uniform random variable drawn from <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5C%7B1%2C%5Cdots%2CN%5C%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\{1,\\dots,N\\}}\" title=\"{\\{1,\\dots,N\\}}\" class=\"latex\" />, and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bo%281%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{o(1)}\" title=\"{o(1)}\" class=\"latex\" /> denotes a quantity that goes to zero as <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN+%5Crightarrow+%5Cinfty%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{N \\rightarrow \\infty}\" title=\"{N \\rightarrow \\infty}\" class=\"latex\" /> (uniformly over other parameters independent of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{N}\" title=\"{N}\" class=\"latex\" />). Every random variable <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf X}}\" title=\"{{\\bf X}}\" class=\"latex\" /> has at least one empirical sequence; indeed, from the strong law of large numbers one can find such a sequence almost surely by taking an infinite number of independent trials of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf X}}\" title=\"{{\\bf X}}\" class=\"latex\" />. </p>\n<p> If <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf X}}\" title=\"{{\\bf X}}\" class=\"latex\" /> is a random variable taking values in some set <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BS%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{S}\" title=\"{S}\" class=\"latex\" />, its <em>Shannon entropy</em> <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathbb H}({\\bf X})}\" title=\"{{\\mathbb H}({\\bf X})}\" class=\"latex\" /> is defined by the formula </p>\n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%29+%3A%3D+%5Csum_%7BX+%5Cin+S%7D+%7B%5Cmathbb+P%7D%28+%7B%5Cbf+X%7D+%3D+X+%29+%5Clog+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B%7B%5Cmathbb+P%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D+%3D+X%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}) := \\sum_{X \\in S} {\\mathbb P}( {\\bf X} = X ) \\log \\frac{1}{{\\mathbb P}({\\bf X} = X)}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}) := \\sum_{X \\in S} {\\mathbb P}( {\\bf X} = X ) \\log \\frac{1}{{\\mathbb P}({\\bf X} = X)}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> with the convention \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B0+%5Clog+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B0%7D+%3D+0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{0 \\log \\frac{1}{0} = 0}\" title=\"{0 \\log \\frac{1}{0} = 0}\" class=\"latex\" />, and using the base two logarithm throughout. We can condition the Shannon entropy to events \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BE%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{E}\" title=\"{E}\" class=\"latex\" /> of positive probability, \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%7CE%29+%3A%3D+%5Csum_%7BX+%5Cin+S%7D+%7B%5Cmathbb+P%7D%28+%7B%5Cbf+X%7D+%3D+X+%7CE%29+%5Clog+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B%7B%5Cmathbb+P%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D+%3D+X%7CE%29%7D%2C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}|E) := \\sum_{X \\in S} {\\mathbb P}( {\\bf X} = X |E) \\log \\frac{1}{{\\mathbb P}({\\bf X} = X|E)},\" title=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}|E) := \\sum_{X \\in S} {\\mathbb P}( {\\bf X} = X |E) \\log \\frac{1}{{\\mathbb P}({\\bf X} = X|E)},\" class=\"latex\" /></p> and condition the Shannon entropy to other random variables \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf Y}}\" title=\"{{\\bf Y}}\" class=\"latex\" /> taking values in a set \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BT%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{T}\" title=\"{T}\" class=\"latex\" /> by \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%7C%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D%29+%3A%3D+%5Csum_%7BY+%5Cin+T%7D+%7B%5Cmathbb+P%7D%28+%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D+%3D+Y%29+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28+%7B%5Cbf+X%7D+%7C+%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D+%3D+Y%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}|{\\bf Y}) := \\sum_{Y \\in T} {\\mathbb P}( {\\bf Y} = Y) {\\mathbb H}( {\\bf X} | {\\bf Y} = Y)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}|{\\bf Y}) := \\sum_{Y \\in T} {\\mathbb P}( {\\bf Y} = Y) {\\mathbb H}( {\\bf X} | {\\bf Y} = Y)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> with the convention that the summand is zero if \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathbb+P%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D+%3D+Y%29+%3D+0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathbb P}({\\bf Y} = Y) = 0}\" title=\"{{\\mathbb P}({\\bf Y} = Y) = 0}\" class=\"latex\" />. \n<p> We record the following standard and easily verified facts: </p>\n<p> \n <blockquote>\n  <b>Lemma 8 (Basic Shannon inequalities)</b> \n  <a name=\"basic\"></a> Let \n  <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%2C+%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D%2C+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf X}, {\\bf Y}, {\\bf Z}}\" title=\"{{\\bf X}, {\\bf Y}, {\\bf Z}}\" class=\"latex\" /> be random variables. \n  <ul> \n   <li>(i) (Monotonicity) If <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf X}}\" title=\"{{\\bf X}}\" class=\"latex\" /> is a deterministic function <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+X%7D+%3D+f%28%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf X} = f({\\bf Y})}\" title=\"{{\\bf X} = f({\\bf Y})}\" class=\"latex\" /> of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf Y}}\" title=\"{{\\bf Y}}\" class=\"latex\" />, then <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B0+%5Cleq+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%29+%5Cleq+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{0 \\leq {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}) \\leq {\\mathbb H}({\\bf Y})}\" title=\"{0 \\leq {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}) \\leq {\\mathbb H}({\\bf Y})}\" class=\"latex\" />. More generally, if <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf X}}\" title=\"{{\\bf X}}\" class=\"latex\" /> is a deterministic function <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+X%7D+%3D+f%28%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D%2C+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf X} = f({\\bf Y}, {\\bf Z})}\" title=\"{{\\bf X} = f({\\bf Y}, {\\bf Z})}\" class=\"latex\" /> of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf Y}}\" title=\"{{\\bf Y}}\" class=\"latex\" /> and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf Z}}\" title=\"{{\\bf Z}}\" class=\"latex\" />, then <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B0+%5Cleq+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%7C%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%29+%5Cleq+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D%7C%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{0 \\leq {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}|{\\bf Z}) \\leq {\\mathbb H}({\\bf Y}|{\\bf Z})}\" title=\"{0 \\leq {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}|{\\bf Z}) \\leq {\\mathbb H}({\\bf Y}|{\\bf Z})}\" class=\"latex\" />. If <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf Y}}\" title=\"{{\\bf Y}}\" class=\"latex\" /> is a deterministic function of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf Z}}\" title=\"{{\\bf Z}}\" class=\"latex\" />, then <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%7C%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%29+%5Cleq+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%7C%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}|{\\bf Z}) \\leq {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}|{\\bf Y})}\" title=\"{{\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}|{\\bf Z}) \\leq {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}|{\\bf Y})}\" class=\"latex\" />. </li>\n   <li>(ii) (Subadditivity) One has <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%2C+%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D%29+%5Cleq+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%29%2B%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}, {\\bf Y}) \\leq {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X})+{\\mathbb H}({\\bf Y})}\" title=\"{{\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}, {\\bf Y}) \\leq {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X})+{\\mathbb H}({\\bf Y})}\" class=\"latex\" />, with equality iff <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf X}}\" title=\"{{\\bf X}}\" class=\"latex\" />, <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf Y}}\" title=\"{{\\bf Y}}\" class=\"latex\" /> are independent. More generally, one has <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%2C+%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D%7C%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%29+%5Cleq+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%7C%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%29%2B%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D%7C%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}, {\\bf Y}|{\\bf Z}) \\leq {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}|{\\bf Z})+{\\mathbb H}({\\bf Y}|{\\bf Z})}\" title=\"{{\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}, {\\bf Y}|{\\bf Z}) \\leq {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}|{\\bf Z})+{\\mathbb H}({\\bf Y}|{\\bf Z})}\" class=\"latex\" />, with equality iff <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf X}}\" title=\"{{\\bf X}}\" class=\"latex\" />, <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf Y}}\" title=\"{{\\bf Y}}\" class=\"latex\" /> are conditionally independent with respect to <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf Z}}\" title=\"{{\\bf Z}}\" class=\"latex\" />. </li>\n   <li>(iii) (Chain rule) One has <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%2C+%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D%29+%3D+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%29+%2B+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D%7C%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%29+%3D+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D%29+%2B+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%7C%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}, {\\bf Y}) = {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}) + {\\mathbb H}({\\bf Y}|{\\bf X}) = {\\mathbb H}({\\bf Y}) + {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}|{\\bf Y})}\" title=\"{{\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}, {\\bf Y}) = {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}) + {\\mathbb H}({\\bf Y}|{\\bf X}) = {\\mathbb H}({\\bf Y}) + {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}|{\\bf Y})}\" class=\"latex\" />. More generally <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%2C+%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D%7C%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%29+%3D+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%7C%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%29+%2B+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D%7C%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%2C%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%29+%3D+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D%7C%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%29+%2B+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%7C%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D%2C%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}, {\\bf Y}|{\\bf Z}) = {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}|{\\bf Z}) + {\\mathbb H}({\\bf Y}|{\\bf X},{\\bf Z}) = {\\mathbb H}({\\bf Y}|{\\bf Z}) + {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}|{\\bf Y},{\\bf Z})}\" title=\"{{\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}, {\\bf Y}|{\\bf Z}) = {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}|{\\bf Z}) + {\\mathbb H}({\\bf Y}|{\\bf X},{\\bf Z}) = {\\mathbb H}({\\bf Y}|{\\bf Z}) + {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}|{\\bf Y},{\\bf Z})}\" class=\"latex\" />. In particular <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B0+%5Cleq+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%7C%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D%29+%5Cleq+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{0 \\leq {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}|{\\bf Y}) \\leq {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X})}\" title=\"{0 \\leq {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}|{\\bf Y}) \\leq {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X})}\" class=\"latex\" />, and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%7C%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D%29+%3D+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}|{\\bf Y}) = {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X})}\" title=\"{{\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}|{\\bf Y}) = {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X})}\" class=\"latex\" /> iff <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%2C%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf X},{\\bf Y}}\" title=\"{{\\bf X},{\\bf Y}}\" class=\"latex\" /> are independent; similarly, <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B0+%5Cleq+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%7C%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D%2C%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%29+%5Cleq+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%7C%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{0 \\leq {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}|{\\bf Y},{\\bf Z}) \\leq {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}|{\\bf Z})}\" title=\"{0 \\leq {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}|{\\bf Y},{\\bf Z}) \\leq {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}|{\\bf Z})}\" class=\"latex\" />, and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%7C%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D%2C%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%29+%3D+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%7C%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}|{\\bf Y},{\\bf Z}) = {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}|{\\bf Z})}\" title=\"{{\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}|{\\bf Y},{\\bf Z}) = {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}|{\\bf Z})}\" class=\"latex\" /> iff <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%2C%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf X},{\\bf Y}}\" title=\"{{\\bf X},{\\bf Y}}\" class=\"latex\" /> are conditionally independent with respect to <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf Z}}\" title=\"{{\\bf Z}}\" class=\"latex\" />. </li>\n   <li>(iv) (Jensen’s inequality) If <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf X}}\" title=\"{{\\bf X}}\" class=\"latex\" /> takes values in a finite set <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BS%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{S}\" title=\"{S}\" class=\"latex\" /> then <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%29+%5Cleq+%5Clog+%7CS%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}) \\leq \\log |S|}\" title=\"{{\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}) \\leq \\log |S|}\" class=\"latex\" />, with equality iff <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf X}}\" title=\"{{\\bf X}}\" class=\"latex\" /> is uniformly distributed in <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BS%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{S}\" title=\"{S}\" class=\"latex\" />. More generally, if <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf X}}\" title=\"{{\\bf X}}\" class=\"latex\" /> takes values in a set <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BS_%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{S_{\\bf Y}}\" title=\"{S_{\\bf Y}}\" class=\"latex\" /> that depends on <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf Y}}\" title=\"{{\\bf Y}}\" class=\"latex\" />, then <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%7C%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D%29+%5Cleq+%7B%5Cmathbb+E%7D+%5Clog+%7CS_%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}|{\\bf Y}) \\leq {\\mathbb E} \\log |S_{\\bf Y}|}\" title=\"{{\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}|{\\bf Y}) \\leq {\\mathbb E} \\log |S_{\\bf Y}|}\" class=\"latex\" />, with equality iff <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf X}}\" title=\"{{\\bf X}}\" class=\"latex\" /> is uniformly distributed in <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BS_%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{S_{\\bf Y}}\" title=\"{S_{\\bf Y}}\" class=\"latex\" /> after conditioning on <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf Y}}\" title=\"{{\\bf Y}}\" class=\"latex\" />. </li>\n   <li>(v) (Gibbs inequality) If <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%2C+%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf X}, {\\bf Y}}\" title=\"{{\\bf X}, {\\bf Y}}\" class=\"latex\" /> take values in the same finite set <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BS%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{S}\" title=\"{S}\" class=\"latex\" />, then <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%29+%5Cleq+%5Csum_%7BX+%5Cin+S%7D+%7B%5Cmathbb+P%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D+%3D+X%29+%5Clog+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B%7B%5Cmathbb+P%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D%3DX%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}) \\leq \\sum_{X \\in S} {\\mathbb P}({\\bf X} = X) \\log \\frac{1}{{\\mathbb P}({\\bf Y}=X)}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}) \\leq \\sum_{X \\in S} {\\mathbb P}({\\bf X} = X) \\log \\frac{1}{{\\mathbb P}({\\bf Y}=X)}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> (we permit the right-hand side to be infinite, which makes the inequality vacuously true). </li>\n  </ul> \n </blockquote> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> See <a href=\"https://terrytao.wordpress.com/2017/03/01/special-cases-of-shannon-entropy/\">this previous blog post</a> for some intuitive analogies to understand Shannon entropy. </p>\n<p> Now we establish some inequalities of relevance to random sets. </p>\n<p> We first observe that any small random set largely determines any of its subsets. Define a <em>random subset</em> of a random set <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+B%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf B}}\" title=\"{{\\bf B}}\" class=\"latex\" /> to be a random set <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+A%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf A}}\" title=\"{{\\bf A}}\" class=\"latex\" /> such that <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+B%7D+%5Csubset+%7B%5Cbf+A%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf B} \\subset {\\bf A}}\" title=\"{{\\bf B} \\subset {\\bf A}}\" class=\"latex\" /> holds almost surely. </p>\n<p> \n <blockquote>\n  <b>Lemma 9 (Subsets of small sets have small conditional entropy)</b> \n  <a name=\"small\"></a> Let \n  <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+B%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf B}}\" title=\"{{\\bf B}}\" class=\"latex\" /> be a random finite set. \n  <ul> \n   <li>(i) One has <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+A%7D%7C%7B%5Cbf+B%7D%29+%5Cleq+%7B%5Cmathbb+E%7D+%7C%7B%5Cbf+B%7D%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathbb H}({\\bf A}|{\\bf B}) \\leq {\\mathbb E} |{\\bf B}|}\" title=\"{{\\mathbb H}({\\bf A}|{\\bf B}) \\leq {\\mathbb E} |{\\bf B}|}\" class=\"latex\" /> for any random subset <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+A%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf A}}\" title=\"{{\\bf A}}\" class=\"latex\" /> of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+B%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf B}}\" title=\"{{\\bf B}}\" class=\"latex\" />. </li>\n   <li>(ii) One has <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28+%7C%7B%5Cbf+B%7D%7C+%29+%5Cleq+1%2B%7B%5Cmathbb+E%7D+%7C%7B%5Cbf+B%7D%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathbb H}( |{\\bf B}| ) \\leq 1+{\\mathbb E} |{\\bf B}|}\" title=\"{{\\mathbb H}( |{\\bf B}| ) \\leq 1+{\\mathbb E} |{\\bf B}|}\" class=\"latex\" />. If <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+B%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf B}}\" title=\"{{\\bf B}}\" class=\"latex\" /> is almost surely non-empty, we can improve this to <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28+%7C%7B%5Cbf+B%7D%7C+%29+%5Cleq+%7B%5Cmathbb+E%7D+%7C%7B%5Cbf+B%7D%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathbb H}( |{\\bf B}| ) \\leq {\\mathbb E} |{\\bf B}|}\" title=\"{{\\mathbb H}( |{\\bf B}| ) \\leq {\\mathbb E} |{\\bf B}|}\" class=\"latex\" />. </li>\n  </ul>\n </blockquote> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> <em>Proof:</em> The set <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+A%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf A}}\" title=\"{{\\bf A}}\" class=\"latex\" /> takes values in the power set <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B2%5E%7B%7B%5Cbf+B%7D%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{2^{{\\bf B}}}\" title=\"{2^{{\\bf B}}}\" class=\"latex\" /> of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+B%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf B}}\" title=\"{{\\bf B}}\" class=\"latex\" />, so the claim (i) follows from Lemma <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11852#basic\">8</a>(iv). (Note how it is convenient here that we are using the base <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{2}\" title=\"{2}\" class=\"latex\" /> for the logarithm.) </p>\n<p> For (ii), apply Lemma <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11852#basic\">8</a>(v) with <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+X%7D+%3D+%7C%7B%5Cbf+B%7D%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf X} = |{\\bf B}|}\" title=\"{{\\bf X} = |{\\bf B}|}\" class=\"latex\" /> and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf Y}}\" title=\"{{\\bf Y}}\" class=\"latex\" /> the geometric random variable <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathbb+P%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D+%3D+n%29+%3D+2%5E%7B-n-1%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathbb P}({\\bf Y} = n) = 2^{-n-1}}\" title=\"{{\\mathbb P}({\\bf Y} = n) = 2^{-n-1}}\" class=\"latex\" /> for natural numbers <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{n}\" title=\"{n}\" class=\"latex\" /> (or <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathbb+P%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+Y%7D+%3D+n%29+%3D+2%5E%7B-n%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathbb P}({\\bf Y} = n) = 2^{-n}}\" title=\"{{\\mathbb P}({\\bf Y} = n) = 2^{-n}}\" class=\"latex\" /> for positive <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{n}\" title=\"{n}\" class=\"latex\" />, if <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+B%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf B}}\" title=\"{{\\bf B}}\" class=\"latex\" /> is non-empty). <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5CBox&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\Box\" title=\"\\Box\" class=\"latex\" /> </p>\n<p> Now we encode the property of a random variable <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+A%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf A}}\" title=\"{{\\bf A}}\" class=\"latex\" /> being <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BR%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{R}\" title=\"{R}\" class=\"latex\" />-spread in the language of Shannon entropy. </p>\n<p> \n <blockquote>\n  <b>Lemma 10 (Information-theoretic interpretation of spread)</b> \n  <a name=\"spread\"></a> Let \n  <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+A%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf A}}\" title=\"{{\\bf A}}\" class=\"latex\" /> be a random finite set that is \n  <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BR%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{R}\" title=\"{R}\" class=\"latex\" />-spread for some \n  <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BR+%5Cgeq+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{R \\geq 1}\" title=\"{R \\geq 1}\" class=\"latex\" />. \n  <ul> \n   <li>(i) If <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+A%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf A}}\" title=\"{{\\bf A}}\" class=\"latex\" /> is uniformly distributed amongst some finite collection <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+A%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal A}}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal A}}\" class=\"latex\" /> of sets, then <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+A%7D+%7C+%7B%5Cbf+S%7D+%29+%5Cleq+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+A%7D%29+-+%28%5Clog+R%29+%7B%5Cmathbb+E%7D+%7C%7B%5Cbf+S%7D%7C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb H}({\\bf A} | {\\bf S} ) \\leq {\\mathbb H}({\\bf A}) - (\\log R) {\\mathbb E} |{\\bf S}|\" title=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb H}({\\bf A} | {\\bf S} ) \\leq {\\mathbb H}({\\bf A}) - (\\log R) {\\mathbb E} |{\\bf S}|\" class=\"latex\" /></p> for all random subsets <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+S%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf S}}\" title=\"{{\\bf S}}\" class=\"latex\" /> of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+A%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf A}}\" title=\"{{\\bf A}}\" class=\"latex\" />. </li>\n   <li>(ii) In the general case, if <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BA_1%2C+A_2%2C+A_3%2C%5Cdots%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{A_1, A_2, A_3,\\dots}\" title=\"{A_1, A_2, A_3,\\dots}\" class=\"latex\" /> are an empirical sequence of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+A%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf A}}\" title=\"{{\\bf A}}\" class=\"latex\" />, then <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+n%7D+%7C+%7B%5Cbf+S%7D+%29+%5Cleq+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%29+-+%28%5Clog+R%29+%7B%5Cmathbb+E%7D+%7C%7B%5Cbf+S%7D%7C+-+o%281%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb H}({\\bf n} | {\\bf S} ) \\leq {\\mathbb H}({\\bf n}) - (\\log R) {\\mathbb E} |{\\bf S}| - o(1)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb H}({\\bf n} | {\\bf S} ) \\leq {\\mathbb H}({\\bf n}) - (\\log R) {\\mathbb E} |{\\bf S}| - o(1)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> as <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN+%5Crightarrow+%5Cinfty%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{N \\rightarrow \\infty}\" title=\"{N \\rightarrow \\infty}\" class=\"latex\" />, where <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf n}}\" title=\"{{\\bf n}}\" class=\"latex\" /> is drawn uniformly from <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5C%7B1%2C%5Cdots%2CN%5C%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\{1,\\dots,N\\}}\" title=\"{\\{1,\\dots,N\\}}\" class=\"latex\" /> and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+S%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf S}}\" title=\"{{\\bf S}}\" class=\"latex\" /> is a random subset of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BA_%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{A_{\\bf n}}\" title=\"{A_{\\bf n}}\" class=\"latex\" />. </li>\n  </ul> \n </blockquote> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> Informally: large random subsets of an <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BR%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{R}\" title=\"{R}\" class=\"latex\" />-spread set <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+A%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf A}}\" title=\"{{\\bf A}}\" class=\"latex\" /> necessarily have a lot of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mutual_information\">mutual information</a> with <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+A%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf A}}\" title=\"{{\\bf A}}\" class=\"latex\" />. Conversely, one can bound the size of a random subset of an <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BR%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{R}\" title=\"{R}\" class=\"latex\" />-spread set by bounding its mutual information with <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+A%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf A}}\" title=\"{{\\bf A}}\" class=\"latex\" />. </p>\n<p> <em>Proof:</em> In case (i), it suffices by Lemma <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11852#basic\">8</a>(iv) to establish the bound </p>\n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+A%7D+%7C+%7B%5Cbf+S%7D+%3D+S+%29+%5Cleq+%5Clog+%7C%7B%5Cmathcal+A%7D%7C+-+%28%5Clog+R%29+%7B%5Cmathbb+E%7D+%7CS%7C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb H}({\\bf A} | {\\bf S} = S ) \\leq \\log |{\\mathcal A}| - (\\log R) {\\mathbb E} |S|\" title=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb H}({\\bf A} | {\\bf S} = S ) \\leq \\log |{\\mathcal A}| - (\\log R) {\\mathbb E} |S|\" class=\"latex\" /></p> for each finite set \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BS%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{S}\" title=\"{S}\" class=\"latex\" /> in the range of \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+S%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf S}}\" title=\"{{\\bf S}}\" class=\"latex\" />. But as \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+A%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf A}}\" title=\"{{\\bf A}}\" class=\"latex\" /> is \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BR%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{R}\" title=\"{R}\" class=\"latex\" />-spread and uniformly distributed in \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+A%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal A}}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal A}}\" class=\"latex\" />, there are at most \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BR%5E%7B-S%7D+%7C%7B%5Cmathcal+A%7D%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{R^{-S} |{\\mathcal A}|}\" title=\"{R^{-S} |{\\mathcal A}|}\" class=\"latex\" /> elements of \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+A%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal A}}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal A}}\" class=\"latex\" /> that contain \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BS%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{S}\" title=\"{S}\" class=\"latex\" />, and the claim follows from a second appeal to Lemma \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11852#basic\">8</a>(iv). Case (ii) follows from case (i) thanks to \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11852#lim\">(6)</a>. \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5CBox&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\Box\" title=\"\\Box\" class=\"latex\" /> \n<p> Given a finite non-empty set <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BX%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{X}\" title=\"{X}\" class=\"latex\" /> and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B0+%5Cleq+k+%5Cleq+%7CX%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{0 \\leq k \\leq |X|}\" title=\"{0 \\leq k \\leq |X|}\" class=\"latex\" />, let <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cbinom%7BX%7D%7Bk%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\binom{X}{k}}\" title=\"{\\binom{X}{k}}\" class=\"latex\" /> denote the collection of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bk%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{k}\" title=\"{k}\" class=\"latex\" />-element subsets of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BX%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{X}\" title=\"{X}\" class=\"latex\" />. A uniformly chosen element <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+V%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf V}}\" title=\"{{\\bf V}}\" class=\"latex\" /> of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cbinom%7BX%7D%7Bk%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\binom{X}{k}}\" title=\"{\\binom{X}{k}}\" class=\"latex\" /> is thus a random <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bk%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{k}\" title=\"{k}\" class=\"latex\" />-element subset of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BX%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{X}\" title=\"{X}\" class=\"latex\" />; we refer to the quantity <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cdelta+%3D+k%2F%7CX%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\delta = k/|X|}\" title=\"{\\delta = k/|X|}\" class=\"latex\" /> as the <em>density</em> of this random subset, and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+V%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf V}}\" title=\"{{\\bf V}}\" class=\"latex\" /> as a <em>uniformly chosen random subset of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BX%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{X}\" title=\"{X}\" class=\"latex\" /> of density <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cdelta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\delta}\" title=\"{\\delta}\" class=\"latex\" /></em>. (Of course, this is only defined when <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B0+%5Cleq+%5Cdelta+%5Cleq+X%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{0 \\leq \\delta \\leq X}\" title=\"{0 \\leq \\delta \\leq X}\" class=\"latex\" /> is an integer multiple of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B1%2F%7CX%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{1/|X|}\" title=\"{1/|X|}\" class=\"latex\" />.) Uniformly chosen random sets have the following information-theoretic relationships to small random sets have the following information-theoretic properties: </p>\n<p> \n <blockquote>\n  <b>Lemma 11</b> \n  <a name=\"absorb\"></a> Let \n  <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BX%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{X}\" title=\"{X}\" class=\"latex\" /> be a finite non-empty set, let \n  <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+W%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf W}}\" title=\"{{\\bf W}}\" class=\"latex\" /> be a uniformly chosen random subset of \n  <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BX%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{X}\" title=\"{X}\" class=\"latex\" /> of some density \n  <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B0+%5Cleq+%5Cdelta+%5Cleq+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{0 \\leq \\delta \\leq 1}\" title=\"{0 \\leq \\delta \\leq 1}\" class=\"latex\" /> (which is a multiple of \n  <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B1%2F%7CX%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{1/|X|}\" title=\"{1/|X|}\" class=\"latex\" />). \n  <ul> \n   <li>(i) (Spread) If <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+S%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf S}}\" title=\"{{\\bf S}}\" class=\"latex\" /> is a random subset of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+W%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf W}}\" title=\"{{\\bf W}}\" class=\"latex\" />, then <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+W%7D+%7C+%7B%5Cbf+S%7D+%29+%5Cleq+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+W%7D%29+-+%28%5Clog+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B%5Cdelta%7D%29+%7B%5Cmathbb+E%7D+%7C%7B%5Cbf+S%7D%7C.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb H}({\\bf W} | {\\bf S} ) \\leq {\\mathbb H}({\\bf W}) - (\\log \\frac{1}{\\delta}) {\\mathbb E} |{\\bf S}|.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb H}({\\bf W} | {\\bf S} ) \\leq {\\mathbb H}({\\bf W}) - (\\log \\frac{1}{\\delta}) {\\mathbb E} |{\\bf S}|.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> </li>\n   <li>(ii) (Absorption) If <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+S%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf S}}\" title=\"{{\\bf S}}\" class=\"latex\" /> is a random subset of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BX%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{X}\" title=\"{X}\" class=\"latex\" />, then <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+W%7D+%5Ccup+%7B%5Cbf+S%7D+%29+%5Cleq+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+W%7D%29+%2B+1+%2B+%281%2B%5Clog+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B%5Cdelta%7D%29+%7B%5Cmathbb+E%7D+%7C%7B%5Cbf+S%7D%7C.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb H}({\\bf W} \\cup {\\bf S} ) \\leq {\\mathbb H}({\\bf W}) + 1 + (1+\\log \\frac{1}{\\delta}) {\\mathbb E} |{\\bf S}|.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb H}({\\bf W} \\cup {\\bf S} ) \\leq {\\mathbb H}({\\bf W}) + 1 + (1+\\log \\frac{1}{\\delta}) {\\mathbb E} |{\\bf S}|.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> </li>\n  </ul> \n </blockquote> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> <em>Proof:</em> To prove (i), it suffices by Lemma <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11852#spread\">10</a>(i) to show that <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+W%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf W}}\" title=\"{{\\bf W}}\" class=\"latex\" /> is <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B%5Cdelta%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\frac{1}{\\delta}}\" title=\"{\\frac{1}{\\delta}}\" class=\"latex\" />-spread, which amounts to showing that </p>\n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cbinom%7B%7CX+%5Cbackslash+S%7C%7D%7B%5Cdelta%7CX%7C+-+%7CS%7C%7D+%5Cleq+%5Cdelta%5E%7B%7CS%7C%7D+%5Cbinom%7B%7CX%7C%7D%7B%5Cdelta+%7CX%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\binom{|X \\backslash S|}{\\delta|X| - |S|} \\leq \\delta^{|S|} \\binom{|X|}{\\delta |X|}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\binom{|X \\backslash S|}{\\delta|X| - |S|} \\leq \\delta^{|S|} \\binom{|X|}{\\delta |X|}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> for all subsets \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BS+%5Csubset+X%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{S \\subset X}\" title=\"{S \\subset X}\" class=\"latex\" /> with \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B0+%5Cleq+%7CS%7C+%5Cleq+%5Cdelta+%7CX%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{0 \\leq |S| \\leq \\delta |X|}\" title=\"{0 \\leq |S| \\leq \\delta |X|}\" class=\"latex\" />. But this comes from multiplying together the inequalities \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cfrac%7B%5Cdelta+%7CX%7C-i%7D%7B%7CX%7C-i%7D+%5Cleq+%5Cdelta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\frac{\\delta |X|-i}{|X|-i} \\leq \\delta}\" title=\"{\\frac{\\delta |X|-i}{|X|-i} \\leq \\delta}\" class=\"latex\" /> for \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B0+%5Cleq+i+%3C+%7CS%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{0 \\leq i < |S|}\" title=\"{0 \\leq i < |S|}\" class=\"latex\" />. \n<p> For (ii), by replacing <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+S%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf S}}\" title=\"{{\\bf S}}\" class=\"latex\" /> with <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+S%7D+%5Cbackslash+%7B%5Cbf+W%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf S} \\backslash {\\bf W}}\" title=\"{{\\bf S} \\backslash {\\bf W}}\" class=\"latex\" /> we may assume that <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+S%7D%2C+%7B%5Cbf+W%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf S}, {\\bf W}}\" title=\"{{\\bf S}, {\\bf W}}\" class=\"latex\" /> are disjoint. From Lemma <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11852#basic\">8</a>(iii) and Lemma <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11852#small\">9</a>(ii) it suffices to show that </p>\n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+W%7D+%5Ccup+%7B%5Cbf+S%7D+%7C+%7C%7B%5Cbf+S%7D%7C+%29+%5Cleq+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+W%7D%29+%2B+%5Clog+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B%5Cdelta%7D+%7B%5Cmathbb+E%7D+%7C%7B%5Cbf+S%7D%7C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb H}({\\bf W} \\cup {\\bf S} | |{\\bf S}| ) \\leq {\\mathbb H}({\\bf W}) + \\log \\frac{1}{\\delta} {\\mathbb E} |{\\bf S}|\" title=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb H}({\\bf W} \\cup {\\bf S} | |{\\bf S}| ) \\leq {\\mathbb H}({\\bf W}) + \\log \\frac{1}{\\delta} {\\mathbb E} |{\\bf S}|\" class=\"latex\" /></p> which in turn is implied by \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+W%7D+%5Ccup+%7B%5Cbf+S%7D+%7C+%7C%7B%5Cbf+S%7D%7C+%3D+k+%29+%5Cleq+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+W%7D%29+%2B+%5Clog+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B%5Cdelta%7D+k&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb H}({\\bf W} \\cup {\\bf S} | |{\\bf S}| = k ) \\leq {\\mathbb H}({\\bf W}) + \\log \\frac{1}{\\delta} k\" title=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb H}({\\bf W} \\cup {\\bf S} | |{\\bf S}| = k ) \\leq {\\mathbb H}({\\bf W}) + \\log \\frac{1}{\\delta} k\" class=\"latex\" /></p> for each \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B0+%5Cleq+k+%5Cleq+%7CX%7C+-+%5Cdelta+%7CX%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{0 \\leq k \\leq |X| - \\delta |X|}\" title=\"{0 \\leq k \\leq |X| - \\delta |X|}\" class=\"latex\" />. By Lemma \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11852#basic\">8</a>(iv) it suffices to show that \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cbinom%7B%7CX%7C%7D%7B%5Cdelta+%7CX%7C%2Bk%7D+%5Cleq+%5Cdelta%5E%7B-k%7D+%5Cbinom%7B%7CX%7C%7D%7B%5Cdelta+%7CX%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\binom{|X|}{\\delta |X|+k} \\leq \\delta^{-k} \\binom{|X|}{\\delta |X|}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\binom{|X|}{\\delta |X|+k} \\leq \\delta^{-k} \\binom{|X|}{\\delta |X|}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> but this follows from multiplying together the inequalities \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cfrac%7BX%2Bi%7D%7B%5Cdelta+%7CX%7C%2Bi%7D%5Cleq+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B%5Cdelta%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\frac{X+i}{\\delta |X|+i}\\leq \\frac{1}{\\delta}}\" title=\"{\\frac{X+i}{\\delta |X|+i}\\leq \\frac{1}{\\delta}}\" class=\"latex\" /> for \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B1+%5Cleq+i+%5Cleq+k%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{1 \\leq i \\leq k}\" title=\"{1 \\leq i \\leq k}\" class=\"latex\" />. \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5CBox&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\Box\" title=\"\\Box\" class=\"latex\" /> \n<p> The following “relative product” construction will be important for us. Given a random variable <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf X}}\" title=\"{{\\bf X}}\" class=\"latex\" /> and a deterministic function <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{f({\\bf X})}\" title=\"{f({\\bf X})}\" class=\"latex\" /> of that variable, one can construct a conditionally independent copy <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf X}'}\" title=\"{{\\bf X}'}\" class=\"latex\" /> of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf X}}\" title=\"{{\\bf X}}\" class=\"latex\" /> subject to the condition <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%29%3Df%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%27%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{f({\\bf X})=f({\\bf X}')}\" title=\"{f({\\bf X})=f({\\bf X}')}\" class=\"latex\" />, with the joint distribution </p>\n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7B%5Cmathbb+P%7D%28+%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%2C+%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%27%29+%3D+%28X%2CX%27%29+%29+%3D+1_%7Bf%28X%29%3Df%28X%27%29%7D+%7B%5Cmathbb+P%7D%28+f%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%29+%3D+f%28X%29+%29+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb P}( ({\\bf X}, {\\bf X}') = (X,X') ) = 1_{f(X)=f(X')} {\\mathbb P}( f({\\bf X}) = f(X) ) \" title=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb P}( ({\\bf X}, {\\bf X}') = (X,X') ) = 1_{f(X)=f(X')} {\\mathbb P}( f({\\bf X}) = f(X) ) \" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle+%7B%5Cmathbb+P%7D%28+%7B%5Cbf+X%7D+%3D+X+%7C+f%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%29+%3D+f%28X%29+%29+%7B%5Cmathbb+P%7D%28+%7B%5Cbf+X%7D+%3D+X%27+%7C+f%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%29+%3D+f%28X%29+%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle {\\mathbb P}( {\\bf X} = X | f({\\bf X}) = f(X) ) {\\mathbb P}( {\\bf X} = X' | f({\\bf X}) = f(X) ).\" title=\"\\displaystyle {\\mathbb P}( {\\bf X} = X | f({\\bf X}) = f(X) ) {\\mathbb P}( {\\bf X} = X' | f({\\bf X}) = f(X) ).\" class=\"latex\" /></p> Note that this is usually \n<em>not</em> the same as starting with a completely independent copy \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf X}'}\" title=\"{{\\bf X}'}\" class=\"latex\" /> of \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf X}}\" title=\"{{\\bf X}}\" class=\"latex\" /> and then conditioning to the event \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%29+%3D+f%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%27%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{f({\\bf X}) = f({\\bf X}')}\" title=\"{f({\\bf X}) = f({\\bf X}')}\" class=\"latex\" />, which has the slightly different distribution \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7B%5Cmathbb+P%7D%28+%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%2C+%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%27%29+%3D+%28X%2CX%27%29+%29+%3D+1_%7Bf%28X%29%3Df%28X%27%29%7D+%7B%5Cmathbb+P%7D%28+%7B%5Cbf+X%7D+%3D+X+%29+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb P}( ({\\bf X}, {\\bf X}') = (X,X') ) = 1_{f(X)=f(X')} {\\mathbb P}( {\\bf X} = X ) \" title=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb P}( ({\\bf X}, {\\bf X}') = (X,X') ) = 1_{f(X)=f(X')} {\\mathbb P}( {\\bf X} = X ) \" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle+%7B%5Cmathbb+P%7D%28+%7B%5Cbf+X%7D+%3D+X%27+%29+%2F+%5Csum_%7BY%2CY%27%3A+f%28Y%29%3Df%28Y%27%29%7D+%7B%5Cmathbb+P%7D%28+%7B%5Cbf+X%7D+%3D+Y+%29+%7B%5Cmathbb+P%7D%28+%7B%5Cbf+X%7D+%3D+Y%27+%29%3B&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle {\\mathbb P}( {\\bf X} = X' ) / \\sum_{Y,Y': f(Y)=f(Y')} {\\mathbb P}( {\\bf X} = Y ) {\\mathbb P}( {\\bf X} = Y' );\" title=\"\\displaystyle {\\mathbb P}( {\\bf X} = X' ) / \\sum_{Y,Y': f(Y)=f(Y')} {\\mathbb P}( {\\bf X} = Y ) {\\mathbb P}( {\\bf X} = Y' );\" class=\"latex\" /></p> cf. \n<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Simpson%27s_paradox\">Simpson’s paradox</a>. By construction, \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf X}'}\" title=\"{{\\bf X}'}\" class=\"latex\" /> has the same distribution as \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf X}}\" title=\"{{\\bf X}}\" class=\"latex\" />, and is conditionally independent of \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf X}}\" title=\"{{\\bf X}}\" class=\"latex\" /> relative to \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf X}'}\" title=\"{{\\bf X}'}\" class=\"latex\" />. In particular, from Lemma \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11852#basic\">8</a> we have \n<a name=\"hxx\"><p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28+%7B%5Cbf+X%7D+%7C+%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%27+%29+%3D+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28+%7B%5Cbf+X%7D+%7C+f%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%29+%29+%3D+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%29+-+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28f%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%29%29+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%287%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb H}( {\\bf X} | {\\bf X}' ) = {\\mathbb H}( {\\bf X} | f({\\bf X}) ) = {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}) - {\\mathbb H}(f({\\bf X})) \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (7)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb H}( {\\bf X} | {\\bf X}' ) = {\\mathbb H}( {\\bf X} | f({\\bf X}) ) = {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}) - {\\mathbb H}(f({\\bf X})) \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (7)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> </a> which we can also write as a “entropy Cauchy-Schwarz identity” \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%2C+%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%27+%29+%3D+2+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%29+-+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28f%28%7B%5Cbf+X%7D%29%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}, {\\bf X}' ) = 2 {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}) - {\\mathbb H}(f({\\bf X})).\" title=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}, {\\bf X}' ) = 2 {\\mathbb H}({\\bf X}) - {\\mathbb H}(f({\\bf X})).\" class=\"latex\" /></p> This can be compared with the combinatorial inequality \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5C%7B+%28x%2Cx%27%29+%5Cin+X%5E2%3A+f%28x%29%3Df%28x%27%29+%5C%7D%7C+%5Cgeq+%5Cfrac%7B%7CX%7C%5E2%7D%7B%7Cf%28X%29%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  |\\{ (x,x') \\in X^2: f(x)=f(x') \\}| \\geq \\frac{|X|^2}{|f(X)|}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  |\\{ (x,x') \\in X^2: f(x)=f(x') \\}| \\geq \\frac{|X|^2}{|f(X)|}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> or equivalently \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clog+%7C%5C%7B+%28x%2Cx%27%29+%5Cin+X%5E2%3A+f%28x%29%3Df%28x%27%29+%5C%7D%7C+%5Cgeq+2+%5Clog+%7CX%7C+-+%5Clog+%7Cf%28X%29%7C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\log |\\{ (x,x') \\in X^2: f(x)=f(x') \\}| \\geq 2 \\log |X| - \\log |f(X)|\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\log |\\{ (x,x') \\in X^2: f(x)=f(x') \\}| \\geq 2 \\log |X| - \\log |f(X)|\" class=\"latex\" /></p> whenever \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%3A+X+%5Crightarrow+Y%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{f: X \\rightarrow Y}\" title=\"{f: X \\rightarrow Y}\" class=\"latex\" /> is a function on a non-empty finite set \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BX%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{X}\" title=\"{X}\" class=\"latex\" />, which is easily proven as a consequence of Cauchy-Schwarz. One nice advantage of the entropy formalism over the combinatorial one is that the analogue of this instance of the Cauchy-Schwarz inequality automatically becomes an equality (this is related to the \n<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Asymptotic_equipartition_property\">asymptotic equipartition property</a> in the microstates interpretation of entropy). \n<p> </p>\n<p align=\"center\"><b> — 2. Proof of refinement inequality — </b></p> \n<p> Now we have enough tools to prove Proposition <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11852#Refinement\">6</a>. Let <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BR%2C+%5Cdelta%2C+%7B%5Cbf+A%7D%2C+%7B%5Cbf+V%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{R, \\delta, {\\bf A}, {\\bf V}}\" title=\"{R, \\delta, {\\bf A}, {\\bf V}}\" class=\"latex\" /> be as in that proposition. On the event when <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+A%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf A}}\" title=\"{{\\bf A}}\" class=\"latex\" /> is empty we can set <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+A%7D%27+%3D+%7B%5Cbf+A%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf A}' = {\\bf A}}\" title=\"{{\\bf A}' = {\\bf A}}\" class=\"latex\" /> so we can instead condition to the event that <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+A%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf A}}\" title=\"{{\\bf A}}\" class=\"latex\" /> is non-empty. In particular <a name=\"eba\"><p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7B%5Cmathbb+E%7D+%7C%7B%5Cbf+A%7D%7C+%5Cgeq+1.+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%288%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb E} |{\\bf A}| \\geq 1. \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (8)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb E} |{\\bf A}| \\geq 1. \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (8)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> </a> </p>\n<p> In order to use Lemma <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11852#spread\">10</a> we fix an empirical sequence <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BA_1%2CA_2%2C%5Cdots%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{A_1,A_2,\\dots}\" title=\"{A_1,A_2,\\dots}\" class=\"latex\" /> for <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+A%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf A}}\" title=\"{{\\bf A}}\" class=\"latex\" />. We relabel <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BX%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{X}\" title=\"{X}\" class=\"latex\" /> as <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5C%7B1%2C%5Cdots%2C%7CX%7C%5C%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\{1,\\dots,|X|\\}}\" title=\"{\\{1,\\dots,|X|\\}}\" class=\"latex\" />, and let <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN+%5Cgeq+%7CX%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{N \\geq |X|}\" title=\"{N \\geq |X|}\" class=\"latex\" /> be a parameter going off to infinity (so in particular <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BX%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{X}\" title=\"{X}\" class=\"latex\" /> is identified with a subset of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5C%7B1%2C%5Cdots%2CN%5C%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\{1,\\dots,N\\}}\" title=\"{\\{1,\\dots,N\\}}\" class=\"latex\" />. We let <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf n}}\" title=\"{{\\bf n}}\" class=\"latex\" /> be drawn uniformly at random from <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5C%7B1%2C%5Cdots%2CN%5C%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\{1,\\dots,N\\}}\" title=\"{\\{1,\\dots,N\\}}\" class=\"latex\" />, and let <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+W%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf W}}\" title=\"{{\\bf W}}\" class=\"latex\" /> be a uniform random subset of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5C%7B1%2C%5Cdots%2CN%5C%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\{1,\\dots,N\\}}\" title=\"{\\{1,\\dots,N\\}}\" class=\"latex\" /> of density <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Clfloor+%5Cdelta+N%5Crfloor%2FN+%3D+%5Cdelta+%2B+o%281%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\lfloor \\delta N\\rfloor/N = \\delta + o(1)}\" title=\"{\\lfloor \\delta N\\rfloor/N = \\delta + o(1)}\" class=\"latex\" /> independent of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf n}}\" title=\"{{\\bf n}}\" class=\"latex\" />. Observe from Stirling’s formula that <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+W%7D+%5Ccap+X%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf W} \\cap X}\" title=\"{{\\bf W} \\cap X}\" class=\"latex\" /> converges in distribution to <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+V%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf V}}\" title=\"{{\\bf V}}\" class=\"latex\" />. Thus it will suffice to find another uniform random variable <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf n}'}\" title=\"{{\\bf n}'}\" class=\"latex\" /> from <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5C%7B1%2C%5Cdots%2CN%5C%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\{1,\\dots,N\\}}\" title=\"{\\{1,\\dots,N\\}}\" class=\"latex\" /> such that <a name=\"gain\"><p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7B%5Cmathbb+E%7D+%7CA_%7B%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%27%7D+%5Cbackslash+%7B%5Cbf+W%7D%7C+%5Cleq+%5Cfrac%7B5%7D%7B%5Clog%28R%5Cdelta%29%7D+%7B%5Cmathbb+E%7D+%7CA_%7B%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%7D%7C+%2B+o%281%29+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%289%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb E} |A_{{\\bf n}'} \\backslash {\\bf W}| \\leq \\frac{5}{\\log(R\\delta)} {\\mathbb E} |A_{{\\bf n}}| + o(1) \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (9)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb E} |A_{{\\bf n}'} \\backslash {\\bf W}| \\leq \\frac{5}{\\log(R\\delta)} {\\mathbb E} |A_{{\\bf n}}| + o(1) \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (9)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> </a> as <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN+%5Crightarrow+%5Cinfty%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{N \\rightarrow \\infty}\" title=\"{N \\rightarrow \\infty}\" class=\"latex\" />, since we can pass to a subsequence in which <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%28A_%7B%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%27%7D%2C+%7B%5Cbf+W%7D+%5Ccap+X%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{(A_{{\\bf n}'}, {\\bf W} \\cap X)}\" title=\"{(A_{{\\bf n}'}, {\\bf W} \\cap X)}\" class=\"latex\" /> converges in distribution to <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%28%7B%5Cbf+A%7D%2C+%7B%5Cbf+V%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{({\\bf A}, {\\bf V})}\" title=\"{({\\bf A}, {\\bf V})}\" class=\"latex\" />. From <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11852#eba\">(8)</a> we have <a name=\"eba-2\"><p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7B%5Cmathbb+E%7D+%7CA_%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%7C+%5Cgeq+1+-+o%281%29.+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2810%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb E} |A_{\\bf n}| \\geq 1 - o(1). \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (10)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb E} |A_{\\bf n}| \\geq 1 - o(1). \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (10)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> </a> </p>\n<p> From <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%2C+%7B%5Cbf+W%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf n}, {\\bf W}}\" title=\"{{\\bf n}, {\\bf W}}\" class=\"latex\" /> we can form the random set <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BA_%7B%5Cbf+n%7D+%5Ccup+%7B%5Cbf+W%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{A_{\\bf n} \\cup {\\bf W}}\" title=\"{A_{\\bf n} \\cup {\\bf W}}\" class=\"latex\" />; we then form a conditionally independent copy <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%28%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%27%2C+%7B%5Cbf+W%7D%27%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{({\\bf n}', {\\bf W}')}\" title=\"{({\\bf n}', {\\bf W}')}\" class=\"latex\" /> of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%28%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%2C+%7B%5Cbf+W%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{({\\bf n}, {\\bf W})}\" title=\"{({\\bf n}, {\\bf W})}\" class=\"latex\" /> subject to the constraint <a name=\"aw\"><p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++A_%7B%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%7D+%5Ccup+%7B%5Cbf+W%7D+%3D+A_%7B%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%27%7D+%5Ccup+%7B%5Cbf+W%7D%27.+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2811%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  A_{{\\bf n}} \\cup {\\bf W} = A_{{\\bf n}'} \\cup {\\bf W}'. \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (11)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  A_{{\\bf n}} \\cup {\\bf W} = A_{{\\bf n}'} \\cup {\\bf W}'. \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (11)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> </a> We use <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf n}'}\" title=\"{{\\bf n}'}\" class=\"latex\" /> as the uniform variable to establish <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11852#gain\">(9)</a>. The point is that the relation <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11852#aw\">(11)</a> implies that </p>\n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++A_%7B%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%27%7D+%5Cbackslash+%7B%5Cbf+W%7D+%5Csubset+A_%7B%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%7D+%5Ccap+A_%7B%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  A_{{\\bf n}'} \\backslash {\\bf W} \\subset A_{{\\bf n}} \\cap A_{{\\bf n}'}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  A_{{\\bf n}'} \\backslash {\\bf W} \\subset A_{{\\bf n}} \\cap A_{{\\bf n}'}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> so it will suffice to show that \n<a name=\"gain-2\"><p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7B%5Cmathbb+E%7D+%7CA_%7B%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%7D+%5Ccap+A_%7B%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%27%7D%7C+%5Cleq+%5Cfrac%7B5%7D%7B%5Clog%28R%5Cdelta%29%7D+%7B%5Cmathbb+E%7D+%7CA_%7B%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%7D%7C+%2B+o%281%29+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2812%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb E} |A_{{\\bf n}} \\cap A_{{\\bf n}'}| \\leq \\frac{5}{\\log(R\\delta)} {\\mathbb E} |A_{{\\bf n}}| + o(1) \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (12)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb E} |A_{{\\bf n}} \\cap A_{{\\bf n}'}| \\leq \\frac{5}{\\log(R\\delta)} {\\mathbb E} |A_{{\\bf n}}| + o(1) \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (12)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> </a> \n<p> By Lemma <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11852#absorb\">11</a>(ii), <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11852#eba-2\">(10)</a> we have </p>\n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28A_%7B%5Cbf+n%7D+%5Ccup+%7B%5Cbf+W%7D%29+%5Cleq+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+W%7D%29+%2B+%282+%2B+%5Clog+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B%5Cdelta%7D%29+%7B%5Cbf+E%7D+%7CA_%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%7C+%2B+o%281%29%2C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb H}(A_{\\bf n} \\cup {\\bf W}) \\leq {\\mathbb H}({\\bf W}) + (2 + \\log \\frac{1}{\\delta}) {\\bf E} |A_{\\bf n}| + o(1),\" title=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb H}(A_{\\bf n} \\cup {\\bf W}) \\leq {\\mathbb H}({\\bf W}) + (2 + \\log \\frac{1}{\\delta}) {\\bf E} |A_{\\bf n}| + o(1),\" class=\"latex\" /></p> and hence by \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11852#hxx\">(7)</a> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28+%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%2C+%7B%5Cbf+W%7D+%7C+%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%27%2C+%7B%5Cbf+W%7D%27+%29+%5Cgeq+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%2C+%7B%5Cbf+W%7D%29+-+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+W%7D%29+-+%282+%2B+%5Clog+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B%5Cdelta%7D%29+%7B%5Cbf+E%7D+%7CA_%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%7C+-+o%281%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb H}( {\\bf n}, {\\bf W} | {\\bf n}', {\\bf W}' ) \\geq {\\mathbb H}({\\bf n}, {\\bf W}) - {\\mathbb H}({\\bf W}) - (2 + \\log \\frac{1}{\\delta}) {\\bf E} |A_{\\bf n}| - o(1)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb H}( {\\bf n}, {\\bf W} | {\\bf n}', {\\bf W}' ) \\geq {\\mathbb H}({\\bf n}, {\\bf W}) - {\\mathbb H}({\\bf W}) - (2 + \\log \\frac{1}{\\delta}) {\\bf E} |A_{\\bf n}| - o(1)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> and hence by Lemma \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11852#basic\">8</a>(ii) and independence of \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%2C+%7B%5Cbf+W%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf n}, {\\bf W}}\" title=\"{{\\bf n}, {\\bf W}}\" class=\"latex\" /> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%29+%5Cleq+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28+%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%2C+%7B%5Cbf+W%7D+%7C+%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%27%2C+%7B%5Cbf+W%7D+%29+%2B+%282+%2B+%5Clog+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B%5Cdelta%7D%29+%7B%5Cbf+E%7D+%7CA_%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%7C+%2B+o%281%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb H}({\\bf n}) \\leq {\\mathbb H}( {\\bf n}, {\\bf W} | {\\bf n}', {\\bf W} ) + (2 + \\log \\frac{1}{\\delta}) {\\bf E} |A_{\\bf n}| + o(1).\" title=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb H}({\\bf n}) \\leq {\\mathbb H}( {\\bf n}, {\\bf W} | {\\bf n}', {\\bf W} ) + (2 + \\log \\frac{1}{\\delta}) {\\bf E} |A_{\\bf n}| + o(1).\" class=\"latex\" /></p> Now we try to relate the first term on the left-hand side with \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BA_%7B%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%7D+%5Ccap+A_%7B%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%27%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{A_{{\\bf n}} \\cap A_{{\\bf n}'}}\" title=\"{A_{{\\bf n}} \\cap A_{{\\bf n}'}}\" class=\"latex\" />. Note from \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11852#aw\">(11)</a> that we have the identity \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7B%5Cbf+W%7D+%3D+%28A_%7B%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%27%7D+%5Ccup+%7B%5Cbf+W%7D%27%29+%5Cbackslash+%28A_%7B%5Cbf+n%7D+%5Cbackslash+%7B%5Cbf+W%7D%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  {\\bf W} = (A_{{\\bf n}'} \\cup {\\bf W}') \\backslash (A_{\\bf n} \\backslash {\\bf W})\" title=\"\\displaystyle  {\\bf W} = (A_{{\\bf n}'} \\cup {\\bf W}') \\backslash (A_{\\bf n} \\backslash {\\bf W})\" class=\"latex\" /></p> and hence by Lemma \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11852#basic\">8</a>(i) \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28+%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%2C+%7B%5Cbf+W%7D+%7C+%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%27%2C+%7B%5Cbf+W%7D%27+%29+%5Cleq+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28+%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%2C+A_%7B%5Cbf+n%7D+%5Cbackslash+%7B%5Cbf+W%7D+%7C+%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%27%2C+%7B%5Cbf+W%7D%27+%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb H}( {\\bf n}, {\\bf W} | {\\bf n}', {\\bf W}' ) \\leq {\\mathbb H}( {\\bf n}, A_{\\bf n} \\backslash {\\bf W} | {\\bf n}', {\\bf W}' ).\" title=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb H}( {\\bf n}, {\\bf W} | {\\bf n}', {\\bf W}' ) \\leq {\\mathbb H}( {\\bf n}, A_{\\bf n} \\backslash {\\bf W} | {\\bf n}', {\\bf W}' ).\" class=\"latex\" /></p> We estimate the relative entropy of \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%2C+A_%7B%5Cbf+n%7D+%5Cbackslash+%7B%5Cbf+W%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf n}, A_{\\bf n} \\backslash {\\bf W}}\" title=\"{{\\bf n}, A_{\\bf n} \\backslash {\\bf W}}\" class=\"latex\" /> here by selecting first \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BA_%7B%5Cbf+n%7D+%5Ccap+A_%7B%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%27%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{A_{\\bf n} \\cap A_{{\\bf n}'}}\" title=\"{A_{\\bf n} \\cap A_{{\\bf n}'}}\" class=\"latex\" />, then \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf n}}\" title=\"{{\\bf n}}\" class=\"latex\" />, then \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BA_%7B%5Cbf+n%7D+%5Cbackslash+%7B%5Cbf+W%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{A_{\\bf n} \\backslash {\\bf W}}\" title=\"{A_{\\bf n} \\backslash {\\bf W}}\" class=\"latex\" />. More precisely, using the chain rule and monotonicity (Lemma \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11852#basic\">8</a>(i), (iii)) we have \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28+%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%2C+A_%7B%5Cbf+n%7D+%5Cbackslash+%7B%5Cbf+W%7D+%7C+%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%27%2C+%7B%5Cbf+W%7D%27+%29+%5Cleq+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28+A_%7B%5Cbf+n%7D+%5Ccap+A_%7B%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%27%7D+%7C+%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%27%2C+%7B%5Cbf+W%7D%27+%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb H}( {\\bf n}, A_{\\bf n} \\backslash {\\bf W} | {\\bf n}', {\\bf W}' ) \\leq {\\mathbb H}( A_{\\bf n} \\cap A_{{\\bf n}'} | {\\bf n}', {\\bf W}' )\" title=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathbb H}( {\\bf n}, A_{\\bf n} \\backslash {\\bf W} | {\\bf n}', {\\bf W}' ) \\leq {\\mathbb H}( A_{\\bf n} \\cap A_{{\\bf n}'} | {\\bf n}', {\\bf W}' )\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%2B+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28+%7B%5Cbf+n%7D+%7C+A_%7B%5Cbf+n%7D+%5Ccap+A_%7B%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%27%7D%2C+%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%27%2C+%7B%5Cbf+W%7D%27+%29+%2B+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28+A_%7B%5Cbf+n%7D+%5Cbackslash+%7B%5Cbf+W%7D+%7C+%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%2C+A_%7B%5Cbf+n%7D+%5Ccap+A_%7B%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%27%7D%2C+%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%27%2C+%7B%5Cbf+W%7D%27+%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  + {\\mathbb H}( {\\bf n} | A_{\\bf n} \\cap A_{{\\bf n}'}, {\\bf n}', {\\bf W}' ) + {\\mathbb H}( A_{\\bf n} \\backslash {\\bf W} | {\\bf n}, A_{\\bf n} \\cap A_{{\\bf n}'}, {\\bf n}', {\\bf W}' ).\" title=\"\\displaystyle  + {\\mathbb H}( {\\bf n} | A_{\\bf n} \\cap A_{{\\bf n}'}, {\\bf n}', {\\bf W}' ) + {\\mathbb H}( A_{\\bf n} \\backslash {\\bf W} | {\\bf n}, A_{\\bf n} \\cap A_{{\\bf n}'}, {\\bf n}', {\\bf W}' ).\" class=\"latex\" /></p> From Lemma \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11852#small\">9</a>(i) we have \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28+A_%7B%5Cbf+n%7D+%5Ccap+A_%7B%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%27%7D+%7C+%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%27%2C+%7B%5Cbf+W%7D+%29+%5Cleq+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28+A_%7B%5Cbf+n%7D+%5Ccap+A_%7B%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%27%7D+%7C+A_%7B%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%27%7D+%29+%5Cleq+%7B%5Cmathbb+E%7D+%7CA_%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%7C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle {\\mathbb H}( A_{\\bf n} \\cap A_{{\\bf n}'} | {\\bf n}', {\\bf W} ) \\leq {\\mathbb H}( A_{\\bf n} \\cap A_{{\\bf n}'} | A_{{\\bf n}'} ) \\leq {\\mathbb E} |A_{\\bf n}|\" title=\"\\displaystyle {\\mathbb H}( A_{\\bf n} \\cap A_{{\\bf n}'} | {\\bf n}', {\\bf W} ) \\leq {\\mathbb H}( A_{\\bf n} \\cap A_{{\\bf n}'} | A_{{\\bf n}'} ) \\leq {\\mathbb E} |A_{\\bf n}|\" class=\"latex\" /></p> and \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28+A_%7B%5Cbf+n%7D+%5Cbackslash+%7B%5Cbf+W%7D+%7C+%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%2C+A_%7B%5Cbf+n%7D+%5Ccap+A_%7B%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%27%7D%2C+%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%27%2C+%7B%5Cbf+W%7D%27+%29+%5Cleq+%7B%5Cmathbb+H%7D%28+A_%7B%5Cbf+n%7D+%5Cbackslash+%7B%5Cbf+W%7D+%7C+A_%7B%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%7D+%29+%5Cleq+%7B%5Cmathbb+E%7D+%7CA_%7B%5Cbf+n%7D%7C.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\"
