src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN%28x%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{N(x)}\" title=\"{N(x)}\" class=\"latex\" /> (at least if \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cxi%2C+N%28x%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\xi, N(x)}\" title=\"{\\xi, N(x)}\" class=\"latex\" /> have the same sign), where \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Comega_-%2C%5Comega_%2B%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\omega_-,\\omega_+}\" title=\"{\\omega_-,\\omega_+}\" class=\"latex\" /> range over pairs of dyadic intervals that are “close” in the sense that \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7C%5Comega_-%7C%3D%7C%5Comega_%2B%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{|\\omega_-|=|\\omega_+|}\" title=\"{|\\omega_-|=|\\omega_+|}\" class=\"latex\" /> and that \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Comega_-%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\omega_-}\" title=\"{\\omega_-}\" class=\"latex\" /> and \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Comega_%2B%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\omega_+}\" title=\"{\\omega_+}\" class=\"latex\" /> are not adjacent, but their parents are adjacent, and with \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Comega_-%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\omega_-}\" title=\"{\\omega_-}\" class=\"latex\" /> to the left of \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Comega_%2B%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\omega_+}\" title=\"{\\omega_+}\" class=\"latex\" />. (Here it is convenient to work with half-open dyadic intervals \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Bj%2F2%5Ek%2C+%28j%2B1%292%5Ek%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{[j/2^k, (j+1)2^k)}\" title=\"{[j/2^k, (j+1)2^k)}\" class=\"latex\" />, to avoid issues with overlap.) If one ignores the caveats and blindly substitutes in the decomposition \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#decomp\">(13)</a>, the expression in the left of \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#est\">(12)</a> becomes \n<p></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7B%5Comega_-+%5Csim+%5Comega_%2B%7D+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+1_E%28x%29+1_%7B%5Comega_%2B%7D%28N%28x%29%29+1_%7B%5Comega_-%7D%28D%29+f%28x%29%5C+dx.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{\\omega_- \\sim \\omega_+} \\int_{\\bf R} 1_E(x) 1_{\\omega_+}(N(x)) 1_{\\omega_-}(D) f(x)\\ dx.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{\\omega_- \\sim \\omega_+} \\int_{\\bf R} 1_E(x) 1_{\\omega_+}(N(x)) 1_{\\omega_-}(D) f(x)\\ dx.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> To decouple further, we will try to decompose \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B1_%7B%5Comega_-%7D%28D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{1_{\\omega_-}(D)}\" title=\"{1_{\\omega_-}(D)}\" class=\"latex\" /> into “rank one” operators. More precisely, we manipulate \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++1_%7B%5Comega_-%7D%28D%29+f%28x%29+%3D+1_%7B%5Comega_-%7D%28D%29+1_%7B%5Comega_-%7D%28D%29%5E%2A+f%28x%29+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  1_{\\omega_-}(D) f(x) = 1_{\\omega_-}(D) 1_{\\omega_-}(D)^* f(x) \" title=\"\\displaystyle  1_{\\omega_-}(D) f(x) = 1_{\\omega_-}(D) 1_{\\omega_-}(D)^* f(x) \" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%3D+%28f+%2A+%5Cwidetilde%7B1%5E%5Cvee_%7B%5Comega_-%7D%7D%29+%2A+1%5E%5Cvee_%7B%5Comega-%7D%28x%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  = (f * \\widetilde{1^\\vee_{\\omega_-}}) * 1^\\vee_{\\omega-}(x)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  = (f * \\widetilde{1^\\vee_{\\omega_-}}) * 1^\\vee_{\\omega-}(x)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%3D+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%28%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+f%28z%29+%5Coverline%7B1%5E%5Cvee_%7B%5Comega_-%7D%28z-y%29%7D%5C+dz%29+1%5E%5Cvee_%7B%5Comega-%7D%28x-y%29%5C+dy&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  = \\int_{\\bf R} (\\int_{\\bf R} f(z) \\overline{1^\\vee_{\\omega_-}(z-y)}\\ dz) 1^\\vee_{\\omega-}(x-y)\\ dy\" title=\"\\displaystyle  = \\int_{\\bf R} (\\int_{\\bf R} f(z) \\overline{1^\\vee_{\\omega_-}(z-y)}\\ dz) 1^\\vee_{\\omega-}(x-y)\\ dy\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%3D+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Cmathrm%7BTrans%7D_y+1%5E%5Cvee_%7B%5Comega_-%7D+%5Crangle+%5Cmathrm%7BTrans%7D_y+1%5E%5Cvee_%7B%5Comega_-%7D%28x%29%5C+dy&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  = \\int_{\\bf R} \\langle f, \\mathrm{Trans}_y 1^\\vee_{\\omega_-} \\rangle \\mathrm{Trans}_y 1^\\vee_{\\omega_-}(x)\\ dy\" title=\"\\displaystyle  = \\int_{\\bf R} \\langle f, \\mathrm{Trans}_y 1^\\vee_{\\omega_-} \\rangle \\mathrm{Trans}_y 1^\\vee_{\\omega_-}(x)\\ dy\" class=\"latex\" /></p> where we use the notation \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Ctilde+g%28x%29+%3A%3D+%5Coverline%7Bg%28-x%29%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\tilde g(x) := \\overline{g(-x)}}\" title=\"{\\tilde g(x) := \\overline{g(-x)}}\" class=\"latex\" />. It will be convenient to try to discretise this integral average. From the uncertainty principle, modifying \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7By%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{y}\" title=\"{y}\" class=\"latex\" /> by \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BO%281%2F%7C%5Comega_-%7C%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{O(1/|\\omega_-|)}\" title=\"{O(1/|\\omega_-|)}\" class=\"latex\" /> should only modify \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cmathrm%7BTrans%7D_y+1%5E%5Cvee_%7B%5Comega_-%7D%28x%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\mathrm{Trans}_y 1^\\vee_{\\omega_-}(x)}\" title=\"{\\mathrm{Trans}_y 1^\\vee_{\\omega_-}(x)}\" class=\"latex\" /> approximately by a phase, so the integral here is roughly constant at spatial scales \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BO%281%2F%7C%5Comega_-%7C%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{O(1/|\\omega_-|)}\" title=\"{O(1/|\\omega_-|)}\" class=\"latex\" />. So we heuristically have \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++1_%7B%5Comega-%7D%28D%29+f%28x%29+%5Capprox+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B%7C%5Comega_-%7C%7D+%5Csum_%7By+%5Cin+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B%7C%5Comega_-%7C%7D+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Cmathrm%7BTrans%7D_y+1%5E%5Cvee_%7B%5Comega_-%7D+%5Crangle+%5Cmathrm%7BTrans%7D_y+1%5E%5Cvee_%7B%5Comega_-%7D%28x%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  1_{\\omega-}(D) f(x) \\approx \\frac{1}{|\\omega_-|} \\sum_{y \\in \\frac{1}{|\\omega_-|} {\\bf Z}} \\int_{\\bf R} \\langle f, \\mathrm{Trans}_y 1^\\vee_{\\omega_-} \\rangle \\mathrm{Trans}_y 1^\\vee_{\\omega_-}(x).\" title=\"\\displaystyle  1_{\\omega-}(D) f(x) \\approx \\frac{1}{|\\omega_-|} \\sum_{y \\in \\frac{1}{|\\omega_-|} {\\bf Z}} \\int_{\\bf R} \\langle f, \\mathrm{Trans}_y 1^\\vee_{\\omega_-} \\rangle \\mathrm{Trans}_y 1^\\vee_{\\omega_-}(x).\" class=\"latex\" /></p> If we now define a \n<em>tile</em> to be a rectangle \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P}\" title=\"{P}\" class=\"latex\" /> in phase space of the form \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++P+%3D+I_P+%5Ctimes+%5Comega_P&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  P = I_P \\times \\omega_P\" title=\"\\displaystyle  P = I_P \\times \\omega_P\" class=\"latex\" /></p> where \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Comega_P%2C+I_P%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\omega_P, I_P}\" title=\"{\\omega_P, I_P}\" class=\"latex\" /> are dyadic intervals and with unit area \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7CP%7C+%3D+%7CI_P%7C+%7C%5Comega_P%7C+%3D+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{|P| = |I_P| |\\omega_P| = 1}\" title=\"{|P| = |I_P| |\\omega_P| = 1}\" class=\"latex\" />, we see that every \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7By%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{y}\" title=\"{y}\" class=\"latex\" /> in the above sum is associated to a tile \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP_-+%3D+%5By%2Cy%2B%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B%7C%5Comega_-%7C%7D%5D+%5Ctimes+%5Comega_-%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P_- = [y,y+\\frac{1}{|\\omega_-|}] \\times \\omega_-}\" title=\"{P_- = [y,y+\\frac{1}{|\\omega_-|}] \\times \\omega_-}\" class=\"latex\" />. The interval \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Comega_%2B%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\omega_+}\" title=\"{\\omega_+}\" class=\"latex\" /> is then similarly assocated to a nearby tile \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP_%2B+%3D+%5By%2Cy%2B%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B%7C%5Comega_-%7C%7D%5D+%5Ctimes+%5Comega_%2B%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P_+ = [y,y+\\frac{1}{|\\omega_-|}] \\times \\omega_+}\" title=\"{P_+ = [y,y+\\frac{1}{|\\omega_-|}] \\times \\omega_+}\" class=\"latex\" />, and we write \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP_-+%5Csim+P_%2B%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P_- \\sim P_+}\" title=\"{P_- \\sim P_+}\" class=\"latex\" /> to indicate the relationship between the two tiles (they share the same spatial interval \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI_%7BP_-%7D+%3D+I_%7BP_%2B%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{I_{P_-} = I_{P_+}}\" title=\"{I_{P_-} = I_{P_+}}\" class=\"latex\" />, but \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP_%2B%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P_+}\" title=\"{P_+}\" class=\"latex\" /> lies just above \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP_-%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P_-}\" title=\"{P_-}\" class=\"latex\" />). We can then approximately write the left-hand side of \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#est\">(12)</a> as \n<a name=\"analog\"><p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7BP_-+%5Csim+P_%2B%7D+%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Cvarphi_%7BP_-%7D+%5Crangle+%5Clangle+%5Cvarphi_%7BP_-%7D+1_%7B%5Comega_%7BP_%2B%7D%7D%28N%29%2C+1_E+%5Crangle+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2814%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{P_- \\sim P_+} \\langle f, \\varphi_{P_-} \\rangle \\langle \\varphi_{P_-} 1_{\\omega_{P_+}}(N), 1_E \\rangle \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (14)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{P_- \\sim P_+} \\langle f, \\varphi_{P_-} \\rangle \\langle \\varphi_{P_-} 1_{\\omega_{P_+}}(N), 1_E \\rangle \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (14)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> </a> where \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cvarphi_%7BP_-%7D%28x%29+%3A%3D+%7CI_%7BP_-%7D%7C%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+1%5E%5Cvee_%7B%5Comega_%7BP_-%7D%7D%28x+-+y%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\varphi_{P_-}(x) := |I_{P_-}|^{1/2} 1^\\vee_{\\omega_{P_-}}(x - y)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\varphi_{P_-}(x) := |I_{P_-}|^{1/2} 1^\\vee_{\\omega_{P_-}}(x - y)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> is an \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BL%5E2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{L^2}\" title=\"{L^2}\" class=\"latex\" />-normalised “wave packet” that is roughly localised to \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP_-%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P_-}\" title=\"{P_-}\" class=\"latex\" /> in phase space. This approximate form of \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#est\">(12)</a> has achieved the goal of decoupling the function \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{f}\" title=\"{f}\" class=\"latex\" /> from the data \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BE%2CN%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{E,N}\" title=\"{E,N}\" class=\"latex\" />, as they both now interact with the tile pair \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP_-%2C+P_%2B%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P_-, P_+}\" title=\"{P_-, P_+}\" class=\"latex\" /> rather than through each other. Note also that the set of tiles \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P}\" title=\"{P}\" class=\"latex\" /> obeys an approximate version of the three symmetries that \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#est\">(12)</a> does. Firstly, the set of tiles is invariant under dilations \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%28x%2C%5Cxi%29+%5Cmapsto+%28%5Clambda+x%2C+%5Clambda%5E%7B-1%7D+%5Cxi%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{(x,\\xi) \\mapsto (\\lambda x, \\lambda^{-1} \\xi)}\" title=\"{(x,\\xi) \\mapsto (\\lambda x, \\lambda^{-1} \\xi)}\" class=\"latex\" /> if \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Clambda%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\lambda}\" title=\"{\\lambda}\" class=\"latex\" /> is a power of two; secondly, once one fixes the scales \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7CI_P%7C%2C+%7C%5Comega_P%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{|I_P|, |\\omega_P|}\" title=\"{|I_P|, |\\omega_P|}\" class=\"latex\" /> of the tiles, the remaining set of tiles is invariant under spatial translations by integer multiples of the spatial scale \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7CI_P%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{|I_P|}\" title=\"{|I_P|}\" class=\"latex\" />, and under frequency translations by integer multiples of \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7C%5Comega_P%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{|\\omega_P|}\" title=\"{|\\omega_P|}\" class=\"latex\" />. (We will need the discrete and nested nature of the tiles \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P}\" title=\"{P}\" class=\"latex\" /> for some subsequent combinatorial arguments, and it turns out to be worthwhile to accept a slightly degraded form of the three basic symmetries of the problem in return for such a discretisation.) \n<p> We now make the above heuristic decomposition rigorous. For any dyadic interval <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Comega+%3D+%5B%5Cinf+%5Comega%2C+%5Cinf+%5Comega+%2B+%7C%5Comega%7C%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\omega = [\\inf \\omega, \\inf \\omega + |\\omega|)}\" title=\"{\\omega = [\\inf \\omega, \\inf \\omega + |\\omega|)}\" class=\"latex\" />, let <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Comega_-+%3A%3D+%5B%5Cinf+%5Comega%2C+%5Cinf+%5Comega+%2B+%7C%5Comega%7C%2F2%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\omega_- := [\\inf \\omega, \\inf \\omega + |\\omega|/2)}\" title=\"{\\omega_- := [\\inf \\omega, \\inf \\omega + |\\omega|/2)}\" class=\"latex\" /> denote the left child interval, and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Comega_%2B+%3A%3D+%5B%5Cinf+%5Comega+%2B+%7C%5Comega%7C%2F2%2C+%5Cinf+%5Comega+%2B+%7C%5Comega%7C%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\omega_+ := [\\inf \\omega + |\\omega|/2, \\inf \\omega + |\\omega|)}\" title=\"{\\omega_+ := [\\inf \\omega + |\\omega|/2, \\inf \\omega + |\\omega|)}\" class=\"latex\" /> the right child interval. We fix a bump function <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Ceta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\eta}\" title=\"{\\eta}\" class=\"latex\" /> supported on <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5B0.1%2C+0.2%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{[0.1, 0.2]}\" title=\"{[0.1, 0.2]}\" class=\"latex\" /> normalised to have <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BL%5E2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{L^2}\" title=\"{L^2}\" class=\"latex\" /> norm <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{1}\" title=\"{1}\" class=\"latex\" />; henceforth we permit all implied constants in the asymptotic notation to depend on <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Ceta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\eta}\" title=\"{\\eta}\" class=\"latex\" />. For each interval <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Comega%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\omega}\" title=\"{\\omega}\" class=\"latex\" /> let <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Ceta_%5Comega%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\eta_\\omega}\" title=\"{\\eta_\\omega}\" class=\"latex\" /> denote the rescaled function </p>\n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Ceta_%5Comega%28%5Cxi%29+%3A%3D+%5Ceta%28+%5Cfrac%7B%5Cxi+-+%5Cinf+%5Comega%7D%7B%7C%5Comega%7C%7D+%29%2C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\eta_\\omega(\\xi) := \\eta( \\frac{\\xi - \\inf \\omega}{|\\omega|} ),\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\eta_\\omega(\\xi) := \\eta( \\frac{\\xi - \\inf \\omega}{|\\omega|} ),\" class=\"latex\" /></p> noting that this is a bump function supported on \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Comega_-%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\omega_-}\" title=\"{\\omega_-}\" class=\"latex\" />. We will establish the estimate \n<a name=\"est-o\"><p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7B%5Comega%7D+%7C%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+1_E%28X%29+1_%7B%5Comega_%2B%7D%28N%28X%29%29+%7C%5Ceta_%5Comega%7C%5E2%28D%29+f%5C+dx%7C+%5Clesssim+%5C%7Cf%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D+%7CE%7C%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2815%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{\\omega} |\\int_{\\bf R} 1_E(X) 1_{\\omega_+}(N(X)) |\\eta_\\omega|^2(D) f\\ dx| \\lesssim \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})} |E|^{1/2} \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (15)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{\\omega} |\\int_{\\bf R} 1_E(X) 1_{\\omega_+}(N(X)) |\\eta_\\omega|^2(D) f\\ dx| \\lesssim \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})} |E|^{1/2} \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (15)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> </a> where \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Comega%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\omega}\" title=\"{\\omega}\" class=\"latex\" /> ranges over all dyadic intervals. We assume \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#est-o\">(15)</a> for now and see why it implies \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#est\">(12)</a>. The left-hand side of \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#est-o\">(15)</a> is not quite dilation or frequency modulation invariant, but we can fix this by an averaging argument as follows. Applying the modulation invariance, we see for any \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cxi_0+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\xi_0 \\in {\\bf R}}\" title=\"{\\xi_0 \\in {\\bf R}}\" class=\"latex\" /> that \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7B%5Comega%7D+%7C%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+1_E%28X%29+1_%7B%5Comega_%2B%7D%28N%28X%29%2B%5Cxi_0%29+%7C%5Ceta_%5Comega%7C%5E2%28D%29+%5Cmathrm%7BMod%7D_%7B%5Cxi_0%7D+f%5C+dx%7C+%5Clesssim+%5C%7Cf%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D+%7CE%7C%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%3B&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{\\omega} |\\int_{\\bf R} 1_E(X) 1_{\\omega_+}(N(X)+\\xi_0) |\\eta_\\omega|^2(D) \\mathrm{Mod}_{\\xi_0} f\\ dx| \\lesssim \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})} |E|^{1/2};\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{\\omega} |\\int_{\\bf R} 1_E(X) 1_{\\omega_+}(N(X)+\\xi_0) |\\eta_\\omega|^2(D) \\mathrm{Mod}_{\\xi_0} f\\ dx| \\lesssim \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})} |E|^{1/2};\" class=\"latex\" /></p> since \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle+%7C%5Ceta_%5Comega%7C%5E2%28D%29+%5Cmathrm%7BMod%7D_%7B%5Cxi_0%7D+%3D+%5Cmathrm%7BMod%7D_%7B%5Cxi_0%7D+%7C%5Ceta_%7B%5Comega-%5Cxi_0%7D%7C%5E2%28D%29+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle |\\eta_\\omega|^2(D) \\mathrm{Mod}_{\\xi_0} = \\mathrm{Mod}_{\\xi_0} |\\eta_{\\omega-\\xi_0}|^2(D) \" title=\"\\displaystyle |\\eta_\\omega|^2(D) \\mathrm{Mod}_{\\xi_0} = \\mathrm{Mod}_{\\xi_0} |\\eta_{\\omega-\\xi_0}|^2(D) \" class=\"latex\" /></p> we thus have \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7B%5Comega%7D+%7C%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+1_E%28X%29+1_%7B%5Comega_%2B-%5Cxi_0%7D%28N%28X%29%29+%7C%5Ceta_%7B%5Comega-%5Cxi_0%7D%7C%5E2%28D%29+f%5C+dx%7C+%5Clesssim+%5C%7Cf%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D+%7CE%7C%5E%7B1%2F2%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{\\omega} |\\int_{\\bf R} 1_E(X) 1_{\\omega_+-\\xi_0}(N(X)) |\\eta_{\\omega-\\xi_0}|^2(D) f\\ dx| \\lesssim \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})} |E|^{1/2}.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{\\omega} |\\int_{\\bf R} 1_E(X) 1_{\\omega_+-\\xi_0}(N(X)) |\\eta_{\\omega-\\xi_0}|^2(D) f\\ dx| \\lesssim \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})} |E|^{1/2}.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> We temporarily truncate to a finite range of scales, and use the triangle inequality, to obtain \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bk%3D-K%7D%5EK+%5Csum_%7B%5Comega%3A+%7C%5Comega%7C+%3D+2%5E%7B-k%7D%7D+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+1_E%28X%29+1_%7B%5Comega_%2B-%5Cxi_0%7D%28N%28X%29%29+%7C%5Ceta_%7B%5Comega-%5Cxi_0%7D%7C%5E2%28D%29+f%5C+dx+%5Clesssim+%5C%7Cf%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D+%7CE%7C%5E%7B1%2F2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{k=-K}^K \\sum_{\\omega: |\\omega| = 2^{-k}} \\int_{\\bf R} 1_E(X) 1_{\\omega_+-\\xi_0}(N(X)) |\\eta_{\\omega-\\xi_0}|^2(D) f\\ dx \\lesssim \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})} |E|^{1/2}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{k=-K}^K \\sum_{\\omega: |\\omega| = 2^{-k}} \\int_{\\bf R} 1_E(X) 1_{\\omega_+-\\xi_0}(N(X)) |\\eta_{\\omega-\\xi_0}|^2(D) f\\ dx \\lesssim \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})} |E|^{1/2}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> for any finite \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BK%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{K}\" title=\"{K}\" class=\"latex\" />. For fixed \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bk%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{k}\" title=\"{k}\" class=\"latex\" />, the expression \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7B%5Comega%3A+%7C%5Comega%7C+%3D+2%5E%7B-k%7D%7D+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+1_E%28X%29+1_%7B%5Comega_%2B-%5Cxi_0%7D%28N%28X%29%29+%7C%5Ceta_%7B%5Comega-%5Cxi_0%7D%7C%5E2%28D%29+f%5C+dx&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{\\omega: |\\omega| = 2^{-k}} \\int_{\\bf R} 1_E(X) 1_{\\omega_+-\\xi_0}(N(X)) |\\eta_{\\omega-\\xi_0}|^2(D) f\\ dx\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{\\omega: |\\omega| = 2^{-k}} \\int_{\\bf R} 1_E(X) 1_{\\omega_+-\\xi_0}(N(X)) |\\eta_{\\omega-\\xi_0}|^2(D) f\\ dx\" class=\"latex\" /></p> is periodic in \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cxi_0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\xi_0}\" title=\"{\\xi_0}\" class=\"latex\" /> with period \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B2%5E%7B-k%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{2^{-k}}\" title=\"{2^{-k}}\" class=\"latex\" />, with average equal to \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++2%5Ek+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+1_E%28X%29+1_%7B%5B%5Czeta%2B2%5E%7B-k-1%7D%2C+%5Czeta%2B2%5E%7B-k%7D%5D%7D%28N%28X%29%29+%7C%5Ceta_%7B%5B%5Czeta%2C+%5Czeta%2B2%5E%7B-k%7D%5D%7D%7C%5E2%28D%29+f%5C+dx%5C+d%5Czeta&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  2^k \\int_{\\bf R} \\int_{\\bf R} 1_E(X) 1_{[\\zeta+2^{-k-1}, \\zeta+2^{-k}]}(N(X)) |\\eta_{[\\zeta, \\zeta+2^{-k}]}|^2(D) f\\ dx\\ d\\zeta\" title=\"\\displaystyle  2^k \\int_{\\bf R} \\int_{\\bf R} 1_E(X) 1_{[\\zeta+2^{-k-1}, \\zeta+2^{-k}]}(N(X)) |\\eta_{[\\zeta, \\zeta+2^{-k}]}|^2(D) f\\ dx\\ d\\zeta\" class=\"latex\" /></p> which we can rewrite as \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+1_E%28x%29+%282%5Ek+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+1_%7B%5B%5Czeta%2B2%5E%7B-k-1%7D%2C+%5Czeta%2B2%5E%7B-k%7D%5D%7D%28N%28x%29%29+%7C%5Ceta%282%5Ek%28%5Cxi-%5Czeta%29%29%7C%5E2%5C+d%5Czeta%29+%5Chat+f%28%5Cxi%29+e%5E%7B2%5Cpi+i+x+%5Cxi%7D%5C+d%5Cxi+dx&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\int_{\\bf R} \\int_{\\bf R} 1_E(x) (2^k \\int_{\\bf R} 1_{[\\zeta+2^{-k-1}, \\zeta+2^{-k}]}(N(x)) |\\eta(2^k(\\xi-\\zeta))|^2\\ d\\zeta) \\hat f(\\xi) e^{2\\pi i x \\xi}\\ d\\xi dx\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\int_{\\bf R} \\int_{\\bf R} 1_E(x) (2^k \\int_{\\bf R} 1_{[\\zeta+2^{-k-1}, \\zeta+2^{-k}]}(N(x)) |\\eta(2^k(\\xi-\\zeta))|^2\\ d\\zeta) \\hat f(\\xi) e^{2\\pi i x \\xi}\\ d\\xi dx\" class=\"latex\" /></p> which one can rewrite further (using the change of variables \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Czeta+%3D+N%28x%29+-+2%5E%7B-k%7D+t%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\zeta = N(x) - 2^{-k} t}\" title=\"{\\zeta = N(x) - 2^{-k} t}\" class=\"latex\" />) as \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+1_E%28x%29+%5CPsi%28+2%5Ek+%28N%28x%29-%5Cxi%29+%29+%5Chat+f%28%5Cxi%29+e%5E%7B2%5Cpi+i+x+%5Cxi%7D%5C+d%5Cxi+dx&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\int_{\\bf R} \\int_{\\bf R} 1_E(x) \\Psi( 2^k (N(x)-\\xi) ) \\hat f(\\xi) e^{2\\pi i x \\xi}\\ d\\xi dx\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\int_{\\bf R} \\int_{\\bf R} 1_E(x) \\Psi( 2^k (N(x)-\\xi) ) \\hat f(\\xi) e^{2\\pi i x \\xi}\\ d\\xi dx\" class=\"latex\" /></p> where \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5CPsi%28%5Cxi%29+%3A%3D+%5Cint_%7B1%2F2%7D%5E1+%7C%5Ceta%28+t+-+%5Cxi+%29%7C%5E2%5C+dt.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\Psi(\\xi) := \\int_{1/2}^1 |\\eta( t - \\xi )|^2\\ dt.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\Psi(\\xi) := \\int_{1/2}^1 |\\eta( t - \\xi )|^2\\ dt.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p> Hence if we average over all <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cxi_0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\xi_0}\" title=\"{\\xi_0}\" class=\"latex\" /> in (say) <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5B0%2C2%5EK%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{[0,2^K]}\" title=\"{[0,2^K]}\" class=\"latex\" />, we conclude that </p>\n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bk%3D-K%7D%5EK+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+1_E%28x%29+%5CPsi%28+2%5Ek+%28N%28x%29-%5Cxi%29+%29+%5Chat+f%28%5Cxi%29+e%5E%7B2%5Cpi+i+x+%5Cxi%7D%5C+d%5Cxi+dx+%5Clesssim+%5C%7Cf%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D+%7CE%7C%5E%7B1%2F2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{k=-K}^K \\int_{\\bf R} \\int_{\\bf R} 1_E(x) \\Psi( 2^k (N(x)-\\xi) ) \\hat f(\\xi) e^{2\\pi i x \\xi}\\ d\\xi dx \\lesssim \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})} |E|^{1/2}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{k=-K}^K \\int_{\\bf R} \\int_{\\bf R} 1_E(x) \\Psi( 2^k (N(x)-\\xi) ) \\hat f(\\xi) e^{2\\pi i x \\xi}\\ d\\xi dx \\lesssim \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})} |E|^{1/2}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> and hence on sending \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BK%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{K}\" title=\"{K}\" class=\"latex\" /> to infinity \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bk+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+1_E%28x%29+%5CPsi%28+2%5Ek+%28N%28x%29-%5Cxi%29+%29+%5Chat+f%28%5Cxi%29+e%5E%7B2%5Cpi+i+x+%5Cxi%7D%5C+d%5Cxi+dx+%5Clesssim+%5C%7Cf%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D+%7CE%7C%5E%7B1%2F2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{k \\in {\\bf Z}} \\int_{\\bf R} \\int_{\\bf R} 1_E(x) \\Psi( 2^k (N(x)-\\xi) ) \\hat f(\\xi) e^{2\\pi i x \\xi}\\ d\\xi dx \\lesssim \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})} |E|^{1/2}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{k \\in {\\bf Z}} \\int_{\\bf R} \\int_{\\bf R} 1_E(x) \\Psi( 2^k (N(x)-\\xi) ) \\hat f(\\xi) e^{2\\pi i x \\xi}\\ d\\xi dx \\lesssim \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})} |E|^{1/2}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> Using dilation symmetry, we also see that \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bk+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+1_E%28x%29+%5CPsi%28+%5Clambda+2%5Ek+%28N%28x%29-%5Cxi%29+%29+%5Chat+f%28%5Cxi%29+e%5E%7B2%5Cpi+i+x+%5Cxi%7D%5C+d%5Cxi+dx+%5Clesssim+%5C%7Cf%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D+%7CE%7C%5E%7B1%2F2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{k \\in {\\bf Z}} \\int_{\\bf R} \\int_{\\bf R} 1_E(x) \\Psi( \\lambda 2^k (N(x)-\\xi) ) \\hat f(\\xi) e^{2\\pi i x \\xi}\\ d\\xi dx \\lesssim \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})} |E|^{1/2}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{k \\in {\\bf Z}} \\int_{\\bf R} \\int_{\\bf R} 1_E(x) \\Psi( \\lambda 2^k (N(x)-\\xi) ) \\hat f(\\xi) e^{2\\pi i x \\xi}\\ d\\xi dx \\lesssim \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})} |E|^{1/2}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> for any \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Clambda+%3E+0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\lambda > 0}\" title=\"{\\lambda > 0}\" class=\"latex\" />. Averaging this for \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Clambda+%5Cin+%5B1%2C2%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\lambda \\in [1,2]}\" title=\"{\\lambda \\in [1,2]}\" class=\"latex\" /> with Haar measure \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bd%5Clambda%2F%5Clambda%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{d\\lambda/\\lambda}\" title=\"{d\\lambda/\\lambda}\" class=\"latex\" />, we conclude that \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+1_E%28x%29+%5Csum_%7Bk+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+%5Cint_1%5E2+%5CPsi%28+%5Clambda+2%5Ek+%28N%28x%29-%5Cxi%29+%29+%5Cfrac%7Bd%5Clambda%7D%7B%5Clambda%7D+%5Chat+f%28%5Cxi%29+e%5E%7B2%5Cpi+i+x+%5Cxi%7D%5C+d%5Cxi+dx+%5Clesssim+%5C%7Cf%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D+%7CE%7C%5E%7B1%2F2%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\int_{\\bf R} \\int_{\\bf R} 1_E(x) \\sum_{k \\in {\\bf Z}} \\int_1^2 \\Psi( \\lambda 2^k (N(x)-\\xi) ) \\frac{d\\lambda}{\\lambda} \\hat f(\\xi) e^{2\\pi i x \\xi}\\ d\\xi dx \\lesssim \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})} |E|^{1/2}.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\int_{\\bf R} \\int_{\\bf R} 1_E(x) \\sum_{k \\in {\\bf Z}} \\int_1^2 \\Psi( \\lambda 2^k (N(x)-\\xi) ) \\frac{d\\lambda}{\\lambda} \\hat f(\\xi) e^{2\\pi i x \\xi}\\ d\\xi dx \\lesssim \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})} |E|^{1/2}.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> But as \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5CPsi%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\Psi}\" title=\"{\\Psi}\" class=\"latex\" /> is a bump function supported in \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%280%2C%2B%5Cinfty%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{(0,+\\infty)}\" title=\"{(0,+\\infty)}\" class=\"latex\" />, one has \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle+%5Csum_%7Bk+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+%5Cint_1%5E2+%5CPsi%28+%5Clambda+2%5Ek+%28N%28x%29-%5Cxi%29+%29+%5Cfrac%7Bd%5Clambda%7D%7B%5Clambda%7D+%3D+%5Csum_%7Bk+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+%5Cint_%7B2%5Ek%7D%5E%7B2%5E%7Bk%2B1%7D%7D+%5CPsi%28+%5Clambda+%28N%28x%29-%5Cxi%29+%29+%5Cfrac%7Bd%5Clambda%7D%7B%5Clambda%7D+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle \\sum_{k \\in {\\bf Z}} \\int_1^2 \\Psi( \\lambda 2^k (N(x)-\\xi) ) \\frac{d\\lambda}{\\lambda} = \\sum_{k \\in {\\bf Z}} \\int_{2^k}^{2^{k+1}} \\Psi( \\lambda (N(x)-\\xi) ) \\frac{d\\lambda}{\\lambda} \" title=\"\\displaystyle \\sum_{k \\in {\\bf Z}} \\int_1^2 \\Psi( \\lambda 2^k (N(x)-\\xi) ) \\frac{d\\lambda}{\\lambda} = \\sum_{k \\in {\\bf Z}} \\int_{2^k}^{2^{k+1}} \\Psi( \\lambda (N(x)-\\xi) ) \\frac{d\\lambda}{\\lambda} \" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%3D+1_%7B%5Cxi+%5Cleq+N%28x%29%7D+%5Cint_0%5E%5Cinfty+%5CPsi%28%5Clambda%29+%5Cfrac%7Bd%5Clambda%7D%7B%5Clambda%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  = 1_{\\xi \\leq N(x)} \\int_0^\\infty \\Psi(\\lambda) \\frac{d\\lambda}{\\lambda}.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  = 1_{\\xi \\leq N(x)} \\int_0^\\infty \\Psi(\\lambda) \\frac{d\\lambda}{\\lambda}.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> The quantity \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cint_0%5E%5Cinfty+%5CPsi%28%5Clambda%29+%5Cfrac%7Bd%5Clambda%7D%7B%5Clambda%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\int_0^\\infty \\Psi(\\lambda) \\frac{d\\lambda}{\\lambda}}\" title=\"{\\int_0^\\infty \\Psi(\\lambda) \\frac{d\\lambda}{\\lambda}}\" class=\"latex\" /> is a non-zero constant, hence \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+1_E%28x%29+1_%7B%5Cxi+%5Cleq+N%28x%29%7D+%5Chat+f%28%5Cxi%29+e%5E%7B2%5Cpi+i+x+%5Cxi%7D%5C+d%5Cxi+dx+%5Clesssim+%5C%7Cf%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D+%7CE%7C%5E%7B1%2F2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\int_{\\bf R} \\int_{\\bf R} 1_E(x) 1_{\\xi \\leq N(x)} \\hat f(\\xi) e^{2\\pi i x \\xi}\\ d\\xi dx \\lesssim \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})} |E|^{1/2}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\int_{\\bf R} \\int_{\\bf R} 1_E(x) 1_{\\xi \\leq N(x)} \\hat f(\\xi) e^{2\\pi i x \\xi}\\ d\\xi dx \\lesssim \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})} |E|^{1/2}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> which is \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#est\">(12)</a>. \n<p> It remains to prove <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#est-o\">(15)</a>. As in the heuristic discussion, we approximately decompose the convolution <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7C%5Ceta_%5Comega%7C%5E2%28D%29+f%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{|\\eta_\\omega|^2(D) f}\" title=\"{|\\eta_\\omega|^2(D) f}\" class=\"latex\" /> into a sum over tiles. We have </p>\n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Ceta_%5Comega%7C%5E2%28D%29+f%28x%29+%3D+f+%2A+%5Ctilde+%5Ceta_%5Comega%5E%5Cvee+%2A+%5Ceta_%5Comega%5E%5Cvee%28x%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  |\\eta_\\omega|^2(D) f(x) = f * \\tilde \\eta_\\omega^\\vee * \\eta_\\omega^\\vee(x)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  |\\eta_\\omega|^2(D) f(x) = f * \\tilde \\eta_\\omega^\\vee * \\eta_\\omega^\\vee(x)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%3D+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%28%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+f%28z%29+%5Coverline%7B%5Ceta_%5Comega%5E%5Cvee%7D%28z-y%29%5C+dz%29+%5Ceta_%5Comega%5E%5Cvee%28x-y%29%5C+dy&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  = \\int_{\\bf R} (\\int_{\\bf R} f(z) \\overline{\\eta_\\omega^\\vee}(z-y)\\ dz) \\eta_\\omega^\\vee(x-y)\\ dy\" title=\"\\displaystyle  = \\int_{\\bf R} (\\int_{\\bf R} f(z) \\overline{\\eta_\\omega^\\vee}(z-y)\\ dz) \\eta_\\omega^\\vee(x-y)\\ dy\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<a name=\"jo\"><p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%3D+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Cmathrm%7BTrans%7D_y+%5Ceta_%5Comega%5E%5Cvee+%5Crangle+%5Cmathrm%7BTrans%7D_y+%5Ceta_%5Comega%5E%5Cvee%5C+dy.+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2816%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  = \\int_{\\bf R} \\langle f, \\mathrm{Trans}_y \\eta_\\omega^\\vee \\rangle \\mathrm{Trans}_y \\eta_\\omega^\\vee\\ dy. \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (16)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  = \\int_{\\bf R} \\langle f, \\mathrm{Trans}_y \\eta_\\omega^\\vee \\rangle \\mathrm{Trans}_y \\eta_\\omega^\\vee\\ dy. \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (16)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> </a> Motivated by this, we define as before a \n<em>tile</em> \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P}\" title=\"{P}\" class=\"latex\" /> to be a rectangle \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI_P+%5Ctimes+%5Comega_P%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{I_P \\times \\omega_P}\" title=\"{I_P \\times \\omega_P}\" class=\"latex\" /> with \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI_P%2C+%5Comega_P%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{I_P, \\omega_P}\" title=\"{I_P, \\omega_P}\" class=\"latex\" /> dyadic intervals with \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7CI_P%7C+%7C%5Comega_P%7C+%3D+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{|I_P| |\\omega_P| = 1}\" title=\"{|I_P| |\\omega_P| = 1}\" class=\"latex\" />; we also split each such tile into an upper half \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP_%2B+%3A%3D+I_P+%5Ctimes+%28%5Comega_P%29_%2B%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P_+ := I_P \\times (\\omega_P)_+}\" title=\"{P_+ := I_P \\times (\\omega_P)_+}\" class=\"latex\" /> and a lower half \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP_-+%3A%3D+I_P+%5Ctimes+%28%5Comega_P%29_-%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P_- := I_P \\times (\\omega_P)_-}\" title=\"{P_- := I_P \\times (\\omega_P)_-}\" class=\"latex\" />. We refer to \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7CI_P%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{|I_P|}\" title=\"{|I_P|}\" class=\"latex\" /> as the \n<em>spatial scale</em> of the tile, and the reciprocal \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7C%5Comega_P%7C+%3D+%7CI_P%7C%5E%7B-1%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{|\\omega_P| = |I_P|^{-1}}\" title=\"{|\\omega_P| = |I_P|^{-1}}\" class=\"latex\" /> as the \n<em>frequency scale</em>. For each tile \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P}\" title=\"{P}\" class=\"latex\" /> define the wave packet \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cphi_P+%3A%3D+%7CI_P%7C%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5Cmathrm%7BTrans%7D_%7B%5Cinf+I_P%7D+%5Ceta_%7B%5Comega_P%7D%5E%5Cvee%2C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\phi_P := |I_P|^{1/2} \\mathrm{Trans}_{\\inf I_P} \\eta_{\\omega_P}^\\vee,\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\phi_P := |I_P|^{1/2} \\mathrm{Trans}_{\\inf I_P} \\eta_{\\omega_P}^\\vee,\" class=\"latex\" /></p> which is a Schwartz function with Fourier support in \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%28%5Comega_P%29_-%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{(\\omega_P)_-}\" title=\"{(\\omega_P)_-}\" class=\"latex\" /> (in fact it is supported in \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5B%5Cinf+%5Comega_P+%2B+0.1+%7C%5Comega_P%7C%2C+%5Cinf+%5Comega_P+%2B+0.2+%7C%5Comega_P%7C%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{[\\inf \\omega_P + 0.1 |\\omega_P|, \\inf \\omega_P + 0.2 |\\omega_P|]}\" title=\"{[\\inf \\omega_P + 0.1 |\\omega_P|, \\inf \\omega_P + 0.2 |\\omega_P|]}\" class=\"latex\" />) that is normalised to have \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BL%5E2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{L^2}\" title=\"{L^2}\" class=\"latex\" /> norm \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{1}\" title=\"{1}\" class=\"latex\" /> and is localised spatially near \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI_P%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{I_P}\" title=\"{I_P}\" class=\"latex\" />, so morally it has “phase space support in \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP_-%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P_-}\" title=\"{P_-}\" class=\"latex\" />“. We will later establish the estimate \n<a name=\"est-2\"><p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_P+%7C%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Cphi_P+%5Crangle+%5Clangle+%5Cphi_P+1_%7B%28%5Comega_P%29_%2B%7D%28N%29%2C+1_E+%5Crangle%7C+%5Clesssim+%5C%7Cf%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D+%7CE%7C%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2817%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_P |\\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\langle \\phi_P 1_{(\\omega_P)_+}(N), 1_E \\rangle| \\lesssim \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})} |E|^{1/2} \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (17)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_P |\\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\langle \\phi_P 1_{(\\omega_P)_+}(N), 1_E \\rangle| \\lesssim \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})} |E|^{1/2} \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (17)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> </a> for all \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{f \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R})}\" title=\"{f \\in {\\mathcal S}({\\bf R})}\" class=\"latex\" /> and sets \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BE%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{E}\" title=\"{E}\" class=\"latex\" /> of finite measure (cf. \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#analog\">(14)</a>), where \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P}\" title=\"{P}\" class=\"latex\" /> ranges over the set of all tiles. For now, we show why this estimate implies \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#est-o\">(15)</a> and hence \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#est\">(12)</a>. Just as \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#est\">(12)</a> was obtained from \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#est-o\">(15)</a> by averaging over dilation and frequency modulations, we shall recover \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#est-o\">(15)</a> from \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#est-2\">(17)</a> by averaging over spatial translations. As before, we first temporarily restrict the size range of \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Comega_P%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\omega_P}\" title=\"{\\omega_P}\" class=\"latex\" /> and use the triangle inequality to obtain \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bk%3D-K%7D%5EK+%5Csum_%7B%7C%5Comega%7C+%3D+2%5E%7B-k%7D%7D+%7C%5Csum_%7BP%3A+%5Comega_P+%3D+%5Comega%7D+%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Cphi_P+%5Crangle+%5Clangle+%5Cphi_P+1_%7B%5Comega_%2B%7D%28N%29%2C+1_E+%5Crangle%7C+%5Clesssim+%5C%7Cf%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D+%7CE%7C%5E%7B1%2F2%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{k=-K}^K \\sum_{|\\omega| = 2^{-k}} |\\sum_{P: \\omega_P = \\omega} \\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\langle \\phi_P 1_{\\omega_+}(N), 1_E \\rangle| \\lesssim \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})} |E|^{1/2}.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{k=-K}^K \\sum_{|\\omega| = 2^{-k}} |\\sum_{P: \\omega_P = \\omega} \\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\langle \\phi_P 1_{\\omega_+}(N), 1_E \\rangle| \\lesssim \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})} |E|^{1/2}.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> Applying translation symmetry, we conclude that \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bk%3D-K%7D%5EK+%5Csum_%7B%7C%5Comega%7C+%3D+2%5E%7B-k%7D%7D+%7C%5Csum_%7BP%3A+%5Comega_P+%3D+%5Comega%7D+%5Clangle+%5Cmathrm%7BTrans%7D_%7Bx_0%7D+f%2C+%5Cphi_P+%5Crangle+%5Clangle+%5Cphi_P+1_%7B%5Comega_%2B%7D%28N%28%5Ccdot+-+x_0%29%29%2C+1_%7BE%2Bx_0%7D+%5Crangle%7C+%5Clesssim+%5C%7Cf%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D+%7CE%7C%5E%7B1%2F2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{k=-K}^K \\sum_{|\\omega| = 2^{-k}} |\\sum_{P: \\omega_P = \\omega} \\langle \\mathrm{Trans}_{x_0} f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\langle \\phi_P 1_{\\omega_+}(N(\\cdot - x_0)), 1_{E+x_0} \\rangle| \\lesssim \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})} |E|^{1/2}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{k=-K}^K \\sum_{|\\omega| = 2^{-k}} |\\sum_{P: \\omega_P = \\omega} \\langle \\mathrm{Trans}_{x_0} f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\langle \\phi_P 1_{\\omega_+}(N(\\cdot - x_0)), 1_{E+x_0} \\rangle| \\lesssim \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})} |E|^{1/2}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> for any \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bx_0+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{x_0 \\in {\\bf R}}\" title=\"{x_0 \\in {\\bf R}}\" class=\"latex\" />. The left-hand side may be rewritten as \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bk%3D-K%7D%5EK+%5Csum_%7B%7C%5Comega%7C+%3D+2%5E%7B-k%7D%7D+%7C%5Csum_%7BP%3A+%5Comega_P+%3D+%5Comega%7D+%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Cphi_%7BP%2B%28x_0%2C0%29%7D+%5Crangle+%5Clangle+%5Cphi_%7BP%2B%28x_0%2C0%29%7D+1_%7B%5Comega_%2B%7D%28N%28%5Ccdot%29%29%2C+1_%7BE%7D+%5Crangle%7C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{k=-K}^K \\sum_{|\\omega| = 2^{-k}} |\\sum_{P: \\omega_P = \\omega} \\langle f, \\phi_{P+(x_0,0)} \\rangle \\langle \\phi_{P+(x_0,0)} 1_{\\omega_+}(N(\\cdot)), 1_{E} \\rangle|\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{k=-K}^K \\sum_{|\\omega| = 2^{-k}} |\\sum_{P: \\omega_P = \\omega} \\langle f, \\phi_{P+(x_0,0)} \\rangle \\langle \\phi_{P+(x_0,0)} 1_{\\omega_+}(N(\\cdot)), 1_{E} \\rangle|\" class=\"latex\" /></p> where we extend the definition of \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cphi_P%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\phi_P}\" title=\"{\\phi_P}\" class=\"latex\" /> to translated tiles \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP+%2B+%28x_0%2C0%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P + (x_0,0)}\" title=\"{P + (x_0,0)}\" class=\"latex\" /> in the obvious fashion. The expression inside the absolute values is periodic in \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bx_0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{x_0}\" title=\"{x_0}\" class=\"latex\" /> with period \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B2%5Ek%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{2^k}\" title=\"{2^k}\" class=\"latex\" />, and averages to \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Cmathrm%7BTrans%7D_y+%5Ceta_%5Comega%5E%5Cvee+%5Crangle+%5Clangle+%5Cmathrm%7BTrans%7D_y+%5Ceta_%5Comega%5E%5Cvee+1_%7B%5Comega_%2B%7D%28N%28%5Ccdot%29%29%2C+1_%7BE%7D+%5Crangle%5C+dy+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\int_{\\bf R} \\langle f, \\mathrm{Trans}_y \\eta_\\omega^\\vee \\rangle \\langle \\mathrm{Trans}_y \\eta_\\omega^\\vee 1_{\\omega_+}(N(\\cdot)), 1_{E} \\rangle\\ dy \" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\int_{\\bf R} \\langle f, \\mathrm{Trans}_y \\eta_\\omega^\\vee \\rangle \\langle \\mathrm{Trans}_y \\eta_\\omega^\\vee 1_{\\omega_+}(N(\\cdot)), 1_{E} \\rangle\\ dy \" class=\"latex\" /></p> which by \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#jo\">(16)</a> simplifies to \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clangle+%7C%5Ceta_%5Comega%7C%5E2%28D%29+f+1_%7B%5Comega_%2B%7D%28N%28%5Ccdot%29%29%2C+1_%7BE%7D+%5Crangle&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\langle |\\eta_\\omega|^2(D) f 1_{\\omega_+}(N(\\cdot)), 1_{E} \\rangle\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\langle |\\eta_\\omega|^2(D) f 1_{\\omega_+}(N(\\cdot)), 1_{E} \\rangle\" class=\"latex\" /></p> and so on averaging in \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bx_0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{x_0}\" title=\"{x_0}\" class=\"latex\" /> and then sending \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BK%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{K}\" title=\"{K}\" class=\"latex\" /> to infinity we recover \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#est-o\">(15)</a>. \n<p> It remains to establish <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#est-2\">(17)</a>. It is convenient to introduce the sets </p>\n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++E_P%5E%2B+%3A%3D+%5C%7B+x+%5Cin+E%3A+N%28x%29+%5Cin+%28%5Comega_P%29_%2B+%5C%7D+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  E_P^+ := \\{ x \\in E: N(x) \\in (\\omega_P)_+ \\} \" title=\"\\displaystyle  E_P^+ := \\{ x \\in E: N(x) \\in (\\omega_P)_+ \\} \" class=\"latex\" /></p> so that the target estimate \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#est-2\">(17)</a> simplifies slightly to \n<a name=\"est-tile\"><p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7BP%7D+%7C%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Cphi_P+%5Crangle+%5Clangle+%5Cphi_P%2C+1_%7BE_P%5E%2B%7D+%5Crangle%7C+%5Clesssim+%5C%7Cf%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D+%7CE%7C%5E%7B1%2F2%7D.+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2818%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{P} |\\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\langle \\phi_P, 1_{E_P^+} \\rangle| \\lesssim \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})} |E|^{1/2}. \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (18)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{P} |\\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\langle \\phi_P, 1_{E_P^+} \\rangle| \\lesssim \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})} |E|^{1/2}. \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (18)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> </a> As advertised, we have now decoupled the influences of \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{f}\" title=\"{f}\" class=\"latex\" /> and the influences of \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BE%2CN%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{E,N}\" title=\"{E,N}\" class=\"latex\" /> (which determine the sets \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BE_P%5E%2B%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{E_P^+}\" title=\"{E_P^+}\" class=\"latex\" />), as these quantities now only directly interact with the wave packets \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cphi_P%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\phi_P}\" title=\"{\\phi_P}\" class=\"latex\" />, rather than with each other. Moreover, \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{f}\" title=\"{f}\" class=\"latex\" /> in some sense only interacts with the lower half \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP_-%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P_-}\" title=\"{P_-}\" class=\"latex\" /> of the tile (as this is where \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cphi_P%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\phi_P}\" title=\"{\\phi_P}\" class=\"latex\" /> is concentrated), while \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BE%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{E}\" title=\"{E}\" class=\"latex\" /> and \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{N}\" title=\"{N}\" class=\"latex\" /> only interact with the upper half \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP_%2B%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P_+}\" title=\"{P_+}\" class=\"latex\" /> of the tile. \n<p> One advantage of this “model” formulation of the problem is that one can naturally build up to the full problem by trying to establish estimates of the form <a name=\"est-tile-finite\"></a></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><a name=\"est-tile-finite\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7BP+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%7D+%7C%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Cphi_P+%5Crangle+%5Clangle+%5Cphi_P%2C+1_%7BE_P%5E%2B%7D+%5Crangle%7C+%5Clesssim+%5C%7Cf%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D+%7CE%7C%5E%7B1%2F2%7D.+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2819%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{P \\in {\\mathcal P}} |\\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\langle \\phi_P, 1_{E_P^+} \\rangle| \\lesssim \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})} |E|^{1/2}. \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (19)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{P \\in {\\mathcal P}} |\\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\langle \\phi_P, 1_{E_P^+} \\rangle| \\lesssim \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})} |E|^{1/2}. \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (19)\" class=\"latex\" /></a></p>\n<a name=\"est-tile-finite\"> </a> where \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal P}}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal P}}\" class=\"latex\" /> is some smaller set of tiles. For instance, if we can prove \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#est-tile-finite\">(19)</a> for all finite collections \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal P}}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal P}}\" class=\"latex\" /> of tiles, then by monotone convergence we recover the required estimate. \n<p></p>\n<p> The key problem here is that tiles <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P}\" title=\"{P}\" class=\"latex\" /> have three degrees of freedom: scale, spatial location, and frequency location, corresponding to the three symmetries of dilation, spatial translation, and frequency modulation of the original estimate <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#est\">(12)</a>. But one can warm up by looking at families of tiles that only exhibit two or fewer degrees of freedom, in a way that slowly builds up the various techniques we will need to apply to establish the general case: </p>\n<p> <b>The case of a single tile</b> We begin with the simplest case of a single tile (so that there are zero degrees of freedom): <a name=\"fop\"></a></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><a name=\"fop\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Cphi_P+%5Crangle+%5Clangle+%5Cphi_P%2C+1_%7BE_P%5E%2B%7D+%5Crangle+%5Clesssim+%5C%7Cf%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D+%7CE%7C%5E%7B1%2F2%7D.+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2820%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\langle \\phi_P, 1_{E_P^+} \\rangle \\lesssim \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})} |E|^{1/2}. \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (20)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\langle \\phi_P, 1_{E_P^+} \\rangle \\lesssim \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})} |E|^{1/2}. \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (20)\" class=\"latex\" /></a></p>\n<a name=\"fop\"> </a> On the one hand, \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cphi_P%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\phi_P}\" title=\"{\\phi_P}\" class=\"latex\" /> is normalised in \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BL%5E2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{L^2}\" title=\"{L^2}\" class=\"latex\" />, by Cauchy-Schwarz we have \n<a name=\"cs\"><p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Cphi_P+%5Crangle+%5Clesssim+%5C%7Cf%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D.+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2821%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\lesssim \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})}. \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (21)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\lesssim \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})}. \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (21)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> </a> From the construction of \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cphi_P%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\phi_P}\" title=\"{\\phi_P}\" class=\"latex\" /> we see that we have the pointwise bounds \n<a name=\"phip\"><p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cphi_P%28x%29+%5Clesssim+%7CI_P%7C%5E%7B-1%2F2%7D+%5Cchi%5E%7B100%7D_%7BI_P%7D%28x%29+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2822%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\phi_P(x) \\lesssim |I_P|^{-1/2} \\chi^{100}_{I_P}(x) \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (22)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\phi_P(x) \\lesssim |I_P|^{-1/2} \\chi^{100}_{I_P}(x) \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (22)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> </a> where we use \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cchi_I%28x%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\chi_I(x)}\" title=\"{\\chi_I(x)}\" class=\"latex\" /> to denote the following variant of the indicator function \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B1_I%28x%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{1_I(x)}\" title=\"{1_I(x)}\" class=\"latex\" /> that has a non-trivial tail: \n<p></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cchi_I%28x%29+%3A%3D+%5Clangle+%5Cfrac%7B%5Cmathrm%7Bdist%7D%28x%2CI%29%7D%7B%7CI%7C%7D+%5Crangle%5E%7B-1%7D.+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\chi_I(x) := \\langle \\frac{\\mathrm{dist}(x,I)}{|I|} \\rangle^{-1}. \" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\chi_I(x) := \\langle \\frac{\\mathrm{dist}(x,I)}{|I|} \\rangle^{-1}. \" class=\"latex\" /></p> In particular from Hölder’s inequality we have the bounds \n<a name=\"p0\"><p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clangle+%5Cphi_P%2C+1_%7BE_P%5E%2B%7D+%5Crangle+%5Clesssim+%5C%7C+%5Cphi_P+%5C%7C_%7BL%5E1%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D+%5Clesssim+%7CI_P%7C%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2823%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\langle \\phi_P, 1_{E_P^+} \\rangle \\lesssim \\| \\phi_P \\|_{L^1({\\bf R})} \\lesssim |I_P|^{1/2} \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (23)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\langle \\phi_P, 1_{E_P^+} \\rangle \\lesssim \\| \\phi_P \\|_{L^1({\\bf R})} \\lesssim |I_P|^{1/2} \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (23)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> </a> and also \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clangle+%5Cphi_P%2C+1_%7BE_P%5E%2B%7D+%5Crangle+%5Clesssim+%5C%7C+%5Cphi_P+%5C%7C_%7BL%5E%5Cinfty%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D+%7CE_P%5E%2B%7C+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\langle \\phi_P, 1_{E_P^+} \\rangle \\lesssim \\| \\phi_P \\|_{L^\\infty({\\bf R})} |E_P^+| \" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\langle \\phi_P, 1_{E_P^+} \\rangle \\lesssim \\| \\phi_P \\|_{L^\\infty({\\bf R})} |E_P^+| \" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clesssim+%7CI_P%7C%5E%7B-1%2F2%7D+%7CE%7C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\lesssim |I_P|^{-1/2} |E|\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\lesssim |I_P|^{-1/2} |E|\" class=\"latex\" /></p> thanks to the trivial bound \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7CE_P%5E%2B%7C+%5Cleq+%7CE%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{|E_P^+| \\leq |E|}\" title=\"{|E_P^+| \\leq |E|}\" class=\"latex\" />, so on taking geometric means we have \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clangle+%5Cphi_P%2C+1_%7BE_P%5E%2B%7D+%5Crangle+%5Clesssim+%7CE%7C%5E%7B1%2F2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\langle \\phi_P, 1_{E_P^+} \\rangle \\lesssim |E|^{1/2}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\langle \\phi_P, 1_{E_P^+} \\rangle \\lesssim |E|^{1/2}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> and the claim \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#fop\">(20)</a> follows. \n<p> <b>The case of separated tiles of fixed scale</b> Now we let <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal P}}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal P}}\" class=\"latex\" /> be a collection of tiles all of a fixed spatial scale <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7CI_P%7C+%3D+2%5Ek%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{|I_P| = 2^k}\" title=\"{|I_P| = 2^k}\" class=\"latex\" /> (so that <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7C%5Comega_P%7C+%3D+2%5E%7B-k%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{|\\omega_P| = 2^{-k}}\" title=\"{|\\omega_P| = 2^{-k}}\" class=\"latex\" /> (so that we have the two parameters of spatial and frequency location, but not the scale parameter). Among other things, this makes the tiles <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P}\" title=\"{P}\" class=\"latex\" /> in <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal P}}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal P}}\" class=\"latex\" /> essentially disjoint (i.e., disjoint ignoring sets of measure zero). This disjointness manifests itself in two useful ways. Firstly, we claim that we can improve the trivial bound </p>\n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clangle+%5Cphi_P%2C+1_%7BE_P%5E%2B%7D+%5Crangle+%5Clesssim+%7CI_P%7C%5E%7B-1%2F2%7D+%7CE%7C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\langle \\phi_P, 1_{E_P^+} \\rangle \\lesssim |I_P|^{-1/2} |E|\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\langle \\phi_P, 1_{E_P^+} \\rangle \\lesssim |I_P|^{-1/2} |E|\" class=\"latex\" /></p> obtained previously to the “mass estimate” \n<a name=\"p1\"><p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7BP+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%7D+%7CI_P%7C%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%7C%5Clangle+%5Cphi_P%2C+1_%7BE_P%5E%2B%7D+%5Crangle%7C+%5Clesssim+%7CE%7C%3B+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2824%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{P \\in {\\mathcal P}} |I_P|^{1/2} |\\langle \\phi_P, 1_{E_P^+} \\rangle| \\lesssim |E|; \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (24)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{P \\in {\\mathcal P}} |I_P|^{1/2} |\\langle \\phi_P, 1_{E_P^+} \\rangle| \\lesssim |E|; \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (24)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> </a> secondly, we claim that we can improve the Cauchy-Schwarz bound \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#cs\">(21)</a> to the “energy estimate” \n<a name=\"p2\"><p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7BP+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%7D+%7C%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Cphi_P+%5Crangle%7C%5E2+%5Clesssim+%5C%7Cf%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D%5E2.+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2825%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{P \\in {\\mathcal P}} |\\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle|^2 \\lesssim \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})}^2. \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (25)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{P \\in {\\mathcal P}} |\\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle|^2 \\lesssim \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})}^2. \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (25)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> </a> (Here we informally use “mass” to refer to expressions and estimates of \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BL%5E1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{L^1}\" title=\"{L^1}\" class=\"latex\" /> type involving the set \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BE%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{E}\" title=\"{E}\" class=\"latex\" /> and graph \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{N}\" title=\"{N}\" class=\"latex\" />, and “energy” to refer to expressions and estimates of \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BL%5E2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{L^2}\" title=\"{L^2}\" class=\"latex\" /> type involving the function \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{f}\" title=\"{f}\" class=\"latex\" />.) If we assume \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#p1\">(24)</a>, \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#p2\">(25)</a> for now, then by combining \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#p1\">(24)</a> with \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#p0\">(23)</a> we have \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7BP+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%7D+%7C%5Clangle+%5Cphi_P%2C+1_%7BE_P%5E%2B%7D+%5Crangle%7C%5E2+%5Clesssim+%7CE%7C%2C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{P \\in {\\mathcal P}} |\\langle \\phi_P, 1_{E_P^+} \\rangle|^2 \\lesssim |E|,\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{P \\in {\\mathcal P}} |\\langle \\phi_P, 1_{E_P^+} \\rangle|^2 \\lesssim |E|,\" class=\"latex\" /></p> and then from \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#p2\">(25)</a> and Cauchy-Schwarz we obtain the required bound \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#est-tile-finite\">(19)</a> in this case. \n<p> Now let us see why <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#p1\">(24)</a> is true. To motivate the argument, suppose that <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cphi_P%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\phi_P}\" title=\"{\\phi_P}\" class=\"latex\" /> had no tail outside of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI_P%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{I_P}\" title=\"{I_P}\" class=\"latex\" />, so that one could replace <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cchi_%7BI_P%7D%5E%7B100%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\chi_{I_P}^{100}}\" title=\"{\\chi_{I_P}^{100}}\" class=\"latex\" /> to <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B1_%7BI_P%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{1_{I_P}}\" title=\"{1_{I_P}}\" class=\"latex\" /> in <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#phip\">(22)</a>. Then would have </p>\n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7CI_P%7C%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5Clangle+%5Cphi_P%2C+1_%7BE_P%5E%2B%7D+%5Crangle+%5Clesssim+%7C%5C%7B+x+%5Cin+E%3A+%28x%2CN%28x%29%29+%5Cin+P_%2B+%5C%7D%7C%2C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  |I_P|^{1/2} \\langle \\phi_P, 1_{E_P^+} \\rangle \\lesssim |\\{ x \\in E: (x,N(x)) \\in P_+ \\}|,\" title=\"\\displaystyle  |I_P|^{1/2} \\langle \\phi_P, 1_{E_P^+} \\rangle \\lesssim |\\{ x \\in E: (x,N(x)) \\in P_+ \\}|,\" class=\"latex\" /></p> and as the tiles \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP_%2B%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P_+}\" title=\"{P_+}\" class=\"latex\" /> are all essentially disjoint the claim \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#p1\">(24)</a> would then follow from summing in \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P}\" title=\"{P}\" class=\"latex\" />, since each \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bx+%5Cin+E%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{x \\in E}\" title=\"{x \\in E}\" class=\"latex\" /> contributes to at most one of the sets \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5C%7B+x+%5Cin+E%3A+%28x%2CN%28x%29%29+%5Cin+P_%2B+%5C%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\{ x \\in E: (x,N(x)) \\in P_+ \\}}\" title=\"{\\{ x \\in E: (x,N(x)) \\in P_+ \\}}\" class=\"latex\" />. Now we have to deal with the contribution of the tails. We can bound \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7BP+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%7D+%7CI_P%7C%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%7C%5Clangle+%5Cphi_P%2C+1_%7BE_P%5E%2B%7D+%5Crangle%7C+%5Cleq+%5Cint_E+%7CI_P%7C%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5Csum_%7BP+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%3A+N%28x%29+%5Cin+%28%5Comega_P%29_%2B%7D+%7C%5Cphi_P%28x%29%7C%5C+dx.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{P \\in {\\mathcal P}} |I_P|^{1/2} |\\langle \\phi_P, 1_{E_P^+} \\rangle| \\leq \\int_E |I_P|^{1/2} \\sum_{P \\in {\\mathcal P}: N(x) \\in (\\omega_P)_+} |\\phi_P(x)|\\ dx.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{P \\in {\\mathcal P}} |I_P|^{1/2} |\\langle \\phi_P, 1_{E_P^+} \\rangle| \\leq \\int_E |I_P|^{1/2} \\sum_{P \\in {\\mathcal P}: N(x) \\in (\\omega_P)_+} |\\phi_P(x)|\\ dx.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> For each \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bx+%5Cin+E%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{x \\in E}\" title=\"{x \\in E}\" class=\"latex\" />, there is at most one dyadic interval \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Comega%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\omega}\" title=\"{\\omega}\" class=\"latex\" /> of the fixed length \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B2%5E%7B-k%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{2^{-k}}\" title=\"{2^{-k}}\" class=\"latex\" /> such that \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN%28x%29+%5Cin+%5Comega_%2B%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{N(x) \\in \\omega_+}\" title=\"{N(x) \\in \\omega_+}\" class=\"latex\" />. Thus in the above sum \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Comega_P%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\omega_P}\" title=\"{\\omega_P}\" class=\"latex\" /> is fixed, and only \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI_P%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{I_P}\" title=\"{I_P}\" class=\"latex\" /> can vary; from \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#phip\">(22)</a> we then see that \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7CI_P%7C%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5Csum_%7BP+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%3A+N%28x%29+%5Cin+%28%5Comega_P%29_%2B%7D+%7C%5Cphi_P%28x%29%7C%5C+dx+%5Clesssim+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{|I_P|^{1/2} \\sum_{P \\in {\\mathcal P}: N(x) \\in (\\omega_P)_+} |\\phi_P(x)|\\ dx \\lesssim 1}\" title=\"{|I_P|^{1/2} \\sum_{P \\in {\\mathcal P}: N(x) \\in (\\omega_P)_+} |\\phi_P(x)|\\ dx \\lesssim 1}\" class=\"latex\" />, giving \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#p1\">(24)</a>. \n<p> Now we prove <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#p2\">(25)</a>. The intuition here is that the essential disjointness of the tiles <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P}\" title=\"{P}\" class=\"latex\" /> make the <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cphi_P%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\phi_P}\" title=\"{\\phi_P}\" class=\"latex\" /> approximately orthogonal, so that <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#p2\">(25)</a> should be a variant of Bessel’s inequality. We exploit this approximate orthogonality by a <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BTT%5E%2A%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{TT^*}\" title=\"{TT^*}\" class=\"latex\" /> method, which we perform here explicitly. By duality we have </p>\n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%28%5Csum_%7BP+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%7D+%7C%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Cphi_P+%5Crangle%7C%5E2%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%3D+%5Csum_%7BP+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%7D+%5Coverline%7Bc_P%7D+%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Cphi_P+%5Crangle&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  (\\sum_{P \\in {\\mathcal P}} |\\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle|^2)^{1/2} = \\sum_{P \\in {\\mathcal P}} \\overline{c_P} \\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle\" title=\"\\displaystyle  (\\sum_{P \\in {\\mathcal P}} |\\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle|^2)^{1/2} = \\sum_{P \\in {\\mathcal P}} \\overline{c_P} \\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%3D+%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Csum_%7BP+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%7D+c_P+%5Cphi_P+%5Crangle&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  = \\langle f, \\sum_{P \\in {\\mathcal P}} c_P \\phi_P \\rangle\" title=\"\\displaystyle  = \\langle f, \\sum_{P \\in {\\mathcal P}} c_P \\phi_P \\rangle\" class=\"latex\" /></p> for some coefficients \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bc_P%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{c_P}\" title=\"{c_P}\" class=\"latex\" /> with \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Csum_%7BP+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%7D+%7Cc_P%7C%5E2+%3D+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\sum_{P \\in {\\mathcal P}} |c_P|^2 = 1}\" title=\"{\\sum_{P \\in {\\mathcal P}} |c_P|^2 = 1}\" class=\"latex\" />, so by Cauchy-Schwarz it suffices to show that \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5C%7C+%5Csum_%7BP+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%7D+c_P+%5Cphi_P+%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D%5E2+%5Clesssim+1.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\| \\sum_{P \\in {\\mathcal P}} c_P \\phi_P \\|_{L^2({\\bf R})}^2 \\lesssim 1.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\| \\sum_{P \\in {\\mathcal P}} c_P \\phi_P \\|_{L^2({\\bf R})}^2 \\lesssim 1.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> The left-hand side expands as \n<a name=\"lhs\"><p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7BP%2C+P%27+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%7D+c_P+%5Coverline%7Bc_%7BP%27%7D%7D+%5Clangle+%5Cphi_P%2C+%5Cphi_%7BP%27%7D+%5Crangle.+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2826%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{P, P' \\in {\\mathcal P}} c_P \\overline{c_{P'}} \\langle \\phi_P, \\phi_{P'} \\rangle. \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (26)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{P, P' \\in {\\mathcal P}} c_P \\overline{c_{P'}} \\langle \\phi_P, \\phi_{P'} \\rangle. \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (26)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> </a> From the Fourier support of \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cphi_P%2C+%5Cphi_%7BP%27%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\phi_P, \\phi_{P'}}\" title=\"{\\phi_P, \\phi_{P'}}\" class=\"latex\" /> we see that the inner product \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Clangle+%5Cphi_P%2C+%5Cphi_%7BP%27%7D+%5Crangle%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\langle \\phi_P, \\phi_{P'} \\rangle}\" title=\"{\\langle \\phi_P, \\phi_{P'} \\rangle}\" class=\"latex\" /> vanishes unless the intervals \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%28%5Comega_P%29_-%2C+%28%5Comega_%7BP%27%7D%29_-%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{(\\omega_P)_-, (\\omega_{P'})_-}\" title=\"{(\\omega_P)_-, (\\omega_{P'})_-}\" class=\"latex\" /> overlap which by the equal sizes of \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Comega_P%2C+%5Comega_%7BP%27%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\omega_P, \\omega_{P'}}\" title=\"{\\omega_P, \\omega_{P'}}\" class=\"latex\" /> force \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Comega_P+%3D+%5Comega_%7BP%27%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\omega_P = \\omega_{P'}}\" title=\"{\\omega_P = \\omega_{P'}}\" class=\"latex\" />. In this case we can use \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#phip\">(22)</a> to bound the inner product by \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clangle+%5Cphi_P%2C+%5Cphi_%7BP%27%7D+%5Crangle+%5Clesssim+%5Clangle+%5Cfrac%7B%5Cmathrm%7Bdist%7D%28I_P%2C+I_%7BP%27%7D%29%7D%7B%7CI_P%7C%7D+%5Crangle%5E%7B-100%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\langle \\phi_P, \\phi_{P'} \\rangle \\lesssim \\langle \\frac{\\mathrm{dist}(I_P, I_{P'})}{|I_P|} \\rangle^{-100}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\langle \\phi_P, \\phi_{P'} \\rangle \\lesssim \\langle \\frac{\\mathrm{dist}(I_P, I_{P'})}{|I_P|} \\rangle^{-100}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> and then a routine application of Schur’s test gives \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#lhs\">(26)</a>. This establishes \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#p2\">(25)</a>, giving \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#est-tile-finite\">(19)</a> in the case of tiles of equal dimensions. \n<p> <b>The case of a regular <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B-%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{-}\" title=\"{-}\" class=\"latex\" />-tree</b> </p>\n<p> Now we attack some cases where the tiles <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P}\" title=\"{P}\" class=\"latex\" /> can vary in scale. In phase space, a key geometric difficulty now arises from the fact that tiles may start partially overlapping each other, in contrast to the previous case in which the essential disjointness of the tile set was crucial in establishing the key estimates <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#p1\">(24)</a>, <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#p2\">(25)</a>. However, because we took care to restrict the intervals <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI_P%2C+%5Comega_P%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{I_P, \\omega_P}\" title=\"{I_P, \\omega_P}\" class=\"latex\" /> of the tiles to be dyadic, there are only a limited number of ways in which two tiles can overlap. Given two rectangles <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BR+%3D+I_R+%5Ctimes+%5Comega_R%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{R = I_R \\times \\omega_R}\" title=\"{R = I_R \\times \\omega_R}\" class=\"latex\" /> and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BR%27+%3D+I_%7BR%27%7D+%5Ctimes+%5Comega_%7BR%27%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{R' = I_{R'} \\times \\omega_{R'}}\" title=\"{R' = I_{R'} \\times \\omega_{R'}}\" class=\"latex\" />, we define the relation <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BR+%5Cleq+R%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{R \\leq R'}\" title=\"{R \\leq R'}\" class=\"latex\" /> if <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI_R+%5Csubset+I_%7BR%27%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{I_R \\subset I_{R'}}\" title=\"{I_R \\subset I_{R'}}\" class=\"latex\" /> and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Comega_R+%5Csupset+%5Comega_%7BR%27%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\omega_R \\supset \\omega_{R'}}\" title=\"{\\omega_R \\supset \\omega_{R'}}\" class=\"latex\" />; this is clearly a partial order on rectangles. The key observation is as follows: if two tiles <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%2C+P%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P, P'}\" title=\"{P, P'}\" class=\"latex\" /> overlap, then either <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP+%5Cleq+P%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P \\leq P'}\" title=\"{P \\leq P'}\" class=\"latex\" /> or <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP+%5Cgeq+P%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P \\geq P'}\" title=\"{P \\geq P'}\" class=\"latex\" />. Similarly if <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%2C+P%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P, P'}\" title=\"{P, P'}\" class=\"latex\" /> are replaced by their upper tiles <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP_%2B%2C+P%27_%2B%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P_+, P'_+}\" title=\"{P_+, P'_+}\" class=\"latex\" /> or by their lower tiles <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP_-%2C+P%27_-%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P_-, P'_-}\" title=\"{P_-, P'_-}\" class=\"latex\" />. Note that if <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%2C+P%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P, P'}\" title=\"{P, P'}\" class=\"latex\" /> are tiles with <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP+%5Cleq+P%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P \\leq P'}\" title=\"{P \\leq P'}\" class=\"latex\" />, then one of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP_%2B+%5Cleq+P%27_%2B%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P_+ \\leq P'_+}\" title=\"{P_+ \\leq P'_+}\" class=\"latex\" /> or <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP_-+%5Cleq+P%27_-%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P_- \\leq P'_-}\" title=\"{P_- \\leq P'_-}\" class=\"latex\" /> holds (and the only way both inequalities can hold simultaneously is if <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%3DP%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P=P'}\" title=\"{P=P'}\" class=\"latex\" />). </p>\n<p> As was first observed by Fefferman, a key configuration of tiles that needs to be understood for these sorts of problems is that of a <em>tree</em>. </p>\n<p> </p>\n<blockquote>\n <b>Definition 10</b> Let \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP_T%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P_T}\" title=\"{P_T}\" class=\"latex\" /> be a tile.
