A \n <em>tree with top <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP_T%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P_T}\" title=\"{P_T}\" class=\"latex\" /></em> is a collection \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BT%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{T}\" title=\"{T}\" class=\"latex\" /> of tiles \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P}\" title=\"{P}\" class=\"latex\" /> with the property that \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP+%5Cleq+P_T%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P \\leq P_T}\" title=\"{P \\leq P_T}\" class=\"latex\" /> for all \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP+%5Cin+T%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P \\in T}\" title=\"{P \\in T}\" class=\"latex\" />. (For minor technical reasons it is convenient to not require the top \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP_T%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P_T}\" title=\"{P_T}\" class=\"latex\" /> to actually lie in the tree \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BT%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{T}\" title=\"{T}\" class=\"latex\" />, though this is often the case.) We write \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI_T+%3D+I_%7BP_T%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{I_T = I_{P_T}}\" title=\"{I_T = I_{P_T}}\" class=\"latex\" /> for the spatial support of the tree, and \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Comega_T+%3D+%5Comega_%7BP_T%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\omega_T = \\omega_{P_T}}\" title=\"{\\omega_T = \\omega_{P_T}}\" class=\"latex\" /> for the frequency support of the tree top. If we in fact have \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP_%2B+%5Cleq+%28P_T%29_%2B%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P_+ \\leq (P_T)_+}\" title=\"{P_+ \\leq (P_T)_+}\" class=\"latex\" /> for all \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP+%5Cin+T%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P \\in T}\" title=\"{P \\in T}\" class=\"latex\" />, we say that \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BT%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{T}\" title=\"{T}\" class=\"latex\" /> is a \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%2B%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{+}\" title=\"{+}\" class=\"latex\" />-tree; similarly if \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP_-+%5Cleq+%28P_T%29_-%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P_- \\leq (P_T)_-}\" title=\"{P_- \\leq (P_T)_-}\" class=\"latex\" /> for all \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP+%5Cin+T%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P \\in T}\" title=\"{P \\in T}\" class=\"latex\" />, we say that \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BT%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{T}\" title=\"{T}\" class=\"latex\" /> is a \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B-%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{-}\" title=\"{-}\" class=\"latex\" />-tree. (Thus every tree can be partitioned into a \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%2B%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{+}\" title=\"{+}\" class=\"latex\" />-tree and a \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B-%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{-}\" title=\"{-}\" class=\"latex\" />-tree with the same top as the original tree.) \n</blockquote> \n<p></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> The tiles in a tree can vary in scale and in spatial location, but once these two parameters are given, the frequency location is fixed, so a tree can again be viewed as a “two-parameter” subfamily of the three-parameter family of tiles. </p>\n<p> We now prove <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#est-tile-finite\">(19)</a> in the case when <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal P}}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal P}}\" class=\"latex\" /> is a <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B-%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{-}\" title=\"{-}\" class=\"latex\" />-tree <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BT%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{T}\" title=\"{T}\" class=\"latex\" />, thus <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP_-+%5Cleq+%28P_T%29_-%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P_- \\leq (P_T)_-}\" title=\"{P_- \\leq (P_T)_-}\" class=\"latex\" /> for all <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP+%5Cin+T%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P \\in T}\" title=\"{P \\in T}\" class=\"latex\" />. Here, the <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Cphi_P+%5Crangle%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle}\" title=\"{\\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle}\" class=\"latex\" /> factors will all “collide” with each other and there will be no orthogonality to exploit here; on the other hand, there will be a lot of “disjointness” in the <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BE_P%5E%2B%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{E_P^+}\" title=\"{E_P^+}\" class=\"latex\" /> that can be exploited instead. </p>\n<p> To illustrate the key ideas (and to help motivate the arguments for the general case) we will also make the following “regularity” hypotheses: there exists two quantities <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cvarepsilon%2C+%5Cmu+%3E+0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\varepsilon, \\mu > 0}\" title=\"{\\varepsilon, \\mu > 0}\" class=\"latex\" /> (which we will refer to as the <em>energy</em> and <em>mass</em> of the tree respectively) for which we have the upper bounds <a name=\"eop\"></a></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><a name=\"eop\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7CI_P%7C%5E%7B-1%2F2%7D+%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Cphi_P+%5Crangle+%5Clesssim+%5Cvarepsilon+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2827%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  |I_P|^{-1/2} \\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\lesssim \\varepsilon \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (27)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  |I_P|^{-1/2} \\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\lesssim \\varepsilon \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (27)\" class=\"latex\" /></a></p>\n<a name=\"eop\"> </a> and \n<a name=\"ipi\"><p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7CI_P%7C%5E%7B-1%7D+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+1_%7BE%7D%28x%29+%5Cchi%5E%7B10%7D_%7BI_P%7D%28x%29%5C+dx+%5Clesssim+%5Cmu+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2828%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  |I_P|^{-1} \\int_{\\bf R} 1_{E}(x) \\chi^{10}_{I_P}(x)\\ dx \\lesssim \\mu \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (28)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  |I_P|^{-1} \\int_{\\bf R} 1_{E}(x) \\chi^{10}_{I_P}(x)\\ dx \\lesssim \\mu \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (28)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> </a> for all \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP+%5Cin+T%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P \\in T}\" title=\"{P \\in T}\" class=\"latex\" />; informally, these estimates assert that \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{f}\" title=\"{f}\" class=\"latex\" /> is size \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BO%28%5Cvarepsilon%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{O(\\varepsilon)}\" title=\"{O(\\varepsilon)}\" class=\"latex\" /> “on average” on the tiles in the tree, and similarly that \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BE%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{E}\" title=\"{E}\" class=\"latex\" /> has density \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BO%28%5Cmu%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{O(\\mu)}\" title=\"{O(\\mu)}\" class=\"latex\" /> on all tiles in the tree. (These are slightly oversimplified versions of the energy and mass concept; we will refine these notions later.) For technical reasons we also need to generalise \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#ipi\">(28)</a> to \n<a name=\"ipi-2\"><p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7CI_%7BP%27%7D%7C%5E%7B-1%7D+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+1_%7BE%7D%28x%29+%5Cchi%5E%7B10%7D_%7BI_%7BP%27%7D%7D%28x%29%5C+dx+%5Clesssim+%5Cmu+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2829%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  |I_{P'}|^{-1} \\int_{\\bf R} 1_{E}(x) \\chi^{10}_{I_{P'}}(x)\\ dx \\lesssim \\mu \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (29)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  |I_{P'}|^{-1} \\int_{\\bf R} 1_{E}(x) \\chi^{10}_{I_{P'}}(x)\\ dx \\lesssim \\mu \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (29)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> </a> for any tile \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P'}\" title=\"{P'}\" class=\"latex\" /> with \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%27+%5Cgeq+P%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P' \\geq P}\" title=\"{P' \\geq P}\" class=\"latex\" /> for some \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP+%5Cin+T%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P \\in T}\" title=\"{P \\in T}\" class=\"latex\" />. (Informally, \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#ipi-2\">(29)</a> asserts that a sort of “Hardy-Littlewood maximal function” of \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B1_E%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{1_E}\" title=\"{1_E}\" class=\"latex\" /> is bounded by \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BO%28%5Cmu%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{O(\\mu)}\" title=\"{O(\\mu)}\" class=\"latex\" /> on the tree.) \n<p></p>\n<p> We also assume that we have the reverse bounds for the tree top: <a name=\"rev\"></a></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><a name=\"rev\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7CI_%7BT%7D%7C%5E%7B-1%2F2%7D+%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Cphi_%7BP_T%7D+%5Crangle+%5Cgtrsim+%5Cvarepsilon+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2830%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  |I_{T}|^{-1/2} \\langle f, \\phi_{P_T} \\rangle \\gtrsim \\varepsilon \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (30)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  |I_{T}|^{-1/2} \\langle f, \\phi_{P_T} \\rangle \\gtrsim \\varepsilon \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (30)\" class=\"latex\" /></a></p>\n<a name=\"rev\"> </a> and \n<a name=\"joe\"><p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7CI_%7BT%7D%7C%5E%7B-1%7D+%5Cint_%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+1_%7BE%7D%28x%29+%5Cchi%5E%7B10%7D_%7BI_%7BT%7D%7D%28x%29%5C+dx+%5Cgtrsim+%5Cmu.+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2831%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  |I_{T}|^{-1} \\int_{\\bf R} 1_{E}(x) \\chi^{10}_{I_{T}}(x)\\ dx \\gtrsim \\mu. \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (31)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  |I_{T}|^{-1} \\int_{\\bf R} 1_{E}(x) \\chi^{10}_{I_{T}}(x)\\ dx \\gtrsim \\mu. \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (31)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> </a> It will be through a combination of both these lower and upper bounds that we can obtain a bound \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#est-tile-finite\">(19)</a> that does not involve either \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cvarepsilon%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\varepsilon}\" title=\"{\\varepsilon}\" class=\"latex\" /> or \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cmu%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\mu}\" title=\"{\\mu}\" class=\"latex\" />. \n<p></p>\n<p> We will use <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#eop\">(27)</a>, <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#ipi\">(28)</a>, <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#ipi-2\">(29)</a> to establish the <em>tree estimate</em> <a name=\"tree\"></a></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><a name=\"tree\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7BP+%5Cin+T%7D+%7C%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Cphi_P+%5Crangle+%5Clangle+%5Cphi_P%2C+1_%7BE_P%5E%2B%7D+%5Crangle%7C+%5Clesssim+%5Cvarepsilon+%5Cmu+%7CI_T%7C.+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2832%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{P \\in T} |\\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\langle \\phi_P, 1_{E_P^+} \\rangle| \\lesssim \\varepsilon \\mu |I_T|. \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (32)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{P \\in T} |\\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\langle \\phi_P, 1_{E_P^+} \\rangle| \\lesssim \\varepsilon \\mu |I_T|. \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (32)\" class=\"latex\" /></a></p>\n<a name=\"tree\"> </a> \n<p></p>\n<p> Note from <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#rev\">(30)</a> and Cauchy-Schwarz that </p>\n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cvarepsilon+%5Clesssim+%7CI_T%7C%5E%7B-1%2F2%7D+%5C%7Cf%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\varepsilon \\lesssim |I_T|^{-1/2} \\|f\\|_{L^2}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\varepsilon \\lesssim |I_T|^{-1/2} \\|f\\|_{L^2}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> and from \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#joe\">(31)</a> and Cauchy-Schwarz one similarly has \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cmu+%5Clesssim+%7CI_T%7C%5E%7B-1%2F2%7D+%7CE%7C%5E%7B1%2F2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\mu \\lesssim |I_T|^{-1/2} |E|^{1/2}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\mu \\lesssim |I_T|^{-1/2} |E|^{1/2}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> and so \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#tree\">(32)</a> recovers the desired estimate \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#est-tile-finite\">(19)</a>. \n<p> It remains to establish the tree estimate <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#tree\">(32)</a>. It will be convenient to use the tree <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BT%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{T}\" title=\"{T}\" class=\"latex\" /> to partition the real line <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf R}}\" title=\"{{\\bf R}}\" class=\"latex\" /> into dyadic intervals <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BJ%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{J}\" title=\"{J}\" class=\"latex\" /> that are naturally “adapted to” the geometry of the tree (or more precisely to the spatial intervals <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5C%7B+I_P%3A+P+%5Cin+T%5C%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\{ I_P: P \\in T\\}}\" title=\"{\\{ I_P: P \\in T\\}}\" class=\"latex\" /> of the tree) in a certain way (in a manner reminiscent of a Whitney decomposition). </p>\n<p> </p>\n<blockquote>\n <b>Exercise 11 (Whitney-type decomposition associated to a tree)</b> \n <a name=\"spat\"></a> Let \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BT%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{T}\" title=\"{T}\" class=\"latex\" /> be a non-empty tree. Show that there exists a family \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+J%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal J}}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal J}}\" class=\"latex\" /> of dyadic intervals with the following properties: \n <ul> \n  <li>(i) The intervals <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BJ%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{J}\" title=\"{J}\" class=\"latex\" /> in <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+J%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal J}}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal J}}\" class=\"latex\" /> form a partition of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\bf R}}\" title=\"{{\\bf R}}\" class=\"latex\" /> (up to sets of measure zero). </li>\n  <li>(ii) For each <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BJ+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+J%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{J \\in {\\mathcal J}}\" title=\"{J \\in {\\mathcal J}}\" class=\"latex\" /> and any <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP+%5Cin+T%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P \\in T}\" title=\"{P \\in T}\" class=\"latex\" /> with <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7CI_P%7C+%3C+%7CJ%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{|I_P| < |J|}\" title=\"{|I_P| < |J|}\" class=\"latex\" />, we have <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cmathrm%7Bdist%7D%28I_P%2CJ%29+%5Cgtrsim+%7CJ%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\mathrm{dist}(I_P,J) \\gtrsim |J|}\" title=\"{\\mathrm{dist}(I_P,J) \\gtrsim |J|}\" class=\"latex\" />. </li>\n  <li>(iii) For each <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BJ+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+J%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{J \\in {\\mathcal J}}\" title=\"{J \\in {\\mathcal J}}\" class=\"latex\" />, there exists <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP+%5Cin+T%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P \\in T}\" title=\"{P \\in T}\" class=\"latex\" /> with <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7CI_P%7C+%5Clesssim+%7CJ%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{|I_P| \\lesssim |J|}\" title=\"{|I_P| \\lesssim |J|}\" class=\"latex\" /> and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cmathrm%7Bdist%7D%28I_P%2CJ%29+%5Clesssim+%7CJ%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\mathrm{dist}(I_P,J) \\lesssim |J|}\" title=\"{\\mathrm{dist}(I_P,J) \\lesssim |J|}\" class=\"latex\" />. </li>\n </ul> (Hint: one can choose \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+J%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal J}}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal J}}\" class=\"latex\" /> to be the collection of all dyadic intervals \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BJ%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{J}\" title=\"{J}\" class=\"latex\" /> whose dilate \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B3J+%3A%3D+%5B%5Cinf+J+-+%7CJ%7C%2C+%5Cinf+J+%2B+2%7CJ%7C%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{3J := [\\inf J - |J|, \\inf J + 2|J|)}\" title=\"{3J := [\\inf J - |J|, \\inf J + 2|J|)}\" class=\"latex\" /> does not contain any \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI_P%2C+P+%5Cin+T%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{I_P, P \\in T}\" title=\"{I_P, P \\in T}\" class=\"latex\" />, and which is maximal with respect to set inclusion.) \n</blockquote> \n<p></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> We can of course assume that the tree <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BT%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{T}\" title=\"{T}\" class=\"latex\" /> is non-empty, since <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#tree\">(32)</a> is trivial for empty sets of tiles. We apply the partition from Exercise <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#spat\">11</a>. By the triangle inequality, we can bound the left hand side of <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#tree\">(32)</a> by </p>\n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7BJ+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+J%7D%7D+%5Csum_%7BP+%5Cin+T%7D+%7C%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Cphi_P+%5Crangle%7C+%5Cint_J+%7C%5Cphi_P%7C+1_%7BE_P%5E%2B%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{J \\in {\\mathcal J}} \\sum_{P \\in T} |\\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle| \\int_J |\\phi_P| 1_{E_P^+}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{J \\in {\\mathcal J}} \\sum_{P \\in T} |\\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle| \\int_J |\\phi_P| 1_{E_P^+}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> which by \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#eop\">(27)</a>, \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#phip\">(22)</a> may be bounded by \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clesssim+%5Cvarepsilon+%5Csum_%7BJ+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+J%7D%7D+%5Csum_%7BP+%5Cin+T%7D+%5Cint_J+%5Cchi_%7BI_P%7D%5E%7B100%7D+1_%7BE_P%5E%2B%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\lesssim \\varepsilon \\sum_{J \\in {\\mathcal J}} \\sum_{P \\in T} \\int_J \\chi_{I_P}^{100} 1_{E_P^+}.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\lesssim \\varepsilon \\sum_{J \\in {\\mathcal J}} \\sum_{P \\in T} \\int_J \\chi_{I_P}^{100} 1_{E_P^+}.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> We first dispose of the narrow tiles \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P}\" title=\"{P}\" class=\"latex\" /> in which \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7CI_P%7C+%3C+%7CJ%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{|I_P| < |J|}\" title=\"{|I_P| < |J|}\" class=\"latex\" />. By Exercise \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#spat\">11</a>(ii) this forces \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cmathrm%7Bdist%7D%28I_P%2C+J%29+%5Cgtrsim+%7CJ%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\mathrm{dist}(I_P, J) \\gtrsim |J|}\" title=\"{\\mathrm{dist}(I_P, J) \\gtrsim |J|}\" class=\"latex\" />. From \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#ipi\">(28)</a> we have \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cint_J+%5Cchi_%7BI_P%7D%5E%7B100%7D+1_%7BE_P%5E%2B%7D+%5Clesssim+%5Cmu+%7CJ%7C+%28%7CI_P%7C+%2F+%5Cmathrm%7Bdist%7D%28I_P%2CJ%29%29%5E%7B20%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\int_J \\chi_{I_P}^{100} 1_{E_P^+} \\lesssim \\mu |J| (|I_P| / \\mathrm{dist}(I_P,J))^{20}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\int_J \\chi_{I_P}^{100} 1_{E_P^+} \\lesssim \\mu |J| (|I_P| / \\mathrm{dist}(I_P,J))^{20}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clesssim+%5Cmu+%7CJ%7C+%28%7CI_P%7C%2F%7CJ%7C%29%5E%7B10%7D+%28%7CI_P%7C+%2F+%5Cmathrm%7Bdist%7D%28I_P%2CJ%29%29%5E%7B10%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\lesssim \\mu |J| (|I_P|/|J|)^{10} (|I_P| / \\mathrm{dist}(I_P,J))^{10}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\lesssim \\mu |J| (|I_P|/|J|)^{10} (|I_P| / \\mathrm{dist}(I_P,J))^{10}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> (say). For each fixed spatial scale \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7CI_P%7C+%3D+2%5Ek+%5Cleq+%7CI_T%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{|I_P| = 2^k \\leq |I_T|}\" title=\"{|I_P| = 2^k \\leq |I_T|}\" class=\"latex\" />, the intervals \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI_P%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{I_P}\" title=\"{I_P}\" class=\"latex\" /> in the tree \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BT%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{T}\" title=\"{T}\" class=\"latex\" /> are all essentially disjoint, so a routine calculation then shows \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7BP%5Cin+T%3A+%7CI_P%7C+%3D+2%5Ek%7D+%28%7CI_P%7C+%2F+%5Cmathrm%7Bdist%7D%28I_P%2CJ%29%29%5E%7B10%7D+%5Clesssim+%7CJ%7C%2F2%5Ek&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{P\\in T: |I_P| = 2^k} (|I_P| / \\mathrm{dist}(I_P,J))^{10} \\lesssim |J|/2^k\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{P\\in T: |I_P| = 2^k} (|I_P| / \\mathrm{dist}(I_P,J))^{10} \\lesssim |J|/2^k\" class=\"latex\" /></p> (say), so that \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7BP+%5Cin+T%3A+%7CI_P%7C+%3C+%7CJ%7C%7D+%5Cint_J+%5Cchi_%7BI_P%7D%5E%7B100%7D+1_%7BE_P%5E%2B%7D+%5Clesssim+%5Cmu+%7CJ%7C+%5Csum_%7B2%5Ek+%5Cleq+%7CI_T%7C%2C+c%7CJ%7C%7D+%282%5Ek%2F%7CJ%7C%29%5E%7B9%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{P \\in T: |I_P| < |J|} \\int_J \\chi_{I_P}^{100} 1_{E_P^+} \\lesssim \\mu |J| \\sum_{2^k \\leq |I_T|, c|J|} (2^k/|J|)^{9}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{P \\in T: |I_P| < |J|} \\int_J \\chi_{I_P}^{100} 1_{E_P^+} \\lesssim \\mu |J| \\sum_{2^k \\leq |I_T|, c|J|} (2^k/|J|)^{9}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clesssim+%5Cmu+%7CJ%7C+%5Cmin%28+1%2C+%7CI_T%7C%2F%7CJ%7C+%29%5E%7B9%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\lesssim \\mu |J| \\min( 1, |I_T|/|J| )^{9}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\lesssim \\mu |J| \\min( 1, |I_T|/|J| )^{9}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> which from Exercise \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#spat\">11</a>(ii) implies that the contribution of the \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7CI_P%7C+%3C+%7CJ%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{|I_P| < |J|}\" title=\"{|I_P| < |J|}\" class=\"latex\" /> case to \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#tree\">(32)</a> is acceptable. \n<p> Now we consider the wide tiles in which <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7CI_P%7C+%5Cgeq+%7CJ%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{|I_P| \\geq |J|}\" title=\"{|I_P| \\geq |J|}\" class=\"latex\" />. From Exercise <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#spat\">11</a>(ii) this case is only possible if <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7CJ%7C+%5Cleq+%7CI_T%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{|J| \\leq |I_T|}\" title=\"{|J| \\leq |I_T|}\" class=\"latex\" /> and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cmathrm%7Bdist%7D%28J%2C+I_T%29+%5Clesssim+%7CI_T%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\mathrm{dist}(J, I_T) \\lesssim |I_T|}\" title=\"{\\mathrm{dist}(J, I_T) \\lesssim |I_T|}\" class=\"latex\" />. Thus the <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BJ%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{J}\" title=\"{J}\" class=\"latex\" /> are now restricted to an interval of length <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BO%28%7CI_T%7C%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{O(|I_T|)}\" title=\"{O(|I_T|)}\" class=\"latex\" />, and it will suffice to establish the local estimate </p>\n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7BP+%5Cin+T%3A+%7CI_P%7C+%5Cgeq+%7CJ%7C%7D+%5Cint_J+%5Cchi_%7BI_P%7D%5E%7B100%7D+1_%7BE_P%5E%2B%7D+%5Clesssim+%5Cmu+%7CJ%7C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{P \\in T: |I_P| \\geq |J|} \\int_J \\chi_{I_P}^{100} 1_{E_P^+} \\lesssim \\mu |J|\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{P \\in T: |I_P| \\geq |J|} \\int_J \\chi_{I_P}^{100} 1_{E_P^+} \\lesssim \\mu |J|\" class=\"latex\" /></p> for each \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BJ%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{J}\" title=\"{J}\" class=\"latex\" />. Note that for each fixed spatial scale \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B2%5Ek%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{2^k}\" title=\"{2^k}\" class=\"latex\" />, there is at most one choice \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Comega_k%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\omega_k}\" title=\"{\\omega_k}\" class=\"latex\" /> of frequency interval \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Comega_P%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\omega_P}\" title=\"{\\omega_P}\" class=\"latex\" /> with \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP+%5Cin+T%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P \\in T}\" title=\"{P \\in T}\" class=\"latex\" /> and \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7C%5Comega_P%7C+%3D+2%5E%7B-k%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{|\\omega_P| = 2^{-k}}\" title=\"{|\\omega_P| = 2^{-k}}\" class=\"latex\" />, thus for fixed \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bk%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{k}\" title=\"{k}\" class=\"latex\" /> the set \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BE_P%5E%2B+%3D+%5C%7B+x+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%3A+N%28x%29+%5Cin+%5Comega_P%5E%2B%5C%7D+%3D+%5C%7B+x+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%3A+N%28x%29+%5Cin+%5Comega_k%5E%2B%5C%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{E_P^+ = \\{ x \\in {\\bf R}: N(x) \\in \\omega_P^+\\} = \\{ x \\in {\\bf R}: N(x) \\in \\omega_k^+\\}}\" title=\"{E_P^+ = \\{ x \\in {\\bf R}: N(x) \\in \\omega_P^+\\} = \\{ x \\in {\\bf R}: N(x) \\in \\omega_k^+\\}}\" class=\"latex\" /> is independent of \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P}\" title=\"{P}\" class=\"latex\" />. We may then sum in \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P}\" title=\"{P}\" class=\"latex\" /> for each such scale to conclude \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7BP+%5Cin+T%3A+%7CI_P%7C+%5Cgeq+%7CJ%7C%7D+%5Cint_J+%5Cchi_%7BI_P%7D%5E%7B100%7D+1_%7BE_P%5E%2B%7D+%5Clesssim+%5Csum_k+%5Cint_J+1_%7BE_k%5E%2B%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{P \\in T: |I_P| \\geq |J|} \\int_J \\chi_{I_P}^{100} 1_{E_P^+} \\lesssim \\sum_k \\int_J 1_{E_k^+}.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{P \\in T: |I_P| \\geq |J|} \\int_J \\chi_{I_P}^{100} 1_{E_P^+} \\lesssim \\sum_k \\int_J 1_{E_k^+}.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> Now we make the crucial observation that in a \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B-%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{-}\" title=\"{-}\" class=\"latex\" />-tree \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BT%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{T}\" title=\"{T}\" class=\"latex\" />, the intervals \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Comega_k%5E%2B%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\omega_k^+}\" title=\"{\\omega_k^+}\" class=\"latex\" /> are all essentially disjoint, hence the \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BE_k%5E%2B%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{E_k^+}\" title=\"{E_k^+}\" class=\"latex\" /> are disjoint as well. As these sets are also contained in \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BE%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{E}\" title=\"{E}\" class=\"latex\" />, we conclude that \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle+%5Csum_k+%5Cint_J+1_%7BE_k%5E%2B%7D+%5Clesssim+%5Cint_J+1_E.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle \\sum_k \\int_J 1_{E_k^+} \\lesssim \\int_J 1_E.\" title=\"\\displaystyle \\sum_k \\int_J 1_{E_k^+} \\lesssim \\int_J 1_E.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> From Exercise \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#spat\">11</a>(iii) and \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#ipi-2\">(29)</a> (choosing a tile \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P'}\" title=\"{P'}\" class=\"latex\" /> with spatial scale \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Csim+%7CJ%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\sim |J|}\" title=\"{\\sim |J|}\" class=\"latex\" /> and within \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BO%28%7CJ%7C%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{O(|J|)}\" title=\"{O(|J|)}\" class=\"latex\" /> of \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BJ%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{J}\" title=\"{J}\" class=\"latex\" />, and with \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%27+%5Cgeq+P%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P' \\geq P}\" title=\"{P' \\geq P}\" class=\"latex\" /> for the tile \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P}\" title=\"{P}\" class=\"latex\" /> provided by Exercise \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#spat\">11</a>(iii)) we have \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle+%5Cint_J+1_E+%5Clesssim+%5Cmu+%7CJ%7C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle \\int_J 1_E \\lesssim \\mu |J|\" title=\"\\displaystyle \\int_J 1_E \\lesssim \\mu |J|\" class=\"latex\" /></p> giving the claim. \n<p> <b>The case of a regular <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%2B%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{+}\" title=\"{+}\" class=\"latex\" />-tree</b> </p>\n<p> We now complement the previous case by establishing <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#est-tile-finite\">(19)</a> for (certain types of) <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%2B%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{+}\" title=\"{+}\" class=\"latex\" />-trees <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BT%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{T}\" title=\"{T}\" class=\"latex\" />. The situation is now reversed: there is a lot of “collision” in the <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BE_P%5E%2B%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{E_P^+}\" title=\"{E_P^+}\" class=\"latex\" />, but on the other hand there is now some “orthogonality” in the <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Cphi_P+%5Crangle%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle}\" title=\"{\\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle}\" class=\"latex\" /> that can be exploited. </p>\n<p> As before we will assume some regularity on the <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%2B%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{+}\" title=\"{+}\" class=\"latex\" />-tree <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BT%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{T}\" title=\"{T}\" class=\"latex\" />, namely that there exist <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cvarepsilon%2C%5Cmu%3E0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\varepsilon,\\mu>0}\" title=\"{\\varepsilon,\\mu>0}\" class=\"latex\" /> for which one has the upper bounds <a name=\"po\"></a></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><a name=\"po\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7CI_P%7C%5E%7B-1%2F2%7D+%28%5Csum_%7BP%27+%5Cin+T%3A+P%27+%5Cleq+P%7D+%7C%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Cphi_%7BP%27%7D+%5Crangle%7C%5E2%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5Clesssim+%5Cvarepsilon+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2833%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  |I_P|^{-1/2} (\\sum_{P' \\in T: P' \\leq P} |\\langle f, \\phi_{P'} \\rangle|^2)^{1/2} \\lesssim \\varepsilon \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (33)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  |I_P|^{-1/2} (\\sum_{P' \\in T: P' \\leq P} |\\langle f, \\phi_{P'} \\rangle|^2)^{1/2} \\lesssim \\varepsilon \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (33)\" class=\"latex\" /></a></p>\n<a name=\"po\"> </a> for all \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP+%5Cin+T%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P \\in T}\" title=\"{P \\in T}\" class=\"latex\" /> (note this is slightly stronger than \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#eop\">(27)</a>), as well as the bound \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#ipi-2\">(29)</a> for any tile \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P'}\" title=\"{P'}\" class=\"latex\" /> with \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%27+%5Cgeq+P%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P' \\geq P}\" title=\"{P' \\geq P}\" class=\"latex\" /> for some \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP+%5Cin+T%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P \\in T}\" title=\"{P \\in T}\" class=\"latex\" />. We complement this with the matching lower bounds \n<a name=\"rev-bound\"><p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7CI_%7BT%7D%7C%5E%7B-1%2F2%7D+%28%5Csum_%7BP+%5Cin+T%7D+%7C%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Cphi_%7BP%7D+%5Crangle%7C%5E2%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5Cgtrsim+%5Cvarepsilon+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2834%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  |I_{T}|^{-1/2} (\\sum_{P \\in T} |\\langle f, \\phi_{P} \\rangle|^2)^{1/2} \\gtrsim \\varepsilon \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (34)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  |I_{T}|^{-1/2} (\\sum_{P \\in T} |\\langle f, \\phi_{P} \\rangle|^2)^{1/2} \\gtrsim \\varepsilon \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (34)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> </a> and \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#joe\">(31)</a>. \n<p></p>\n<p> As before we will focus on establishing the tree estimate <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#tree\">(32)</a>. From <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#joe\">(31)</a> and Cauchy-Schwarz as before we have </p>\n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cmu+%5Clesssim+%7CI_T%7C%5E%7B-1%2F2%7D+%7CE%7C%5E%7B1%2F2%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\mu \\lesssim |I_T|^{-1/2} |E|^{1/2}.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\mu \\lesssim |I_T|^{-1/2} |E|^{1/2}.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> As we now have a \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%2B%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{+}\" title=\"{+}\" class=\"latex\" />-tree, the tiles \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP_-%2C+P+%5Cin+T%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P_-, P \\in T}\" title=\"{P_-, P \\in T}\" class=\"latex\" /> become disjoint (up to null sets), and we can obtain an almost orthogonality estimate: \n<p> </p>\n<blockquote>\n <b>Exercise 12 (Almost orthogonality)</b> \n <a name=\"ao\"></a> For any \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%2B%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{+}\" title=\"{+}\" class=\"latex\" />-tree \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BT%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{T}\" title=\"{T}\" class=\"latex\" />, show that \n <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5C%7C%5Csum_%7BP+%5Cin+T%7D+c_P+%5Cphi_P+%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D%5E2+%5Clesssim+%5Csum_%7BP+%5Cin+T%7D+%7Cc_P%7C%5E2&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\|\\sum_{P \\in T} c_P \\phi_P \\|_{L^2({\\bf R})}^2 \\lesssim \\sum_{P \\in T} |c_P|^2\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\|\\sum_{P \\in T} c_P \\phi_P \\|_{L^2({\\bf R})}^2 \\lesssim \\sum_{P \\in T} |c_P|^2\" class=\"latex\" /></p> for all complex numbers \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bc_P%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{c_P}\" title=\"{c_P}\" class=\"latex\" />, and use this to deduce the Bessel-type inequality \n <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7BP+%5Cin+T%7D+%7C%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Cphi_%7BP%7D+%5Crangle%7C%5E2+%5Clesssim+%5C%7Cf%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D%5E2.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{P \\in T} |\\langle f, \\phi_{P} \\rangle|^2 \\lesssim \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})}^2.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{P \\in T} |\\langle f, \\phi_{P} \\rangle|^2 \\lesssim \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})}^2.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n</blockquote> \n<p></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> From this exercise and <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#rev-bound\">(34)</a> we see that </p>\n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cvarepsilon+%5Clesssim+%7CI_T%7C%5E%7B-1%2F2%7D+%5C%7Cf%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\varepsilon \\lesssim |I_T|^{-1/2} \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\varepsilon \\lesssim |I_T|^{-1/2} \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> and so the desired bound \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#est-tile-finite\">(19)</a> will follow from the tree estimate \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#tree\">(32)</a>. \n<p> In this case it will be convenient to linearise the sum to remove the absolute value signs; more precisely, to show <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#tree\">(32)</a> it suffices to show that </p>\n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7BP+%5Cin+T%7D+%5Cepsilon_P+%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Cphi_P+%5Crangle+%5Clangle+%5Cphi_P%2C+1_%7BE_P%5E%2B%7D+%5Crangle+%5Clesssim+%5Cvarepsilon+%5Cmu+%7CI_T%7C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{P \\in T} \\epsilon_P \\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\langle \\phi_P, 1_{E_P^+} \\rangle \\lesssim \\varepsilon \\mu |I_T|\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{P \\in T} \\epsilon_P \\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\langle \\phi_P, 1_{E_P^+} \\rangle \\lesssim \\varepsilon \\mu |I_T|\" class=\"latex\" /></p> for any complex numbers \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cepsilon_P%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\epsilon_P}\" title=\"{\\epsilon_P}\" class=\"latex\" /> of magnitude \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{1}\" title=\"{1}\" class=\"latex\" />. Again we may assume that the tree \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BT%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{T}\" title=\"{T}\" class=\"latex\" /> is non-empty, and use the partition \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+J%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal J}}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal J}}\" class=\"latex\" /> from Exercise \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#spat\">11</a>, to split the left-hand side as \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7BJ+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+J%7D%7D+%5Cint_J+%5Csum_%7BP+%5Cin+T%7D+%5Cepsilon_P+%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Cphi_P+%5Crangle+%5Cphi_P+1_%7BE_P%5E%2B%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{J \\in {\\mathcal J}} \\int_J \\sum_{P \\in T} \\epsilon_P \\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\phi_P 1_{E_P^+}.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{J \\in {\\mathcal J}} \\int_J \\sum_{P \\in T} \\epsilon_P \\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\phi_P 1_{E_P^+}.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> The contribution of the narrow tiles \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7CI_P%7C+%3C+%7CJ%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{|I_P| < |J|}\" title=\"{|I_P| < |J|}\" class=\"latex\" /> can be disposed of as before without any additional difficulty, so we focus on estimating the contribution \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7BJ+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+J%7D%7D+%5Cint_J+%5Csum_%7BP+%5Cin+T%3A+%7CI_P%7C+%5Cgeq+%7CJ%7C%7D+%5Cepsilon_P+%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Cphi_P+%5Crangle+%5Cphi_P+1_%7BE_P%5E%2B%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{J \\in {\\mathcal J}} \\int_J \\sum_{P \\in T: |I_P| \\geq |J|} \\epsilon_P \\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\phi_P 1_{E_P^+}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{J \\in {\\mathcal J}} \\int_J \\sum_{P \\in T: |I_P| \\geq |J|} \\epsilon_P \\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\phi_P 1_{E_P^+}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> of the wide tiles. As before, in order for this sum to be non-empty \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BJ%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{J}\" title=\"{J}\" class=\"latex\" /> has to be contained in an \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BO%28%7CI_T%7C%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{O(|I_T|)}\" title=\"{O(|I_T|)}\" class=\"latex\" /> neighbourhood \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BCI_T%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{CI_T}\" title=\"{CI_T}\" class=\"latex\" /> of \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI_T%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{I_T}\" title=\"{I_T}\" class=\"latex\" />. \n<p> The main difficulty here is the dependence of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BE_P%5E%2B%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{E_P^+}\" title=\"{E_P^+}\" class=\"latex\" /> on <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P}\" title=\"{P}\" class=\"latex\" />. We rewrite </p>\n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++1_%7BE_P%5E%2B%7D%28x%29+%3D+1_E%28x%29+1_%7BN%28x%29+%5Cin+%5Comega_P%5E%2B%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  1_{E_P^+}(x) = 1_E(x) 1_{N(x) \\in \\omega_P^+}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  1_{E_P^+}(x) = 1_E(x) 1_{N(x) \\in \\omega_P^+}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> so that the above expression can be written as \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7BJ+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+J%7D%7D+%5Cint_%7BJ+%5Ccap+E%7D+%5Csum_%7BP+%5Cin+T%3A+%7CI_P%7C+%5Cgeq+%7CJ%7C%3B+N%28x%29+%5Cin+%5Comega_P%5E%2B%7D+%5Cepsilon_P+%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Cphi_P+%5Crangle+%5Cphi_P%28x%29%5C+dx.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{J \\in {\\mathcal J}} \\int_{J \\cap E} \\sum_{P \\in T: |I_P| \\geq |J|; N(x) \\in \\omega_P^+} \\epsilon_P \\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\phi_P(x)\\ dx.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{J \\in {\\mathcal J}} \\int_{J \\cap E} \\sum_{P \\in T: |I_P| \\geq |J|; N(x) \\in \\omega_P^+} \\epsilon_P \\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\phi_P(x)\\ dx.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> Now for a key geometric observation: the intervals \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Comega_P%5E%2B%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\omega_P^+}\" title=\"{\\omega_P^+}\" class=\"latex\" /> are nested (and decrease when \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7CI_P%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{|I_P|}\" title=\"{|I_P|}\" class=\"latex\" /> increases), so the condition \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN%28x%29+%5Cin+%5Comega_P%5E%2B%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{N(x) \\in \\omega_P^+}\" title=\"{N(x) \\in \\omega_P^+}\" class=\"latex\" /> is equivalent to a condition of the form \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7CI_P%7C+%5Cleq+R%28x%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{|I_P| \\leq R(x)}\" title=\"{|I_P| \\leq R(x)}\" class=\"latex\" /> for some scale \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BR%28x%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{R(x)}\" title=\"{R(x)}\" class=\"latex\" /> depending on \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bx%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{x}\" title=\"{x}\" class=\"latex\" />. Thus the above sum can be written as \n<a name=\"j-sum\"><p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7BJ+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+J%7D%7D+%5Cint_%7BJ+%5Ccap+E%7D+%5Csum_%7BP+%5Cin+T%3A+%7CJ%7C+%5Cleq+%7CI_P%7C+%5Cleq+R%28x%29%7D+%5Cepsilon_P+%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Cphi_P+%5Crangle+%5Cphi_P%28x%29%5C+dx.+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2835%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{J \\in {\\mathcal J}} \\int_{J \\cap E} \\sum_{P \\in T: |J| \\leq |I_P| \\leq R(x)} \\epsilon_P \\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\phi_P(x)\\ dx. \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (35)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{J \\in {\\mathcal J}} \\int_{J \\cap E} \\sum_{P \\in T: |J| \\leq |I_P| \\leq R(x)} \\epsilon_P \\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\phi_P(x)\\ dx. \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (35)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> </a> One can bound the integrand here by a “maximal Calderón-Zygmund operator” \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csup_R+%7C%5Csum_%7BP+%5Cin+T%3A+%7CJ%7C+%5Cleq+%7CI_P%7C+%5Cleq+R%28x%29%7D+%5Cepsilon_P+%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Cphi_P+%5Crangle+%5Cphi_P%28x%29%7C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sup_R |\\sum_{P \\in T: |J| \\leq |I_P| \\leq R(x)} \\epsilon_P \\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\phi_P(x)|\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sup_R |\\sum_{P \\in T: |J| \\leq |I_P| \\leq R(x)} \\epsilon_P \\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\phi_P(x)|\" class=\"latex\" /></p> which is basically a sup over truncations of the “(modulated) pseudodifferential operator” \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++f+%5Cmapsto+%5Csum_%7BP+%5Cin+T%3A+%7CJ%7C+%5Cleq+%7CI_P%7C%7D+%5Cepsilon_P+%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Cphi_P+%5Crangle+%5Cphi_P.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  f \\mapsto \\sum_{P \\in T: |J| \\leq |I_P|} \\epsilon_P \\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\phi_P.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  f \\mapsto \\sum_{P \\in T: |J| \\leq |I_P|} \\epsilon_P \\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\phi_P.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> The point of this formulation is that the integrand can now be expressed as a sort of “Littlewood-Paley projection” of the function \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++F%28x%29+%3A%3D+%5Csum_%7BP+%5Cin+T%7D+%5Cepsilon_P+%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Cphi_P+%5Crangle+%5Clangle+%5Cphi_P%28x%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  F(x) := \\sum_{P \\in T} \\epsilon_P \\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\langle \\phi_P(x)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  F(x) := \\sum_{P \\in T} \\epsilon_P \\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\langle \\phi_P(x)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> to the region of frequency space corresponding to those intervals \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Comega_P%5E%2B%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\omega_P^+}\" title=\"{\\omega_P^+}\" class=\"latex\" /> with \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7CJ%7C+%5Cleq+%7CI_P%7C+%5Cleq+R%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{|J| \\leq |I_P| \\leq R}\" title=\"{|J| \\leq |I_P| \\leq R}\" class=\"latex\" />: \n<p> </p>\n<blockquote>\n <b>Exercise 13</b> Establish the pointwise estimate \n <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csup_R+%7C%5Csum_%7BP+%5Cin+T%3A+%7CJ%7C+%5Cleq+%7CI_P%7C+%5Cleq+R%7D+%5Cepsilon_P+%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Cphi_P+%5Crangle+%5Cphi_P%28x%29%7C+%5Clesssim+%5Csup_%7BI%3A+I+%5Csupset+J%7D+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B%7CI%7C%7D+%5Cint_I+%7CF%7C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sup_R |\\sum_{P \\in T: |J| \\leq |I_P| \\leq R} \\epsilon_P \\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\phi_P(x)| \\lesssim \\sup_{I: I \\supset J} \\frac{1}{|I|} \\int_I |F|\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sup_R |\\sum_{P \\in T: |J| \\leq |I_P| \\leq R} \\epsilon_P \\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\phi_P(x)| \\lesssim \\sup_{I: I \\supset J} \\frac{1}{|I|} \\int_I |F|\" class=\"latex\" /></p> for all \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bx+%5Cin+J%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{x \\in J}\" title=\"{x \\in J}\" class=\"latex\" /> where \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{I}\" title=\"{I}\" class=\"latex\" /> ranges over all intervals (not necessarily dyadic) containing \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BJ%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{J}\" title=\"{J}\" class=\"latex\" />. \n</blockquote> \n<p></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> From <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#ipi-2\">(29)</a> and Exercise <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#spat\">11</a>(iii) as before we have </p>\n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7CJ+%5Ccap+E%7C+%5Clesssim+%5Cmu+%7CJ%7C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  |J \\cap E| \\lesssim \\mu |J|\" title=\"\\displaystyle  |J \\cap E| \\lesssim \\mu |J|\" class=\"latex\" /></p> and so we can bound the expression \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#j-sum\">(35)</a> by \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clesssim+%5Csum_%7BJ+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+J%7D%3A+J+%5Csubset+CI_T%7D+%5Cmu+%7CJ%7C+%5Csup_%7BI%3A+I+%5Csupset+J%7D+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B%7CI%7C%7D+%5Cint_I+%7CF%7C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\lesssim \\sum_{J \\in {\\mathcal J}: J \\subset CI_T} \\mu |J| \\sup_{I: I \\supset J} \\frac{1}{|I|} \\int_I |F|\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\lesssim \\sum_{J \\in {\\mathcal J}: J \\subset CI_T} \\mu |J| \\sup_{I: I \\supset J} \\frac{1}{|I|} \\int_I |F|\" class=\"latex\" /></p> which one can bound in terms of the Hardy-Littlewood maximal function \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BMF%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{MF}\" title=\"{MF}\" class=\"latex\" /> of \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BF%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{F}\" title=\"{F}\" class=\"latex\" />, followed by Cauchy-Schwarz and the Hardy-Littlewood inequality, and finally Exercise \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#ao\">12</a>, as \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clesssim+%5Csum_%7BJ+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+J%7D%3A+J+%5Csubset+CI_T%7D+%5Cmu+%5Cint_J+MF&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\lesssim \\sum_{J \\in {\\mathcal J}: J \\subset CI_T} \\mu \\int_J MF\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\lesssim \\sum_{J \\in {\\mathcal J}: J \\subset CI_T} \\mu \\int_J MF\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clesssim+%5Cmu+%5Cint_%7BCI_T%7D+MF+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\lesssim \\mu \\int_{CI_T} MF \" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\lesssim \\mu \\int_{CI_T} MF \" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clesssim+%5Cmu+%7CI_T%7C%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5C%7C+MF+%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\lesssim \\mu |I_T|^{1/2} \\| MF \\|_{L^2({\\bf R})}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\lesssim \\mu |I_T|^{1/2} \\| MF \\|_{L^2({\\bf R})}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clesssim+%5Cmu+%7CI_T%7C%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5C%7C+F+%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\lesssim \\mu |I_T|^{1/2} \\| F \\|_{L^2({\\bf R})}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\lesssim \\mu |I_T|^{1/2} \\| F \\|_{L^2({\\bf R})}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clesssim+%5Cmu+%7CI_T%7C%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%28%5Csum_%7BP+%5Cin+T%7D+%7C%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Cphi_P+%5Crangle%7C%5E2%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\lesssim \\mu |I_T|^{1/2} (\\sum_{P \\in T} |\\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle|^2)^{1/2}.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\lesssim \\mu |I_T|^{1/2} (\\sum_{P \\in T} |\\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle|^2)^{1/2}.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> On the other hand, from \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#po\">(33)</a> we have \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7BP+%5Cin+T%3A+P+%5Cleq+P_%2A%7D+%7C%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Cphi_P+%5Crangle%7C%5E2+%5Cleq+%5Cvarepsilon%5E2+%7CI_%7BP_%2A%7D%7C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{P \\in T: P \\leq P_*} |\\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle|^2 \\leq \\varepsilon^2 |I_{P_*}|\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{P \\in T: P \\leq P_*} |\\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle|^2 \\leq \\varepsilon^2 |I_{P_*}|\" class=\"latex\" /></p> for every \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP_%2A+%5Cin+T%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P_* \\in T}\" title=\"{P_* \\in T}\" class=\"latex\" />. By grouping the tiles in \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BT%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{T}\" title=\"{T}\" class=\"latex\" /> according to their maximal elements \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP_%2A%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P_*}\" title=\"{P_*}\" class=\"latex\" /> (which necessarily have essentially disjoint spatial intervals) and applying the above inequality to each such group and summing, we conclude that \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7BP+%5Cin+T%7D+%7C%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Cphi_P+%5Crangle%7C%5E2+%5Cleq+%5Cvarepsilon%5E2+%7CI_T%7C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{P \\in T} |\\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle|^2 \\leq \\varepsilon^2 |I_T|\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{P \\in T} |\\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle|^2 \\leq \\varepsilon^2 |I_T|\" class=\"latex\" /></p> and the tree estimate \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#tree\">(32)</a> follows. \n<p> <b>The general case</b> </p>\n<p> We are now ready to handle the general case of an arbitrary finite collection <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal P}}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal P}}\" class=\"latex\" /> of tiles. Motivated by the previous discussion, we define two quantities: </p>\n<p> </p>\n<blockquote>\n <b>Definition 14 (Energy and mass)</b> For any non-empty finite collection \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal P}}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal P}}\" class=\"latex\" /> of tiles, we define the \n <em>energy</em> \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cmathrm%7BEnergy%7D%28%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\mathrm{Energy}({\\mathcal P})}\" title=\"{\\mathrm{Energy}({\\mathcal P})}\" class=\"latex\" /> to be the quantity \n <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cmathrm%7BEnergy%7D%28%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%29+%3A%3D+%5Csup_T+%7CI_T%7C%5E%7B-1%2F2%7D+%28%5Csum_%7BP+%5Cin+T%7D+%7C%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Cphi_P+%5Crangle%7C%5E2%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Energy}({\\mathcal P}) := \\sup_T |I_T|^{-1/2} (\\sum_{P \\in T} |\\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle|^2)^{1/2}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Energy}({\\mathcal P}) := \\sup_T |I_T|^{-1/2} (\\sum_{P \\in T} |\\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle|^2)^{1/2}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> where \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BT%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{T}\" title=\"{T}\" class=\"latex\" /> ranges over all \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%2B%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{+}\" title=\"{+}\" class=\"latex\" />-trees in \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal P}}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal P}}\" class=\"latex\" />, and the \n <em>mass</em> \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cmathrm%7BMass%7D%28%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\mathrm{Mass}({\\mathcal P})}\" title=\"{\\mathrm{Mass}({\\mathcal P})}\" class=\"latex\" /> to be the quantity \n <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cmathrm%7BMass%7D%28%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%29+%3A%3D+%5Csup_%7BP+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%7D+%5Csup_%7BP%27+%5Cgeq+P%7D+%7CI_%7BP%27%7D%7C%5E%7B-1%7D+%5Cint_%7BE_%7BP%27%7D%7D+%5Cchi_%7BI_%7BP%27%7D%7D%5E%7B10%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Mass}({\\mathcal P}) := \\sup_{P \\in {\\mathcal P}} \\sup_{P' \\geq P} |I_{P'}|^{-1} \\int_{E_{P'}} \\chi_{I_{P'}}^{10}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Mass}({\\mathcal P}) := \\sup_{P \\in {\\mathcal P}} \\sup_{P' \\geq P} |I_{P'}|^{-1} \\int_{E_{P'}} \\chi_{I_{P'}}^{10}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> where \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BE_%7BP%27%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{E_{P'}}\" title=\"{E_{P'}}\" class=\"latex\" /> is the set \n <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++E_%7BP%27%7D+%3A%3D+%5C%7B+x+%5Cin+E%3A+N%28x%29+%5Cin+%5Comega_%7BP%27%7D+%5C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  E_{P'} := \\{ x \\in E: N(x) \\in \\omega_{P'} \\}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  E_{P'} := \\{ x \\in E: N(x) \\in \\omega_{P'} \\}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> (thus for instance \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BE_%7BP%27%7D%5E%2B+%5Csubset+E_%7BP%27%7D+%5Csubset+E%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{E_{P'}^+ \\subset E_{P'} \\subset E}\" title=\"{E_{P'}^+ \\subset E_{P'} \\subset E}\" class=\"latex\" />). By convention, we declare the empty set of tiles to have energy and mass equal to zero. \n</blockquote> \n<p></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> Note here that the definition of mass has been modified slightly from previous arguments, in that we now use <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BE_%7BP%27%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{E_{P'}}\" title=\"{E_{P'}}\" class=\"latex\" /> instead of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BE%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{E}\" title=\"{E}\" class=\"latex\" />. However, this turns out to be an acceptable modification, in the sense that we still continue to have the analogue of <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#tree\">(32)</a>: </p>\n<p> </p>\n<blockquote>\n <b>Exercise 15 (Tree estimate)</b> \n <a name=\"tree-ex\"></a> If \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BT%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{T}\" title=\"{T}\" class=\"latex\" /> is a tree, show that \n <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle+%5Csum_%7BP+%5Cin+T%7D+%7C%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Cphi_P+%5Crangle+%5Clangle+%5Cphi_P%2C+1_%7BE_P%5E%2B%7D+%5Crangle%7C+%5Clesssim+%5Cmathrm%7BEnergy%7D%28T%29+%5Cmathrm%7BMass%7D%28T%29+%7CI_T%7C.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle \\sum_{P \\in T} |\\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\langle \\phi_P, 1_{E_P^+} \\rangle| \\lesssim \\mathrm{Energy}(T) \\mathrm{Mass}(T) |I_T|.\" title=\"\\displaystyle \\sum_{P \\in T} |\\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\langle \\phi_P, 1_{E_P^+} \\rangle| \\lesssim \\mathrm{Energy}(T) \\mathrm{Mass}(T) |I_T|.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n</blockquote> \n<p></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> Since <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cchi_%7BI_%7BP%27%7D%7D%5E%7B10%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\chi_{I_{P'}}^{10}}\" title=\"{\\chi_{I_{P'}}^{10}}\" class=\"latex\" /> has an <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BL%5E1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{L^1}\" title=\"{L^1}\" class=\"latex\" /> norm of <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BO%28%7CI_%7BP%27%7D%7C%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{O(|I_{P'}|)}\" title=\"{O(|I_{P'}|)}\" class=\"latex\" />, we also have the trivial bound </p>\n<p> <a name=\"mass-t\"></a></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><a name=\"mass-t\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cmathrm%7BMass%7D%28%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%29+%5Clesssim+1+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2836%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Mass}({\\mathcal P}) \\lesssim 1 \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (36)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Mass}({\\mathcal P}) \\lesssim 1 \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (36)\" class=\"latex\" /></a></p>\n<a name=\"mass-t\"> </a> for any finite collection of tiles \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal P}}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal P}}\" class=\"latex\" />. \n<p></p>\n<p> The strategy is now to try to partition an arbitrary family <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal P}}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal P}}\" class=\"latex\" /> of tiles into collections of disjoint trees <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BT%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{T}\" title=\"{T}\" class=\"latex\" /> (or “forests”, if you will) whose energy <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cmathrm%7BEnergy%7D%28T%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\mathrm{Energy}(T)}\" title=\"{\\mathrm{Energy}(T)}\" class=\"latex\" />, mass <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cmathrm%7BMass%7D%28T%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\mathrm{Mass}(T)}\" title=\"{\\mathrm{Mass}(T)}\" class=\"latex\" />, and spatial scale <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7CI_T%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{|I_T|}\" title=\"{|I_T|}\" class=\"latex\" /> are all under control, apply Exercise <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#tree-ex\">15</a> to each tree, and sum. To do this we rely on two key selection results, which are vaguely reminiscent of the Calderón-Zygmund decomposition: </p>\n<p> </p>\n<blockquote>\n <b>Proposition 16 (Energy selection)</b> \n <a name=\"energy-select\"></a> Let \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal P}}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal P}}\" class=\"latex\" /> be a finite collection of tiles with \n <a name=\"energ\"><p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cmathrm%7BEnergy%7D%28%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%29+%5Cleq+%5Cvarepsilon+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2837%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Energy}({\\mathcal P}) \\leq \\varepsilon \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (37)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Energy}({\\mathcal P}) \\leq \\varepsilon \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (37)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> </a> for some \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cvarepsilon+%3E+0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\varepsilon > 0}\" title=\"{\\varepsilon > 0}\" class=\"latex\" />. Then one can partition \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal P}}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal P}}\" class=\"latex\" /> into a collection \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+T%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal T}}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal T}}\" class=\"latex\" /> of disjoint trees \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BT%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{T}\" title=\"{T}\" class=\"latex\" /> with \n <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7BT+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+T%7D%7D+%7CI_T%7C+%5Clesssim+%5Cvarepsilon%5E%7B-2%7D+%5C%7Cf%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D%5E2&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{T \\in {\\mathcal T}} |I_T| \\lesssim \\varepsilon^{-2} \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})}^2\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{T \\in {\\mathcal T}} |I_T| \\lesssim \\varepsilon^{-2} \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})}^2\" class=\"latex\" /></p> together with a remainder set \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal P}'}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal P}'}\" class=\"latex\" /> with \n <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cmathrm%7BEnergy%7D%28%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%27%29+%5Cleq+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B2%7D+%5Cvarepsilon.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Energy}({\\mathcal P}') \\leq \\frac{1}{2} \\varepsilon.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Energy}({\\mathcal P}') \\leq \\frac{1}{2} \\varepsilon.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n</blockquote> \n<p></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<blockquote>\n <b>Proposition 17 (Mass selection)</b> \n <a name=\"mass-select\"></a> Let \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal P}}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal P}}\" class=\"latex\" /> be a finite collection of tiles with \n <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cmathrm%7BMass%7D%28%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%29+%5Cleq+%5Cmu&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Mass}({\\mathcal P}) \\leq \\mu\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Mass}({\\mathcal P}) \\leq \\mu\" class=\"latex\" /></p> for some \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cmu+%3E+0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\mu > 0}\" title=\"{\\mu > 0}\" class=\"latex\" />. Then one can partition \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal P}}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal P}}\" class=\"latex\" /> into a collection \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+T%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal T}}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal T}}\" class=\"latex\" /> of disjoint trees \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BT%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{T}\" title=\"{T}\" class=\"latex\" /> with \n <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7BT+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+T%7D%7D+%7CI_T%7C+%5Clesssim+%5Cmu%5E%7B-1%7D+%7CE%7C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{T \\in {\\mathcal T}} |I_T| \\lesssim \\mu^{-1} |E|\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{T \\in {\\mathcal T}} |I_T| \\lesssim \\mu^{-1} |E|\" class=\"latex\" /></p> together with a remainder set \n <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal P}'}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal P}'}\" class=\"latex\" /> with \n <p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cmathrm%7BMass%7D%28%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%27%29+%5Cleq+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B2%7D+%5Cmu.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Mass}({\\mathcal P}') \\leq \\frac{1}{2} \\mu.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Mass}({\\mathcal P}') \\leq \\frac{1}{2} \\mu.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n</blockquote> \n<p></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> (In these propositions, “disjoint” means that any given tile <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P}\" title=\"{P}\" class=\"latex\" /> belongs to at most one of the trees <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BT%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{T}\" title=\"{T}\" class=\"latex\" /> in <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+T%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal T}}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal T}}\" class=\"latex\" />; but the tiles in one tree are allowed to overlap the tiles in another tree.) </p>\n<p> Let us assume these two propositions for now and see how these (together with Exercise <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#tree-ex\">15</a>) establishes the required estimate <a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#est-tile-finite\">(19)</a> for an arbitrary collection <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal P}}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal P}}\" class=\"latex\" /> of tiles. We may assume without loss of generality that <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5C%7Cf%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{\\|f\\|_{L^2}}\" title=\"{\\|f\\|_{L^2}}\" class=\"latex\" /> and <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7CE%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{|E|}\" title=\"{|E|}\" class=\"latex\" /> are non-zero. Rearranging the above two propositions slightly, we see that if <img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D_n%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal P}_n}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal P}_n}\" class=\"latex\" /> is a finite collection of tiles such that <a name=\"mod\"></a></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><a name=\"mod\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cmathrm%7BEnergy%7D%28%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D_%7Bn%7D%29+%5Cleq+2%5E%7B-n%2F2%7D+%5C%7Cf%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D%3B+%5Cquad+%5Cmathrm%7BMass%7D%28%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D_n%29+%5Cleq+2%5E%7B-n%7D+%7CE%7C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2838%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Energy}({\\mathcal P}_{n}) \\leq 2^{-n/2} \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})}; \\quad \\mathrm{Mass}({\\mathcal P}_n) \\leq 2^{-n} |E| \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (38)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Energy}({\\mathcal P}_{n}) \\leq 2^{-n/2} \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})}; \\quad \\mathrm{Mass}({\\mathcal P}_n) \\leq 2^{-n} |E| \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (38)\" class=\"latex\" /></a></p>\n<a name=\"mod\"> </a> for some integer \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{n}\" title=\"{n}\" class=\"latex\" /> then after applying Proposition \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#energy-select\">16</a> followed by Proposition \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#mass-select\">17</a>, we can partition \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D_n%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal P}_n}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal P}_n}\" class=\"latex\" /> into a disjoint collection \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+T%7D_n%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal T}_n}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal T}_n}\" class=\"latex\" /> of trees \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BT%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{T}\" title=\"{T}\" class=\"latex\" /> with \n<a name=\"t-size\"><p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7BT+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+T%7D_n%7D+%7CI_T%7C+%5Clesssim+2%5En+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2839%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{T \\in {\\mathcal T}_n} |I_T| \\lesssim 2^n \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (39)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_{T \\in {\\mathcal T}_n} |I_T| \\lesssim 2^n \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (39)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> </a> together with a remainder \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D_%7Bn%2B1%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal P}_{n+1}}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal P}_{n+1}}\" class=\"latex\" /> with \n<p></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cmathrm%7BEnergy%7D%28%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D_%7Bn%2B1%7D%29+%5Cleq+2%5E%7B-%28n%2B1%29%2F2%7D+%5C%7Cf%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D%3B+%5Cquad+%5Cmathrm%7BMass%7D%28%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D_%7Bn%2B1%7D%29+%5Cleq+2%5E%7B-%28n%2B1%29%7D+%7CE%7C.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Energy}({\\mathcal P}_{n+1}) \\leq 2^{-(n+1)/2} \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})}; \\quad \\mathrm{Mass}({\\mathcal P}_{n+1}) \\leq 2^{-(n+1)} |E|.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Energy}({\\mathcal P}_{n+1}) \\leq 2^{-(n+1)/2} \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})}; \\quad \\mathrm{Mass}({\\mathcal P}_{n+1}) \\leq 2^{-(n+1)} |E|.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> Note that any finite collection of tiles \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal P}}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal P}}\" class=\"latex\" /> will obey \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#mod\">(38)</a> for some sufficiently large and negative \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{n}\" title=\"{n}\" class=\"latex\" />. Starting with this \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{n}\" title=\"{n}\" class=\"latex\" /> and then iterating indefinitely, and discarding any empty families, we can therefore partition any finite collection of tiles \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal P}}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal P}}\" class=\"latex\" /> as \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D+%3D+%5Cbigcup_n+%5Cbigcup_%7BT+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+T%7D_n%7D+T+%5Ccup+%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D_%7B-%5Cinfty%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathcal P} = \\bigcup_n \\bigcup_{T \\in {\\mathcal T}_n} T \\cup {\\mathcal P}_{-\\infty}\" title=\"\\displaystyle  {\\mathcal P} = \\bigcup_n \\bigcup_{T \\in {\\mathcal T}_n} T \\cup {\\mathcal P}_{-\\infty}\" class=\"latex\" /></p> where \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+T%7D_n%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal T}_n}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal T}_n}\" class=\"latex\" /> are collections of trees (empty for all but finitely many \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{n}\" title=\"{n}\" class=\"latex\" />) such that \n<a name=\"ener\"><p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cmathrm%7BEnergy%7D%28%7B%5Cmathcal+T%7D_%7Bn%7D%29+%5Cleq+2%5E%7B-n%2F2%7D+%5C%7Cf%5C%7C_%7BL%5E2%28%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%29%7D%3B+%5Cquad+%5Cmathrm%7BMass%7D%28%7B%5Cmathcal+T%7D_n%29+%5Cleq+2%5E%7B-n%7D+%7CE%7C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2840%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Energy}({\\mathcal T}_{n}) \\leq 2^{-n/2} \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})}; \\quad \\mathrm{Mass}({\\mathcal T}_n) \\leq 2^{-n} |E| \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (40)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Energy}({\\mathcal T}_{n}) \\leq 2^{-n/2} \\|f\\|_{L^2({\\bf R})}; \\quad \\mathrm{Mass}({\\mathcal T}_n) \\leq 2^{-n} |E| \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (40)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> </a> and \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#t-size\">(39)</a> holds, and \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D_%7B-%5Cinfty%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{{\\mathcal P}_{-\\infty}}\" title=\"{{\\mathcal P}_{-\\infty}}\" class=\"latex\" /> is a residual collection of tiles with \n<a name=\"resid\"><p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cmathrm%7BEnergy%7D%28%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D_%7B-%5Cinfty%7D%29+%3D+%5Cmathrm%7BMass%7D%28%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D_%7B-%5Cinfty%7D%29+%3D+0.+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2841%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Energy}({\\mathcal P}_{-\\infty}) = \\mathrm{Mass}({\\mathcal P}_{-\\infty}) = 0. \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (41)\" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\mathrm{Energy}({\\mathcal P}_{-\\infty}) = \\mathrm{Mass}({\\mathcal P}_{-\\infty}) = 0. \\ \\ \\ \\ \\ (41)\" class=\"latex\" /></p> </a> We can then bound the left-hand side of \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#est-tile-finite\">(19)</a> by \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_n+%5Csum_%7BT+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+T%7D_n%7D+%5Csum_%7BP+%5Cin+T%7D+%7C%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Cphi_P+%5Crangle+%5Clangle+%5Cphi_P%2C+1_%7BE_P%5E%2B%7D+%5Crangle%7C+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_n \\sum_{T \\in {\\mathcal T}_n} \\sum_{P \\in T} |\\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\langle \\phi_P, 1_{E_P^+} \\rangle| \" title=\"\\displaystyle  \\sum_n \\sum_{T \\in {\\mathcal T}_n} \\sum_{P \\in T} |\\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\langle \\phi_P, 1_{E_P^+} \\rangle| \" class=\"latex\" /></p> \n<p align=\"center\"><img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%2B+%5Csum_%7BP+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D_%7B-%5Cinfty%7D%7D+%7C%5Clangle+f%2C+%5Cphi_P+%5Crangle+%5Clangle+%5Cphi_P%2C+1_%7BE_P%5E%2B%7D+%5Crangle%7C.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"\\displaystyle  + \\sum_{P \\in {\\mathcal P}_{-\\infty}} |\\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\langle \\phi_P, 1_{E_P^+} \\rangle|.\" title=\"\\displaystyle  + \\sum_{P \\in {\\mathcal P}_{-\\infty}} |\\langle f, \\phi_P \\rangle \\langle \\phi_P, 1_{E_P^+} \\rangle|.\" class=\"latex\" /></p> From Exercise \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#tree-ex\">15</a> applied to individual tiles \n<img src=\"https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+P%7D_%7B-%5Cinfty%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0\" alt=\"{P \\in {\\mathcal P}_{-\\infty}}\" title=\"{P \\in {\\mathcal P}_{-\\infty}}\" class=\"latex\" /> and \n<a href=\"http://terrytao.wordpress.com/?p=11764#resid\">(41)</a> we see that the second term in this expression vanishes.
